INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(4, 5, 'I realized recently that the wiser question is "are you who God wants you to be?". That said, if the rest of the concert convinces you that what you want to be is closer to God, this song could help push you to actually do something about that... -Ken ', 3, '2011-04-11 15:16:31'),
(5, 5, '    * Lyrics really resonate\r\n    * One of our signature songs (at this point)\r\n    * A good challenge song ', 3, '2011-04-11 15:16:52'),
(6, 6, 'Initially added to set in Spring 2011 but dropped due to concerns aboutthe message.', 3, '2011-04-11 15:19:46'),
(7, 8, 'This song just makes me want to cry sometimes... i suppose for a good way, but because it reminds me of what Christ did for us. Other pros: already arranged and it''s a good arrangement. mmm... also Spanish may be appropriate for Spring Break in LA. -shion', 3, '2011-04-11 15:44:39'),
(8, 8, 'It''ll take a bunch of finesse and practice. It''s a great song that sounds spectacular if we put the time into it; it depends on whether we want to do that here or in a newer song. There are compelling arguments for picking this one: I don''t think we''ve done it in a while, Spanish would be cool, and it''s a solid bet. That said, spring break is awfully early in Lent this year (we did this a few years ago much closer to Holy Week). But it''s still Lent, so it''s still reasonable. -geofft ', 3, '2011-04-11 15:44:59'),
(10, 11, 'I love this song!', 3, '2011-04-12 02:09:28'),
(11, 12, '    * Good upbeat song\r\n    * Fun stuff\r\n    * A lot of members of the group know this song \r\n\r\nGreat statement of what we believe: that Jesus is the King Above All Kings, and someday we will worship Him in Heaven! -Jacob\r\n\r\nIt''s a classic and we know we have a good arrangement of it, but I can''t say I''m particularly tied to it especially if there are good new songs to do this term. But I don''t have the usual praise song objection to it; it''s listenable, not that "me"-ish, not overly repetitive, pretty scriptural, etc. -geofft ', 3, '2011-04-12 23:17:52'),
(12, 13, 'Empty Me is a great song by American Idol contestant Chris Sligh. It''s pretty cool to see that he wrote such a selfless song, especially after seeing the glitz and glam of Hollywood.\r\n\r\nI love it! It''s like a softer (but still poignant) version of Ruin Me. -Jacob\r\n\r\nIntriguing. Yeah, I can see it as a Ruin Me that''s more usable in sets and such. -geofft\r\n\r\nAlmost spring break compatible if we take out "Lord", which is possible. Very a cappella arrangeable, so that''s good :) I do like the lyrics a lot. -shion-\r\n\r\nI really like this song. -Kristina ', 3, '2011-04-12 23:21:54'),
(13, 14, 'JR: This is the only version of the song I had on hand. My big idea was to split up the four choruses as a series of four duets sung by different Cross Products - standing together as a group declaration of our faith and what we believe. But that was just my idea....\r\n\r\nReally wordy song - cas\r\n\r\nSo good! - everybody\r\n\r\nJust plain confessing Christ. Measureless did this a while back; iirc we did one soloist per verse, then all together on the last half stanza (where some versions repeat). This is what we believe, this is what we know. This is our hope, this is our joy. In Christ alone. -Ken ', 3, '2011-04-12 23:31:02'),
(14, 218, 'Never again.', 3, '2011-05-12 11:02:30'),
(15, 40, 'i like how it answers the questions that we have, but it''s not in your face. it just says it, and it''s so true. -shion-\r\n\r\neveryone sings words, it''s musically interesting. and it can be done in a smaller group. -daniel- ', 3, '2011-05-12 13:08:44'),
(16, 40, 'Succinctly describes a personal journey of faith and transformation by God''s truth. Slow jazzy-ish song (toward the end in particular), change of pace from everything else we perform. I think our current group would sound good on this song.', 3, '2011-05-12 13:12:26'),
(17, 394, 'I could see this song being very strong musically, perhaps as an opener or finale. The percussionist(s) are showcased. Since the song is so familiar, blurb would be necessary to bring attention to the message.', 3, '2011-05-12 14:13:53'),
(18, 245, 'From the wiki:     * This song makes everyone smile\r\n    * Really great song for us to sing, really leave the audience enjoying the show\r\n    * Bridge could do better job of explaining "why it''s okay to be ourselves"\r\n    * "I''m free to be myself" is a little disturbing and could be taken the wrong way ', 3, '2011-05-12 16:45:11'),
(19, 245, 'It''s a proven winner, and I think it''s been long enough that we can bring this one back. Underneath the silliness, the song does a decent job of testifying to God''s love in an unassuming, non-threatening way.', 3, '2011-05-12 16:47:45'),
(21, 245, 'I think this perfect for Cross Products, and we should resurrect it at least every two years.\r\n\r\nIn particular, I think we could brainstorm lyrics for an MIT audience... I noticed that our current lyrics are already slightly modified from the original Scott Krippayne song, and I think we could do a good job updating the lyrics.\r\nOne possibility that I brainstormed with Shion over spring break:\r\n\r\n...\r\nAnd coding is my claim to fame\r\nI spell "elite" using numbers (1337)\r\nIn fact, that''s my Kerberos name', 27, '2011-05-12 16:58:05'),
(22, 17, 'Cool-sounding girl solo, and the background isn''t too difficult (we did it in XLinked). The message reminds me a little of Who You Are, in a good way- God is unexplainable, yet He provides a "deep, deep reassurance" to those who "trust the unseen." It''s not going to be the hardest hitting song in the set message-wise, but it isn''t flippant either. It can contribute to the set both musically and spiritually.', 3, '2011-05-12 21:16:35'),
(23, 396, 'So it''s not done by a Christian artist, but it seems to be a song about a man searching for deeper meaning in his life (the official music video shows this unhappy guy surrounded by the gambling/amusement-park scene in Atlantic City.)  \r\nIt''s certainly a prayer I have in times of doubt for God to lead me past confusion and reveal himself/ will for me- to show me what I''m looking for. \r\n\r\nIt reminds me of "This is your Life" in that it is a spiritual song that can be sung in an explicitly non-Christian setting. Also- it''s been featured on a few TV shows so it''s recognizable which I guess is a plus? \r\n', 17, '2011-05-16 06:55:18'),
(24, 397, 'When''s the last time we did a cute upbeat praise song that had an awesome girl-guy duet?  We rarely get to do real duets, let a lone a girl-guy duet, because usually those are love songs, but this is a love song about Jesus!   This song reminds us that the reason we''re all in this relationships with Jesus isn''t because we were super spiritual and smart and deep and "figured it out", but the Lord found and lead us to him. ', 17, '2011-05-16 07:07:07'),
(25, 398, 'What a cool verse rhythm!  Talks about the struggle of maintaining a close relationship with God when it''s so contrary to the world''s ways.  ', 17, '2011-05-16 07:18:40'),
(26, 397, '"When''s the last time we did a cute upbeat praise song that had an awesome girl-guy duet?" - That would be the last time we did You Found Me, which was last year :) It wouldn''t be a bad song to bring back, though!', 3, '2011-05-16 19:29:56'),
(27, 52, 'I really like this song- I think because the chorus reflects my prayers. In a works-based society, this song speaks to what we really need: the unconditional love of Christ. This song has a Country Music set up to it- taking different stories and applying the same chorus to it. And yes, it is predictable, but I think it has a great sweetness to it. If it were to be arranged, I think the arranger would need to add something a little different to each chorus repetition and verse just to keep it musically interesting, since it is a rather slow song lyrically (especially the bridge.)', 17, '2011-05-16 22:25:03'),
(28, 402, 'So besides Kristina, I''m sure none of us can smell the color 9. \r\nThis song isn''t the deepest of songs, but I think this song is a clever reminder of the reality that sometimes we just don''t feel God''s presence.', 17, '2011-05-16 22:35:45'),
(29, 402, 'hahahahahahaaa i started reading these lyrics and started laughing. i''m not sure i could keep a straight face during this song!! And then I actually listened to the song and he said "nine''s not a color". I was like grrrrrrrrrr maybe to you it''s not and got kinda really mad. >.<\r\n\r\nAnyway, I love the message of this song. I think what scares some people away from Christianity is the fear that they''ll try but they''ll never "get it" because they think Christianity is about having divine enounters and such. So yeah, this is a cool reminder that you don''t have to actually feel God or hear Him to still believe in Him and follow His will. Because, ultimately, He''s going to lead you to where He wants you to go, even if you''re not sure you''re heading in the right direction because you didn''t receive a "direct order".\r\n\r\nThe picture at the end with the butterfly and flower was fairly close! Nine''s a yellowy orange :)', 24, '2011-05-25 23:43:51'),
(30, 401, 'This song just cheers me up when I listen to it. Just a prayer asking God to show us a fulfilling life following Him.  ', 17, '2011-05-26 00:06:26'),
(31, 400, 'What if we were all in?  Actually following God the way the bible told us to follow him?  Wouldn''t that be legit?  ', 17, '2011-05-26 00:09:21'),
(32, 404, 'So, one day, we''re going to get to hang out with Christ forever!  That''s pretty cool.  I was thinking about how heaven fits in with our relationship with God.  We''re not in this relationship just for heaven and to get out of hell, but rather because heaven is a state where we can share with the ONE we love.  In the same way you don''t just get into a marriage for the money or sex, but rather it''s a state where you can express your love with no inhibitions.  Anyways now I''m rambling.  But I really love the female harmony part (go Dolly Parton!)  and think this would be a good spring break song.     ', 17, '2011-05-26 00:32:26'),
(33, 403, 'So I really wanted to suggest a low song- since a lot of guy songs are super high.  Also I love how this song is about how we can sing and speak all we want, but nothing we say or sing can ever describe how awesome our God is.  :-)(but we still gonna praise him) ', 17, '2011-05-26 00:45:11'),
(34, 397, 'I like the idea of a girl/guy duet, but this song sounds melody-less to me. It''s just kinda flat in the melody, if that makes any sense? That might not necessarily be bad, but I don''t like the lack of range very much.', 24, '2011-05-26 02:05:22'),
(35, 40, 'I love this song... Boston Found does it too :) For what it''s worth - this solo is either male or female - so I thought it was worth changing to reflect that. ', 32, '2011-05-26 02:08:50'),
(36, 245, 'Agreed with Peter.... adapting lyrics even moreso would be awesome. Truly, one of my favorite xprod songs of all time (and i never actually personally sang it!)  :D', 32, '2011-05-26 02:10:38'),
(37, 405, 'When I first heard this song, it was earlier this semester when I was really stressed out with school and was mad that I couldn''t ever seem to match up to how everyone else was performing. I was trying so hard to do well academically and this part of the song especially touched me "I know youre wanting to belong; they always tell you that you''re wrong... need a face, need a name, I''ve got a better way."', 24, '2011-05-26 02:23:08'),
(38, 405, 'Aw,  I do appreciate the lyrics of this song, although the song is a bit too poppy for my taste.  (but that''s what I thought about the LIGHTs song and then Peter''s arrangement made me really like it- so a good arrangement of this could prove me wrong again)  ', 17, '2011-05-26 17:54:48'),
(39, 245, 'lol Super cute.  Also loved the choreo from one of the vids.  ', 17, '2011-05-26 17:56:55'),
(40, 397, 'Yeah that does make sense @ Kristina,  I think the background of this song is a heck a lot more musically interesting than the soloists. I''d really like to hear our arrangement of the song, if it was a kind of flat arrangement than that would change my opinion for voting.   ', 17, '2011-05-26 17:59:21'),
(41, 399, 'Okay I know this isn''t a readily accessible song for non-Christian audiences.  But I love how this song imagines us when Christ has finally come and returned, and we are just standing there as one people, worshiping him. I''d really love to try to convey that end-of-time image to our audience with this song.  I picture in the arrangement that we''d have multiple soloists for the verses, and just all stand and sing the chorus together, and that picture makes me happy :-) ', 17, '2011-05-26 18:07:45'),
(42, 17, 'Yay cool-sounding girl solos!  ', 17, '2011-05-26 18:13:39'),
(43, 399, 'Love love LOVE this song :)', 24, '2011-05-27 04:51:38'),
(44, 405, 'Catchy, though firmly in the "could be about God or a boyfriend depending on context" zone, which makes it less useful for Spring Break than other songs that don''t explicitly mention God.', 3, '2011-05-27 20:02:29'),
(45, 406, 'Kristina wrote a song! And it''s catchy and nerd-ful. Pros: approaches the topic of God and physics coexisting like few songs do; "all you need has already been given" will get etched in the minds of an MIT audience. Cons: not particularly useful outside MIT (unless we go to Caltech again); might be a bit much to do it in the same term as I''m Not Cool.', 3, '2011-05-27 20:17:27'),
(46, 406, 'It''s a bit lengthy, so I might take out the first verse. Also, the highest sop note is an F# so it''s totally do-able for firsts :) <br> <br> I''m putting up youtube video for those of you (like me) that are having problems with listening to mp3/other audio files put up on the site.', 24, '2011-05-28 03:53:26'),
(47, 406, 'also BOOOOOOO html code doesn''t work D;', 24, '2011-05-28 03:53:53'),
(48, 40, 'Yeah, I do like the jazzyness, it just sorta abruptly ended. but I do like the jazziness. ', 17, '2011-05-28 06:54:41'),
(49, 24, 'I''m sorry! I know I just went over the 10 song suggested suggestion. But I really like this song''s message.  ', 17, '2011-05-28 07:00:30'),
(50, 407, 'Based on Psalm 23!  I think it''s a super cherry girl guy duet praising God.  ', 17, '2011-05-29 18:55:24'),
(51, 233, 'From the wiki: The best praise song ever??? Disputable, I know, but it''s on my list. Anyway, this song is a praise song that also reminds us that we should all praise God all the time, good days and bad.\r\n\r\nIf you find yourself doubting that there is a colossal amount of vintage 90''s fun contained within this song, check out the you tube video below.-cw\r\n\r\nI think this is a great praise song b/c we could have a lot of fun w/ it and people would be like "look how much they enjoy praising God" which is what we want. -jw there are other songs that give the same or stronger message that are equally fun to sing. -daniel- ', 3, '2011-05-29 21:51:27'),
(52, 233, 'Strong opener/closer, especially opener. If we get into it like we did for the 8-bit concert (see the video) then it really sets the tone for having a fun concert.', 3, '2011-05-29 22:13:55'),
(53, 75, 'From the wiki: I don''t get it. I understand the words, but it doesn''t resonate, and it seems a bit scattered in terms of thoughts. -geofft\r\n\r\nthe verses are more scattered, but I do like the chorus. I think the verses make sense though, it''s just more metaphoric (like what nichole nordeman often does). I think if you take the whole song into context, then the message is great. i also like that solo. mmm last thing, i like the change between verse (quiet, sleeping) vs chorus (louder, vibrant) -shion-\r\n\r\nI like how the soloist is so confident in her faith. -Jacob\r\n\r\nGood song! Wondering if there slowness of music in the verses will lead to stagnant acapella, but I guesss that''s the arrangangers thing. ', 3, '2011-05-29 23:36:44'),
(54, 75, 'The song''s message is kinda-sorta similar to Never Alone, but this song has a more positive vibe. It has an interesting solo line and seems like it would have a very singable background part.', 3, '2011-05-30 00:01:39'),
(55, 111, 'From the wiki: This song is sung from the perspective of God. He is speaking to a sinner who has neglected his faith to focus on worldly things but is turning back to God after hardship involving, in particular, persecution from friends/family/etc. If something bad happens to you that causes you to become closer to God, the silver lining more than outweighs the cost! Musically, it''s very Flyleaf. I wish it was a little shorter. But if you listen closely to the background especially during the verse, there are some moving parts that would be interesting in a cappella. -Jacob\r\n\r\nI''m intrigued. The verses are about finding concerns for social justice and looking beyond the wisdom of the world driving your search to God, instead of the other way around as usually portrayed, which is kind of cool. -geofft ', 3, '2011-05-30 00:06:45'),
(56, 75, 'Ah!  I really like this song, especially the musically-interesting chorus. Good message as well, despite everything- I will find refuge in Christ.   ', 17, '2011-05-30 07:40:56'),
(57, 408, 'I feel like this is a really appropriate song for Cross Products. I think it expresses our desire and the fact that we live loving and wanting to know more about Christ- even after the songs we stop, the concerts, the rehearsals end. We don''t just sing Christian a cappella. It''s not just a student group that we''re part of or something we do on occasion like many other things we do, but loving God is our life and purpose. I also like how it portrays this message with joy and an upbeat rhythm. I think the chorus and the bridge (more so than the verses) have the "core" of the message. \r\n-shion\r\n\r\nIt''s a decent song, but it seems to me like a praise song that can''t easily be a performance song (see the criticism of Indescribable, which I don''t actually think applies there): it''s not something I can really respond to someone else singing. I could sing along with them, perhaps. That said, we''ve done it. I just don''t find that it resonates with me in performance (it''s kind of hard for this song to click even passively listening to the recording).\r\n-geofft', 31, '2011-05-30 23:20:28'),
(58, 408, 'The previous comment was from the suggestions in the spring. I think that as a musical group seeking to be closer to Christ, this song is one that is an active demonstration about how we feel about it. It embodies the joy of wanting to grow closer to Him. It also serves as encouragement to the Christians that we do sing for.', 31, '2011-05-30 23:25:18'),
(59, 409, 'So these two songs by Adam Young are awwwesoooome and because of the repitition of lyrics in the songs, I thought it''d be fun to do a mashup! This might be something I have to play around with and suggest again for spring semester, but in any case I think it''s a cool idea :)', 24, '2011-05-31 21:08:42'),
(60, 410, 'Not her usual electro-galatic genre... because this is from her very first EP!! It''s such a simple song, but so great. Plus, she randomly stops to use a fake lazer gun in her acoustic vid. hahahahaaa', 24, '2011-05-31 21:14:41'),
(62, 17, 'It''s a really good song too- I relate to it strongly, and the song can be really powerful', 29, '2011-06-01 01:09:05'),
(63, 413, 'Not arranged by us, but perhaps we can ask for the arrangement? ', 29, '2011-06-01 01:20:07'),
(64, 414, 'It''s a good contrast to many of our upbeat songs. It''s recognizable, meditative, and it has a good, solid message. The arrangement is good, and the harmony by the two boy/girl singers with the background is beautiful :)', 29, '2011-06-01 01:23:30'),
(65, 408, 'whoops. I forgot this song was suggested by John already. uhhh.. how do you delete a song suggestion?', 29, '2011-06-01 01:25:12'),
(66, 415, 'I <3 this song. Great and simple arrangement. It''s an upbeat song but still has a different feel than like, rock, and the message is empowering. I think the call for us to take courage in Christ and take the next step is applicable to anyone, regardless of wherever they are in their walk of faith. ', 29, '2011-06-01 01:29:26'),
(67, 416, 'It''s a tried and tested arrangement and it''s musically strong/powerful. It also adds variety to our set. ', 29, '2011-06-01 01:31:55'),
(68, 417, 'Pre-arranged, yay! Another good variety to our set, and provides a solid Christian message of Jesus Christ and his relationship to the church, which is important. More comments here: http://xprod.mit.edu/w/Twila_Paris_-_How_Beautiful', 29, '2011-06-01 01:46:11'),
(69, 418, 'We''ve been trying to do this song.. for a long long time. http://xprod.mit.edu/w/Matthew_West_-_All_the_Broken_Pieces ', 29, '2011-06-01 01:47:33'),
(70, 418, 'But yes, the lyrics are just so powerful and it''s driven me to tears. Especially in the last two years, I''ve interacted with so many people at MIT who are broken in many ways, and we all are. It''s the amazing healing and forgiveness of Christ that is declared in this song. I also like that it''s from the perspective of God. \r\n\r\nbut yeah, I think we''ve all had moments like the first line of the song, "Did you feel, feel it break". ', 29, '2011-06-01 01:49:49'),
(72, 422, 'I do like the prodigal son reference- it can be a good pre or post extended blurb and can help with maybe even the skit or general message of the set. also the thought that there are actually two prodigal sons- the older and younger, and many people relate to both or either.\r\n\r\nApart from that, this song matches xprod well- it''s a type of song/music style that xprod is good at singing and being excited about. The verses are strong, but even stronger is the chorus, and I especially like how it references how our journey with Christ is a continuous wrestling with ourselves and becoming closer to the image of Christ- it can lead to a powerful blurb.\r\n\r\nIt needs to be rearranged, perhaps entirely, but I''m totally up for doing that, and i''m sure many others are as well. ', 29, '2011-06-01 02:04:59'),
(73, 423, 'Comments Fall 2009\r\ni really like this song!!! it''s really cool! one note though, is that X.ado is singing this song right now, so do we want to overlap?-shion-\r\n\r\nComments Fall 2010\r\nLyrics changed to "He is..." Tamiko loves this song from BAG... good arrangement, she says.\r\nArrangement captures the motion very well; it''s very upbeat. I like upbeat songs - Tamiko\r\n\r\nIs it OK for us to do the same songs as BAG? - Tamiko and Geoff', 31, '2011-06-01 02:37:13'),
(74, 424, 'Comments Winter 2010\r\nWe did this song last spring, and at BIDB people from other groups commented that this is "our" song. If we are rolling over songs from last year, this one is at the top of my list. -Peter\r\nI remember thinking during Spring Break that this song sounded really good, yeah. -Martin           \r\nI''m afraid of doing too many recent songs over again, but that''s just about the most criticism I can find about this song. The joy, not duty, not just peace, not simply faith, is something that''s often missed by other songs. -geofft             \r\n[edit] Comments Song Party sp 10     \r\nturk, shion, katie endorse this song.        \r\ni like daniel''s comment from last song party. check out later - shion-\r\nsays as much with "i like it" that other songs use "i love it" - jacob-\r\ncreative, makes people wake up, good contrast to other depressing songs- katie         \r\n[edit] Comments Song Party        \r\narrangement pretty good. it can use a bit of re-touch. -daniel-      \r\ni would like a blurb for this song- it keeps repeating "i like it" a lot, so we need to clarify what we like and why we like it, and that''s God and His joy. but i love this song :) -shion-       \r\nit''s corporeal -amanda-          \r\nit''s earthly and human- and people can understand and be familiar with it. and it has a sincerity to it because it''s I like it, vs the sappy I love you. -daniel-        \r\nfollowing Christianity is a Joy- we like it!!! -shion-          \r\n[edit] Comments Fall 2009        \r\nThis song could be awesome iff we can replace all the "If life is..." lines with nerdy jokes. - Jacob       ', 31, '2011-06-01 02:53:54'),
(76, 426, 'Meaning: This is a song about waking up to the greater conversation about life and justice, and the realities that we are implicated in the sufferings and joys of a global community. We need to be rescued from the trivia that keeps us blinded to our role in changing the world and paralyzed to act against our complacency. - Dan Haseltine; lead singer of Jars of Clay; Found in WOW Hits 2007 cover booklet', 31, '2011-06-01 03:02:19'),
(77, 427, 'Well, it''s memorable. And it''s a sufficiently odd message at face value that you''re going to have to figure out the slightly non-obvious meaning. -geofft\r\nNice! I totally was going to suggest this until I just saw it. The bonus is that it''s actually a pseudo-popular song in the secular scene (as in I''ve heard it on some of those ''light rock from the 70s, 80s, 90s, and today''- type radio stations on my drives in the suburbs. not... admitting to listening to those types of stations of course... <-< >-> o-O) But I like the message and the interesting take on denying yourself for Christ, I think it would be nice to explain that idea via a blurb and then song at our spring concert to our xtian and non xtian friends. Also, I can just hear the bell tones turning out nicely in an acapellafied version - Dorothy', 31, '2011-06-01 03:05:38'),
(79, 429, 'Comments Spring 2010\r\nWe did this Spring ''07 and it was pretty reasonable. It has a good message, and I think we can quickly make the verses accessible with a blurb. I think people have heard at least the concepts of Jesus walking on water and of David and Golith, if not the details. And the "tried before and failed" / "boy, you''ll never win" message is something a lot of people (at MIT and not) can recognize.... -geofft\r\n[edit] Comments Spring 2007\r\nAnother song we did a couple years ago... but it''s so good. =) - abarr\r\nWe like this song, but how accessible are the verses? - everybody\r\nThis is the only one of their songs that Daniel actually likes...', 31, '2011-06-01 03:12:20'),
(80, 430, 'Song Party\r\na bunch of us know it. it''s "almost" an alum song.\r\nthis is my choir back home''s "staple" song.\r\n[edit] Comments (Spring 10)\r\nSooooo pretty! We did this last year but I think it would work again. -Jacob\r\nPretty and true! This is one of our clearer expositions of the Gospel, and often encourages people (i.e., gives them courage to trust Jesus). Also, nhis song has unofficial alum song status, so this year''s group should at least know it. I thought about it after closing up last night, and decided that if someone hadn''t suggested it, I would have motioned for a late addition. But thanks Jacob! :) -Ken\r\nI support the group knowing it, and I support making it the actual alum song. I support spending time for the group to learn it whether or not it is considered part of our concert set. -geofft\r\n[edit] Comments (old)\r\nI changed the recording to the really good version that''s on the live CD. -WB\r\nWe all love it - everybody\r\nMore alums actually know this song [I think he means "than the alum song"]. We could do even better musically! - DJW', 31, '2011-06-01 03:16:54'),
(81, 431, 'The best "God is Awesome" song I know. We could probably not sing this song for non Christians, but for those who understand the words, this song is truly awe-inspiring (It''d kind of have to be- it''s a list of the titles of God).', 19, '2011-06-01 03:43:07'),
(82, 432, 'I really like this song. It speaks to me, particularly when I''m "too busy" for God.', 19, '2011-06-01 03:49:04'),
(83, 433, 'This is not the XProd version, which contains a really good mix with "Holy is the Lord," but it gets the point across. It really conveys the beauty and majesty of God, which I often underappreciate when I''m having a bad day or am simply too tired to think about it.', 19, '2011-06-01 03:54:00'),
(84, 434, '', 19, '2011-06-01 04:00:29'),
(85, 434, '', 19, '2011-06-01 04:00:36'),
(86, 434, 'I think this song really captures the feeling of having lost someone, from both the perspective of the lost and the one doing the losing. ', 19, '2011-06-01 04:02:19'),
(87, 435, '"I will lift my eyes to the maker of the mountains I can''t climb"- This line sums up this song rather well. I appreciate the juxtaposition of God''s might and God''s love in the verse, they are both equally important to our ability to ask God for help when we have need.', 19, '2011-06-01 04:07:51'),
(88, 436, '', 19, '2011-06-01 04:09:53'),
(89, 436, 'I will admit that I''m half hoping to replace "Reason" by this suggestion (not really). Anyways, I like this song because it both reminds me why I''m singing (even when I don''t particularly feel like it), as well as what it is that''s truly important in life.', 19, '2011-06-01 04:12:09'),
(90, 437, 'We are not called to be safe. We are called to be fearless nonetheless. I''m reminded of Paul''s writing of Philippians 1. It''s one of my favorite passages in the Bible, probably because it always shames me and my trivial challenges a little. I think that if anything would convince me that fear is a sign of lack of faith, this might be it.', 19, '2011-06-01 04:29:13'),
(91, 24, 'I might be biased but I love this song and I think it''s still a message MIT needs to hear.', 23, '2011-06-01 04:39:25'),
(92, 438, 'natalie grant rocks it! I really like this song''s "can''t stop me now because my Jesus is the bomb!" attitude.  ', 17, '2011-06-01 04:54:31'),
(93, 435, 'Ah this song has such depth- both musically and spiritually.  ', 17, '2011-06-01 04:57:37'),
(94, 439, 'Admittedly I kinda just want to sing/maybe even arrange the intro. Really though I love the contrast between the knowing what I''ve been and who I am. And the part that gets stuck in my head is the good part =)', 23, '2011-06-01 05:13:00'),
(95, 437, 'This is the first song I heard by LIGHTS where I was like "Dude! She''s christian!!" Daniel in the lion''s den, david and goliath, and jesus. I love how she starts out this song saying put me at the head of the battle. I''ll fight.', 24, '2011-06-01 05:41:05'),
(96, 437, 'Plus, her verses contain references to WoW, for the nerd at heart ^_^', 24, '2011-06-01 23:07:22'),
(97, 439, 'dude this is awesome! thanks for suggesting this kellie!! and you''re right, the intro is great, but honestly the whole song is too :D', 24, '2011-06-02 21:07:49'),
(98, 422, 'This song reminds me of Romans 7 in that no matter what I am trying to do I never get it right. Sometimes the prodigal son and sometimes the other brother. I always screw up and God is always there to save me.', 23, '2011-06-12 17:27:12'),
(99, 52, 'Yes it is predictable but that doesn''t take away from the message. It''s a bit of a different style from most of our songs. I like how this unifies all these stories under a need for God. I think it could be really powerful on spring break too.', 23, '2011-06-12 17:41:01'),
(100, 434, 'I think this song could work well in the context of a skit. I like how it ties in scripture, and our soloists could do a great job with this song.', 3, '2011-06-19 15:48:18'),
(101, 398, 'Spring Break appropriate, poetic, expresses a righteous desire to be faithful to God. Content-wise, it''s a winner in my book.', 3, '2011-06-19 15:57:16'),
(102, 401, 'Pros: it made me happy too, and it''s Spring Break kosher. Cons: a couple lines could be mistaken for boyfriend-ness, and I don''t the song is particularly strong lyrically or musically. Seems good but not great.', 3, '2011-06-19 16:17:45'),
(103, 440, '"I hear you say my love is over- it''s underneath. It''s inside, it''s in between." A wonderful song to remind us that God loves us at all times.', 19, '2011-07-05 02:44:33'),
(104, 441, 'This song is kinda catchy, so it wasn''t until I listened to it several times that I realized the artist was making a really important point. I know that I for one tend to personalize my struggles into me vs whatever, when it should really be God vs whatever, and therefore many of the things which make me too insecure to do what I know I should shouldn''t have that effect on me.', 19, '2011-07-05 02:57:23'),
(105, 406, 'sorry...', 3, '2011-07-11 04:08:18'),
(106, 436, 'It''s a little worship song-y, but the message is clearly stated, and the bridge is powerful.', 3, '2011-07-11 04:16:30'),
(107, 438, 'Loud/soft contrast, cool little instrumental parts, the cool harmony, and the attitude all suggest that this song will make for interesting a cappella.', 3, '2011-07-11 04:42:51'),
(108, 432, 'Let it be recorded here for all posterity that BU has an absolutely epic arrangement of this song.', 3, '2011-07-11 05:10:58'),
(109, 431, 'This song could partially fill the "here, this is what we believe" role in the concert set, so long as there''s another song that features salvation through Christ more prominently.', 3, '2011-07-11 05:20:08'),
(111, 414, 'Looking at the arrangement, it seems the background parts are pretty simple and singable and would be a nice way to break in new singers. The exception is the soprano line in a few spots. Incidentally, it''s likely that we''ll have multiple newbies on each part this term, except for soprano.', 3, '2011-07-12 05:16:31'),
(113, 413, 'The similes and metaphors are laid on thick in the verses, and I don''t think they do a good job of supporting the overall message of the song. It''s unusual for me to dislike a Stanford arrangement, but this one seems awfully plain- except for the random faux Asian riff, which is just weird.', 3, '2011-07-12 05:33:24'),
(114, 407, 'If we really want a song that talks about God giving us freedom from our burdens, and we''re not doing "Shackles", then I think this song expresses that idea in a more accessible way than "Free" or "Free to Be Me".', 3, '2011-07-12 05:54:21'),
(115, 111, 'I absolutely love the crux of the message of the song, which is that bad things that happen to you can become great things if they bring you closer to God. That, coupled with the attitude and uniqueness of the song enable it to be both a spiritual and musical centerpiece of the set.', 3, '2011-07-12 06:16:39'),
(116, 111, 'Pretty repetitive, but has a good edge and message. If we could pull off the hardcoreness with an arrangement, yes, although I worry acafying it would make it less hardcore.   ', 17, '2011-07-16 22:16:57'),
(117, 401, 'Song Party notes:  - in a secular context, it can be mistaken for a "boyfriend" song\r\n - it''s catchy, makes us happy, nice Spring Break song\r\n - very simple - no depth to the message', 3, '2011-07-16 22:43:45'),
(118, 413, 'Yeah, a feel good song for sure.  We don''t have to to Stanford version, right?  ', 17, '2011-07-16 22:44:30'),
(119, 413, 'Party notes: - very cute\r\n- the message of God being undeniable is not very strongly pushed\r\n- more interesting than Show me Life (much more unique)\r\n- (although dordor likes showmelike bettah)  but we could make changes to standford''s arrangement', 3, '2011-07-16 22:50:34'),
(120, 17, 'Party notes: - The singer is singing both sides, where they know where God is, but they don''t know... not clear and it''s confusing\r\n- it read''s more harshly than it sounds\r\n- need a good blurb to do it, Good for Spring Break\r\n', 3, '2011-07-16 23:00:13'),
(121, 17, 'Additional party note: - nice to have a minor key girl''s song', 3, '2011-07-16 23:01:21'),
(122, 422, 'Party notes: - John dislikes the way the bridge sounds...\r\n- the chorus is a little convoluted... I always have what?\r\n- sounds like a sig other song.  \r\n- partial arrangment.. very difficult to finish \r\n', 3, '2011-07-16 23:08:19'),
(123, 434, 'Party notes: - phrasing the parable of the prodigal son in a different way\r\n- a story\r\n- at the end, it says it''s about you... it''s deep in a non-subtle way\r\n- technical challenge for the soloist... she must really express the emotion\r\n- potential to affect others\r\n', 3, '2011-07-16 23:21:22'),
(124, 404, 'Party notes: - harmony is pretty darn hard\r\n- question of - only believe in God b/c there''s heaven\r\n- nice for the Christian audience\r\n- focus on the family, not on God...\r\n- but in the context of Country songs, God is the big one the final thing at the end.\r\n- even though things are terrible now like family dying, it''s only temporary\r\n', 3, '2011-07-16 23:33:18'),
(125, 435, 'Party notes: - lots methaphors , Jacob thinks that it will be inaccessable, Dorothy thinks it makes it more accessable\r\n-  deep/ interesting lyrically and musically\r\n- more worship than poppy\r\n- could see this sung at a chrch service\r\n- Christianese, not necessarily in a bad way\r\n- cool song musically and lyrically', 3, '2011-07-16 23:44:37'),
(126, 441, 'I think this could be a good penultimate song.  It''s like "okay, so here''s the deal, God loves you, don''t be afraid to love him back!"  ', 17, '2011-07-16 23:46:48'),
(127, 441, '- < arranged, catchy, musical than brave\r\n- > stronger words\r\npoppy \r\n- a lot of girls could probably do it\r\n- good penultimate song, works well paired with others/good for spring break\r\n', 3, '2011-07-16 23:54:24'),
(128, 441, '^ those were the party notes', 3, '2011-07-16 23:54:37'),
(129, 75, 'Party notes: - Drop dead gorgeous chorus.  WOAH!\r\n- message similar to WTMF, but in the positive rather than in the negative (when the mountians fall, I WILL be found in you)\r\n- musically very nice', 3, '2011-07-17 00:02:04'),
(130, 396, 'Party notes: -  line that differentiates it "save me from being confused"  from lack of direction, knowledge, wisdom.  \r\n- interesting from a skeptic''s point of view: God, if you''re there, reveal the truth...\r\n- paying a cost for learning the truth? shouldn''t it be paying a cost because of love? disagreement over whether this is a problem\r\n- what is this guy looking for? we think he''s looking for who God is and for God to provide direction for his life', 3, '2011-07-17 00:15:28'),
(131, 429, 'Party notes: - a solid song, encouraging, not the solid gospel prayer song...\r\n- speaks to God being behind you if your motives are righteous (similar to Brave or Walk on the Water)\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 00:25:52'),
(133, 402, 'Party notes: - really focuses on, "well, what if I can''t hear God''s voice?" \r\n- let''s christians and nonchristians, know- even though you can''t hear God, that''s okay\r\n- quirky, fun, kind of deep', 3, '2011-07-17 00:43:03'),
(134, 414, 'Party notes: - pretty darn christian, never says God or Jesus so ok for the careful places\r\n- easy song\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 00:53:01'),
(135, 111, 'Party notes: - definitely needs a blurb, easily up for misinterpretation....\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 01:23:57'),
(137, 394, 'Party notes: - SKIP TO 1:30!!!!!!\r\n- out of the box, percussion show, maybe two percussionists out front (where the soloists usually are) doing a beatbox battle during the instrumental break\r\n- good opener, cool, fun... good for one concert\r\n- could also be a closer\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 01:44:45'),
(138, 52, 'Party notes: - message is God''s forgiveness - lyrics could be misunderstood without blurb', 3, '2011-07-17 01:53:46'),
(139, 426, 'Party notes: - musically very very cool\r\n- thematically, it''s about God, carry me, change me.\r\n- Very Spring Break Appropriate', 3, '2011-07-17 01:58:23'),
(140, 421, 'Party notes: - requires blurbing...\r\n- need a strong soloist\r\n- not really safe for spring break', 3, '2011-07-17 02:02:32'),
(141, 407, 'Party notes: - effectively Psalm 23\r\n- being free''d message/giving your burdens\r\nJacob: the reason you''re free and happy because you''ve found the one who can take your burdens from you', 3, '2011-07-17 02:18:40'),
(142, 406, 'Party notes: - message is a little ambiguous?\r\n- good context for GBIS\r\n- wish some of the verses were a little more prominent\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 02:20:14'),
(143, 410, 'Party notes: - like the music\r\n- theologically, we owe God one? (it''s understatement, just like Joy)\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 02:25:53'),
(144, 423, 'Party notes: - solid Gospel message\r\n- arrangement is pretty good (fun according to Martin)\r\n- high solo', 3, '2011-07-17 02:30:24'),
(145, 431, 'party notes: - message is solid - musically, very cool with wrapping the ends of lines\r\n\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 02:34:20'),
(146, 418, 'Party notes: - Jacob has mostly arranged version\r\n- as safe as a Flowery Song for spring break...\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 02:39:27'),
(147, 427, 'Party notes: - creative take on the "renewed" message\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 02:42:33'),
(148, 420, 'Party notes: Jacob: similar message to "enough" \r\nGod is our highest authority.  I screw up. \r\n- message solid\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 02:46:25'),
(149, 24, 'Party notes: - not musically spectacular (Eric)\r\n- need a strong soloist, high energy - don''t be discouraged that you kinda suck...\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 02:53:29'),
(150, 438, 'Party notes: -riff is awesome\r\n-rockin'' girl songs\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 02:57:53'),
(151, 415, 'Party notes: - will be on the cd\r\n- encouragement for the christians...\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 03:06:09'),
(152, 409, 'Party notes: - Message-wise: "God is cool"... a little opaque \r\n- cool music !!!\r\n- arranging the mashup would be musically attractive\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 03:12:54'),
(153, 399, 'Party notes: - praise song, solid for church gigs\r\n- worship heavy\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 03:16:02'),
(154, 398, 'Party notes: cool rhythm! ', 3, '2011-07-17 03:26:55'),
(155, 440, 'Party notes: - nice and slow\r\n- interesting take on forgiveness and perfect people\r\n- clever lyrics\r\n', 3, '2011-07-17 03:35:03'),
(157, 432, 'Party notes: seems a little too soon after BU floored us with it for us to do it... would feel pretty strange doing it', 3, '2011-07-17 03:41:08'),
(158, 443, 'My arrangement is SSATBB + Solo/Duet, rich and dense.  It has a phenomenal message of who we are and how our identity in Jesus is the only way to have meaning in an otherwise ephemeral life.', 34, '2011-12-15 14:38:27'),
(159, 444, 'This arrangement is SATB + solo.  I think the message is perfect for an environment like MIT (and Georgia Tech, hence why I arranged it), where individuals are by and large convinced intellectually that the Gospel is irrevelant fantasy.  It confronts the listeners with a very simple but poignant question: what if you''re wrong?', 34, '2011-12-15 14:52:34'),
(160, 445, 'I''ll let Rachel describe her arrangement, but I really like this song, how it describes life here on earth ("in the valley"), and is a cry to God to rescue us as in Psalm 40:2.', 34, '2011-12-15 15:08:06'),
(161, 446, 'This song is very choral (similar to ACIB), and would be a great opportunity to showcase our group musicality.  The lyrics of my arrangment are slightly different than the youtube I found, and also the youtube is different in that they are a huge choir...but this arrangment sounds good in the context of a smaller a cappella group, and is actually best in un-miked situations and in acoustical settings (cathedral, etc).  Simple lyrics, beautiful chord progression, one of these choral songs per semester is a good way to change up the pace from aca-bopping all the time.', 34, '2011-12-15 15:22:09'),
(162, 447, 'I love how this song sounds, and singing with it on the cd.  The arrangement looks very crazy, but is fun!\r\n\r\nThe lyrics are so powerful.  They talk about how we listen to lies of doubt and unbelief and start to fear... but that we can cling to God in those moments and know that we are his children, and that we are secure in Christ and don''t have to be afraid!', 35, '2011-12-15 17:04:18'),
(163, 445, 'My arrangement has SATB plus a tenor (or ambitious alto...) solo, with a bass solo double and some echos.', 35, '2011-12-15 17:06:54'),
(164, 448, 'We can have a very simple understanding of God: knowing that he made the world, saying flowery prayers, or going to church and sitting in the seat, not seeing the meaning in it all-- Salvation and a personal relationship with a God who loves us!  Not realizing that God is waiting to free our souls... This is about desiring to get to know God better-- to run towards him with our whole hearts, and fall in love with our savior...\r\n\r\nI like this song for our set because it makes the distinction between surface Christianity (believing in God, saying your prayers, going to church) and the real thing... which might be something people can relate to if they grew up in church but don''t own it for themselves.\r\n\r\nI found an existing arrangement on the Xprod NWC database, which sounded pretty (SATB with solo and duet, if I recall). ', 35, '2011-12-15 18:43:04'),
(165, 449, 'Nothing can save us but Jesus'' blood and righteousness!  We cannot be pardoned from our sin because of anything good we have done!\r\n\r\nThis is a really fun, upbeat, different arrangement of the awesome hymn "Nothing But the Blood of Jesus"... It''s not arranged yet, but I think that it would be a really interesting style to add to our set, and is such a straight gospel message--especially that no good we do can save us!', 35, '2011-12-15 22:39:40'),
(166, 450, 'Light, fun message: Lots of little things can drive us crazy!  Things going wrong throughout our day can really make us get frustrated and upset.  But Jesus has the power to transform our lives, and teaching us how to deal with this stuff--with God''s peace and praise to him-- is one way non-Christians can see this in our lives.  Like Brad''s friends told him, this was a witness to them that we didn''t let these mishaps in our concert freak us out.  We knew that God was working things out, and people can see that!  Also, this song has a fun upbeat feel and is different in style than some of our usual stuff.  And has a female solo, which we need more of!  :D\r\n--Having a lighter-feeling message for some songs is also nice, to break up the intensity...', 35, '2011-12-15 22:43:24'),
(167, 163, 'I actually think the original soloist for the Supertones is male... but perhaps this is arranged in a key that would make it difficult for a guy soloist?...', 35, '2011-12-15 23:53:47'),
(168, 453, 'Declaring that God has touched our lives, and that we will seek him with our whole hearts and hang onto his promises, even in hard times...\r\n<3 this song.  So pretty.', 35, '2011-12-16 00:23:59'),
(169, 163, 'That''s correct. The version on the CD (I''ll upload it later when I get the chance) has a female solo. I think we should keep it that way because it''s generally harder to find girl-solo songs.', 3, '2011-12-16 00:26:07'),
(170, 163, 'Sounds good...', 35, '2011-12-16 00:33:33'),
(171, 163, 'I had the song, so I uploaded it.', 35, '2011-12-16 00:40:13'),
(172, 454, 'This song addresses the fact that a lot of people are put off of Christianity by what a lot of misled Christians have done in the past... things done in the name of Jesus that are not in line with the gospel!  This song wants to convince these dubious people that the God we know, the truth we know, isn''t like that... If they REALLY knew what He was like, they might change their minds... I think this would be very relevant to our audience...\r\n \r\nI really like this song!  And it has a fun style and lots of cool girly vocal parts!  :D', 35, '2011-12-16 02:21:05'),
(173, 446, 'Are those lyrics the only things they were singing?  I couldn''t really hear their words, so I wasn''t sure...', 35, '2011-12-16 02:48:07'),
(174, 446, 'yes, I have a copy of UnBounded singing this somewhere that I''ll try to post...it will give a much clearer picture of what we''d sound like', 34, '2011-12-16 16:04:46'),
(175, 451, 'This song has a similar message (albeit presented in a more modern way) to "I''m not cool" (Scott Krippayne), which has also been suggested.  I''m not sure I''m OK with either song in the sense that they seem to convey the message "Jesus loves me so I can be myself", as opposed to the more accurate "Jesus loves me so I can be more like Him".  \r\n\r\nNow, I know that neither songwriter intended the former to be the primary message (or at least I sincerely hope not), and we could do either of these songs with an appropriate qualifying blurb with no problems.  HOWEVER we discussed at term in review that as an a cappella group it makes sense for the songs to speak for themselves insofar as possible, and that being the case I would prefer to select songs in the set that don''t require qualification to convey an accurate theological message.', 34, '2011-12-16 16:11:25'),
(176, 245, 'Comment essentially repeated from "Free to be me"...   This song has a similar message (albeit presented in a more 80''s way) to "free to be me" (Francesca Battistelli), which has also been suggested.  I''m not sure I''m OK with either song in the sense that they seem to convey the message "Jesus loves me so I can be myself", as opposed to the more accurate "Jesus loves me so I can be more like Him".  \r\n\r\nNow, I know that neither songwriter intended the former to be the primary message (or at least I sincerely hope not), and we could do either of these songs with an appropriate qualifying blurb with no problems.  HOWEVER we discussed at term in review that as an a cappella group it makes sense for the songs to speak for themselves insofar as possible, and that being the case I would prefer to select songs in the set that don''t require qualification to convey an accurate theological message.', 34, '2011-12-16 16:13:43');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(177, 452, 'I love this song (and anything by Sanctus Real, actually), and the lyrics resonate with me...not sure that it appeals to the stage of life of 90% of our typical audience, though (i.e. without wife and kids).  Still, never too early to start thinking about how you''ll do all that when the time comes :-)  ', 34, '2011-12-16 16:22:53'),
(178, 442, 'This would be difficult to fill out a 4-part arrangement since it''s written as 3 parts.  It would be an interesting technical variation from our usual musical style, but barbershop is a fickle friend...it can be surprisingly difficult because of how exposed all of the parts are.', 34, '2011-12-16 16:28:21'),
(179, 450, 'Agree on all points.  It would be easy to change the lyrics to something closer to home for MIT students...things about p-sets and tests...', 34, '2011-12-16 16:38:57'),
(180, 455, 'I would love to arrange this song...it speaks of surrender in difficult times, faith that God has a great plan for our lives even if we can''t see what He''s doing all at once.', 34, '2011-12-16 16:47:02'),
(181, 456, 'This soung could be very powerful in an a cappella setting, and it tells the gospel straight up.  Added bonus: it talks about Jesus returning, which is a message we don''t often get to sing about (at least not this semester...)', 34, '2011-12-16 16:55:33'),
(182, 454, 'I support a girl-band song. Perhaps a mini-skit featuring the "Nice Girls" (play off of spice girls...?)  ', 34, '2011-12-16 17:02:57'),
(183, 452, 'You might be the only non-awkward soloist for it :)\r\nI was thinking that although a very cool song, it might not be so relevant for most of the group and the audience, although certainly some!  Not a deal-breaker tho.', 35, '2011-12-16 19:51:41'),
(184, 163, 'Btw... it would be so fun to do this one!! I am in favor.  Especially with it being ska, interesting style... and a bass part that at least SOUNDS really fun...since they often get lots of whole notes.', 35, '2011-12-16 19:57:32'),
(185, 245, 'I''ll defend "I''m Not Cool" against Brad''s point. Although there is a line in the bridge that says "I can be myself," in context the more precise (and extremely clear) meaning is "the world''s standards don''t matter." At best, it''s implied that God''s standards do matter. Even at worst, I think only Amelia Bedelia would take away "God loves me so I can define my own morality."', 3, '2011-12-17 01:07:00'),
(186, 454, 'Very in-your-face message to non-Christians that they are missing out! Not sure if it''s too in-your-face or just right. I wish it weren''t so wordy.', 3, '2011-12-17 01:42:44'),
(187, 454, 'Hmm.  That''s true that it''s very direct.  If we wanted to do the song but everyone agreed it''s a bit too much, we could just shorten it or something, or even remove/adapt small parts while retaining the message.\r\n"If you really knew, you MIGHT change your mind"... I don''t know what would be best.  As Ken had said, Jesus was also very direct, and as long as we are speaking the truth in love, it might be the best method at least for one or two songs.  We''ll see.', 35, '2011-12-17 02:18:52'),
(188, 450, '2nd verse... "I''ve got three midterms in a row | And I forgot the Athena combo"', 3, '2011-12-17 02:25:05'),
(189, 450, 'hahaha... excellent!  I like it even more now with the prospect of adapting it to MIT.. especially since the parts about cars and speeding weren''t relevant to me.  ', 35, '2011-12-17 02:26:06'),
(190, 450, 'Btw I am willing to arrange this if it gets chosen.  I will have time during IAP.', 35, '2011-12-17 02:27:16'),
(191, 457, 'This song is one of my all time favorites, speaking to me whenever I feel wretched or heartbroken or angry at God. I plan to (help) arrange it this spring whether or not it''s one of our songs. ', 39, '2011-12-24 02:21:13'),
(192, 457, 'Never heard this before, but I like it.  It could be an interesting/texturally complex arrangment, I would support working on it.', 34, '2011-12-24 03:52:01'),
(193, 451, 'I love this song too!  It''s been suggested before so just merging the comments section. It definitely helped me get through freshman year. \r\n\r\n"Comments here: http://xprod.mit.edu/w/Francesca_Battistelli_-_Free_to_Be_Me Still with agreement that it''s similar to Free and Perfect People-  Shion\r\n\r\nPpl at the song listening party last year also thought it could be up for misinterpretation. "\r\nDorothy\r\n\r\n', 17, '2011-12-24 07:57:07'),
(194, 5, 'eeeeeeeoooooooooooaaaaaahhhhhh!!!!\r\n\r\nIs all I have to say', 17, '2011-12-24 08:04:28'),
(195, 450, 'Aw this is super cute.  It kinda reminds me of not so long ago when I called my parents about being disappointed with my grades this term and the first thing they did was pray praising God for the things He has blessed me with.  aww, that was the stuff.  :)', 17, '2011-12-24 08:25:43'),
(196, 402, 'I love the whimsical nature of this song, both lyrically and musically.  The theological truth of ultimate reality is an excellent message, and one that I think is easy to lose since we tend to talk about our personal experiences with God instead of His objective existence.', 34, '2011-12-24 18:57:51'),
(197, 462, 'From 1 of the song suggestion pages.. last year, or two years ago-not sure there are like 3 pgs total. \r\n\r\nComments Spring 2011 We did this last year. It was a Geofft arrangement and was super-awesome! - Amanda -D The concept''s great and the lyrics are great. I think my biggest worry this term is style overlap, since we''ve got "Never Change" and I actually kind of would like us to do one of the Lecrae pieces or something and even that''s pushing it. -geofft [edit] Song Party Spring 2010 it would be different. maybe a bit repetitive? i''m going to love vs i was made to love - implies God is the Maker it''s nice in that it''s a different type of song so it''s out of our "circle" of songs that we sing, but it''s not like...too far out. easily can be sung to a girl?? it does contradict a little but still.... [edit] Comments Spring 2010 i''d be so down for perc/soloing this song -ron- it seemed pretty clear to me that it''s a statement of God''s value as opposed to a statement of our intent. I''m so glad this song was suggested again. The message that we should love God is a great one- this song could contribute much to our set both in terms of message and musical variety. - Jacob I don''t see an issue with the bridge; I see it in terms of Philippians 3 "I consider all things rubbish compared to knowing God" etc. I think we should be able to follow through on such promises (like Luther''s "God, if you save me from this thunderstorm, I''ll become a monk!"). Anyway. I like the song, it''s clear, it gets a message across that is worthwhile and sufficiently different from some of the messages we tend to focus on, and the verse is pitched so we are bounded on exactly how much we can make fools of ourselves. :) And the phrase "I was made to love you" is pretty memorable. -geofft [edit] Comments Song Party the rap isn''t like...hardcore rap. so i think that''s singable -shion- the bridge? a bit of mush-fluff? it''s a good profession of love that people use, but it might not mesh with the message of the song which is stronger.-daniel- if it''s a statement of God''s value, then it''s good. but if it''s a statement of our intent, then it''s lame. do we follow through on promises like that? i''d be willing to give up anything for you vs ill do anything for you.-daniel/martin- [edit] Comments Fall 2009 This is a little bit different from our normal style of songs, but it might add some variety to a set and I think it would make an interesting a capella arrangement. I also really like the message of this song: that our purpose is, most simply, to love God and be loved by God. My favorite part is when the singer addresses God as "Daddy." - Amanda', 17, '2011-12-26 00:06:01'),
(198, 407, 'oh boy I wonder if the pitches will pick this one... if only we had an arrangement in the works... ohwait.  -_-', 17, '2011-12-26 00:10:14'),
(199, 462, 'I can''t seem to find any video, but we did this song a couple years ago with Ron Perez soloing. The arrangement is pretty good, and we had some fun choreo. It''d be a good song to do again if (and only if) we have a soloist up to the challenge (Brad or Levi?)', 3, '2011-12-26 05:05:19'),
(200, 408, 'I don''t know if we have our own, but Stanford has a really nice arrangement of this; it''s the one playing in the background of this page at the time of this comment.', 26, '2011-12-29 15:02:09'),
(201, 214, 'Comments from Fa09 suggestions:\r\nThis song basically tells the story of the Gospel, repeatedly... I''ll let the lyrics speak for themselves! And I like the music, too. The alum group sang it at our concert in the Spring, but I still think it could be a good one to do (already arranged, too). - Martin\r\nI almost suggested this too. But then Karen said the lyrics are so slow that it would take a very engaging soloist to keep the audience from zoning out and missing the great words. Upon a second listen I agree. But I still do love it, and if other people think it''s not too boring, yay! -Daniel', 26, '2011-12-29 15:11:46'),
(202, 214, '...I still agree with my previous comment: presents the Gospel repeatedly! I think it could be really captivating with an emotive female soloist (e.g., in the style of a dramatic story reading)', 26, '2011-12-29 15:25:26'),
(203, 34, 'From Sp10 suggestions: We have a nice choralish (SATB aca) arrangement of this by Gabe, who wrote it in the plane on the way to Spring Break (Omaha, IIRC) because the pastor wanted us to sing it the next day. It''s a fine arrangement. Note that this is actually a fairly recent hymn. -geofft ::\r\nI really like this song, and in particular our arrangement of it. Part of that may be nostalgia (it was my first spring break, and I have some good memories of both xprods and Jacob''s parents taking care of me when I was sick), but it really does have some beautiful, eloquent, gospel-filled lyrics... e.g., "Why should I gain from His reward? / I cannot give an answer / But this I know with all my heart / His wounds have paid my ransom". \r\nI think what I love about it is how it repeatedly drives in how God suffered for our wrongs, and how we''re rewarded for Jesus''s works:\r\n"That He should give His only Son / To make a wretch [me] His treasure",\r\n"As wounds which mar the chosen One, Bring many sons [us] to glory",\r\n"His dying breath has brought me life",\r\n"Why should I gain from His reward", and for course,\r\n"His wounds have paid my ransom"\r\n- MS', 26, '2011-12-29 15:47:51'),
(204, 34, 'tl/dr of above: Beautiful, eloquent, gospel-filled lyrics which repeatedly present the contrast inherent in Jesus''s sacrifice for us (e.g., "His dying breath has brought me life"), and a really nice musical arrangement too.', 26, '2011-12-29 15:55:28'),
(205, 464, 'I heard this song again on the radio yesterday and was reminded of how poignant the message is.  It explains (in a tender loving way) that sometimes the best things God has for us are trials.  I learned to play it a while back, so I think arranging it would be a snap.  Good female solo, and a soft lyrical song with beautiful arpeggiated chords.', 34, '2011-12-29 16:20:05'),
(206, 458, 'Personal opinion: fun beat, probably fun to sing, but lyrically vapid.  ', 34, '2011-12-29 16:43:13'),
(207, 214, 'I love the lyrics, but agree that the song is kind of slow to develop.  We would have to be on our musical A-game to pull this off, there are some very exposed parts of the arrangement.', 34, '2011-12-29 16:54:38'),
(208, 465, 'This song connects both with a spiritual/religous and secular audience. I think the theme of hope in the song about being fixed doesn''t necessarily refer to humanity working towards building up their brothers and sisters insomuch as God helping us to become more prepared for his Kingdom. It is POWERFUL. It is a good message for MIT students to be reminded that they don''t need to depend on their own strengths to survive.', 36, '2011-12-29 22:11:25'),
(209, 466, 'Once again I am all for meeting people where they are with the secular music vibe. The Fray is a great band that really connects with the audience and I think the message of this song is that we all face challenges in life that lead us to making decisions we may never think would happen. The theme is very relevant to MIT as students are dealing with issues that make them question what their purpose is. I think to find God in this song is a beautiful thing and that sharing this song would mean allowing people to really look deeper into their own relationships. We are relational beings; we were created to love and be loved. How To Save A Life reminds us to cherish and invest deeply in our friendships while also reminding us that we are instruments of God''s love for our brothers and sisters and even a small smile can change someone''s world.', 36, '2011-12-29 22:21:26'),
(210, 467, 'Audrey Assad challenges her listeners to question what life really is in her music. She can show the connection God has to every soul in a way that resonates with many people. Breaking Through uses really neat Biblical imagery to reinforce the fact that heaven is truly breaking through into our lives everyday; God desires to see us at his eternal banquet in heaven.', 36, '2011-12-29 22:26:43'),
(211, 468, 'Jesus is everywhere. In every man. And in every place. His fingerprints are placed upon every heart.', 36, '2011-12-29 22:34:30'),
(212, 465, 'Do you remember when Penn State''s Rhythm of Faith did this for Jam More Baltimore?  I do!  I thought it was kinda cute that they changed the last couple lyrics to "Jesus will fix you."    One cool thing about doing a secular song is that hopefully by performing it in a Christian acapella setting we encourage our audience to think about a secular song from a Christian perspective.  I know that after listening to RoF''s cover of fix you that song became associated with a spiritual message for me.  ', 17, '2011-12-31 20:01:27'),
(213, 465, 'Also, Big Mike''s perc... lolol', 17, '2011-12-31 20:01:57'),
(214, 463, 'I know I know, yet another emo Barlow girl song.  But I think the powerful message from this is that we actually _need_ God''s love.  Whether we realize it to love him back or not.  I think often I wonder to myself "why should I love God?  why should I be praying? why should I do this?"  When really, I need God to love me, I need that relationship with him.  ', 17, '2011-12-31 20:06:16'),
(215, 463, 'Also, because I know this will come up:  Is this one of those "could be about my boyfriend" songs?  mm, well I certainly wouldn''t interpret it that way.  also:  \r\n\r\n"''Cause You''re a God who has all things "\r\n\r\n', 17, '2011-12-31 20:08:39'),
(216, 472, 'I think of this song as very similar to Praise You In the Storm. It does need a follow-up though- a response saying "Yes, God is with us and he is faithful, He does hear us". But I like this song almost as much as I like Praise You In the Storm. maybe more. -shion-', 29, '2012-01-03 07:49:05'),
(217, 473, 'Sorry, the first video is the wrong one and I can''t take it down >.<', 29, '2012-01-03 08:11:39'),
(218, 473, 'This song would take a lot of effort in terms of arranging, but it could turn out to be amazing as the song appears to have a very very very high ceiling in terms of potential. This would also be a tough but very fun solo. Overall this song is pretty straightforward lyrically too aside from the "darling" toward the end which needs to be replaced with an appropriate word to refer to God/Jesus. ', 29, '2012-01-03 08:12:55'),
(219, 473, 'Secular song but with blurb and one minor line change plus blurb could have a very clear and powerful Christian message. And a recognizable one for non-Christians. ', 29, '2012-01-03 08:14:25'),
(220, 475, 'Ok, I''m suggesting this not primarily because I want this song in our set, but can we just take 20 min of retreat/rehearsal and learn this song? Practically every other Christian a cappella group knows this song, it''s not that hard to learn, and it often gets busted out during things like BIDB, but xprods don''t know it (granted, it''s not too hard to follow, but I don''t know the lyrics). Other than that my opinion of this song is that reminds me of the 80s like Reason We Sing does but without the doo doo doo...doo. ', 29, '2012-01-03 08:24:56'),
(221, 476, 'This song is super fun to sing and is a solid proclamation of how good and great the Lord is! High power/energy, and it really brings joy, both to the group and to the audience. ', 29, '2012-01-03 08:42:14'),
(222, 444, 'I agree with Brad that it does confront the listeners with a poignant question. And something that many people ask at one point or another during their walk in faith. I think it will add an interesting feel to our set. One con may be that it''s not as versatile- we can''t just sing it at any gig/any place because it may be well suited for a place like MIT, but it can very well get lost at other locations, or with children/etc. \r\n\r\nHehe I remember this song from a particular audition... :P', 29, '2012-01-03 08:48:11'),
(223, 163, 'I like the energy of this song, but I think there are other songs (ex: All Things Are Possible) that are equally high-energy and fun, but has more substance. This song addresses some points, but I feel like it''s not really saying anything. These were some of my takeaways from when I led Cross Linked two summers ago and we did this song. ', 29, '2012-01-03 08:54:58'),
(224, 5, 'I love this song. But I think we did it enough last year and it can sit another year or so. :/', 29, '2012-01-03 08:55:59'),
(226, 466, 'I have an arrangement from my undergrad group (attached a separate youtube video).  I don''t mind blurring the secular/sacred music line in general, but I have a few reservations about for this song in particular: I think most people will know it''s a song about a drug intervention, and I don''t know how easily we can spin it to Levi''s interpretation with a blurb.  Also, the song has been SO VERY OVERDONE both on the radio and in a cappella circles for years now.  ', 34, '2012-01-03 17:42:34'),
(227, 476, 'I think this would be very challenging to do in an a cappella setting since most of the musical variety and energy is generated by horn licks and percussion.  In my opinion, this is really the gospel choir''s territory.', 34, '2012-01-03 21:03:39'),
(228, 473, 'Went ahead and changed the pre-arranged flag, since I have a mixed arrangement of this from undergrad days.  Also had the recording handy (from live concert so apologize for minor tuning issues up front).  I remember this arrangement is fun to sing.', 34, '2012-01-03 21:11:49'),
(229, 475, 'Agree with Shion on all points: it''s too overdone to be a dedicated concert song, but too easy not to have in our back pocket for nursing home gigs.', 34, '2012-01-03 21:13:52'),
(230, 472, 'I love it.  I''d volunteer to help arrange.', 34, '2012-01-03 21:16:18'),
(231, 462, 'I think I''d defer to Levi on this one...he is far more gangster than I.', 34, '2012-01-03 21:26:59'),
(232, 460, 'A dense metaphor...I''m not sure what he''s trying to say.  I need a Lit junkie to explain it.  Kevin?', 34, '2012-01-03 21:40:23'),
(233, 461, 'Similarly to another marriage-based Sanctus Real song suggested by Caitlin, I''m not sure how much relevance this song has for our average audience member (although I like it!).  I guess you could try to sing it from a "don''t give up on love vis-a-vis our relationship with God" perspective, but that''s stretching it a bit.', 34, '2012-01-03 22:05:58'),
(234, 459, 'I think this song would make an interesting a cappella arrangement.  It''s definitely unique, beautiful, and has very honest declarations of love for our savior.  The rythmic variation is awesome.  My only beef with this song is purely of personal preference...that since i''m a dude I prefer to think of Jesus as an all-merciful hunting buddy instead of a jealous lover...but that''s just me. :-)', 34, '2012-01-03 22:21:27'),
(235, 408, 'I like the a cappella version a lot!  I agree that it should be a core message of any worship-music-leading entity.  I agree many praise songs don''t make the transition well to performance, but I don''t think that applies here.', 34, '2012-01-03 22:46:08'),
(236, 470, 'Beautiful song.  Like some other hymns it seems a bit schizophrenic to me...I can''t pick out a single theme running through the song; it seems more like a jumble of christian-ese.  Maybe I just need Kevin to explain it to me...  ', 34, '2012-01-03 23:08:51'),
(237, 463, 'Interesting.  Before I read the first comment I was ready to criticize the song because the line "I need you to love me" implies to me that it''s something in question, like the artist is asking God to love them (which would be silly).  I was translating the song "I desire that you love me" in my head, instead of "my very existence requires that you love me", which I don''t have a theological issue with.  As long as that''s explained, I like it.  Especially the "stop pretending I can deserve what I already have".  My pastor used to say that "deserve" is a stupid concept in light of the very definition of grace.', 34, '2012-01-03 23:19:42'),
(238, 470, 'To me the parsing/ poetic lyrics makes it hard for me to get the meaning without the written lyrics.  So I wonder if audiences would feel a similar way.   It''s pretty and has a lot of imagery, but also slow.  ', 17, '2012-01-04 02:52:12'),
(239, 466, 'I like the idea but I''ve never been a big fan of this song.  ', 17, '2012-01-04 03:11:03'),
(240, 477, 'So, if we did this our arrangement doesn''t have to sound like (nor be as complicated) as this one.   But I like how this hymn reminds us that this world is transient, and we''re on a journey home to heaven.   Plus it''s so pretty and a spiritual where you don''t have to have a gospelly-powerhouse voice to sing it! ', 17, '2012-01-04 04:13:57'),
(241, 34, 'Ahh I love this song.  And yay to a clear gospel message!  ', 17, '2012-01-04 04:21:43'),
(242, 477, 'Wow, I LOVE this song.  It just kept getting better and better.  I love the tight chords, the groove in the middle, the progression of soloists, and most of all the message.  However, there is no doubt that this would be a VERY challenging song to execute well (as written...I guess we could dumb it down but where''s the fun in that??).  By the by, do we have any sopranos who have a high A flat (last note of the song)?  How about a HIGH D ABOVE THE STAFF (@ 3:24)????  Wow...', 34, '2012-01-04 16:19:49'),
(243, 476, 'Hehe; does anyone have the video of Senna soloing this at GBIS (parent''s weekend concert) 2008? It seems to suggest that it''s possible to do it with a lot of energy... by God''s grace much of Kresge auditorium was clapping along with a Christian song! ', 26, '2012-01-05 17:30:22'),
(244, 402, 'Still in favor of this song!! Loveeeee :)', 24, '2012-01-06 05:22:02'),
(245, 476, 'Well, after listening to the xprod video posted, I stand corrected about my previous comment (worried about energy...seriously, I should know this group better by now). :-)  However, I still think this song requires a pretty strong gospel-esque soloist.', 34, '2012-01-06 16:00:17'),
(246, 408, 'my comment from before still holds - I love this song! upvote it!! :D', 31, '2012-01-07 18:50:02'),
(247, 407, 'lol - apparently, arranging this has been really difficult because it''s so.. musically repetitive. and just fyi, it''s not absolutely set into the setlist this term, having spoken with the arrangers, so if you actually want to see this in the setlist - vote it!', 31, '2012-01-07 18:53:09'),
(248, 462, '<3 this song. bring out the g inside', 31, '2012-01-07 19:00:49'),
(249, 478, 'Musically - an easier song and simple. But it''s definitely "Public Venue safe" (never says God), biblical, and gets to the point of his grace despite our failures.', 31, '2012-01-07 19:13:28'),
(250, 478, 'Oh - it would require a very solid soloist though because it''s very exposed.', 31, '2012-01-07 19:13:45'),
(251, 34, '<3', 31, '2012-01-07 19:14:45'),
(252, 479, 'Light-hearted reminder to put faith into action, directed towards believers. not particularly useful on spring break, and marginally more in our final concert, but would be a fun extra song if we have our concert that early.', 31, '2012-01-07 19:24:22'),
(253, 480, 'Here''s a link to Psalm 27, the inspiration for this song: http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Psalm+27&version=NIV', 31, '2012-01-07 19:36:58'),
(254, 480, 'Anyway, this song is a little bit abstract in terms of message. It speaks to our foundation in God - and by his strength, we can face our fears and move even when we can''t see where we''re going.\r\n\r\nMusically, I think this song is fantastic - interesting, and lots of great potential for a capella', 31, '2012-01-07 19:38:54'),
(255, 129, 'This song is a prayer for God to save us when we won''t be able to make it on our own. When it comes to message - not very deep. But it is musically interesting.', 31, '2012-01-07 19:44:45'),
(256, 481, 'Message: I suppose it''s less for our audience than for us and other believers - it''s a request/reminder/confession that God is the one running the show. To give up our pride and trust Him. When it comes to our set, this song could be our proclamation that we are not at the center of what we are singing, but it is God. That we humble ourselves before Him.', 31, '2012-01-07 19:56:11'),
(257, 482, 'Message: God is more than enough. Very pointed tip towards the worldly things many people seek. Presentation: a little more abrasive than what we''re accustomed to, but it still speaks.', 31, '2012-01-07 20:11:54'),
(258, 30, 'We sing this fairly often during prayer. It''s our proclamation to praising God even when times are rough. Great message, but says the word God so it wouldn''t be very good for spring break.', 31, '2012-01-07 20:44:06'),
(259, 483, 'Kevin- Too long\r\nPolly- also too long\r\nDorothy- didn''t like it\r\nMaria- too long, too bubbly\r\nJacob- we could make it shorter: \r\n\r\n1st song about God''s faithful ness\r\n2nd, How God makes us joyful.  \r\n\r\nMartin:  Worried it goes toward "prosperity gospel"  not relateable ', 17, '2012-01-07 23:54:04'),
(260, 30, ' Arr feels like it''d be really hard to get right (emotion)  would be up for helping to rearranging (Maria). \r\n:  Great song, don''t like the arrangement.  Indifferent', 17, '2012-01-08 00:08:29'),
(261, 408, 'Good mission statement, prayer from us to God.  Drawback "what does the chorus even mean?"  Which is the memorable. ', 17, '2012-01-08 00:18:06'),
(262, 471, 'Forceful, climax building up in the bridge, anti-climatic at the end. Message : a school safe version of Amazing Grace. Seemingly repetitive. Although limited message-wise, could be a good performance piece.', 31, '2012-01-08 00:28:48'),
(263, 471, '*above from song-listening party', 31, '2012-01-08 00:29:03'),
(264, 471, 'Good praise song.  Many people like the music, but not necessarily the lyrics.  Like Amazing Grace but High School friendly', 17, '2012-01-08 00:32:47'),
(265, 476, 'SP12 Party notes: - Our live recording on youtube sounded good, which bodes well. - Might be difficult to pull off without someone like Senna - Good ending song - style of the song makes it sound less preachy than the lyrics appear on paper', 3, '2012-01-08 00:33:31'),
(266, 476, 'Message:  God is really powerful, and when he is with us he can do anything. ', 17, '2012-01-08 00:33:53'),
(267, 482, 'I really like this song!  Also has Psalm 23.  suited well to MIT audience', 17, '2012-01-08 00:40:03'),
(268, 481, 'SP12 Party Notes: - Rapper could be either gender - Background parts are a little blase - has John 3:16 !!! - anti-commercialism is good ', 3, '2012-01-08 00:40:06'),
(269, 227, 'Good Spring Break song? Story is out of the Bible but doesn''t explicitly mention God. Also, a rockin'' arrangement.', 26, '2012-01-08 00:45:06'),
(270, 459, 'Messsage: Learning to depend on God.  God brings you to the barrenness and brokeness, so that you can learn to depend on him.  \r\n\r\nMusically boring?  Song for other Christians.  "Jealous Lover"  a true Christianese phrase.  \r\n\r\n', 17, '2012-01-08 00:48:00'),
(271, 464, 'Song Party: We tend to doubt God when things go wrong, but we shouldn''t/  People pray for things and don''t get answered the way they don''t  get it answered the way they want it.  Saying that God answers our prayers sometimes through trials.  God is the silversmith, using the fire to mold us to something new.    Non-christians may be very confused by this message, Polly "Why do I want to trust God if I have to deal with raindrops every day?" ', 17, '2012-01-08 00:55:24'),
(272, 467, 'This sounds musically great! whoa!  ', 17, '2012-01-08 00:55:49'),
(273, 467, '  Song Party:  Meaning:  She''s wandering in her life, searching for meaning.  And she realizes the meaning is God.   Heaven is breaking through= God is breaking into our lives.  \r\n\r\nIt is a song that is not very widely accessible to the general population, perhaps.  ', 17, '2012-01-08 01:02:43'),
(274, 473, 'Suggested a lot because it has a lot going musically, good for lot of venues.  But, some ppl are like "It''s Evanenecense!"   Probably hard to pull off as an acapella group.  But ppl do recognize it.  Good for setting up the .   Qualms about asking God to call my name and save me from the dark, as if He hasn''t done it already.  However it is perfectly acceptable to pray for it.  ', 17, '2012-01-08 01:09:31'),
(275, 475, 'Good crowd pleaser song,  doesn''t have a lot of depth.    Good song to have in pocket, but probably not a priority song.  Possibly just a fun thing, but not a setlist thing.  ', 17, '2012-01-08 01:16:15'),
(276, 461, 'Song can sound accusatory?  Worried that although message of song is about "don''t'' give up on Love"  other things that seem like love could be encouraged.   With a blurb, we could change the meaning of the song to be the old school marriage to Christ metaphor to make it relatable.  But  do we want to change the meaning that way?  \r\n\r\nInterpreting song based on "Don''t give up on Love" as God=Love  "Don''t'' give up on God".  Could reach out to ppl in that place.  Think about "would you be comfortable singing this song to ppl without the chance to explain it."  ', 17, '2012-01-08 01:27:30'),
(277, 461, 'I would only want to do it if we could do a really clear blurb!  Otherwise i would say no.   All i heard was the marriage meaning personally,  cause I always feel that way about divorce.   But as long as we explain it,  it could be cool for people who gave up on God. ', 35, '2012-01-08 01:29:37'),
(278, 457, 'From song party:  Perspective  from Jesus.  Shows him wanting our lives.  Worry, that the line "I''m only asking for your life"  could possibly be interpreted as trivializing the great commitment?  But other disagree.  Spring break apropro', 17, '2012-01-08 01:38:19'),
(279, 453, 'Song party: I love this song.  Good missions statement.  Great arrangement.  Interesting to sing.  ', 17, '2012-01-08 01:41:45'),
(280, 465, 'Long term change on people''s perspective of this song.  Downside: audience might not like uschanging the meaning of this song.  ', 17, '2012-01-08 01:48:51'),
(281, 465, 'Might be possible to change the meaning of "I promise you I will learn from my mistakes" by having someone else sing that verse (e.g., as a "response" to the first soloist)?', 26, '2012-01-08 01:51:03'),
(282, 129, 'Agreed with John''s assessment of song.  Jacob''s take:  certain class of song that have esoteric but not particularly challenging message, but really cool musically- and this is the best of the class of that songs.    Most of the song that we sing should have a clear message, but not every song needs to.  Maria- doesn''t seem interesting enough for the audience. ', 17, '2012-01-08 01:54:00'),
(283, 453, 'One note- I did get a few comments from when we sang the song last time that it''s a song that''s fun to sing, but not as fun/engaging to listen to. (like, it''s more of a song you sing along to for personal conviction, but not a performance-type song). Just wanted to throw that out there. ', 29, '2012-01-08 01:56:54'),
(284, 471, 'I agree with the high school friendly. This song spoke to me a lot in times of need. ', 29, '2012-01-08 01:58:28'),
(285, 468, 'Pretty song,  not just about God rescuing us for something, but also adding praise.  Lots of metaphor.  People question if this song is unique meaning wise.  Stylistically sounds similar to many other songs.   But lyrically it certainly is poetic.  ', 17, '2012-01-08 02:00:11'),
(286, 30, 'Needs to be rearranged. Though, I feel like some a cappella group out there has an arrangement. The current arrangement we have is not that good at capturing the intensity of the song. ', 29, '2012-01-08 02:00:17'),
(287, 34, 'our current arrangement is pretty good, and it''s easy to learn though the alto part is a bit tricky.', 29, '2012-01-08 02:01:57'),
(288, 451, 'I agree with Brad, hence my comments from previous times that this song has been suggested. ', 29, '2012-01-08 02:03:45'),
(289, 214, 'Song Party:  Like the story telling of the song, does tell the history which adds to it.  No one is going to leave concert saying "oh that song was the coolest song in the set." but is a nice presentation of the gospel.   We''d need to have a really good soloist to do this song really well.  And we''d have to work on it a lot.  Possibly boring.  ', 17, '2012-01-08 02:08:24'),
(290, 451, 'Same things. ', 17, '2012-01-08 02:15:33'),
(291, 456, 'Agreed, this is one of the few songs that talk about his return.  Musically boring/ predictable.  ', 17, '2012-01-08 02:21:02'),
(292, 482, 'How are we going to translate this to acapella?  Message wise, we like it,  has a good role model message.   Other lecrae song would be safer to do musically.  Both are good lyrically.  ', 17, '2012-01-08 02:27:52'),
(293, 482, 'I really like this song but i think it would be safer to do the other lacrae song ', 35, '2012-01-08 02:30:30'),
(294, 163, 'Message:  God loves us unconditionally.  Some  ppl really like the ska style.  Some ppl don''t.  ', 17, '2012-01-08 02:33:34'),
(295, 163, 'need a good soloist to do it well', 31, '2012-01-08 02:33:46'),
(296, 398, 'Song Party:  Concern that nonChristians might not understand what gravity is pulling down toward.  Song doesn''t give an explicit reason why you''d want to not be part of the world:', 17, '2012-01-08 02:44:44'),
(297, 449, 'Comments from the listening party: \r\nKevin-- really fun, would be great to do!  Could present pitch issues--if we are even the slightest bit off pitch-wise, it could crash and burn\r\n\r\nJohn-- Not so crazy about the style, since he doesn''t like things that remind him of Country\r\n\r\nRachel--One of the few straight-gospel-message songs that is actually really UPBEAT and FUN!! And love the style.\r\n\r\n', 35, '2012-01-08 17:35:08'),
(298, 484, 'This song was recently arranged by an alum (Gabriel Ha) for XProd to sing. I think this song has several good qualities, namely that it is:\r\n\r\n1) Solid, but simple, message\r\n2) Spring break safe (just omit the word Jesus, the song works without it)\r\n3) Catchy and energetic\r\n4) A great option for reducing the seriousness of an otherwise morose set', 19, '2012-01-08 17:36:39'),
(299, 5, 'I agree with both-- LOVE it, and it would be really cool (as a new member) to learn it and sing it... but since it was just done last year, it seems nicer to give some other songs a chance this semester.', 35, '2012-01-08 17:38:13'),
(300, 245, 'This song has really grown on me listening to the CD... it''s a lot of fun.  But the first few times I heard it, all I really heard was "here are some of your characteristics... they are NOT cool, but it''s ok cause Jesus loves you." Emphasis on "Hey, you over there, these things about you aren''t cool." Maybe I''m the only one who reacted that way, but it annoyed me the first few times I heard it.  It is fun and upbeat tho :)  And clearly if it''s a crowd favorite, the audience doesn''t agree.  But that is my opinion...', 35, '2012-01-08 17:45:07'),
(301, 454, 'I know I was the one who suggested this one--but I have since decided that I don''t think it''s a good idea.  I personally like it (mainly for the sound), and think the message IS important, but it could really be taken as just arrogant in-your-face "If you knew what I know, you would change your mind".  Emphasis on, MEEEE knowing best, and knowing what you would do in a given situation.  So ya, I will vote no.', 35, '2012-01-08 17:51:36'),
(302, 445, 'From listening party:  A prayer song.  Jacob says "Down here in the valley" reminds him of MIT... "every puddle of mud comes from tears and blood"...\r\n Also, there is some anti-materialism in here as well, with the "folks spend their days digging round for diamonds and gold, till they just get old"  Jacob--"I got old...digging around at MIT..."   Kevin and Rachel like the line "When you touch me, that''s when I know I''m alive", although Kevin expected them to do more with that.  ', 35, '2012-01-08 17:57:30'),
(303, 445, 'Arrangement is DONE-- if anyone wants to take a look at it (just to look or to give comments if desired) let me know!  I uploaded the midi above.', 35, '2012-01-08 17:58:23'),
(304, 445, 'I apologize if it''s difficult to hear all the parts on the midi--I couldn''t really hear the guy parts well playing it off the website.', 35, '2012-01-08 18:02:26'),
(305, 402, 'I like the message of the song, but for some reason have never been much of a fan of it in general.  I guess I don''t really like the sound of it or something.  I do agree with the message points of others though...', 35, '2012-01-08 18:12:34'),
(306, 438, 'This one reminds me a little of "Gravity", except I like that it''s a really strong declaration!  And I like the part about feeling like your prayers bounce off the wall sometimes--so not FEELING like God is there, but standing firm in your belief anyway, and knowing that He is a firm foundation.', 35, '2012-01-08 18:17:19'),
(307, 442, 'I agree it would be hard to make it 4 parts and be interesting for everyone.  And this one is a little like "I Live for You", being four parts with words and no backgrounds (to speak of) or perc, but still pop style singing.  But I prefer to go with "I Live for You" instead of this one, because I feel like the message is so strong, and I like the overall sound better personally.', 35, '2012-01-08 18:21:40'),
(308, 443, 'I LOVE this song, and think it would be awesome to sing it--and I would be excited to try another song with 6 parts!  So for the message, the emphasis is on how temporary we are, and not worthy of God''s attention, but that he saved us anyway.  Which is great!  There may be some other songs suggested though, that have even more to say with the same message.  So I''m not sure if I would choose this one over the others with this message.  But I might.', 35, '2012-01-08 18:25:08'),
(309, 444, 'I like this song, and I think it has a kind of similar message to "If You Really Knew", (which I suggested), but in a much less "in your face" way.  Asking it as a question is a really good way to present it I think... \r\n', 35, '2012-01-08 18:27:47'),
(310, 446, 'So Brad, will you be able to post UnBounded singing this, before the deadline for votes?  :)', 35, '2012-01-08 18:28:58'),
(311, 448, 'About our relationship to God being deep, and personal!  Wanting to know him more!  ', 35, '2012-01-08 18:31:53'),
(312, 455, 'I like the message of letting go of your own will and letting God transform you... It does sound similar style to a lot of other suggested songs though.  But it''s a nice song, with a good message...', 35, '2012-01-08 18:36:38'),
(313, 458, 'It does sound fun to sing.  I''m having a hard time finding a strong message or meaning though... I''m not sure what they are referring to really... what is the message??', 35, '2012-01-08 18:38:56'),
(314, 460, 'It sounds like he is saying that his walk with God is tough at times, full of storms and tides trying to pull him off course, but he''s sailing toward eternal life, and God is sustaining him.  He is chasing after God, seeking him with perseverance, leaving everything else behind.\r\nSo I guess the message is Seeking God, throwing off everything that holds us back, and looking to Jesus?  \r\n', 35, '2012-01-08 18:43:46'),
(315, 460, 'I like the sound, kind of an interesting beat.  Could be another song suggested with a similar message, but a little more accessible?', 35, '2012-01-08 18:44:28'),
(316, 462, 'I really like the message, focusing on the different aspects of who God made us to be--we were made to love him, be loved by him, adore him-- really shows how God made us to be in a close relationship, not just to believe He died for us. \r\nI agree the success would hinge a lot on the soloist pulling it off...  Addressing the comments above about the bridge... we could tweak the lyrics to be something more like "You''re worth giving up everything, you''re worth giving it all away" or something.  That would clear up the possible interpretations of our intentions!  ', 35, '2012-01-08 19:11:23'),
(317, 463, 'I don''t think it''s emo.  It has a very hopeful vibe to it, I think.  Also, I like the line about "YOu''re a God who has all things, but still you want me".  I like the sound of it, with the pretty "finger-picking" guitar high nores in the background... and the interesting duet.  And ya, they clearly say "God" several times, so we wouldn''t need to explain that it''s talking about God.  I like the distinction Brad made about desiring God''s love vs. requiring God''s love... the message either way works, I think, because desiring God''s love doesn''t mean he isn''t offering it, just that we are feeling that way.  But it''s more powerful with the message of requiring his love...which could be in the blurb.', 35, '2012-01-08 19:18:28'),
(318, 470, 'I really like this song!  Very pretty, and has some really good parts.  I do agree with the previous comments tho, about it being hard to follow what they are trying to say throughout.  There are a lot of parts I don''t really get what they mean... It has a great melody tho, and sounds cool to me.  And I like the end of the first verse "Jesus Christ who died for me \r\ngave his life so that I could be free \r\nhe gave his life so that I could be free", both musically and the words...\r\nI like various chunks, but I agree with Dorothy that it might be hard for an audience to follow.', 35, '2012-01-09 01:06:57'),
(320, 477, 'I''m pretty sure Caitlin can handle it, if not others :)  Although I could be wrong.  I really liked it too.  The older language (and talking about "Jordan", which people not familiar with the bible wouldn''t get) might make the message less accessible for non-Christians.  I was also thinking the same thing, about how one reason it sounded so great was because it was PERFECTLY executed in a recording studio, and they were all really strong and on pitch.  So it would be difficult, but might be a really neat challenge.  Unless we were really strong, it might come off as a kind of slow, old-timey language song.', 35, '2012-01-09 01:17:12'),
(321, 479, 'This is quite fun... and it''s lighthearted in style, but at the same time it''s a pretty deep topic it''s addressing.  That without something to show your faith is real, your faith is fake and useless??  That''s pretty serious.  But ya, I''m not certain whether it would be the best addition to a set list... it is interesting though.', 35, '2012-01-09 01:23:28'),
(322, 480, 'Ya, very fun to listen to musically.  Interesting.  I like a lot of the parts, but the main title line, I feel like saying "huh?".  I guess it''s like, with God''s word as a lamp to our feet, we can find our way even in the dark... but I felt it was pretty ambiguous, and it''s the main line said over and over.  So for that reason, I don''t really think it would be the best choice.  Pretty cool otherwise tho...', 35, '2012-01-09 01:28:17'),
(323, 484, 'I really enjoyed listening to this... upbeat and celebration-y.  Good for just saying "Yay God!" and choosing to praise him and enjoy it.  I had to think about the line "all you have for me is good", because I immediately thought of how plenty of bad things come into our lives, and that God doesn''t promise us everything will be good.  But I guess it means all He has for us can be USED for our good... or that blessings from him are good... but I just snagged at that line.  Otherwise I like it.', 35, '2012-01-09 01:31:52'),
(325, 468, 'I like the focus of the message on God lighting a fire inside of us--giving us a passion to live for!  His love making us come alive.', 35, '2012-01-09 02:25:45'),
(326, 481, 'The verses have hardly any audible background parts (at least with my speakers).  The intro and some of the choruses/bridge have some cool sounding background though.', 35, '2012-01-09 02:34:34'),
(327, 447, 'I''ve tried to add the lyrics many times, but it just crashes on me every time :(  So, sorry there are no lyrics!  I tried.  You can look them up!!  ', 35, '2012-01-09 02:58:19'),
(328, 449, 'Seems like it would have a lot of cool interesting parts musically', 35, '2012-01-09 03:00:57'),
(329, 457, 'I really like this song!! Cool to hear from God''s perspective to come back to Him.  A little like "Made to Love" message-wise, although very different style.', 35, '2012-01-09 03:06:15'),
(330, 468, 'Most of the background sounds like quarter notes, ya? Might get a little boring for the bg''s rythm-wise, esp. since it''s only keyboard, so there aren''t other layered instrument parts to draw from arrangement wise... At least the majority of the song.  I really like the song though...', 35, '2012-01-09 03:13:15'),
(331, 486, 'Sorry I can''t post the lyrics.  It''s a pretty little song written by an a cappella group from Minnesota.  The lyrics can definitely be related to God, and I think the music is up-beat, and already in a cappella form!  The perc would be demanding though.  ', 25, '2012-01-09 03:32:13'),
(332, 477, 'Content-wise, I really like the last verse, which is about praising Jesus in Heaven, but less enthused about the first verses which are just about the other properties of Heaven (which may be true but not necessarily deserving of time in our set).', 3, '2012-01-09 04:55:25'),
(333, 453, 'What Shion said is definitely true. This song is useful because it expresses things we believe about God''s love, omnipresence, and forgiveness, but we shouldn''t count on it for big entertainment value.', 3, '2012-01-09 04:59:08'),
(334, 460, 'I like "I''m On A Boat", er, I mean, "Sailing On A Ship". It''s technically Spring Break appropriate but uses the boat analogy to get across a positively spiritual message: "With every storm I face | I find a greater grace | That pulls me deeper into Your heart." Unfortunately the solo line is slow and boring. I think a solo-less arrangement where the parts sing the lyrics could be more interesting.', 3, '2012-01-09 05:42:52'),
(335, 459, 'I''m usually not a big fan of gratuitous lyrical changes, but there''s probably a pretty easy one-word swap, "jealous" for something else, that would help the audience focus on the core meaning of the song rather than on the phrase "jealous lover".', 3, '2012-01-09 05:58:38'),
(336, 466, 'Every year, including this one, multiple suicides occur at MIT. Just about all of us who have been here for more than a couple years know at least one person who has taken their own life. It''s hard not to think about how things might have been different if only we had known that they were hurting and reached out to them. On the one hand, it''s unreasonable/impossible for us to reach out to absolutely everyone we know and give them spiritual support, much less prevent them from committing suicide if they are so inclined. On the other hand, I think we (meaning both us and the audience) tend to err on the side of not being caring enough toward the people around us. When YOU are despairing, even JUST ONE person sitting down and talking with you and making you feel loved can make a HUGE difference. When that person is a Christian who loves you because God first loved them, it''s that much more powerful. I have always found this song annoying, but if anyone is going to sing it, it should be the Christian a cappella group at an institution with a tragically high suicide percentage. I doubt we can sing this song without the audience thinking about suicide, so if we don''t want to talk about suicide at our concert, we shouldn''t sing this song.', 3, '2012-01-09 06:32:33'),
(337, 466, 'Fully agreed with Jacob. ', 29, '2012-01-09 17:31:16'),
(338, 484, 'Yeah, the same line that nagged Rachel also nagged at me too. I don''t expect any song to ever be able to capture the fullness of who God is and what He means for our lives, but this song made me feel like it was missing something. ', 29, '2012-01-09 17:34:33'),
(339, 39, 'We sang this song my freshman spring. It was a fun, upbeat song to sing, but it wasn''t terribly memorable (Cristi did a great job soloing though). The arrangement is not one of xprod''s strongest arrangements- so if someone has some time to look at it- I think it will be good. I recall it needing some depth and fullness. ', 29, '2012-01-09 17:37:54'),
(340, 227, 'It''s a great arrangement. It''s a bit hard for the audience to know what this song is all about without a blurb. But I love the metaphors in this song.', 29, '2012-01-09 17:39:16');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(341, 402, 'I like singing this song when I''m walking around campus and stuff cause it''s amusing, but I don''t know if I want to perform it. (Though, it does a great job of providing variety and interesting content to our set.) Remember- most of the audience will only hear a song once, so they don''t get a chance to listen to it over and over again and ponder about the deeper meanings. And my first reaction after I heard this song (I think in August) was "that was funny. but what was that..?"', 29, '2012-01-09 17:50:16'),
(342, 408, 'Yay Happy Song! Random thought- but I think it''ll be cool to have this song in our set/performance because it carries the message that even after this song is over, the concert is over, God continues to be with us and moves through us. And that can be extended to- even when church service ends, when the prayer ends, fellowship time, etc. In summary- though our faith in God is manifested in the things we do, it''s more than that- it''s actually our whole life. ', 29, '2012-01-09 18:02:03'),
(343, 486, 'THis is cool!  I like the sound of it.  It sounds more old-a-capella style, so a little sparse sounding to me in parts.  But there is a lot there in general, so I could imagine the arranger filling it out a little more for the parts.  The message is pretty clear, we were lost and far from God, and He rescued us and gave us Peace and Himself, which is more than we deserve.  I think it would be fun to do.  Only... 10... votes... gah... Hard decisions :)', 35, '2012-01-09 19:16:40'),
(344, 482, 'This song is so interesting... and has a great message.  It''s like the Chris Tomlin song "enough", except so much less predictable!  I would be interested in playing around concept-wise with this one, figuring out how to pull it off/arrange it for another time...', 35, '2012-01-09 19:23:27'),
(345, 407, 'This song has been growing on me since the first listen.  I think cutting one of the last choruses would be in order for the arrangement to keep it from being too repetitive.', 34, '2012-01-09 19:58:23'),
(346, 482, 'It''s def an interesting song. But like Rachel mentioned, we already have "Enough" from fall term, so it won''t add a new message to our repertoire. It will add, though, interesting music', 29, '2012-01-09 20:20:25'),
(347, 486, 'I like the simplicity and straightforwardness!', 29, '2012-01-09 20:24:14'),
(348, 459, 'Ooh the rhythmic variations are so interesting!', 29, '2012-01-09 20:27:55'),
(349, 477, 'Pretttyy :) I agree with Rachel though, this sounds amazing because it''s in a recording studio... but I also think it will be sad if we don''t give it a shot simply because of that reason. We have had songs before where there were incredibly high notes or difficult passages. (like Be My Escape original sop part, Via Dolorosa, etc) If someone in our group is transcribing this song, then they can tweak those parts accordingly so that it''s appropriate for xprod. However, if we can''t do that, then I don''t think we should do a song that we can''t rely on it being consistent, or gives a particular part a difficult time. ', 29, '2012-01-09 20:38:30'),
(350, 468, 'I like this song too! And I love the message that we come alive because of God! I think my favorite part is the end, where it says in everything we do, it stems from the love that God shows us. I also like the energy!', 29, '2012-01-09 20:43:55'),
(351, 446, 'Posted the UB recording...upon further reflection I think there are some better choral options suggested by others this semester, like Poor Wayfaring Stranger and How Deep the Father''s Love for Us, to name two that I''ll be voting for :-)', 34, '2012-01-09 21:21:44'),
(352, 446, 'This is really pretty... Thanks for posting!  Much easier to hear. I would agree though, those others have more message packed in with a cool sound as well.  ', 35, '2012-01-09 21:43:45'),
(353, 457, 'I think that the line "I''m only asking for your life" puts into accurate perspective the committment God desires, in light of everything he did for us and gave us first.  Is giving up our lives trivial?  Maybe not to us, but in light of God giving His life up first... and in light of what we get in return... I''d have to say yes.', 34, '2012-01-09 23:39:59'),
(354, 484, 'I actually don''t mind that line in a Romans 8:28 way.  I like this song for all of Kevin''s reasons...it manages to be simple and joyful without being completely devoid of substance.', 34, '2012-01-09 23:45:48'),
(355, 486, 'One line I''d want to change to remove the girlfriend/boyfriend ambiguity: "I''ve been blessed by God/so far beyond my wildest dreams".  Other than that, love it!', 34, '2012-01-09 23:54:12'),
(356, 482, 'This song sucker-punches Tomlin''s ''Enough'' with a fist of awesomeness.', 34, '2012-01-10 00:02:03'),
(357, 482, 'We should experiment with arranging this and see if we can get it singable (rappable?).  I would actually be more concerned with performing it than arranging it. (E.g. audience: "awww, look at the cute white/asian kids pretending to be funky")', 34, '2012-01-10 00:05:52'),
(358, 481, 'Anyone catch the irony of discussing whether this song would lend itself to interesting/entertaining background parts....?  :-)', 34, '2012-01-10 00:12:39'),
(359, 481, 'In all seriousness, sustained chords are all you''d want underneath a rap anyway, since you don''t want to distract from the audience being able to follow the words.', 34, '2012-01-10 00:13:58'),
(360, 480, 'Started out intreguing, but never arrived at the musical peak I''d hoped it would hit.  Maybe we could change that in our arrangement, and also reduce the repetitiveness.  ', 34, '2012-01-10 00:28:42'),
(361, 484, 'Ya, that interpretation of the line makes sense.  Although it wasn''t how I heard it at first.', 35, '2012-01-10 01:58:14'),
(362, 482, 'Hahaha... I love that--fist of awesomeness... I totally agree.  \r\nAnd I am also a bit concerned about my own performance of a rap song, even as a background part...haha...', 35, '2012-01-10 02:01:31'),
(363, 481, 'I suppose.  "God is Enough" seems to have much more going there tho, while also being a rap.  Maybe that''s because there is so much singing integrated in between the rapping...', 35, '2012-01-10 02:03:11'),
(364, 462, 'baha. I''m def gangsta. ;)', 36, '2012-01-10 04:29:57'),
(365, 442, 'I agree with Rachel.', 29, '2012-01-10 04:58:41'),
(366, 438, 'I like Natalie Grant too! I like the energy and conviction behind the lyrics, and that yes, we will stumble and fall, but we can''t be moved from our foundation, which is Christ :)', 29, '2012-01-10 05:01:25'),
(367, 464, 'I love the line "What if trials of this night, are Your mercies in disguise?". I agree it may confuse non-christians, but I think that confusion in a way, is a good one. Because then it poses another question- so why do Christians still follow Jesus, even if it may mean dealing with raindrops everyday?', 29, '2012-01-10 05:21:47'),
(368, 450, 'This is cool and super cute! I think it has a very interesting message that is unique (I can''t think of another song like this.. maybe I''m Not Cool or Dead and Gone). I''d be down for working with Rachel to arrange!', 29, '2012-01-10 05:30:50'),
(371, 5, 'Now that we''ve given this song a year''s break... Could we?!', 40, '2012-05-30 00:47:10'),
(372, 463, '"the line "I need you to love me" implies to me that it''s something in question, like the artist is asking God to love them"\r\n\r\nI''m suggesting this song again BECAUSE it implies that. Yes, as Relient K says, "I can''t ask you to give what you already gave," but this song hits at the HEART of the issue of taking God''s love for granted. We should want to serve Him so much, seek His true love so much that it feels like a need. (and in fact, his love IS a need! ''Man doesn''t live on bread alone'')\r\n\r\n', 39, '2012-05-30 17:23:30'),
(374, 493, 'Currently arranging it', 31, '2012-06-01 03:31:44'),
(375, 415, 'Though I find this song to be a little obnoxious at times, there are at least a couple good reasons to sing it this term specifically: 1) It''s an easy-to-sing arrangement that can build a young group''s confidence. 2) The solo can be sung by a true alto, and it''s versatile because it can sound good with either a new soloist singing simply or an experienced soloist adorning it with feeling and embellishment. 3) It''s on our soon-to-be-released CD. 4) There are a small handful of returning members who have sung it before in X-Linked.', 3, '2012-06-01 04:28:41'),
(376, 463, 'oh, Maria, I think what Brad meant by that comment is that he thought the song implied that God didn''t love someone in the first place, which is why Barlow girl was asking God for it.  That isn''t what the song is implying, but it is implying what you said, that God''s love is a need.  ', 17, '2012-06-01 09:03:06'),
(377, 494, 'Will put up a cut mp3 by the 6th so you can get a better idea of the two songs together. ', 39, '2012-06-01 13:27:57'),
(378, 494, 'I would like to (help) arrange this- I know we already have the TAN song arranged.', 39, '2012-06-01 13:31:58'),
(379, 495, 'I think this song would be great in the musical format, since some the lyrics are kind of vague or there can be lots of interpretations for ''these walls we''ve built are caving in'' (we could illustrate walls around our hearts in many different ways). ', 39, '2012-06-01 13:36:37'),
(380, 157, 'If selected, I would like to work on re-arranging it. I''m a bit obsessed with this song and didn''t think our arrangement was everything it could be, based on seeing it performed on Youtube a few times. ', 39, '2012-06-01 13:43:26'),
(381, 138, 'There''s a theme with the songs I suggest, yes. Which would be great for a musical- Epic cheo or really could be really powerful in a story-telling venue.', 39, '2012-06-01 13:47:04'),
(382, 12, 'The name of Jesus is powerful, and this song actually says it (it''s surprising how few of our songs do). It''s good to have a couple songs in the set that declare what we believe, and this is a happy song that declares, "Jesus is King!"', 3, '2012-06-01 16:51:59'),
(383, 157, 'Pretty much every Christian a cappella group has a rendition of this song because it''s so awesome, so there are plenty of ideas out there to pull from for the arrangement. Though I think our arrangement has some really good parts. BAIR-NAIR-NING-A-NA-NAIR-NA-NAIR-NAIR. Also our choreo was pretty neat when we last did this song.', 3, '2012-06-01 17:10:05'),
(384, 167, 'Because of its cool beginning and cool ending, this song can be either a great opener or great finale.', 3, '2012-06-01 17:11:51'),
(385, 495, 'I absolutely LOVE this song musically. This would be fun to sing. I think "Reach Out" is a great basic message for MIT students (kinda like "Give Me Your Eyes", except in a different style). My one concern is that since the first verse and chorus focus on the soloist''s own spiritual needs instead of others'', the song isn''t well-focused.', 3, '2012-06-01 18:04:14'),
(386, 482, 'I will probably attempt an arragement of this regardless if it''s picked or not...it is an interesting challenge :-)', 34, '2012-06-01 18:33:21'),
(387, 496, 'I would love to arrange this song, I think it could be very powerful performed.  I would want to change the first bridge lyric to "He is our portion and He is our prize"...that''s always bothered me about this song but otherwise I love it.', 34, '2012-06-01 18:41:12'),
(388, 455, 'Re-suggest, would still love to arrange this...', 34, '2012-06-01 18:44:46'),
(389, 497, 'The arrangement I have for this is easy to learn but awesome to sing; it''s a wonderful surrender statement of worship.  It''s a mashup of the traditional hymn and this Tomlin version, builds to a powerful climax in the middle...it could be an opportunity for audience interaction/joint worship to sing with us.', 34, '2012-06-01 18:49:55'),
(390, 497, 'I should also note that there''s a lot of repitition in the original recording that is cut out in the arrangement.', 34, '2012-06-01 18:50:46'),
(391, 450, 'A re-suggest because I still think tweaking the Lyrics to be MIT-applicable is an awesome idea, and would make the song super applicable to student life', 34, '2012-06-01 19:01:30'),
(392, 394, 'How much utility we get out of what is traditionally a Christmas song is up for debate.  I like this rendition but I think there''s better stuff off of this Go Fish album (Snow) that we could cover.  Even with the cool/unique beat, it gets a little repetitive.', 34, '2012-06-01 20:28:13'),
(393, 233, 'The xprod version is better than the original, having listened to that I could support doing this song.  I think I just don''t have whatever qualities it takes to appreciate ska as a musical genre...', 34, '2012-06-01 20:31:38'),
(394, 5, 'We should do a mashup of this song and dare you to move since EVERY SWITCHFOOT SONG SOUNDS EXACTLY THE SAME', 34, '2012-06-01 20:37:16'),
(395, 463, 'Precisely', 34, '2012-06-01 20:38:40'),
(396, 450, 'I wish the verses were longer. The humorous part is over almost before it begins.', 3, '2012-06-02 00:34:06'),
(397, 497, 'Could you upload the arrangement or a recording?', 3, '2012-06-02 00:40:40'),
(398, 498, 'This song has such a powerful message... And it can be a really pretty, strong girl ballad.  I also had ideas of adding in snippets of the hymn "come just as you are" at strategic points, to highlight the fact that that''s what this song is saying!\r\nAnd for those who are distracted by the super 90''s feel.... it wouldn''t have to be that way in the arrangement!!  :)  \r\n', 35, '2012-06-03 01:39:43'),
(399, 445, 'NEW comment:  For those of you who were in our very last monday rehearsal, we learned this arrangement!  :)', 35, '2012-06-03 01:42:21'),
(400, 499, 'This song is super fun and upbeat!  And the message is that we won''t give up, we''ll keep moving forward and growing in our relationship with the Lord... In the craziness of life we choose to drop everything and follow him.  And we give him our burdens and just go where he leads, not knowing where.\r\n\r\nI can see this song having lots of potential for fun choreo!  :D', 35, '2012-06-03 01:51:25'),
(401, 450, 'Haha, if we are already tweaking verses, maybe we can extend them ;)', 35, '2012-06-03 02:35:25'),
(402, 500, 'This song hits hard on the sheer awesomeness of God. I love how bold the lyrics are in saying that it''s OUR GOD that''s GREATER, STRONGER, and HIGHER than anything you can imagine. Because if our God is with us, then what could EVER stand against us?\r\n\r\nAs far as arrangement goes, I''d love to attempt to arrange this song with the dubstep remix in mind (youtube clip above) and add back in the bridge that the youtube clip remix left out. Also, because this song is meant to be a worship song, it''s repetitive, so I was thinking of adding in another chunk of lyrics, maybe doing a bit of a mashup with another song? Haven''t thought of the right one yet though.', 24, '2012-06-03 23:51:04'),
(403, 501, 'Keeping up with the xprod rap trend/wanting to add variety... Okay, but seriously, this song speaks clearly of the problem with being polluted by the world that the bible warns us of. (like in James 1:19-27)Just throwing the song out there because I found it while going through KJ-52''s songs and I found that the lyrics were really direct in a loving way and the song has the possibility to be powerful to people in a personal way.', 24, '2012-06-04 01:25:45'),
(404, 329, 'I think these three lines summarize why I love this song so much: "There is no better loss than to lose myself in you, There is no better find than to find myself with you, There is no reason I should breathe unless you''re in the air." This song expresses not just how much we need God, but how much we love that we need God and want to surrender everything to Him, which, as the song says, is beautiful.', 24, '2012-06-04 01:48:03'),
(405, 233, 'What do you have against horns??!?  random comments: It''s really REALLY hard to understand. Lyrically and constructionally, though maybe it''s just my bad ears. But that''s something that could be fixed by a really good blurb I''m sure. I love the idea of going all out showing how fun it is to praise God, but I agree with Daniel and think it borders on being TOO out-there. It feels like the solo is too low to pay attention to with such a strong background.', 39, '2012-06-04 15:12:05'),
(406, 504, 'God had such mercy for ME... he suffered and died when it should have been me.  The gospel straight up!  Very powerful lyrics.\r\nWe could even do a little more with the "nothing but the blood of Jesus" snippet of the melody in there.\r\n', 35, '2012-06-04 16:40:09'),
(407, 505, 'This is such a great, upbeat, joyful song that''s straight up gospel and rocking out celebration!  And it''s really shouting out what we''re doing as a group... "sing it out, to let all the world know that Jesus saves!" .  And I love that there is just so much packed into the lyrics, but it''s all easy to hear...', 35, '2012-06-04 16:43:43'),
(408, 176, 'Does someone have a video of Xprod doing this?  I listened to the original song and didn''t like it nearly as much as the Xprod arrangement. And there is nothing posted here!!', 35, '2012-06-04 17:43:25'),
(409, 176, 'Nearly as GOOD as Xprod arrangement, sorry.', 35, '2012-06-04 17:43:42'),
(410, 497, 'Unfortunately I don''t have access to a recording of it being performed...I could post a midi if you want', 34, '2012-06-04 20:00:20'),
(411, 500, 'When I clicked on this song suggestion I was gearing up to write a "please not another Chris Tomlin worship song" plea (since they tend to translate so terribly to a cappella)...then I saw the word "Dubstep" in Kristina''s comment and I was like "SOMETHING HAS GONE HORRIBLY WRONG", since no one in their right minds would seriously suggest dubstep in a cappella as anything other than a joke.  BUT, having listened to the youtube above, I think it''s a cool idea.  It would have to be very well executed to keep from coming across as a joke (a-la techno emmanuel).  I suggest "Here is our King" by David Crowder as a potential mash-up; it has a similar theme and feel.  Any other suggestions?', 34, '2012-06-04 20:13:24'),
(412, 504, 'I like it! The music isn''t terribly exciting, but we could make it sound pretty at least. This song expresses the gospel clearly, and it''s hard to find songs that do that other than hymns and choral pieces.', 3, '2012-06-04 22:12:16'),
(413, 176, 'Uploaded a recording from the first time we performed the song.', 3, '2012-06-04 23:12:31'),
(414, 510, 'Solid choral song full of the gospel. I recommend listening to the Youtube of GLAD (2nd video- it sounds so glorious around 2:00!!) and the Cross Products one (3rd video) because that''s our actual arrangement. The non-acappella one by Todd Agnew (1st one) is not as great. \r\n\r\nI recommend this song because it''s always good to have at least one choral song in a set, and we keep using And Can It Be and How Deep, which are both great songs, but it''s been done over and over again in the past 3 years. We haven''t done this song since 2008. I also like this song because it has a really great ending, similar to Before the Throne. \r\n\r\n', 29, '2012-06-05 02:31:41'),
(415, 508, 'Great song! The bridge reminds me of Glory to God''s bridge "Take my life and let it be, all for you and for your glory, take my life and let it be yours."  I think what''s good about this song in particular is that not only does it express the singer''s desire to give up their life to God, but also the reasons for why they want to. (reached out in love, trading righteousness for shame, etc) Also, because this page was blank I decided to add the lyrics and youtube videos, which includes one from my collection. Cue the wails of "oh kristina and her christian dubstep..."', 24, '2012-06-05 06:14:08'),
(416, 500, 'WAIT FOR IT. When I commented on Like an Avalanche, it hit me. Glory to God''s bridge: Take my life and let it be, all for you and for your glory. Take my life and let it be yours. GOLD. (i was looking for mashup possibilities more along the lines of Okay, God''s awesome, so now what''s our response?) Also, Brad, "SOMETHING HAS GONE HORRIBLY WRONG" ...lolz. But yeah I like the idea of Here is Our King, too.', 24, '2012-06-05 06:21:37'),
(417, 176, 'I like the Xprod version', 34, '2012-06-05 16:44:03'),
(418, 141, 'This could be a fun song, with funny choreo.  I like the feel and think it would be fun to sing, and the message is just telling people that this life isn''t forever!  We need to think about what we''re doing with it, and what comes next... but it''s not depressing.', 35, '2012-06-06 03:07:11'),
(419, 484, 'I would like to give this song another chance, with the new and improved Brad-tweaked arrangement!  We got a lot of comments where people really loved this song, and it was Joe''s favorite.  But we got so little time to appreciate it, since we were still learning it during dress rehearsal.  And we didn''t get a chance to do choreo.  overall this is just a great, exciting song where we get to rock out and worship God and get the audience into it too!  :D   It deserves another chance this term!', 35, '2012-06-06 03:09:17'),
(420, 513, 'I love this song-- the lyrics are so powerful!  And for someone who is not a big fan of rap, I feel like this song actually allows me to appreciate it... The words are echoing Paul''s words about everything to gain in this life being counted as loss, because Christ is everything.  Boasting only in Christ.  And I feel like the melody in the chorus is great, and it sounds like it would be fun to sing...\r\nOne of the schools (I forget which) sang this at BIDB...', 35, '2012-06-06 03:15:26'),
(421, 514, 'This is one of those epic sounding songs, kind of like the one at BIDB "Hold tight, it''ll be alright..." for me.  Talking about when we don''t know where to go, at the end of our rope in life, we can listen to God calling us and let him lead us home.  And I really like the music, and how the gospel choir comes in the background at some point.  It''s long, so would have to be trimmed of course.  ', 35, '2012-06-06 03:20:50'),
(422, 514, 'End of the lyrics is cool... "So go ahead and give it over to/ the one who chose to give his life for you/ Leave it to me/ I''ll lead you home"', 35, '2012-06-06 03:22:58'),
(423, 484, 'For the Xprod youtube video, the song itself begins at 2:30!!  Sorry about that, I will split the intro at some point.', 35, '2012-06-06 13:11:44'),
(424, 484, 'I hadn''t thought about it, but it''s an interesting idea. It would be a fast song to learn because we all know it and good for spring break....', 24, '2012-06-06 23:47:31'),
(425, 219, 'This is an amazing song. I could go on for quite a while about it''s simple yet moving lyrics and beautiful melody, but you can hear those for yourself. But in addition to being a great song, it has a host of other, not-so-obvious benefits including:\r\n1) It''s an xprod original (so we don''t have to worry about copyrights)\r\n2) It''s pretty spring break friendly \r\n3) It speaks to all audiences, both Christian and non-Christian, because it talks about our need to trust God more and have him play a bigger role in our lives, which is applicable to everyone.', 19, '2012-06-07 00:15:49'),
(426, 517, 'I think this song suits its name very well. I really get the sense of God as the artist creating us from nothing, piece-by-piece. The slow buildup of the background throughout the song is a marvelous touch, as well as the fact that the artist moves from singing mostly the verses about his own weakness in the intro to the chorus about God''s artistry also helps this feeling.\r\n\r\nIt''s a very simple message, yet has some very deep meanings attached. Apparently, the artist wrote this album during the toughest period of his life, when everything fell apart and he realized that God was the source of everything that he was (hence the line "if I never sing again, my soul will be my song")', 19, '2012-06-07 00:37:33'),
(427, 484, 'Intro is gone!! song starts right away now.', 35, '2012-06-07 00:49:19'),
(429, 518, 'So this song''s really interesting... it takes lyrics from some top 40 songs by artists such as Lady Gaga, Katy Perry, and Ke$ha, and refutes what they say. Also, I like the part that says "No teenage dream could ever be worth your soul" haha...', 24, '2012-06-07 02:49:09'),
(430, 14, 'A modern hymn, one of my favorites. :) Plus we have a sweet arrangement', 24, '2012-06-07 03:25:05'),
(431, 495, 'In general, I really like the original. I do have some doubts about how it will sound a cappella. \r\n\r\nInsofar as this semester is concerned, I think the message of the song is very in-line with the Pitches'' goal, but it sounds heavily dependent on strong perc/base, which is problematic this semester since basically all of our members with low range are gone. Maybe hold off for a semester?', 19, '2012-06-07 14:53:03'),
(432, 455, 'It''s a great song with a good message, but very set/message-specific. Basically, pitches'' call', 19, '2012-06-07 15:11:50'),
(433, 497, 'I would strongly suggest learning this song at some point while we have a good arrangement so as to preserve it in XProd memory (such as it is). There are too few good hymn arrangements which our audiences are not already overly familiar with, so I feel like we should snap them up when we get the chance.', 19, '2012-06-07 15:14:59'),
(434, 501, 'Wow, I can think of quite a few people who this song would hit pretty hard in a good way. And like he said, one of them is me.', 19, '2012-06-07 16:30:54'),
(435, 394, 'I really love this song, but could only see it if it were faster/less repetitive. ', 39, '2012-06-07 23:01:14'),
(436, 394, 'Rachel just said "I think this song has a lot more to offer musically than musically." I agree but love it as a joy song- almost like the purpose people said A Flowery Song served.', 39, '2012-06-07 23:02:42'),
(437, 502, 'I have no idea what this song means during the verses... The bridge is pretty clear though!  The style is fun.  I think it would be fun, but maybe repetitive for the backgrounds.  For me personally it''s a little too poetic for me to understand', 35, '2012-06-07 23:09:30'),
(438, 502, 'Would need an amazing blurb, but I think with that it''s totally doable. Reminds me of Breaking Through in that if you really let yourself get into it, the imagery becomes clearer and you can really appreciate what the song''s trying to say, even if you don''t quite understand what he''s saying.', 39, '2012-06-07 23:10:08'),
(439, 407, 'Great message, but the soloist needs to sound happier than this guy! ', 39, '2012-06-07 23:14:02'),
(440, 407, 'I really like the message for this one!  And i love the style too, and singing it is fun.  But I can def see how it would be repetitive... maybe it could be mashed up with something else?  Or even not have a soloist, but fold the lyrics and duet into the parts...', 35, '2012-06-07 23:14:06'),
(441, 407, 'It''s a great message, but it doesn''t say a whole lot of things.', 39, '2012-06-07 23:15:15'),
(442, 514, 'I think this would be best as really gospel-choir-ey and more in your face or just louder. \r\n\r\nI also like the challenge the first two lines set up \r\n"Wandering the road of desperate life\r\nAimlessly beneath the barren sky"\r\n\r\nWhich to many, even proclaimed Christians, doesn''t register at all- It''s a smidge affronting to be all ''you''re aimless''', 39, '2012-06-07 23:21:13'),
(443, 484, 'Love the idea of being able to do more with it this term since some of us know it. Don''t know how much time we would actually save since half our members won''t know it. ', 39, '2012-06-07 23:26:42'),
(444, 138, 'I really like this song!  It''s so powerful!  It really challenges me to be deliberate about seeking God... and it''s cool musically too.  I''m for doing it.', 35, '2012-06-07 23:26:59'),
(445, 5, 'I''m not in love with this arrangement. I love a lot of aspects of it, but two main comments I''ve been thinking about a lot lately, especially since I only recently listened to the original:\r\n\r\nFor ME, the arrangement is missing something. And I guess that something is the harpsichord. The high notes that the original does give it a feel of hope for me, but our arrangement just sounds eerie and creepy. None of those things are bad, it just always leaves me more pessimistic about the lyrics than committed to them. \r\n\r\nAlso, because the arrangemtne is so cool/has fun elements, I''m caught either listening to the background or lyrics, not both together, and am not able to digest the song as I should be. ', 39, '2012-06-07 23:32:21'),
(446, 141, 'Basically he''s saying that we need to realize life is temporary!  We need to make good use of our lives and fill it with things that matter!  Implied: use it to serve God!  Not for ourselves, and STUFF.', 35, '2012-06-07 23:37:04'),
(447, 141, '''wake up, because soon today will be gone'' is how Rachel put it, which makes a lot more sense than what I was thinking. My first impression is that the chorus and title are saying to forget about the past and that history isn''t important to you right now, which I disagree with. I don''t actually think it''s saying that, but that might be an important distinction to make in the blurb or whatnot.\r\n\r\nI agree that it would be really really fun, but I have a hard time connecting with the more casual feel and references. ', 39, '2012-06-07 23:37:13'),
(448, 510, 'Some of the most beautiful lyrics ever. Plus it has a really Christmas-y feel, which will be really great to have in a song for a fall concert. \r\n\r\nSo so beautiful. Great arrangement.', 39, '2012-06-07 23:42:28'),
(449, 510, 'I love how it goes through the different stages of Jesus'' life and how each enriches us.  His birth gives hope, his life teaches and heals, his death saves, his resurrection does everything ever.  Beautiful!', 35, '2012-06-07 23:43:41'),
(450, 110, 'You don''t see singing like that often at all- comPLETELY engrossed in God/worship. It''s really powerful and kind of a testimony in itself, because you''re showing such an intimate moment with God.', 39, '2012-06-07 23:48:29'),
(451, 110, 'For me personally I don''t really resonate with the way she describes things... But ya, I like Maria''s point.  And I like that, like Never alone, it''s crazy guitar-y.', 35, '2012-06-07 23:50:12'),
(452, 110, 'It''s a different message- one of being in Him so much that you can feel Him, that you''re actually taking in the way he loves us. And the bridge is a statement of faith made even more powerful by the fact that the singer is already immersed in God''s love.', 39, '2012-06-07 23:54:51'),
(453, 500, 'I love the intro/mashup aspect and taking this traditional song and vamping it. Let''s do GOOD dubstep though.', 39, '2012-06-07 23:58:42'),
(454, 500, 'I really like the choruses and how they are the same song with the cool message and melody, but with a cool beat and faster pace.  But I''m not so sure about the actual dubstep parts with no words... they sound kind of unimpressive, maybe it''s these speakers/low quality file.  \r\nI love the chorus of this song in general.\r\n', 35, '2012-06-07 23:59:20'),
(455, 500, '"keep in mind, live processing is a possibility" -Ken', 39, '2012-06-08 00:00:22'),
(456, 227, 'Agreed, needs a blurb to describe the meaning.  Also I find the part about being awake and counting sheep weird and confusing.  I like how the solo sounds...', 35, '2012-06-08 00:04:20'),
(457, 513, 'Message = awesome', 35, '2012-06-08 00:14:49'),
(458, 513, 'Maria: fun to sing musically', 35, '2012-06-08 00:15:42'),
(459, 521, 'Maria: the lyrics are really powerful! Big concepts, executes them well.  The part about the bullets never come. Don''t get the last line of the bridge right away... \r\nAlvin: Some parts of the lyrics are hard to interpret... Likes it musically, not sure how it might translate to a Capella.\r\n', 35, '2012-06-08 00:24:44'),
(460, 111, 'I really like a lot of pieces of the lyrics... what God is saying as he''s trying to bring the person back in.  It might be very relevant to college students who were raised in Christian homes and have turned to worldly things.  And it''s very different message-wise, how it''s focused, like the first comment says.  \r\nI like how it says you can''t fix the world on your own!  You have a good heart, but it''s turned the wrong way.  This song would be good in conjunction with the other songs that tell people they are aimless without God.', 35, '2012-06-08 00:32:16'),
(461, 499, '--Might be a good closer... send-off song, lyrically, and due to the energy!!\r\nCould also be a climax/changing point song.\r\n--Doesn''t have very much it''s saying, but what it says is a good message.', 35, '2012-06-08 00:37:03'),
(462, 519, 'Alvin: would be interesting for acapella, with all the moving parts\r\n', 35, '2012-06-08 00:44:18'),
(463, 519, 'The verses and chorus seem really disconnected- they''re saying totally different things. The verses are outstanding in message. The ''he''s watching me'' sounds really creepy. It''s supposed to be comforting that he''s watching? It''s a lot more comforting knowing he loves us etc, at least for me. ', 39, '2012-06-08 00:44:57'),
(464, 519, 'Very happy and bright song, could be a really different vibe a cappella.', 39, '2012-06-08 00:45:29'),
(465, 519, 'different/bright being a good thing', 39, '2012-06-08 00:45:39'),
(466, 498, 'Totally agree. The powerful message and powerful solo stand so well on its own that the arranged background can be anything that compliments it. ', 39, '2012-06-08 00:49:11'),
(467, 498, 'The arrangement would have to be really good and spice up the style to make it interesting for the backgrounds.  But the solo and message are really strong!', 35, '2012-06-08 00:50:14'),
(468, 498, 'THIS WOULD BE SO PERFECT FOR A MUSICAL. I vote this song as amazing for whichever semester we do a musical.', 39, '2012-06-08 00:50:39'),
(469, 518, 'I know!  It''s a pretty cool song, and I love those songs they are referring to haha... though they are horrible message wise so it''s awesome that this song refutes them.  ', 35, '2012-06-08 00:56:35'),
(470, 518, 'This song does a REALLY good job with sort of ''exposing the lies'' of the pop songs. Favorite line: We don''t want what you''re calling love.\r\n\r\nAt the same time, it''s very youthful and ''AGAINST THE MAN,'' which would not be a good fit for a strong emotional musical. Sometimes it ALMOST stretches to get the pop references, but it does do a good job all around. \r\n\r\nI didn''t get the references in the bridge, so it might be hit or miss in the reference regard, though I think there''s enough good stuff in the beginning to make it worth it.\r\n\r\nOverall LOVE IT LOVE IT!', 39, '2012-06-08 01:00:29'),
(471, 503, 'This feels like Today is the Day, just in the energy and celebration feel, going crazy.\r\nThe message is really strong, that Jesus frees us from sin.  Lots of good lyrics in there.  Lots of fun music going on.  Interesting mash between the two styles--the spiritual and the rap...\r\n', 35, '2012-06-08 01:05:09'),
(472, 503, 'Even though DC Talk can get very teenager-ey, the rapish parts of this one are really clear and quality. \r\nI think the arrangement could do without so many changing things at the beginning but has strength in all the different sections. Partly because it builds well throughout. Great musical song or on par with Today Is The Day since it''s so gospel-ey-happy.\r\nIt has so much substance. ', 39, '2012-06-08 01:05:38'),
(473, 503, 'Alvin: I like it!', 35, '2012-06-08 01:05:48'),
(474, 507, 'OMG we can never compete with the super cute kid soloist!!', 35, '2012-06-08 01:07:42'),
(475, 507, 'Really great words, could be really powerful as sung by not-children too. \r\nToo short/repetitive though. Can we write additional lyrics?', 39, '2012-06-08 01:10:34'),
(476, 507, 'It does sound like a kid song, but to me a translatable Child-of-God song no matter what age.', 39, '2012-06-08 01:12:29'),
(477, 507, 'I like the message, God knows and chooses us even before we''re born... he''s our shepherd, stay close to him... Maybe we can mash it with something if it needs to be longer :) It definitely sounds like a kid song as is (of course) so our arrangement would need to sound... not so kid song. -Rachel.  Start with this song and then transition into something else... -Alvin\r\n', 35, '2012-06-08 01:12:33'),
(478, 507, 'The "kid song" comment referring only to the music, not the lyrics.', 35, '2012-06-08 01:13:09'),
(479, 517, 'Alvin: If this were a really strong girl solo, it could be really awesome.  \r\nRachel: This one reminds me of Empty Me-- super pretty, soaring solo, about giving up everything to God and letting him work!  I really like it.  Oo, pretty piano stuff in the end-ish.\r\n', 35, '2012-06-08 01:17:48'),
(480, 517, 'I like how it can relate to us as singers... "if i never sing again, my soul will my song" etc.', 35, '2012-06-08 01:19:06'),
(481, 517, 'Totally agree with Kevin. \r\nI don''t like that it repeats so much at the end. I feel like the end could be really chorally like Empty Me, and building the end like that that way could make it really powerful. ', 39, '2012-06-08 01:19:57'),
(482, 517, 'Alvin: The blurb can be a really powerful opportunity', 35, '2012-06-08 01:20:02'),
(483, 515, 'Seems to have a lot of potential for easy and awesome arrangement because it''s simple and no one in our listening party can resist harmonizing.', 39, '2012-06-08 01:23:05'),
(484, 515, 'This song is sooo pretty... and could sound really pretty acapella too.  Such  great lyrics, just about being still and listening to God, which we many times don''t take time to do... \r\n3-4 part harmony?!?!?', 35, '2012-06-08 01:24:32'),
(485, 515, 'I think this would be a better musical song than stand-alone song.', 39, '2012-06-08 01:24:35'),
(486, 511, 'Cool song! To some degree I feel like the background parts sound a lot like.... Background... \r\nLet''s all bow down to Jesus!!  A call for everyone to make Jesus their king.  And not later, or somewhere else... HERE AND NOW!!', 35, '2012-06-08 01:30:46'),
(487, 511, 'The repeating lyrics could be really powerful in musical format, but otherwise it''s kind of sad everything repeats. \r\nFeel like it could be mashed up with Chris Tomlin- God of This City. \r\nI like that it progresses from a recognition of needing to start now to a commitment and call for everyone to do so, as a whole, as a city, unified as the body of Christ.', 39, '2012-06-08 01:31:08'),
(488, 505, 'Would make a great duet!\r\nI don''t know if it''s too close to Reason (the chorus anyway).\r\nWonderful message!', 39, '2012-06-08 01:36:31'),
(489, 505, 'Alvin: It''s repetitive...\r\n', 35, '2012-06-08 01:37:13'),
(490, 495, 'In contrast with what Jabob said, I think the song''s strength comes from the journey from realizing we are selfish first, then realizing others depend on us too. Since the change starts with us. Because it''s a big general, the audience can relate to the first verse/chorus, then see beyond themselves. That''s one idea anyway. ', 39, '2012-06-08 01:40:32'),
(491, 443, 'The buildup to the chorus always makes me feel a little disappointed that the first half of the chorus just says that we are fragile and temporary like flowers... I dunno, I expect the chorus to say something more profound after the buildup of awesomeness of the verses.', 35, '2012-06-08 01:42:45'),
(492, 443, 'I like the idea of a 6-part Brad arrangement... that sounds fun...', 35, '2012-06-08 01:43:59'),
(493, 495, 'I just now realized this doesn''t have to be a Christian song at all... can be about getting up and helping others in the world.  I saw it as reaching out to God, and then to others to share the gospel... which is the message we would want to send!  But at the same time a lot of the song would be directed towards Christians (calling non-Christians "them" and saying "we" and "us") so it wouldn''t be as universal in message.  So the blurb would need to be clear about how the song is focused for us', 35, '2012-06-08 01:54:52'),
(494, 494, 'Alvin: I really like where you''re going with it.  Sounds like it could be really cool!\r\nRachel: I like the back and forth, and how the speaker changes and there is  conversation.  Especially since they ARE two different songs, they really are two different speakers, one answering the other, which is cool.', 35, '2012-06-08 02:05:37'),
(495, 494, 'So Run To You is man, By Your Side is God. I had one cohesive background in mind, but I don''t actually know what might be good as a background. Also, I have blocking in mind for how the solo and duet could interact already =). ', 39, '2012-06-08 02:07:16'),
(496, 494, 'https://www.dropbox.com/sh/w8hx8b99gxo9182/BoehHwGV-O', 39, '2012-06-08 03:51:48'),
(497, 494, 'Link to MP3 of mashup above. Sorry, no other way of getting media up was working for me. So obviously the two songs just together have some bugs. Hopefully it is enough to let you know what I was going for. There''s a silent space after the bridge cause the idea is to be abrupt and there was no good and easy way to do that with the audio. Also the tempo isn''t quite as desired, but that would be all to work out.', 39, '2012-06-08 03:55:16'),
(498, 111, 'The main reason why I picked this song again for suggestions is because I feel that a lot of people come to college with some kind of religious background, and coming to MIT leaves people lost sooner or later. We all find ourselves on our knees at some point in our lives, and it''s a matter of where we turn to that ultimately determines how we get through it-- for this song, it invites people to turn to God. I agree with the comments above, however; needs a blurb. Spring break safe!', 38, '2012-06-08 06:34:39'),
(499, 494, 'I''m looking over the lyrics again to this on my computer now, but I really REALLY like the juxtaposition of the two songs in the lyrics. It really describes well the longing of an imperfect person for God, and God''s grace and willingness to call us back to Him. I found it resonates a lot with me, and could have the potential to be one of our most powerful songs if we have a solid arrangement and we pull it off right.', 40, '2012-06-08 07:11:47'),
(500, 242, 'We did this song in Xlinked, and I really prefer the original song to the Xprod version, just personally.  Even listening to Xprod concert performance of it, I feel the same.  It kind of loses the sound I like about the original song, in the arrangement.  And it''s difficult to "sound like a guitar", which is what it seems to require...', 35, '2012-06-09 17:12:12'),
(501, 242, 'I really like the original song, and the message of it :)', 35, '2012-06-09 17:12:25'),
(502, 502, 'I wonder if it would be difficult to achieve the cool electronic-y light airy sound that makes Owl City so cool... I feel skeptical at the moment, but it all depends on the arrangement I guess!', 35, '2012-06-09 17:21:41'),
(503, 242, 'I like the arrangement, except for maybe the syllables and the repetitiveness. \r\nGreat message, and I think the message is great but hard to understand sometimes. \r\n', 39, '2012-06-10 22:21:44'),
(504, 372, 'Love the song, never thought of it as a God song, but it''s great!\r\nIt seems to do what All Around Me by Flyleaf does which is just illustrate an intimate moment between man and God. I think it would sound great a cappella too. ', 39, '2012-06-10 22:26:07'),
(505, 501, 'Amen. So clear, and so applicable to most, if not everyone. \r\n', 39, '2012-06-10 22:33:12'),
(506, 516, 'I love the verses but don''t find much in the choruses in terms of message. Maybe there is, but it''s oversimplified for resonance with me. ', 39, '2012-06-10 22:37:34'),
(507, 513, 'A few lines in this song concern me theologically, though I admit I don''t have much knowledge of the Bible yet. \r\nwithout the cross there''s only condemnation.\r\nIf Jesus wasn''t executed there''s no celebration.\r\nCan someone explain those lines? There are other ones that make me uncomfortable, but that''s probably a ''don''t want to admit it''s right'' feeling.\r\nEverything in the song is really powerfully said, which is a good thing. Lecrae lyrics are really good at challenging people. I really love this song musically too.', 39, '2012-06-10 22:45:12'),
(508, 493, 'Love the feel. Very excited thinking about choreo...\r\nAs for the message, I think it''s a good one, though a little simple, almost a little shallow, but that might just be me that gets caught up rocking out more than meaning what I''m singing. Love the first verse, but after that, gets to vague for me. Has great potential with blurb, choreo, and soloist performance. ', 39, '2012-06-10 22:52:22'),
(509, 398, 'Yep, have no idea if it''s God''s gravity pulling us back to sensibility or the world''s gravity trying to pull us ''down.''\r\nI think it would be great to add ''your'' in front of gravity. \r\nOr if it''s the other way, change gravity to ''the world.''\r\nOnly first impression, but as an MIT student, not very quickly and clearly understanding an analogy to gravity is a REALLY REALLY BIG NO NO!', 39, '2012-06-10 23:02:51'),
(510, 12, 'Great arrangement. Simple and well-stated message. I think we need more energy to or conviction in the performance of it, but love its statement, which I feel like would be a good focal point for both returning and new members. ', 39, '2012-06-10 23:09:34'),
(511, 167, 'It does a really great job of encouraging us to take the leap of faith, not just outline how hard it is like a lot of songs do. The music sounds almost like it would be a prosperity gospel song, but the words are not so! As in, the feel of it is really fun and lively, but the lyrics complement is really well saying that you ARE going to run through the darkness, the world IS going to crumble beneath your feet unless you believe. It also does a good job of being illustrating the type of situation when you feel vulnerable and makes me consider the world falling around, and then being encouraged to follow God even in those moments. ', 39, '2012-06-10 23:13:12'),
(512, 176, 'LOVE the diversity within the song itself. Keeps it interesting and building on the central message that WE have the problem, not God.', 39, '2012-06-10 23:19:53'),
(513, 506, 'This song is really good at challenging the idea of ONLY leading by example and deciding because it''s easier and seems to work, that it''s okay to ignore our call to preach to all the nations. I think it''s got a great point and message (AND ALL THE BASS, SO IN LOVE MUSICALLY)', 39, '2012-06-10 23:24:41'),
(514, 450, 'Totally agree that we should do this song and tweak it. \r\nI like the fact that it''s light, but also the last line of the chorus for me hits the hardest. Little things seem so frustrating, this we all know, but it''s also really easy to dismiss them when they''re over as ''let''s just forget about what happened and let''s avoid it in the future.'' this especially can hit home to people- and I would like to see keeping it light but also some seriousness to it. Maybe just because it resonated with me in the sense that even bigger things are what he uses- like my bike being stolen, like failing classes...', 39, '2012-06-10 23:36:07'),
(515, 507, 'I''m up for arranging a mashup if need be!', 37, '2012-06-10 23:41:45'),
(516, 329, 'To me, there are other songs that say those better, but I do like it. A bit repetitive, but it does have a good message.', 39, '2012-06-10 23:44:57'),
(517, 91, 'Can someone explain the lines ''nothing can separate even if I ran away'' and ''there may be pain in the night but joy comes in the morning?\r\nI think the second is a bible verse, but I don''t get how to think about them in a way that isn''t ''it''s okay to run away sometimes'' or ''ha, certainly not literally true.''', 39, '2012-06-10 23:48:49'),
(518, 455, 'I think it''s a great message and stands on its own well. I think Brad''d make a great arrangement that would be more interesting than the background of the song. I love how the last line for the message of letting go but other parts of the song for the message of deciding it''s time to do that, then moving on from there.', 39, '2012-06-10 23:53:59'),
(519, 482, 'LOVE this song. It''s SO dynamic and fun and true. I think a lot of different people can relate, or that some key audience member can be challenged by saying education isn''t everything (all of us), pill-poppin (senior haus), etc.\r\nSO eager to see an arrangement. So much possibility...', 39, '2012-06-11 00:01:35'),
(520, 509, 'Though I was thinking of mashing a more upbeat, possibly rap song with You Are the Shepherd, this works really well! In terms of mashing the choruses together (by this I mean all of BTMV and the chorus of YATS). I have the mixed part mostly figured out. That would be a good option for a slower song.', 37, '2012-06-11 00:05:25'),
(521, 513, 'Let''s see.  "Without the cross there''s only condemnation" refers to the fact that we would all be condemned for our sin if Jesus had not died on the cross in our place.  And so "If Jesus wasn''t executed there''s no celebration" means that without Jesus dying, we couldn''t celebrate because our sins would still be separating us from God--we would not be freed from sin, reconciled to God, rescued from death...any of the things we celebrate because of his grace!!  :)  I hope that is helpful for understanding!', 35, '2012-06-11 00:09:25'),
(522, 509, 'Can someone add some information for this song? Anything?? Caitlin, what do you mean?  What is being mashed with this?... ', 35, '2012-06-11 00:11:38'),
(523, 509, 'Mashing Be Thou My Vision with You Are the Shepherd, the song from the African Children''s Choir.', 37, '2012-06-11 00:17:53');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(524, 520, 'So musically, I think this song has a great melody and the lyrics are easily heard, which is important especially for when we''re lacking microphones on spring break. As far as lyrics go, I love the line "I''ve got nothing to lose, and I''ve got everything to find". It feels like that''s a push in the song, the reason why she''s leaving the world behind, because of the love and freedom she finds in Jesus.', 24, '2012-06-11 18:14:01'),
(525, 519, 'I don''t understand why it''s creepy saying He''s watching us, because that would make Emanuel (the real version, not ron''s actual creepy version) sound creepy, too. The watching us and the connection between the sparrow and us comes from Matthew 10:29 where Jesus says, "Are not two sparrows sold for a penny? Yet not one of them will fall to the ground apart from the will of your Father," and Matthew 6:26, "Look at the birds of the air; they do not sow or reap or store away in barns, and yet your heavenly Father feeds them. Are you not much more valuable than they?" talking about how God cares for even the sparrow and if He''s watching them, how much more will he be watching/caring for you? ', 24, '2012-06-11 18:20:50'),
(526, 157, 'I agree with Maria, I''d want it to be rearranged. I never liked the ending because it always felt like it just killed the energy from the rest of the song....', 24, '2012-06-11 19:23:40'),
(527, 519, 'At least when I was there in person-- it sounded like Maria wasn''t referring so much to the concept of Him watching us---but how it sounded/ came across in this particular song, with it repeated several times by itself.  I could be wrong...', 35, '2012-06-11 19:28:44'),
(528, 415, 'While it''s an easy song to sing/learn, I feel like it''s also one of those songs where it''s easy to slide into sing-along song mode, which is really bad musically', 24, '2012-06-11 19:31:00'),
(529, 517, 'I would be happy to arrange, btw.', 19, '2012-06-11 22:34:42'),
(530, 433, 'I always wonder about "told every lightning bolt where it should go".  I feel skeptical that he actually controls every lightning bolt, and other such things--then you end up saying "So God told the lightning to strike my loved one??" It just bugs me.  Other than that I like the Xprod version of this.  I agree with Kevin, the message is really cool... how awesome God is!', 35, '2012-06-12 02:03:52'),
(531, 246, 'LOVE THIS SONG!  And sometimes I don''t pay attention to the message of the whole song, but I''m just seeing again how it''s a song of just... worship.  Sitting alone in your room, lifting your hands to God, and giving everything to Him.  And lifting your voice in worship!  Dedicating your life and everything you have to Him, and taking time just to listen to Him singing to you.  Beautiful.', 35, '2012-06-12 02:08:13'),
(532, 205, 'I really love this song... when I first heard it, I listened to it over and over and over hahaha.  It''s really pretty and sort of pulls you along as you listen.  I feel like for our sets, there are probably going to be other songs that have more powerful messages (at least for me) that I would go for instead though.  ', 35, '2012-06-12 02:14:26'),
(533, 233, 'I agree with Maria that I get lost in all the super fast lyrics... honestly every time I have heard the song I have not gotten anything out of the verses because of that--so I only know what it''s trying to say from reading the lyrics.  I really enjoy ska personally, but I am having a hard time getting used to the transition to (sk)a Capella......\r\nThe energy and choreo for this video are really fun though :)', 35, '2012-06-12 02:17:00'),
(534, 91, 'I think the first line is just saying that God loves even though we don''t always reciprocate. As for the second line, it''s from Psalm 30:5- "For his anger is but for a moment, and his favor is for a lifetime. Weeping may tarry for the night, but joy comes with the morning." If we are saved, then any pain is temporary and we have an eternal reward.', 3, '2012-06-12 16:51:06'),
(535, 516, 'I love this song as a response to modern-day moral relativism. I might be overly paranoid here, but does "there''s black and there''s white" bring racial issues to mind, even though that''s not what the song is about? That''s my biggest concern with this song.', 3, '2012-06-12 17:01:29'),
(536, 500, 'It''s okay to do something goofy that will make the audience laugh.', 3, '2012-06-12 19:21:20'),
(537, 510, 'You can easily have as many as 6 or 7 people singing brief solo or duet parts in this song. That makes it a good breaking-in-new-xprods song. Also, Christmas.', 3, '2012-06-12 19:29:02'),
(538, 141, 'Here''s some discussion from the old wiki. Summary: We could make it cool by MIT-ifying the lyrics, but our main reservation was that this was "X.ado''s Signature Song" (is that still true?)', 3, '2012-06-12 19:33:37'),
(539, 141, 'I feel this is one of those songs people would walk away with it sticking in their head, and switchfoot is always a hit. It has a good message without being too, what''s that word someone used, Christianese? -jw\r\nThis is X.ado''s signature song though.. -z\r\nYou Lift Me Up is ATD''s and Testify to Love is UC''s I think as well?\r\nWhat''s ours? I''m Not Cool? (haha, jk) -jw\r\nlolol yup! Also, This is Your Life & Via Dolorosa -z\r\n', 3, '2012-06-12 19:34:00'),
(540, 141, '(Some of these are obviously outdated) my 5.0 is gone\r\nmy 4.0\r\nmy 3.2\r\nCaltech Cannon is gone\r\nlike Pass No Record, gone\r\nmy Med School Hopes are gone\r\nCourse 13 is gone\r\nGPA...going..going..gone\r\nlike ATO is gone\r\nour arcade (DDR) is gone\r\nmy brass rat is gone...$400 is gone\r\ncampus dining''s gone.. NOT!!\r\nDaniel Wendel''s gone...NOT!! or DanWendel''s never gone\r\nYTK is gone\r\n6.001\r\nmy parent''s money''s gone\r\nmy social life is gone\r\npersonal hygiene gone\r\nmy sanity is gone\r\npistol team is gone\r\nall the glacier''s gone\r\ngone, the internet is... WAIT WHAT?? no i''m just kidding, it''s a song...\r\nmy room back home is gone\r\nplanet pluto''s gone\r\n', 3, '2012-06-12 19:35:54'),
(541, 141, 'The X.ado thing was the main reason we didn''t do this song the last time IIRC, but I don''t remember the last time I saw X.ado sing it (and there''s no youtube evidence from the last 4 years) so maybe that''s not an issue anymore. This song has huge potential from comedy, music, and message standpoints.', 3, '2012-06-12 19:44:35'),
(542, 5, 'I will respectfully disagree with the above two comments. This is one of our best arrangements. The verses have a cool alternative feeling that fits the off-beat lyrics ("Yesterday is a kid in the corner") and the choruses are energetic and rocking. It''s a great Spring Break public institution go-to song because even without a blurb, the hook in the chorus challenges the listener to evaluate the way they live their life.', 3, '2012-06-12 20:03:57'),
(543, 514, 'At graduation, hearing the MIT Chaplain pray for the people who have committed suicide over the last year made me think that "comfort for the hurting" might deserve a bigger focus at Cross Products concerts than in years'' past. I think "New Perspective", which challenges us to reach out to those who are hurting, would make an interesting pairing with this song, which speaks directly to people who are hurting, pointing them to God.', 3, '2012-06-12 20:27:55'),
(544, 5, 'I think mashup would be ridiculously awesome. And I see your point, Maria... but I do agree with Jacob. Maybe we could add one soprano doing the harpsichord if the pitches agree, in order to get that feel from the original song, again.', 38, '2012-06-13 00:56:53'),
(545, 500, 'Mashup! Dubstep! If this makes it to our set, it''s gonna be awesome. The reason I love this song is because it''s (as Kristina said), such a declarative song. We are declaring in faith and boldness who God actually is. So awesome.', 38, '2012-06-13 01:04:36'),
(546, 516, 'I feel like a blurb would fix Jacob''s concern, since it seems like color imagery is a theme throughout the first half of this song.', 38, '2012-06-13 01:07:59'),
(547, 246, 'I think this would be cool to have in our set because it''s a song that''s also known in the secular world. I feel like a lot of people in the audience would be like, "Wow, I know I heard that somewhere..." and try and pay attention to the lyrics more. ', 38, '2012-06-13 01:19:51'),
(548, 517, 'Just as a piece of trivia: the lead singer said that "if I never sing again, my soul will be my song" was about when he had serious vocal problems and was in danger of losing his voice forever. I really like this song, mostly for what Kevin has already mentioned.', 38, '2012-06-13 01:23:39'),
(549, 415, 'Mmm... I don''t find the lyrics particularly compelling. I''m not against having this song in the set; I just feel like that spot in our setlist can be filled by another song that is more powerful.', 38, '2012-06-13 01:29:13'),
(550, 157, 'Also in favor in rearrangement. Choreo that''s already been created is a plus for this song.', 38, '2012-06-13 01:32:41'),
(551, 494, 'I really like how one song is from a Christian''s perspective, and the other is from God''s perspective.', 38, '2012-06-13 01:36:21'),
(552, 509, 'The youtube video I put up is just something I found online; I''ve always had some kind of choral arrangement in mind when I thought about xprod doing this song, but also more of an upbeat and modern version of it. I''m totally in favor of Caitlin''s idea.', 38, '2012-06-13 01:45:18'),
(553, 513, 'This song''s chorus is always repeating in my head after I listen to it. Good for memorability. Lyrics are good, too.', 38, '2012-06-13 01:48:36'),
(554, 12, 'I think this message is the crux of why xprod even exists. Would be good to have in our set.', 38, '2012-06-13 02:08:25'),
(555, 398, 'I always interpreted the gravity thing as the world pulling us away from God. I think changing the lyrics to "the world" instead of "gravity" would take away such an essential part of the song that it loses its identity. I would prefer to keep it the way it is with perhaps a blurb to clarify its meaning.', 38, '2012-06-13 02:10:38'),
(556, 518, 'I really like the cultural references in this song, especially since it takes a stance against the worldly view in a musically engaging way. I wonder how we would do this a cappella, though, since there are a lot of synth embellishments and stuff. Totally awesome!', 38, '2012-06-13 02:32:41'),
(557, 498, 'This screams musical to me, as well. ', 38, '2012-06-13 02:34:18'),
(558, 499, 'Mmm I feel like the point of this song isn''t explicit enough, but it does kind of fit in with this semester''s theme/vision.', 38, '2012-06-13 02:37:18'),
(559, 521, 'I especially love this line: "I don''t need a miracle to believe", since I feel that a lot of people (at MIT especially) are looking for scientific facts or a miracle to believe in the gospel. But in reality, it''s God''s love that transforms hearts.', 38, '2012-06-13 02:39:18'),
(560, 508, 'I really like this song because it declares who God is, and the second chance He has given us. I feel this fits into the theme for this semester very well, and it''s one of my favorite songs off this album.', 38, '2012-06-13 03:43:45'),
(561, 113, 'One of my favorite worship songs expressing adoration to the King of Kings. I feel like this song encapsulates the epitome of worship. Love this version.', 38, '2012-06-13 03:48:50'),
(562, 141, 'Which group is X.ado again?  I had no idea another group sang it a lot... Joe and I just like listening to it on the switchfoot cd ha ha...', 35, '2012-06-13 13:43:54'),
(563, 499, 'Ya I think you''re right... when I listen to it with Xprod ears I keep wanting to hear the message louder and more of it.', 35, '2012-06-13 13:47:33'),
(564, 141, 'X.ado is Dartmouth''s group.', 3, '2012-06-13 15:16:23'),
(565, 520, 'I like that line the best,  and "my little heart longs for the kindness in your eyes"... Overall I really like this song!  It''s pretty and interesting musically, and the message is her being super interested in God, and like Kristina says, feeling like leaving behind the world feels like she has nothing to lose and everything to find.   I like that the feel is less striving than some of the others with this kind of message (like empty me, although I love that one).   She''s not waiting until she''s at rock bottom to run after Him!   Which is cool. ', 35, '2012-06-13 21:31:58'),
(566, 520, 'Oh ya AND...  I love the mashing with "I have decided to follow Jesus" hymn!! ', 35, '2012-06-13 21:34:04'),
(567, 496, 'I love the chorus...  It gets stuck in my head really easily and of course is a great message to get stuck in your head :-)   and I agree with the proposed lyric change.   That sounds weird to me too.   ', 35, '2012-06-13 21:39:22'),
(568, 496, 'I''m not as attached to the verses and bridge as to the chorus and the overall feel.   I have to look at the lyrics and say "ok what does this mean"...  And think about it, and then I think i get it.   ', 35, '2012-06-13 21:41:41'),
(569, 501, 'Cool song, powerful message!   I kept noticing every time he said "junk",  seems like a lot of times.   Not important though.   The part that gets in my head is "dangerous...  Dangerous... " and so I sort of forget what it was that was dangerous.  That''s just a comment for what sticks out and is most memorable.   ', 35, '2012-06-13 21:58:56'),
(570, 506, 'Wow, ya that''s a really important message, that I for one need to hear a lot.  I have a hard time understanding some of the lines and phrases, mostly just figuring out exactly what they are referring to. "How hard I''ve tried to bring you into this world"... is that the same person talking?  Are they saying they have tried hard, meaning by example as Maria said?  It doesn''t fit with what''s after it, for me... also, "Why is your name offensive?"-- do you think they are asking "why do people I talk to not want to hear it?" It almost sounds to me like "Jesus, your name IS offensive (even to me).  Why?" although I don''t think that''s intended of course.  One more... "If I avoid to speak Your name\r\nTell me would You do the same to me"  Sounds kind of awkward to me.  I guess it''s referring to "If you deny me before men, I will deny you before my Father".  But it''s not quite the same, so Jesus avoiding our names sounds strange and not as powerful as a parallel.  Anyway, if someone has insights to these, cool!  I think I just don''t jive with the exact way the writer phrases things... maybe...', 35, '2012-06-13 22:27:21'),
(571, 512, 'I keep wanting her to go on and say what the promise IS that she was given.  I''m guessing the hope of Salvation?  It just bugs me that she doesn''t actually say explitly.  otherwise it''s a good message of holding onto God and not despairing because you know He''s there, even "when the mountains fall"... :) I wasn''t very drawn by the music, but maybe hearing a nice arrangement I would like it better music-wise.  ', 35, '2012-06-13 22:36:19'),
(572, 509, 'I really like the mashup idea too--partly because although I love Be Thou My Vision, the language is so old that it might be difficult for audiences to understand what it''s trying to say if they are not familiar with it already.  So having a really understandable song (like you are the shepherd, or a chorus of another song with the same message as BTMV) with it would be really cool.', 35, '2012-06-13 22:39:15'),
(573, 497, 'I really like when hymns are slightly reworked to give them a bit of modern musical flavor, while still preserving the words and major melody for the most part.  So I like this idea... and I feel like it''s a bit more understandable lyric-wise than the straight hymn for BTMV.', 35, '2012-06-13 22:43:07'),
(574, 508, 'Great worship song... I like the melody and how it''s almost kind of haunting.  And I like the line "your word is a lamp to my path" in there.  Ohhh Kristina and her Christian dubstep!  :)  Once again I don''t have the speakers to appreciate it.  But having strong perc and neat effects could really pair nicely with this song, because of that slightly haunting feel.  ', 35, '2012-06-13 22:52:48'),
(575, 512, 'Easily helped by blurb =)', 39, '2012-06-14 00:20:51'),
(576, 516, 'I agree that the blurb setting up "black and white" as just polar opposites should avoid that.  I also agree with Maria that the choruses don''t do very much for me... I like the part that says "I won''t go one more night without telling you I''m sorry"... reminding us to confess our sins to God often.  But  the different things that are said in the chorus seem disconnected to me.  And the part saying "I feel so lost without you here" seems to say that God ISN''T there with him, which isn''t true if the speaker has a relationship and is seeking God...  Also the almost disco-like feel of the chorus totally surprised me!  I didn''t expect that to be the style.  I''m not sure how interesting that would really sound a Capella...', 35, '2012-06-14 01:40:07'),
(577, 14, 'Yay!  I already liked this song, and I really like the arrangement!  And how the solos change...it really builds nicely!  And the message is just so strong.  Wow we are moving to lightning speed by the end, ha ha ha...', 35, '2012-06-14 01:45:16'),
(578, 329, 'I really like those lines that Kristina pointed out!  But I agree with Maria that it is really repetitive.  After some of the beginning, I was liking what I was hearing and looking forward to more... but they kept saying the same things instead :(  So I was sad that there weren''t more new lyrics from where those cool lines came from.', 35, '2012-06-14 01:50:26'),
(579, 15, 'Cool song!  I really like that message of asking for God''s eyes to see people as he sees them, and asking to have his heart for people.  The message that we want to care about other people, and that God already does.  The whole first verse came out of nowhere for me... I was like huh?  Wait, I think a plane is landing?  But the rest of the song makes sense to me.  I''m not sure how much there is musically that is interesting.  Depends on the arrangement I guess!  But it sounded kind of repetitive for the backgrounds maybe.  ', 35, '2012-06-14 01:56:06'),
(580, 432, 'Anti-materialism song.  Cool laid-back style in the chorus, I like.  Maybe it''s not too soon now?... :)  Since BU floored us, I mean.  I had a hard time grasping the verses without reading the lyrics along with it.  "Now I''m Paul"  that would have fit well with our skit this term :)\r\nI like the song, good message, sounds fun.', 35, '2012-06-14 02:03:05'),
(581, 372, 'I never thought it was about God hearing it on the radio... but now i''m totally seeing it.  Cause it says "Desperate for changing, starving for truth".  Although the rest of it could be someone''s worship-like song about a girlfriend, these lines suggest to me something more, and therefore it sounds like it''s someone seeking God.  And I think I resonate more with these particular lyrics than the Flyleaf song.  They are saying some similar things.  I think it would be a great choice because it''s so well known on secular radio, and we could highlight the fact that it''s about searching for truth in God.  I agree it would sound good with a capella', 35, '2012-06-14 02:09:25'),
(582, 91, 'I like this song, and find it powerful and encouraging singing it at church.  And I like the melody.  Seems like a good option.', 35, '2012-06-14 02:13:53'),
(583, 113, 'I really like this song too.  I feel like you don''t have to be feeling a certain way to sing it in worship... it''s just adoring him for who he is.  Could be really cool sounding too if we did it right...', 35, '2012-06-14 02:17:48'),
(584, 434, 'Ya this could be really powerful... It illustrates God''s grace, and also could be personal for some people who might be estranged from family.  ', 35, '2012-06-14 02:21:49'),
(585, 512, 'Well, I meant even for me I am wondering what promise.  So in the blurb we would be assuming something and telling the audience... but I guess there is nothing wrong with figuring it''s probably the promise of salvation and saying that in the blurb.', 35, '2012-06-14 02:23:53'),
(586, 524, '', 51, '2012-12-11 16:11:51'),
(591, 8, 'I think this is a beautiful song about Christ''s sacrifice, and I second what was said above.', 38, '2012-12-11 22:46:55'),
(592, 523, 'I''ll admit this isn''t a very lyrically dense song, but I like the metaphors and imagery this song invokes when talking about God''s love. It''s something I feel that some non-Christians may not understand; the fact that God loves us, and how much that strong love can actually change someone.', 38, '2012-12-11 22:48:57'),
(593, 167, 'An upbeat, lively song that we can definitely rely on during Spring Break. Also, nobody doesn''t like Mountains, right?', 40, '2012-12-12 02:44:23'),
(594, 528, 'This was a pet project of mine from Spring 2011, with equal parts pi, pie, and theology of grace. The song is designed to be a mnemonic for memorizing pi out to the 100th decimal place: the number of letters in each word corresponds to the digit(s).\r\n\r\nSome clarification on the lyrics:\r\nStating the obvious, "Love" = God and "cookbook" = Bible. It can be said that God''s grace is not "rational" in the context given by the preceding lines (i.e. it''s not something we can claim to inherently deserve - Eph 2:4-9). I use the word "saints" not in the canonical sense, but more colloquially to refer to believers who have been sanctified through Christ. (e.g., 1 Cor 1:2)', 27, '2012-12-13 20:49:47'),
(595, 455, 'I re-suggested it because it''s exactly where I am right now, and where I think a lot of MIT students are, recognizing they need to move on from...something. \r\n\r\nI also think it''d be a great spring song for seniors leaving because of "Time for a milestone\r\nTime to begin again\r\nRevaluate who I really am\r\nAm I doing everything to follow your will\r\nor just climbing aimlessly over these hills"\r\n\r\nThose are just what I thought of, not necessarily everyone''s interpretation.', 39, '2012-12-13 23:52:17'),
(596, 423, 'God''s the answer, and he''s always with us through everything. Awesome message, awesome song. We can''t steal X.ado''s choreo, but this sounds like a really good song to choreo too.', 40, '2012-12-14 02:03:33'),
(597, 23, 'Looks like a really fun arrangement, with lots and lots of energy. I could easily see our singing this during Spring Break and other gigs.', 40, '2012-12-14 02:56:29'),
(598, 526, 'reminder to quiet our hearts and remember that God is there; slow but pretty song!', 47, '2012-12-14 07:25:42'),
(599, 527, 'clearly declares praise and awe for Jesus; really catchy song too!', 47, '2012-12-14 07:27:21'),
(600, 529, 'Why, by Nichole Nordeman, is an important reminder of just how much God loves us.  The dialogue between the Father and the Son is absolutely heart-wrenching.  We spend a lot of time praising and thanking God for his love and forgiveness, but I think it''s easy to forget how greatly Jesus suffered to win our salvation out of His love for us.', 46, '2012-12-14 18:44:15'),
(601, 530, 'Not a high energy song, but a good one. It would be difficult to arrange, and we probably wouldn''t want to keep the background as simple as the acoustic guitar, but it would be a nice song to sing, and the lyrics say a lot.', 49, '2012-12-14 18:45:07'),
(602, 218, 'Such a beautiful affirmation of the strength we get from God! Why never again? :(', 46, '2012-12-14 18:49:34'),
(603, 8, 'Second what Polly said (and what Shion/Jacob said about this song making me want to cry sometimes. It''s so beautiful)', 46, '2012-12-14 18:55:15'),
(604, 15, 'It wouldn''t have fit it with our set this past semester, but I like that it calls us to pay attention to the people that we so often walk by who need help. Like Rachel said last semester, the first verse does seem kind of random, unless you watch the music video.', 49, '2012-12-14 18:55:34'),
(605, 218, 'Haha, iirc our arrangement of this song is pretty difficult to sing and it didn''t turn out well. Certainly not to say we should never do the song again, but I would highly recommend redoing or retooling the arrangement if you do.', 3, '2012-12-14 22:10:01'),
(606, 531, 'A powerful, but subtle reminder in this song is in the chorus: "Your love, your love, is all I have to give".... Dear friends, let us love one another, for love comes from God. Everyone who loves has been born of God and knows God. Whoever does not love does not know God, because God is love. -1 John 4:7-8. I love how the whole point of this song is about how God is love- how he''s the one that satisfies our hunger, how he''s our hope and our light in the darkness. Plus- spring break friendly!!', 24, '2012-12-17 18:59:00'),
(607, 532, 'This song helped me through a tough time of questioning in undergrad... I just felt really unsure whether my beliefs were real.  It really helped me being able to sing "I''ll trust you when I cannot see, I''ll trust you when the shadow covers over me, and I''ll love you when the distance leaves me cold... I will love you, I will still believe that you are sovereign, Lord!" \r\n"I''m learning to trust, I''m learning to feel, i''m learning to love you always".  \r\n\r\nBy the way, the mp3 I uploaded is best quality.  The youtube video is the only one I could find!  So... don''t be distracted by the shots of Kirby saying "praise God!" and stuff.  he he.', 35, '2012-12-18 02:13:32'),
(608, 533, 'On Cross Products cd from 2002!  :)\r\nWe don''t really have any other songs (that I''ve heard of) that are truly "a capella" style songs.  It''s a fun and very different feel than a lot of the rock songs or hymns we have been doing.\r\nThe mp3 uploaded above is the Cross Products version from the cd.', 35, '2012-12-18 02:28:01'),
(609, 534, 'For one thing one of my best friends who is not a Christian loves this song.  Also, in the light of recent tragedies I have seen a lot of people just crying out to God, being faced with such evil in the world.  This is a song that lets us do that... I find it really moving.', 35, '2012-12-18 02:44:45'),
(610, 533, 'I like the Cross Products version better.  Less echo...', 35, '2012-12-18 03:00:40'),
(611, 524, 'Dude, lyrics please?  :)', 35, '2012-12-18 03:01:35'),
(612, 245, 'Is it time to resurrect it yet? I fell in love with this song when I first heard it from the CD. As to Rachel''s comment from ''08, I realized a long time ago (back in high school) that I wasn''t cool. I like that this song says it''s okay, that God doesn''t care if you''re "cool" or not. It''s also kind of scary how much of this applies to me (about 80% or so), though I guess I shouldn''t be surprised. As for the lyrics, I''d be okay with either changing them or not.', 49, '2012-12-19 21:59:12'),
(613, 245, 'Sorry, not ''08, but 2012-01-08.', 49, '2012-12-19 21:59:59'),
(614, 537, '<story> so i was driving in the car with my sister and the top 40 radio station was playing in the background as we were talking(cue commercial break. kristina is talking about xprod. she transitions to talking about song suggestions) Kristina: "Yeah... it would be really cool if we could have some top 40 songs that have christian messages. Like Meant to Live, only more recent." Then this song came on, like literally the second after I said that. </story> Point being that this song has some cool potential because it''s super popular right now, and on secular stations nonetheless. Also have the possibility of doing a small mashup (like how i added "take my life" lyrics into Our God is Greater as a bridge) with the song Save the World. (with a slight change in lyrics) ', 24, '2012-12-26 01:42:01'),
(615, 538, 'happy song! :D if we do this song, i don''t think we have to do the spoken parts', 47, '2012-12-26 04:45:57'),
(616, 418, 'This song reminded me of what we''d talked about at the last Cru large group of the semester. MIT''s a really difficult place and it sometimes feels like it breaks people. In reality, though, it doesn''t; MIT just shows people how broken they already were. God is the only one who can fix our brokenness, and it is from our brokenness and our surrender that His Name is glorified.', 50, '2012-12-26 05:09:57'),
(617, 537, '2:54-3:24 in the Pentatonix video shows how the mashup could work. (Who''s going to save the world tonight? Who''s going to bring you back to life? Don''t you worry child, because I''m going to bring you back to life)', 24, '2012-12-26 05:15:24'),
(618, 61, 'If we say that we dedicate our lives to God, are we really pointing to Him in everything we do? and are we willing to surrender everything that we desire for the sake of His kingdom? Is that what other people see when they look at us?', 50, '2012-12-26 05:23:30'),
(619, 539, 'The message of this song is really powerful. On one hand you have this broken world that we live in, and on the other you have God, who doesn''t need us and yet His heart breaks for every single one of us. I really like how the song doesn''t just stop there, though, because God calls us to go and do likewise - to love like He loves us.', 50, '2012-12-26 05:54:14'),
(620, 34, 'I realize that Xprod did this just last spring, but I really like this song (and the arrangement). The lyrics come right from the Gospel that we''ve all heard before, but they make you stop and remember what that truly means. On part that especially stands out to me is that God didn''t just save us as lost and frightened children, but as those who mocked and rejected Him... I also like how this hymn doesn''t have a soloist because it makes the message more full and powerful, and lets us focus more on God and less on whoever''s singing it.', 50, '2012-12-26 06:11:36'),
(621, 418, 'Great song.  If we sing it this semester, I think we should add in the high harmony from the original song.  I miss it in the acapella version... easy to add a duet!  ', 35, '2012-12-26 18:06:32'),
(622, 537, 'I like it.  Especially the mashup.  And the pentatonix video was very useful to show how you really can do trance music acapella...haha.  Sounds cool!  And it''s a simple message.  In a good way.', 35, '2012-12-26 18:14:02'),
(623, 537, 'While I felt the first video was too unclear in the message, the second video of the mashup really helped clear things up, so I do like it. (:  I think this song has potential.', 48, '2012-12-26 18:25:25'),
(624, 418, 'It is a wonderful song, but I do feel that there needs to be more around it, like if we use it to tie it to another song or part of the play?  It felt kind of short to me, and maybe even that the music was a little out of tone with the message?  I felt there was more weight in the lyrics than in the music.', 48, '2012-12-26 18:30:39'),
(625, 9, 'I love this song, a favorite of mine since I was young, and one of the few I fully memorized.  It has such a beautiful message of simple praise for how little we are, how much he is, and how much he loves us.  I would love to have this as a part of our song selection.', 48, '2012-12-26 18:34:22'),
(626, 34, '"Ashamed, I hear my mocking voice/call out among the scoffers"  I love so much of this song, but when I first heard it in high school, that was the line that gripped my heart.  Wherever you come from, this song is one that will stop you and grab your heart, and make you see how far we have fallen from glory, and how beautiful a gift our Father is.  I love this song.', 48, '2012-12-26 18:46:35'),
(627, 539, 'I do like this song a lot, it is very clear in the message, and I love the part where we are asking to be like him, but doesn''t that part make it more of a song directed to people who already believe?  Other than that, I thought the rest of the song did point out God''s love for those who are lost, which is why I still like it.', 48, '2012-12-26 18:52:48'),
(628, 61, 'I like this one too, but I don''t know how well it would fit for a group of ministry to those who don''t know as well as those who do know him?', 48, '2012-12-26 18:57:43'),
(629, 538, 'That is definitely one happy song and I like it, but I don''t know where it would fit well, I just think it could.', 48, '2012-12-26 19:03:43'),
(630, 435, 'I love this song. (:', 48, '2012-12-26 19:16:36'),
(631, 219, 'I love it. (:', 48, '2012-12-26 19:22:24'),
(632, 245, 'When I first heard this song, I thought it was just a silly song that was used to get a laugh as much to get a message.  I don''t know, all the times I heard cross products sing it, it sounded like they were trying to sing it "not cool," which is what I expected until I watched this video.  The video for me gave such a different vibe than being "not cool" and that''s okay, but more like "I''m not cool," and I am cool ;) with that.  Literally, I imagined the soloist dancing around just loving all that was different about him, because God made him that way.  All the times I heard it before, it sounded more like the singer was just accepting that he was not cool.  If we do this song again, I feel we really need to give it the vibe the original had, and just start praising God for how not cool I am, and THANKING him for it. :D', 48, '2012-12-26 19:44:33'),
(633, 136, 'because I did not suggest this, I will put the video here, but is this the song you recommended?  I saw no video or lyrics?\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RrnrGdpVI88', 48, '2012-12-26 19:55:29'),
(634, 539, 'It''s ok for at least some of our message to be directed at believers-- there''s plenty we as believers can learn and grow in... I''ve heard many times that believers who went to our concert were touched by the message. ', 35, '2012-12-26 20:01:06'),
(635, 246, 'It''s beautiful, filled with such a simple love.', 48, '2012-12-26 20:09:46'),
(636, 246, 'the greatest love.', 48, '2012-12-26 20:10:00'),
(637, 521, 'I like several parts of this song, including the not needing a miracle.  But the phrase "everything is beautiful" honestly just makes me think "It doesn''t make EVERYTHING beautiful, you just don''t focus on those things--you focus on Jesus.  There are still bad and ugly things in the world, they just are triumphed over by Jesus".  So anyway, I think that every time I hear that line, so it''s not my favorite.  Even though I get what he is trying to say.', 35, '2012-12-26 20:16:15'),
(638, 15, 'I like the Xprod version better.  A bit hard to hear the solo in this particular recording... But I like it.', 35, '2012-12-26 20:25:29'),
(639, 34, 'Luckily 2 altos already know the tricky part fairly well... :)  Pretty song.', 35, '2012-12-26 20:33:29'),
(640, 524, 'I think this song has a lot of potential, definitely.', 48, '2012-12-26 20:33:52'),
(641, 34, 'I prefer to do a different but equally powerful hymn first though, before repeating this one so soon', 35, '2012-12-26 20:34:22'),
(642, 524, 'Would you replace "baby" with "Jesus"?....... I''m not really seeing the full potential... does Jesus have a halo or something?', 35, '2012-12-26 20:48:09'),
(643, 538, 'I sort of wish the meaty lyrics about "God is working" and the power of the holy spirit and joy were more prominent... instead of just smiling all the time.  Not sure how powerful that is for people who are going through something, but I don''t know.  Sure would be fun tho!', 35, '2012-12-26 21:03:06'),
(644, 538, 'Joe''s comment: "It kind of sounds like they''re saying "You look ugly when you don''t smile"... he he.  ', 35, '2012-12-26 21:09:00'),
(645, 435, 'Nice song, pretty and with good harmonies.  Didn''t really strike me in any way though.  Some Christianese.', 35, '2012-12-26 21:17:06'),
(646, 498, 'This is a lot like "All the Broken Pieces" in message... "In return for a torn life, he''ll give you life abundantly".  We always wanted to change the line to "Put the pieces back together into something better", and this kind of says that exact thing.  He gives us even more than just stitching us back up!', 35, '2012-12-26 21:29:43'),
(647, 61, 'I like the part that refers to "Store up for yourselves treasures in heaven, not things on earth where moth and rust will destroy"... Good song.  ', 35, '2012-12-26 21:43:39'),
(648, 136, 'Cross Products have done this one... pretty!', 35, '2012-12-26 22:00:15'),
(649, 246, 'Such a pretty arrangement!  The Xprod video sounds great, especially for a live recording.', 35, '2012-12-26 22:10:06'),
(650, 535, 'I always enjoy the chorus more than the verses--something about the style.  But the lyrics are good!  And I like the song.  Powerful.  "My God was, is, and is always going to be"', 35, '2012-12-26 22:15:12'),
(651, 23, 'It''s also on the older Xprod cd with Daniel soloing.  :)', 35, '2012-12-26 22:16:21'),
(652, 437, 'I don''t think I would have realized it could be Christian without you guys saying so.  Lions and giants are pretty widespread references, and people talk about faith in general meaning perhaps faith in yourself or something.  So I''m sure with a strong blurb it would be there, but at least for some of us it''s pretty obscure seeing biblical references...\r\nWhen keeping your comments in mind, I thought the idea was cool and challenging.', 35, '2012-12-26 22:22:05'),
(653, 521, 'I just love this song, never heard it before.  It speaks a lot to God''s grace, that even when it all falls, we have so much reason to rejoice and sing.  When I am weak, then I am strong.', 48, '2012-12-27 00:00:40'),
(654, 521, 'Rachel: Totally understand where you''re coming from, but I think what I interpret from the song is that everything becomes beautiful when looked at through Jesus'' eyes.  And I think the verses of the song qualify the "everything" of the song as being everything that happens to the singer...\r\n\r\nThat said, I love the message, recognizing pain, but how love rescues.  And the beat, melody, etc, are appropriate to the message and even captivating.', 44, '2012-12-27 00:43:28'),
(655, 523, 'Since the first time I heard this song, I loved it, and I think while it''s maybe not a complex song, with the context of the concert and the overall message, this song could make a big impression.', 44, '2012-12-27 00:48:06'),
(656, 540, 'I can''t find this anywhere on youtube... :(   ', 35, '2012-12-27 01:24:41'),
(657, 540, '...But my sister has the song apparently, so I was able to listen :)  Might want to upload the mp3 or something!!\r\nGood message, about how God gives us our purpose and everything done apart from him is in vain.  ', 35, '2012-12-27 01:29:28'),
(658, 541, 'I fell in love with this song when I first heard it, it almost made me cry.  I suggest this song because I think it is such a powerful call to us and those who listen, asking if we would "fall to pieces," would let go and surrender all that we hold on to, for the glory of our God and his kingdom.  It is one of my favorites, even among my favorites. XD', 48, '2012-12-27 01:52:57'),
(659, 543, 'This song is a beautiful song, that just comes out and says that we need more of God, ever and ever more of him, and less of ourselves.  It speaks of the endless process of being transformed in Him, of our need for him, and one I often listen to to remind myself of where I am going, most of all when I am down and distraught in my wayward heart and thoughts.  I love it, and I sing it so often, because I know I need it.  And I think it is a gift worth reminding and sharing to those who don''t know it yet - just how much God really has for us, is more than he has already given us.', 48, '2012-12-27 02:09:04'),
(660, 128, 'I basically second geofft''s comment on the old wiki (http://xprod.mit.edu/w/It_Is_Well):\r\n\r\n"So. I like this song. I have done some excellent choral versions, most memorably a festival version at my state''s United Methodist Annual Conference a few years back where we joined a bunch of other choirs and there was an actual trump resounding in the corner. (Very sadly that is not an option for us.) There are also a couple of fun covers by CCM artists, videos below. We can probably do our own cover, written for a cappella, and make it awesome."\r\n\r\n\r\nMy only concern is that the lyric grammar is antique. But I tried briefly to modernize it and like what I''m coming up with, so if I who have no poetry skills to speak of can do half-decently, surely a moderately skilled bard could make a good revision. Or just leave it, and use the blurb to explain the lyrics (which I like because it makes people pay attention to them).\r\n', 22, '2012-12-27 02:23:12'),
(661, 12, 'I think this makes a great stand-by song for the group to know whether or not it''s part of the main set -- e.g, it''s great for Spring Break gigs where you can actually say Jesus :)', 22, '2012-12-27 02:25:31'),
(662, 513, 'Re-suggested. My fav Lecrae song -- lyrics are clear and on-point, and yes the chorus is memorable :)\r\n', 22, '2012-12-27 02:37:22'),
(663, 61, 'The following comments are from the old wiki  (http://xprod.mit.edu/w/Nichole_Nordeman_-_Legacy) (I''m trying to html-format the following so sorry if this looks weird): \r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nI agree with geofft below. We shouldn''t care about how "they" will remember us but rather how God will remember us. -Jacob\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nI''m distinctly not okay with this song. I don''t think being remembered as a pointer to God is something I want to be. I want to be known, in the present, as a pointer to God, and have the legacy just be God. (Maybe this song would be okay if it''s "I don''t want to leave a legacy?") I don''t want to live my life to hear "Well done, good and faithful servant"; Satan can say that just as well. I want to live my life for God because he is good. And there are so many other Nichole Nordeman songs that say that so much better, from "Holy" to the almost-pantheist-but-really-it''s-quite-acceptable "Every Season", both of which I''m happy for this group to do. -geofft\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nkind of like the above, i thought about the end of my life, and my conclusion is, I want people to remember that "God is good and great", not necessarily that "Shion left a good legacy following God"- the first one is eternal. the latter is not. Or I don''t know, I never really cared about living to leave a legacy... I''m kind of also along the lines of we live soley for God regardless of being forgotten and alien from the world -shion-\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\nI haven''t thought about this in detail, so I''m leaving an X just to flag this discussion.', 22, '2012-12-27 02:43:19'),
(664, 23, 'The first time I heard this song I couldn''t stop thinking that it was about a girl. Jesus != girlfriend. But a good blurb and an encore performance by dj could save it. :) -ken \r\n\r\n(I stole my comment off <a href="http://xprod.mit.edu/w/DC_Talk_-_Since_I_Met_You">the ol'' wiki page</a>.)\r\n', 22, '2012-12-27 02:46:48'),
(665, 246, 'Once again, the <a href="http://xprod.mit.edu/w/Switchfoot_-_Only_Hope">old wiki page</a>.\r\n\r\n<br>br> I said there:\r\n<br>br>\r\nself crash, surrender to God. Anchord did it, but with the Mandy Moore lyrics ("destiny" instead of "apathy"). But I really connected with it back in my proto-Christian days because of the idea of surrendering all that I am, even my apathy (which I had a lot of) to God--coming to him just as I am, messed up but wanting to be his. But this is a more "me-centered" song than my other suggestions, so I''d be happy to see it lose to something with more God-centered lyrics. -ken ', 22, '2012-12-27 02:49:32'),
(666, 52, 'I''m re-suggesting this because I still think it could be a powerful spring break song for the women''s shelter category of gigs. It could be paired with a powerful blurb too for the MIT crowd. Also it would give the group some musical variety, plus I''d love to arrange it!', 23, '2012-12-27 02:50:37'),
(667, 34, 'If people already know it, reviewing it even once or twice now will make it <em>so much</em> easier to learn next time.\r\n', 22, '2012-12-27 02:50:46'),
(668, 544, 'I think of this as a similar takeaway as Perfect People but a different musical style. There was a big discussion in my department at Berkeley over the Meltdown blog post. Through that I ended up sharing a lot that part of why people are so much more open to religion at MIT than other schools is because absolutely everyone in their four years hits a point where they can''t do it on their own. They need God, they "need a miracle."', 23, '2012-12-27 03:11:41'),
(669, 513, 'I LOVE YOU KEN!!!  This is one of my favorites too!! :D  I want to highly recommend it from experience with this song since it was released. (:  It really does have a powerful message of where we should boast, which I know has been a struggle for me, because it is easy to desire my own praise and be able to boast in all that I have done for the Lord and all that I am worth, rather than realizing that I have done nothing, but that all of it was done by Him for me, through me.  My absolute favorite lines, "I volunteer for your sanctifying surgery./I know the Spirit''s purging me of everything that''s hurting me," just speaks of the hope that of all this selfishness and guilt, He is working through to his greater glory and purpose in my life.  It is such a powerful, and needed message.', 48, '2012-12-27 03:13:20'),
(670, 438, 'Re-suggesting since I still love this song and I have it halfway arranged.', 23, '2012-12-27 03:13:34'),
(671, 542, 'Pretty arrangement, and a feeling that we can all relate to at one point or another. Despite the things we go through, God loves us fully and freely. Lyrics are repetitive and emphasized. ', 40, '2012-12-27 03:17:44'),
(672, 540, 'Sorry Rachel! Yes strange how it''s not on youtube...but hopefully now everyone can listen to the uploaded version. I think this song has a really good, quite obvious message that we need God because ultimately, every minute without Him (or every decision, every step away...) is worthless. It would be a good transition song - going from learning about God to realizing how much we need Him and accepting Him as our savior. Plus, it''s fun to sing :) I like the change from ballady to rocky (hence my not knowing what to classify it as in the genre section).', 37, '2012-12-27 16:25:30'),
(673, 443, 'Ouhh- if we could get this arrangement from Brad, it would be pretty awesome. This song just makes me awestruck at God''s love for us- cause really- Who am I that the Lord of all the earth would care to know my name, would care to feel my hurt? And "I am Yours," same thing. This song really focuses on how unworthy we are, but that God still saved us.', 37, '2012-12-27 16:34:13'),
(674, 545, 'I find this song so lyrically rich and when I hear it it reminds me that I''ve forgotten that God has called us to love everyone, and just how important love is in HIs plan.  \r\n\r\nAlso, I wikipediaed this song and here is an excerpt from the wikipedia page:  \r\n\r\nThe song is a lyrical paraphrase of 1 Corinthians 13, which is a passage that speaks of love. The duo shared their personal stories with New Release Tuesday in July 2012. Luke explained, "Joel came to me in the studio that day and told me he wanted to write something that would gently nudge and encourage people and at the same time challenge them. That''s a very difficult line to balance. People don''t want to be challenged too much and be turned away. When we were looking at the Bible passage 1 Corinthians 13, we knew there was something significant that we hadn''t written about. We decided to put those words into this song. That''s how the song came to be." Joel also explained, "Adding to that, there''s a powerful message in proclaiming those truths from God''s Word first. The lyrics have me singing, "If I sing, but don''t have love, I waste my breath with every song." Rather than have this be a judgment to listeners, it''s time for me to proclaim it. Then you can make it your own and put your tent pegs in the ground and announce that you are standing by those same words."[1]', 17, '2012-12-27 18:15:25'),
(675, 546, 'I love how this song is presented from someone who is like "honestly God, I don''t want to forgive this person, even though I know it''s what you want me to do... halp?"  Also the refrain "this is love, this is hate, we have a choice to make" reminds me that forgiveness is just that: a choice!  sometimes I feel so consumed in my self-pity and hurt from someone wronging me I forget, that forgiveness is a choice, a hard one, but God is there to give us strength to make it.  I feel like this song touches on a topic that we don''t always hear in christian contemporary music (forgiveness), but is important and so so applicable to our daily lives.  Also I''m a sucker for a gospel choir-esque ending, which this song has.  Also I feel is a good song for Spring Break ministry, since I think forgiveness is something that everyone can relate to struggling with.  ', 17, '2012-12-27 18:27:31'),
(676, 545, 'Also, I am a sucker for spoken bible lyrics in a song.  ', 17, '2012-12-27 18:30:57'),
(677, 438, 'I would just like to say I love Kelkel''s arrangements.    Also I think this song reminds me of how awesomely backwards faith in God is.  The verses of this song, if without God, seem like a sad thing, there''s chaos, mistakes, and heartaches in Natalie''s life, but because of Christ, she can turn these challenges she''s gone through in life just further her motivation and conviction that she knows she will not be turned away from God.  ', 17, '2012-12-27 18:36:17'),
(678, 513, 'I would just like to share Dartmouth''s cover of Boasting we heard at BIDB this spring.  Because it was HOTT!  Alot of it is driven by that wicked perc and paired with a solid rap.  So those are good to have to pull it off. ', 17, '2012-12-27 18:47:36');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(679, 541, 'This song is beautiful!  I''ve heard it summed as a lyrical interpretation of CS Lewis''s "The great divorce."  It would be a nice slow and contemplative moment in a set of high energetic songs.  Question: what do you think the writer means by "the high countries?" Like would we fall to pieces in the places of our lives where we think we have gained it all, only to realize it is not enough without God?  (that''s what I think it means but am open to other unique interpretations)', 17, '2012-12-27 19:04:37'),
(680, 541, 'The more I think about it, the more I view this song as like a musical alter call.  The slow and simple line forces you to slow down and reflect.  I think it''d be great to use it in a set (or gig) that way.  With perhaps a blurb explaining that this song reflects something that God has asked all of us.... I dunno this is still not a full fledged idea yet but hopefully I make sense.  But basically I really like this song. :P', 17, '2012-12-27 19:19:08'),
(681, 541, 'and like I''m not saying you have to do much extra with a blurb for this song (really you don''t have to/ shouldn''t listen to a word I say lol),  like I think that just explaining what the lyrics mean to y''all in a very personal way will allow the song to speak for itself.  ok I''m done I just got excited. ', 17, '2012-12-27 19:21:58'),
(682, 218, 'Oh dear - I just read this comment thread. The arrangement was tough, yes, though if we want to do it I''m sure some combination of us / Gabe / others can either modify it as needed.', 26, '2012-12-27 19:32:54'),
(683, 544, 'Well no matter who you are \r\nAnd no matter what you''ve done \r\nThere will come a time \r\nWhen you can''t make it on your own \r\nAnd in your hour of desperation \r\nKnow you''re not the only one \r\nPrayin'' "Lord above, I need a miracle" \r\nI need a miracle  .         Seconding Kellie.  I do think that the MIT student body is more poised than ever to here this message.  ', 17, '2012-12-27 20:07:09'),
(684, 48, 'Not 100% sure that the verses tell a relatable story, but the chorus and bridge definitely drive the message home "God knows our pain, and His promise remains...He will be with you always"', 44, '2012-12-27 20:40:18'),
(685, 537, 'wait I was thinking about how this would be great for xprod just the other day.  and now you guys suggested.  wait yes yes yes yes!!\r\nYES!\r\nYESSSSSS!!!!!', 17, '2012-12-27 20:43:00'),
(686, 537, 'ooh and mayybe you could change like the very last "heaven''s got a plan for your" to Jesus has a plan for you.  too cheezy?  this is a-cappella, baby!  ', 17, '2012-12-27 20:43:53'),
(687, 537, 'ooh yeah I could definitely hear someone singing "our god is greater/ stronger" during the quiet bridge of the pentatonix mashup (when the girl sings.)  that''d be sweet. good ear, Kristina!', 17, '2012-12-27 20:48:52'),
(688, 537, 'and I don''t mean _literally_ I could hear someone singing that.  just mean I could imagine someone singing it and it working well.  just to clarify. ', 17, '2012-12-27 20:50:01'),
(689, 537, 'also I like how the song talks about someone who once was the "king" of his world and then all of that went away.  and he had the girl of his dreams, but  that went away too. (yeesh reminded me of how many ugly breakups has God led me through... so many! thanks God! so applicable)   But he''s left with his Father telling him not to worry, Heaven has a plan for him.  ', 17, '2012-12-27 20:54:24'),
(690, 547, 'In two quick verses, this song packs a lot of spiritual truth, as well as a natural response in light of what that truth is. I can see it being a showstopper, a crowd-clapper (if you will), and a song that really points to the life and work of Jesus and our desire to rep him.\r\n\r\nSide note--if you like rap, you''ll probably like the rest of Lecrae''s latest album--Gravity. Highly recommend it. :)', 28, '2012-12-27 21:07:34'),
(691, 548, 'Somewhat the same idea as "Like an Avocado", but another good song about surrender, "let my world crumble" -- big idea', 44, '2012-12-27 21:13:55'),
(692, 549, 'I sang this song in my Christian children''s choir with sign language and all that. I don''t particularly like this youtube version (the uploaded version is from my choir- I apologize for some screeching :)). But I think it has a very important message- that God is listening to us and cares about our lives, similar to "Who Am I"''s message. And it''s pretty. I think we could go the choral route, or we could come up with some insane arrangement and take it a different direction if need be.', 37, '2012-12-27 21:56:46'),
(693, 538, 'I loled a Joe''s comment XD', 17, '2012-12-27 22:09:36'),
(694, 550, 'I sang this song with my choir with children and women- it had a different feel, not really how Hillsong United or Rebecca St. James did it- it was more choral/a capella-y. I definitely like that feel better than these videos. I like that this is different from what we typically sing, especially music-wise.', 37, '2012-12-27 22:18:48'),
(695, 302, 'Could we get X.ado''s arrangement of this song?', 37, '2012-12-28 01:54:55'),
(696, 537, 'wait wait lol dorothy, that our god is greater was a comment on how this song could be a mashup of don''t you worry child/save the world like how i did a small mashup of our god is greater/glory to god forever. on a separate note, i agree with your last comment :)', 24, '2012-12-28 02:06:25'),
(697, 552, 'I first thought of xprod singing this song when I was thinking "xprod should do a musical!" So that was my thought process with this song. I think these are the most powerful lyrics, especially for people who may be losing hope at MIT or due to whatever: "I believe though God is out of sight He''s working in the middle of all things." I don''t really care for the rest of the lyrics- they''re not too intensely Christian, just more generally positive. But, if we were to do a musical and wanted to acknowledge that we were doing a musical, this song would work. Other than that, I''m not too crazy about it- but I thought I''d put it up anyway, just in case.', 37, '2012-12-28 02:13:52'),
(698, 553, 'Can you tell I like Point of Grace? They were basically all I listened to from 3rd-8th grade. Anyway, I really like "My God." It is very upbeat and happy, like other happy songs like the smile one that Phoebe suggested and the more to life that I suggested, but I feel like My God has a better, more substancial (if you want to can call it that) message. I think the chorus says it all. I also like the switch from talking about me to you, the audience.', 37, '2012-12-28 02:18:06'),
(699, 553, '*substantial, can''t spell', 37, '2012-12-28 02:19:02'),
(700, 554, 'I think this song speaks to the struggle we go through every day, especially as believers, but even not.  There is so much uncertainty in everything, I know I was filled with uncertainty for many years, and at times it still hits me.  I love this song, and it speaks so truly to my struggle, and I believe many others.', 48, '2012-12-28 04:52:45'),
(701, 555, 'Well, I love this one too. (:  It really helped me speak a question I never could learn how to ask, and it''s one that always even now reminds me who holds me together.', 48, '2012-12-28 05:07:27'),
(702, 547, ':DDD  I totally upvote/like/recommend this song.  I wanted to recommend it, but I was afraid it would not fit or something.  I am so happy someone else did though.  And Ron, Gravity is awesome, I already have it. ;)', 48, '2012-12-28 05:24:02'),
(703, 535, 'If we wanted to do a mashup, this would be a good song to do one with. I have always loved this song but have also been annoyed by its repetitiveness... Though it does get the message through to the listeners :)', 37, '2012-12-28 05:24:24'),
(704, 545, 'I like that this song goes beyond the message that God loves us (which is what a lot of the suggested songs say) and talks about more of an active role on the part of the singer.', 37, '2012-12-28 05:39:24'),
(705, 556, 'This song says everything in the extended chorus at the end. The singer talks about insecurity and sorrow BUT THEN he was given grace and love, was blind but now can see, because of a hope from above which now gives him hope.', 24, '2012-12-28 05:55:25'),
(706, 557, 'So I thought of this song after church on Christmas Eve. There was someone who shared his testimony about how he grew up in a rough family and started stealing which escalated to worse things and basically he''s been in and out of prison since he was 15. But then he got enrolled in a program where the inmates do an intensive bible study. The whole point of his testimony was that no matter how fall you''ve fallen, God is still calling your name and wants you to come to Him. I think this song perfectly illustrates this perfect forgiveness that God blesses us with.', 24, '2012-12-28 06:01:04'),
(707, 545, 'ditto cahtlin', 24, '2012-12-28 06:06:03'),
(708, 535, 'So this might be a small point, but the first thing I thought of when I listened to this song came from the very beginning, "I am not skilled to understand, What God has willed what God Has planned, I only know at his right hand, Stands one who is my Savior" I feel like a lot of the time people (and especially mit students) are convinced that they have to understand something logically/intuitively to believe something is true. But at the very beginning of this song, the singer clearly states that he''s (and in fact we all are) not skilled to understand the will of God, but the one thing that he''s sure of is his Savior and that he takes Him at his word when He says that He came and died to save us. The singer doesn''t need to fully understand it to believe it.', 24, '2012-12-28 06:13:37'),
(709, 535, 'Another thing that lyrically stands out to me is, "You count it strange so once did I, Before I knew my Savior". I like how the singer addresses the fact that the listener may find the beliefs of the singer strange, but how the singer himself found it strange until he fully came to know God as his Savior of the universe. Important to note that this line is sung twice.', 24, '2012-12-28 06:20:50'),
(710, 547, 'Wow! This song is super dense and, like Ron says, packs a lot in! This can be both a plus and a minus. In my book it''s more of a plus, but I am concerned with using this song (like during spring break for instance where we don''t have programs with lyrics inside of them) and people not understanding everything. So I think the one thing with this song that lyrically bothers me is when he says "And what do I have to deserve this lovin?" but then doesn''t resolve this question well. The closest thing I can see to a resolution is in the next verse when he says that God''s love is unconditional. I''m just afraid that people won''t make that connection.', 24, '2012-12-28 06:30:50'),
(711, 555, 'I <3 <3 <3 Royal Tailor. Like seriously, girl crush. (although I don''t think I''ve heard this song before) I love how this song is (correct me if I''m wrong) from the point of view of someone who''s heard about Christianity and heard that God is mercy and can save and heal. I also like how this song talks about God being there even when nobody else is. (both in the first verse, and i''m assuming in the second verse when the singer talks about the "negativity")And I think we all can relate to the singer saying he''s been lost for so long and he''s not sure what to pray.', 24, '2012-12-28 06:37:36'),
(712, 554, 'So just feasibility speaking, I dunno if we have anyone who can rap this hardcore. Lyrically, I definitely like what Matthew mentioned about the struggles, specifically I liked the part where he talked about feeling fake. I also think the part about the guilt taking over his faith is applicable to a lot of people.', 24, '2012-12-28 06:41:02'),
(713, 553, 'The point of view/who the singer is singing to is slightly altering/jarring to me, so I think that part is negative to me. Because first she''s talking to God, then to herself/the audience?, then to the audience?, then about "us", then the audience again. The "He loves us even though I know you don''t deserve Him" bothered me a little. I think it''s just worded in a way that can sound somewhat finger pointing.', 24, '2012-12-28 06:46:10'),
(714, 552, 'After reading your comment about doing a musical, I am loling at the "love is waiting in the wings". Anyways... This song is interesting in how it points out that satan does have his way in the world, but faith can overpower him. "Fear and desperation have their day, At least until faith steps up to say I believe though God is out of sight, He''s working in the middle of all things, Evil may have its time in the spotlight, But love is waiting in the wings" Musically, I find this song somewhat typical/boring.', 24, '2012-12-28 06:51:16'),
(715, 61, 'While I''m not sure if I agree with everything Geoffrey said in his comment, I do agree with "I don''t think being remembered as a pointer to God is something I want to be. I want to be known, in the present, as a pointer to God, and have the legacy just be God."', 24, '2012-12-28 07:11:56'),
(716, 61, 'While I''m not sure if I agree with everything Geoffrey said in his comment, I do agree with "I don''t think being remembered as a pointer to God is something I want to be. I want to be known, in the present, as a pointer to God, and have the legacy just be God."', 24, '2012-12-28 07:12:13'),
(717, 432, 'I added BU''s arrangement.  This is I think the first time xprod had ever heard it in Jam More Baltimore (you can even see John and Shion in purple sitting in the second row, and Kevin Yue in his brightly colored seafoam green shirt in the third row... lol ', 17, '2012-12-28 23:13:16'),
(718, 432, 'oh nvm just realized girl in purple next to John is me.... lol.  whatever all asians look alike.  ', 17, '2012-12-28 23:34:55'),
(719, 432, 'LOL YES DOROTHY. no but actually, that was the best. remember how we sat in rainbow order? and that girl was a wicked sweet perc!! So, lyrically, I like the message of this song. This song clearly states "What good is it for a man to gain the whole world, yet forfeit his soul? -Mark 8:36" in ways that people can relate to. The second verse is hard for me to understand. It''s kind of jumpy and some parts I just simply don''t get. Feasibility wise, this song has a unique vibe that requires a certain type of rapping that I''m not sure we have in somebody currently. That would probably be a challenge.', 24, '2012-12-29 07:01:41'),
(720, 541, 'Love the sound of this song... I admit though the lyrics are extremely over my head.  I get little chunks here and there, but most of the time I don''t know what in the world they are talking about.   So for me it would definitely need blurbing to know what it''s trying to say.  Cause if I had heard it at a concert I''d give up on the lyrics and just enjoy the prettiness.  ', 35, '2012-12-29 18:42:53'),
(721, 546, 'Agreed... forgiveness is such a powerful testimony-- in this others can see that Jesus is changing us.  ', 35, '2012-12-29 18:54:09'),
(722, 553, 'Well, it was actually worded "WE don''t deserve him"...which at least is including the singer.  As opposed to just YOU.', 35, '2012-12-29 22:28:00'),
(723, 551, 'This is what we are made for.', 35, '2012-12-29 22:31:59'),
(724, 553, 'Weird, I heard "you". Sorry, I take that comment back then!', 24, '2012-12-29 22:32:01'),
(725, 246, 'merrrr this song still sounds too boyfriend-y to me. During the time this song was on the radio, i never once thought it was about god. We''d have to do some lyrics changes for me to feel comfortable with it.', 24, '2012-12-29 22:45:15'),
(726, 455, '"Whatever you''re doing inside of me, it feels like chaos, but somehow there''s peace.  It''s hard to surrender to what I can''t see, but I''m givin in to something heavenly" --love those lyrics', 35, '2012-12-29 22:49:42'),
(727, 551, 'It''s funny, every time I hear the chorus, all I can think about is the Chronicles of Narnia. (if you don''t understand what I''m talking about, listen to http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6nlbiajMrew) This is a very beautiful song about the holiness and glory of God. *thumbs up*', 24, '2012-12-29 23:21:53'),
(728, 455, 'Wonderful, wonderful song. This song has a good balance between 1) the singer talking about how it''s time to reevaluate who he is and if he''s doing everything to follow God and wanting to change for the better and 2) God himself changing the singer. ie; good balance between the singer''s desire to change and God working inside of him at the same time.', 24, '2012-12-29 23:26:53'),
(729, 542, 'Not gonna lie, her singing alone there at the begining was kinda awkward. I was like "uh wait, is this like a reverse karaoke?" Anyway, biblically speaking I think this song is strong. Musically, I found it slightly boring. Arrangement is okay.', 24, '2012-12-29 23:43:38'),
(730, 546, 'The "this is love, this is hate" confuses me. What is that talking about? When I first heard this song I was like "wait, what? they were just talking about people doing bad things and now they''re saying that''s love. oh wait now it''s hate???" The best I could think was that it''s love when we forgive them even though they''re giving us hate. But still, it really confused me. Otherwise, I think it''s a good song about making the choice to forgive and reminding us all that we need to do it even when we don''t want to.', 24, '2012-12-29 23:48:46'),
(731, 541, 'I''m really torn with this song. While it is ABSOLUTELY BEAUTIFUL, the lyrics are hard to grasp. :/', 24, '2012-12-29 23:51:09'),
(732, 556, 'also, because this song overlaps words in the verses, i was thinking it''d be fun to do a duet where they trade off the singing then do a melody/harmony thing in the chorus :)', 24, '2012-12-30 00:12:43'),
(733, 546, 'oh I think it means (or I interpret it as)   love= forgiving, and hate= not forgiving.  That''s the choice we make.  I think sometimes we think that not forgiving is a passive thing,  that _not_ forgiving doesn''t hurt anyone.  But that isn''t true.  not forgiving is allowing hate to fester.  So I think the lyricist is saying "here allow me to tell you the choice you have.  This path is love, this path is hate,  we all have that choice to make"', 17, '2012-12-30 00:33:50'),
(734, 302, 'Arrangement sharing within Christian a cappella groups (from my past experience) generally works out pretty well. Sometimes they ask for something in return. I dunno if they just have quiet guys or if the , but this arrangement sounds kind of girl-heavy. Arrangement aside, this song seems like a strong candidate, especially for the category of "Spring Break Friendly" and "Slower, but still powerful". It''s a great song about the strength, hope, and peace given to us by God and about how He really is everything we need.', 24, '2012-12-30 00:38:12'),
(735, 549, 'I love the version you uploaded Caitlin! It''s very pretty. I think my concern with this song is the repetitiveness of it. Even though it''s musically pretty, it might get boring simply because of how much it repeats.', 24, '2012-12-30 00:46:09'),
(736, 546, 'Oh also for more where this song is coming from, an interview with the lead singer.  http://youtu.be/Pqu2j0IM3lg?t=6m8s\r\n\r\nAnd from another interview "We got a bunch of letters to a radio station, and almost all of them dealt with this idea of struggling with forgiveness. So we wrote a song called ''Losing,'' about how when you forgive people it actually feels like you''re losing. But that''s what we''re called to do, called to absorb more pain than we inflict. But to give grace actually means someone has to die. Spiritually speaking, you have to take that pain in order to get back mercy, you have to absorb the pain of defense."', 17, '2012-12-30 00:47:44'),
(737, 246, 'Lyric changes are something I would definitely see as important, if we do choose this to be in our set.', 38, '2012-12-30 02:13:33'),
(738, 546, 'I don''t know if I''m the only one who feels this... but I feel like it has a  holier-than-thou feel with the "forgive them" part, but I guess that''s mitigated by the second half of the refrain. Still not crazy about this being in the set because of that, though.', 38, '2012-12-30 02:16:31'),
(739, 550, 'I can see how this could be really awesome chorally! I could also see us doing it well as a more pop-y song like the Rebecca St. James version. I don''t resonate too much with the lyrics though. It feels a bit empty, but that could just be me.', 24, '2012-12-30 02:21:34'),
(740, 550, 'ah, such a classic. I feel like the music can be revamped a bit (read: a LOT) in our xprod arrangement if this is chosen. The lyrics are simple and pure, which I think can either be a hit or miss for the audience.', 38, '2012-12-30 02:25:08'),
(741, 551, 'Definitely needs a blurb, especially for an audience of non-Christians. I feel like the word "holy" brings up very different images/thoughts/perceptions for each person. Love the song and DC*B though :]', 38, '2012-12-30 02:30:05'),
(742, 538, 'Agree with Rachel. The emphasis in this song seems to be more on the "you look so much better when you smile" rather than the "God is working so I smile". Also, the ending of the song is "I just want you to be happy... I want you to have joy cause cant nobody take that away from you. I see you.. SMILE!!" Again, feels like the emphasis has been shifted away from God.', 24, '2012-12-30 02:30:57'),
(743, 553, 'The "He loves us even though I know we don''t deserve Him" bothers me... I understand the band''s intentions for the meaning of it and all, but I feel like the point of grace isn''t necessarily about deserving love anyway. I''m not sure if this makes sense, but there''s an implicit focus on "us" instead of God by wording it like this. If we do this song, I would like to have this lyric changed.', 38, '2012-12-30 02:34:31'),
(744, 61, '^ ditto, Shion.', 38, '2012-12-30 02:38:24'),
(745, 552, 'I have problems with this lyric: "Evil may have its time in the spotlight" and the "As darker deeds/ Have their time on center stage" parts. As a believer, I feel like it''s just a matter of perspective. Perception of what is the focus of trying times or trials can definitely be different from what someone is actually going through. (wow... don''t know if that made sense.). Basically I feel like there are much better songs that can take up a spot in the setlist that talk about God all the time vs. choosing this song, which lends time to talking about evil stuff being "center stage" in our life. Our job is to magnify God, not the devil.', 38, '2012-12-30 02:45:01'),
(746, 48, 'I agree with Dorian in that this song really does hit the message that God is with you no matter what, even through the sorrow and the struggles of this world. The bridge is my favorite part where the singer turns to the audience and says "I don''t know where you are, and I don''t know how close you are to giving up, but hear this- God is still there so hold on".', 24, '2012-12-30 02:46:57'),
(747, 554, 'Would like a few lyric changes if we do choose this to be in our set, to emphasize repentance (turning away for good) vs. just being "sorry" for sin. And echo Kristina''s concern about the rap. ', 38, '2012-12-30 02:47:34'),
(748, 554, 'Would like a few lyric changes if we do choose this to be in our set, to emphasize repentance (turning away for good) vs. just being "sorry" for sin. And echo Kristina''s concern about the rap. ', 38, '2012-12-30 02:47:34'),
(749, 537, 'LOVE LOVE LOVE. Love Pentatonix (though our version may be a let down after theirs). And I like the edit to Save the World (Who''s going to save the world tonight? Who''s going to bring you back to life? Don''t you worry child, because I''m going to bring you back to life).', 37, '2012-12-30 02:49:24'),
(750, 48, 'The soloist for this song is going to have to really tell the story to make it believable/ relateable. Other than that, I think it''s a good option.', 38, '2012-12-30 02:51:20'),
(751, 537, 'This would obviously work well for a salvation skit, for a God is in control skit... I think there are a lot of messages in this song, and we could pick which one we wish to highlight for skit purposes through blurbing.', 37, '2012-12-30 02:52:49'),
(752, 537, 'I. LOVE. THIS. SONG. Tis all. :]', 38, '2012-12-30 02:54:22'),
(753, 544, 'So it took me a while to put together that the guy in the second/third verses is the husband from the lady in the first verse. Or it might not be... I''m still not really sure, but I think so. Lyrically this song feels a bit disjunct to me, but I do like the part in the chorus where it says "know that you''re not the only one" because (while this probably isn''t the main point) I think it''s true that most people externally seem to have it all together and it can make you feel weak when you feel like you''ve hit the end of your rope because everybody else looks like they''re managing just fine.', 24, '2012-12-30 02:56:00'),
(754, 555, 'I think this is a really good option for this term because of its relatability to MIT students.', 38, '2012-12-30 02:58:12'),
(755, 535, 'Kristina''s point about understanding the will of God reminded me of these lyrics from Hillsong''s "Tear Down The Walls": "I dont need to see it to believe it/ I dont need to see it to believe it". Perhaps consider a mashup of these two songs? If not with this song, I still think a mashup of "My Savior My God" with another song is a great idea.\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hJNYXzzfjvQ', 38, '2012-12-30 03:05:38'),
(756, 557, 'Has some potential for being part of the storyline for an xprod musical, haha.', 38, '2012-12-30 03:10:48'),
(757, 61, 'I see the concerns Shion and Polly and others have with the focusing on us instead of God. The message I get from this song (while looking for a more Christ-centered message) is that we need to be Christ''s hands and feet and show His love to the world (similar to how I interpreted How Beautiful), and that it doesn''t matter how other people see us, but hopefully they can see Christ in us (which is important and typically isn''t in our set). I think if we did this song, it would need to be blurbed very well because it can easily be interpreted as Polly/Shion did, especially to non-Christians, which is more worrisome. Tricky tricky.', 37, '2012-12-30 03:20:39'),
(758, 557, 'Ouh yes Polly musical (and choreo! the images that are popping into my mind are Alvin soloing and someone pushing him down a bunch of times and him getting up every time it says again).', 37, '2012-12-30 03:24:08'),
(759, 546, 'to Polly- if we do a musical, it could be part of the storyline (people beat up Alvin, gossip about him, he sings this song to ask God to help him forgive them). not too God-central a message, though.', 37, '2012-12-30 03:27:29'),
(760, 302, 'This song sticks out to me as the most powerful one at BIDB (and Boasting, too).', 37, '2012-12-30 03:30:40'),
(761, 481, 'I tend to be afraid of raps for xprod because of our lack of rappers... unless something changes with spring auditions?', 37, '2012-12-30 03:33:11'),
(762, 541, 'I am sitting here with my family so I am only looking at lyrics currently and will listen later (probably not the best way to do this, but I''m mostly only looking at songs I''ve heard before so I know how they go, except for this one) - ANYWAY so, after just looking at the lyrics for this song, I am very confused. I have no clue what it means. Though I''m sure it''s very pretty, remember, we are a ministry that happens to sing...\r\nUnless it was blurbed very well?', 37, '2012-12-30 03:38:38'),
(763, 435, 'I really like this lyric: I will lift my eyes to the Maker Of the mountains I can''t climb. I think it''s good for the "we can''t get through MIT without God''s help"-type skit.', 37, '2012-12-30 04:01:42'),
(764, 246, 'Hmm, I can see that.  I first heard it as a switchfoot song, so I knew it was about God because of the band and because in the movie Mandy Moore is a devout Christian girl playing an angel in a play...haha.  More obvious with that context.', 35, '2012-12-30 17:03:49'),
(765, 546, 'Also, we could even change the first part of the chorus to "Father, forgive me!  I''m stuck on what they''re doing" or something better than that-- "Oh Father, I need to forgive them" instead of "won''t you forgive them"-- focusing on the person needing the grace to forgive, since God has already forgiven the other person, and now it''s up to the speaker to wrestle with this and forgive.  I really think this is an important message tho.  ', 35, '2012-12-30 17:10:52'),
(766, 553, 'I see what you''re saying Polly-- but I think they are emphasizing this simply because the meaning of grace is a gift we don''t deserve... so not deserving it is a really important part, because that shows how great God is, that he doesn''t just love those who deserve it.  That is what makes his love unconditional.', 35, '2012-12-30 17:17:29'),
(767, 438, 'Good song about brokeness. I especially like the line "my brokenness helped me to see, it''s grace I''m standing on". Ditto Dorothy. Also "Kelkel"... haven''t heard that one before!', 24, '2012-12-30 20:47:29'),
(768, 435, 'I think what''s neat about his song is even though in the chorus the singer is saying the "maker of the mountains" and the "calmer of the seas" God is also those things to us, too.', 24, '2012-12-30 21:21:31'),
(769, 548, 'I could see this song being really cool with a cappella. I''m also a big fan of the lyrics, which are very heavy on surrendering where the singer is realizing that he needs to let go of trying to control everything and give it up to God instead.', 24, '2012-12-30 21:25:45'),
(770, 443, 'I could see this as a really cool girl solo! Also I love the lyrics- it''s a really powerful message to say "but really, i''m absolutely nothing in the vast scale of things, not to mention how much i fail, and yet God still loves me and knows me"', 24, '2012-12-30 21:32:01'),
(771, 546, 'lol why are we having a musical where the pitch is beaten up?? poor alvin...', 24, '2012-12-30 21:35:57'),
(772, 557, 'NO. NO BULLYING ALVIN. lolz', 24, '2012-12-30 21:40:52'),
(773, 557, 'So, yes, this song could be used well in a musical, but I think it stands on its own really well and is powerful even without the whole musical aspect.', 24, '2012-12-30 21:42:37'),
(774, 540, 'Boarders on the edge of "boyfriend song", which is fixed by the mention of "Lord" in the bridge. I think Caitlin''s right though when she says it could be a good transition song!', 24, '2012-12-30 21:46:44'),
(775, 52, 'Wow! Super powerful song! I agree with Kelly that this could be really powerful at a shelter or halfway house.', 24, '2012-12-30 22:05:11'),
(776, 23, 'Bouncy!! And feels like we could have some fun choreo! (and I like it! *thumbs up* and I like it *other thumbs up* yeeeaaaahh) Agree that it''s slightly on the  boyfriend/girlfriend side. Also... why does winter have to be portrayed as bad?? :(', 24, '2012-12-30 22:10:59'),
(777, 12, 'Fun song with fun choreo! Agreed- this is a great praise song for gigs where we can sing about Jesus!', 24, '2012-12-30 22:26:56'),
(778, 128, 'Agree that the lyrics could be inaccesible to some people. But the idea of a mixed choral/rocking a cappella sounds musically attractive.', 24, '2012-12-30 22:31:40'),
(779, 414, 'ZOOM ZOOM ZOOM This is a fun song to sing! It''s just that we just did it last year. Granted, that''s not terrible, I just think it should slumber a bit longer. I do agree with the party notes that this song is pretty neat for spring break because it''s pretty obviously christian and yet it''s "spring break friendly".', 24, '2012-12-30 22:48:20'),
(780, 523, 'haha this is another one of those songs where I go "WAIT, THIS IS SUPPOSED TO BE CHRISTIAN??" O.o But anyway, I like how this song is musically different from other songs we''ve done, especially in the melody. The "your love is symphony" reminds me of compose me :)', 24, '2012-12-30 22:51:38'),
(781, 521, 'I agree with what Dorian said. I like how this song recognizes the pain but talks about being lifted up by the love of God', 24, '2012-12-30 23:28:26'),
(782, 524, 'Not really seeing the potential either.', 24, '2012-12-30 23:45:14'),
(783, 15, 'This is a fun arrangement to sing and the lyrics are an important reminder that we all need to stop once and a while and ask God to let us see how He sees.', 24, '2012-12-30 23:46:26'),
(784, 539, 'I''m glad you mentioned that Matthew! Rachel is right, we minister not only to those who don''t know God, but also to believers who need encouragement just as much as we do at times! But I think as much as this song is directed towards supporting people who already believe, this song is also a great opportunity for showing non-believers the characteristics of our loving God.', 24, '2012-12-30 23:55:41'),
(785, 9, 'I loved singing the arrangement for this song. The lyrics are beautiful and tell the gospel in a vivid way.', 24, '2012-12-31 00:07:39'),
(786, 514, 'The melody of the chorus sounds a bit cheesy to me, but I do like the lyrics. And I''m always for a gospel-choir-ey background part!', 24, '2012-12-31 00:47:43'),
(787, 447, 'While I''ve never really liked the melody of the chorus, I do really like our arrangement! The background sounds really fun! Lyrically, I think the first half of the first verse especially is very applicable to MIT students', 24, '2012-12-31 00:55:52'),
(788, 539, 'This song seems to have great potential for an awesome, poignant arrangement, and the words are very powerful :).', 44, '2012-12-31 01:58:04'),
(789, 524, 'There would need to be many lyric changes for this to work, haha.', 38, '2012-12-31 02:34:47'),
(790, 481, 'Mmm I feel this should slumber a bit before we reuse it again.', 38, '2012-12-31 02:47:45'),
(791, 437, 'Blurb would be needed, but I think the subtle Biblical references are pretty cool.', 38, '2012-12-31 02:52:25'),
(792, 437, 'Hmm...I do like the song musically, and the lyrics do make sense for me...but I think for those who don''t really read into the lyrics, this song is extremely vague.  It''d need a very explanatory blurb for sure.', 44, '2012-12-31 03:19:23'),
(793, 52, 'I agree with all the above, and really like this song!  I wonder if it would be possible to have two or three different solos, to differentiate between the stories, or if that would be too corny, or possibly just have a duet come in for the initial choruses.', 44, '2012-12-31 03:29:26'),
(794, 546, 'yeah actually when I first heard this song, I didn''t initially like it because of the Holier than thou vibe that Polly talked about with the "oh father, won''t you forgive them."  Like that was cool when Jesus said it on the cross but us saying it? When Jesus said "Father forgive them"  was that a prayer we could pray?  Or was that Jesus being Jesus in his ability to forgive sins.    However when Stephen the martyr was getting stoned he did pray to God for a similar thing  "Lord, do not hold this sin against them" (Acts 7:59,60).  and also the stanza points out that those who wrong us need forgiveness from God/ we all do (even moreso than from each other.)   but I was really struck by the rest of the song (also a pity that the meatiest part of the song lyrically happens to be the quickest (not like it''s super fast or anything it''s just quicker relatively during the bridge)... so enunciation/ not rushing will be critical for that if this were picked...       How about "Oh father, won''t you help me forgive them?" to replace the first stanza of the chorus?  (use same syllable pattern as the "oh father give me grace to forgive them")  or maybe even "oh father, we need to be forgiven/ ''cause we don''t know what we''ve been doing"', 17, '2012-12-31 04:06:18'),
(795, 530, 'Agree that it would be difficult to arrange because there isn''t much in the background of this song besides a strumming guitar, but at the same time that gives you a bit more creativity liberty to make this song fit the genre mold that you want it to fit, which could be advantageous to us.', 24, '2012-12-31 04:30:40'),
(796, 530, 'I actually really like the simplistic acoustic guitar arrangement in the original, but I understand that doing this a cappella will warrant some more interesting arrangements. ', 38, '2012-12-31 04:30:43'),
(797, 529, 'This would need blurbing and probably isn''t spring break friendly. The lyrics are interesting, though.', 38, '2012-12-31 04:32:18'),
(798, 39, 'Normally what sticks out in songs the most is the chorus, or at least that''s often what gets stuck in people''s heads the easiest. The chorus of this song and the chorus of Meant to Live (There''s gotta be more to life.... We were meant to live for so much more...) seem too similar to me to want to do this song this semester. This song might be better in another year where we aren''t already doing Meant to Live, because I think a big point of this song is that it''s spring break friendly but what''s the use of having this song for spring break if we already have Meant to Live? </musings>', 24, '2012-12-31 04:49:10'),
(799, 39, 'Good point- yes that is the role I thought this song could play well in a set, but if we are going with a different theme/don''t need a song like this, it would not be essential since it is very similar to Meant to Live. The one difference is that Meant to Live seems to be for a more let down person (fumbling his confidence and wondering why the world has passed him by) whereas More to Life might be for a more accomplished person that feels empty, perhaps like some MIT students (I''ve got it all, but I feel so deprived).', 37, '2013-01-01 03:23:57'),
(800, 545, 'I think this does a good job with what Legacy is trying to get across (let my life be the proof The proof of Your love), but this song gets the message across with a larger focus on God and not just the legacy of the "narrator."', 37, '2013-01-01 03:33:06'),
(801, 545, 'Nice connection! Didn''t even see that before', 24, '2013-01-01 03:39:35'),
(802, 539, 'Mashup with He Knows My Name (He knows your name)? :)', 37, '2013-01-01 03:56:30'),
(803, 539, 'or more of an opening/closing hymn-type thing like never change', 37, '2013-01-01 04:07:10'),
(804, 8, 'I like that (despite the Spanish) this song explains the passion very well. I think it does a better job than "Why" because in "Why," the narrative aspect seems to get in the way and complicate things a bit. Also, "Why" has the punch at the end that Jesus suffered and died for you, but Via Dolorosa talks about His love throughout.', 37, '2013-01-01 04:22:52'),
(805, 437, 'I agree with an explanatory blurb. The line "Death is a charade" worries me for non-Christians hearing it and getting confused (with lots of people believing there is no heaven or hell...). We would have to explain that to us, death is a charade because Jesus died in our place and we can have eternal life because we accepted His salvation.', 37, '2013-01-02 01:47:32'),
(806, 539, 'I''m playing with it and it works really well! Mashup!!!', 37, '2013-01-02 01:58:30'),
(807, 23, 'Totally agree with winter being awesome!! haha.  I love snow.  But I can see how for ya know, trees and plants and other growing things, winter is the time when they are nearly dead and not growing and thriving--so that''s a useful metaphor for spiritual non-growth.  ', 35, '2013-01-02 02:02:17'),
(808, 246, 'Actually I was thinking-- as long as (at least in the blurb) we make it crystal clear that the recipient of this song is Jesus, it doesn''t have to be a problem that is sounds boyfriendy.  Someone at our church had her brother (nonbeliever) visiting, and the woman in front of him during worship had her eyes closed and was just saying Jesus'' name over and over.  Afterwards he said "it was like she was in LOVE with him or something..." and his sis said "that''s the point!  We really are in love with our Lord!" and he found that really interesting.  As a church our relationship with Jesus is eerily similar to a romantic one in some ways... and as long as the audience is told  explicitly that God/Jesus is the one we are singing to, that can be ok...', 35, '2013-01-02 02:08:02'),
(809, 552, 'Agreed Polly--I feel the same way.  I think maybe what they were going for was more the idea that God is allowing the devil to run freely around and cause havoc now, but in the end evil will be destroyed--so maybe a more good vs. evil battle sort of focus, instead of in one person''s life.  At least that is what it sounds like to me.  But either way I agree there are better ways to fill the set.', 35, '2013-01-02 02:13:41'),
(810, 549, 'In that case mashing it with something might be better.  (This was one you wanted to mash with something, right Caitlin?)  On the other hand I do like Who am I even more :)', 35, '2013-01-02 02:15:21'),
(811, 481, 'Agreed', 35, '2013-01-02 02:20:29'),
(812, 429, 'The verses are more accessible than several of the other suggested songs, as far as recognizing the references.  :)  (referring to the top comment)', 35, '2013-01-02 02:23:37'),
(813, 218, 'Although I really like this song, I have this feeling of it being overplayed on the radio--almost like following in the footsteps of "I believe i can fly".  Maybe I''m wrong... \r\nI have no idea what it would be combined with, but I feel like I would be more in favor of us singing this as Xprod if it were combined with something or done in a different style to make it sound less overdone.  But really though... I''ve always liked this song.  \r\nThe Selah version (I think the original, and more hymn-sounding) might be a nice choral version to work from.', 35, '2013-01-02 02:27:53'),
(814, 418, 'I agree with Matthew, the lyrics are awesome, but I don''t think the music helps the lyrics sink in...unsure how that would be remedied in the arranged version.', 44, '2013-01-02 04:17:24'),
(815, 233, 'The energy of this song is amazing, and I loved what you did with this song when performing. :D', 48, '2013-01-02 05:21:12'),
(816, 528, 'This. is. amazing.  WAAAHOOO style amazing!', 48, '2013-01-02 05:22:47'),
(817, 48, 'I agree with Polly, but done well it can be a powerful song.', 48, '2013-01-02 09:00:10'),
(818, 534, 'I think it''s a beautiful song that really does get that cry out of who is holding us together in all this strife and pain we go through in each day, and I believe it is relatable to people who don''t know Jesus, because it calls on the struggles we all face, but this time gives an answer.  I really like it.', 48, '2013-01-02 09:06:57'),
(819, 302, 'I just want to mention, I first heard this song in Colombia using it as a background to an excellent skit, which we have performed for probably four years.  If you ever want a short skit to add that is really powerful, I am more than willing to help.  Of course, I don''t if that''s possible in concert, but I still think the song is amazing, and a mini skit like that might be viable for something like spring break maybe?  Here is a link if you have not seen the skit before: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cyheJ480LYA', 48, '2013-01-02 09:28:25'),
(820, 541, 'If I could, I would get the blurb my friend Zachary Mayer wrote for this.  I will actually ask him if I could see it.  Living Water sang this song at Milford Bible Church 10 minutes from where I lived, and I had no idea what the song was either before I went.  But Zachary gave a one minute blurb that if I can remember correctly (and I haven''t read the book, so please forgive me for any error), that this song is drawn from CS Lewis'' book The Great Divorce (on the spot Dorothy), and his description of the High Countries.  There were two people, the people in the High Countries, and the gray people, people that lived in a world where houses grew further and further apart, as the people grew further apart.  Separating the two lands was a giant field that as you walked through it, would cut you to pieces, break you down.  And so the song enters this tale, singing of a person that is leaving the great grey land, to go to the higher countries.  And as they travel to higher and more beautiful ground, it is asking if you will continue on, to fall to pieces for what lies beyond?  The last part of the last verse really captures this when it says, "Out on the green plains, I am but a ghost./Bound up with all that I call mine, still the light grows."  It emphasizes how different we are from Christ, and that as we come home to his land, all that we are falls apart, so that all that remains is all that he has for us, a weight of glory far greater than all our treasure.   The blurb that Zachary gave was sadly not included in the youtube clip, but I do hope to ask him about it.  It really spoke to me, this song, and I did cry, even though I never read the book before or understood the song outside of anything he said.', 48, '2013-01-02 09:57:34'),
(821, 541, 'P.S. I actually was there live both times that Living Water was filmed in these two youtube clips. XD  The song just never really struck me until I heard Zach''s blurb the second time.', 48, '2013-01-02 09:59:10'),
(822, 541, 'If this helps, I found this link about it: http://www.brianghedges.com/2008/04/high-countries.html', 48, '2013-01-02 10:02:30'),
(823, 447, 'I got kind of confused at first, wondering why the lyrics are alternately in the first and second person, but when I read the lyrics, it made a lot more sense.', 49, '2013-01-02 19:13:17'),
(824, 39, 'I like the message, but I get the feeling that it''s only half the story. "There''s more to life", yes, but what is that more? I think this would be a great option for the middle of a setlist, if it''s followed by something that explains what that "more" is. The lyrics are a little repetitive, but they share a good message.', 49, '2013-01-02 19:22:18'),
(825, 445, 'I really like the song musically, as well as Rachel''s arrangement. The lyrics say a lot too - we''re stuck down in the valley, waiting for God to take us and remake us.', 49, '2013-01-02 20:02:28'),
(826, 541, 'I agree with Kristina; I didn''t understand the "pilgrims of the great divorce" reference, and I think the majority of our audience would have trouble too.', 49, '2013-01-02 20:20:33'),
(827, 481, 'I was in band/orchestra for several years, never playing instruments that carried the melody, always a background part, and I was okay with that, because I never played anything perfectly, not enough for a lead part. I like that this song takes the same approach, and I like the way the lyrics convey that the background is the right place for us, with God taking lead. I agree with Rachel that this semester would be too soon, but I definitely want to see this song come back.', 49, '2013-01-02 20:48:25'),
(828, 34, 'I really like this song, and that it tells not just about the actual crucifixion, but everything that it meant to us during and after, too.', 49, '2013-01-02 21:06:53'),
(829, 246, 'I agree that it sounds too boyfriend-ish, but I think a blurb or a few lyric changes would take care of that. I also like that this song is heard outside of Christian music circles.', 49, '2013-01-02 21:21:51'),
(830, 530, 'I like it... refreshingly simple and pretty.  ', 35, '2013-01-03 00:58:04'),
(831, 526, 'I really like this one.  There is potential for it to be really cool, but a good arrangement would be key... There are not many lyrics.  Perhaps something with neat layering of the repeated words... i dunno.', 35, '2013-01-03 01:01:31'),
(832, 302, 'I have seen several churches do this skit too.  I can hardly hear the song without it reminding me of it... ', 35, '2013-01-03 01:05:54'),
(833, 438, 'I totally agree with Rachel about bouncing off the wall, but standing firm in your faith anyway.  I think this is a very powerful song, but you can probably already tell that.', 48, '2013-01-03 01:07:40'),
(834, 541, 'Thanks for the explanation, Matthew!  I feel like to do this song properly we would almost have to have the story from the book be part of the skit or something, otherwise it might be hard to explain in the blurb wihtout taking too long or losing the personal meaning part of the blurb we usually have from soloists.  Could be kind of cool though, to involve that.', 35, '2013-01-03 01:08:18'),
(835, 527, 'I like this one... it has a powerful message that got to me.  I''m not certain how "Christianese" some of these phrases are without explanation (although certainly much more straightforward than many metaphors in other songs), so the blurb would need to explain what it means for the soloist to help with that, I think.  ', 35, '2013-01-03 01:13:43'),
(836, 536, 'Which group is this recording of?  ', 35, '2013-01-03 01:15:17'),
(837, 528, 'my non-MIT brain doesn''t know what to do with this...haha', 35, '2013-01-03 01:17:57'),
(838, 531, 'I really like the part that says "every day I''m getting older, I''m running out of dreams"-- because it shows what happens when you focus too much on going after your dreams.  Facing the end of life or the end of your dreams is devastating if you''re not keeping your eyes on what is eternal.', 35, '2013-01-03 01:20:31'),
(839, 48, 'I agree that the verses are very specific stories and may or may not relate to the audience.  But the bridge is awesome.  I have a hard time with the chorus musically, like I find the melody not so interesting.', 35, '2013-01-03 01:25:49'),
(840, 498, 'I love this song, it speaks so much of how much he loves and has for us, something I feel even so many believers don''t understand, as they struggle with what little they have, not giving it up to God to see what he has.  It is important to remember who is our provider, not only of material things, but of all things, and most of all, of Love.', 48, '2013-01-03 01:32:41');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(841, 52, 'I like it.  So I JUST listened to "Always" before this, and these have super similar structures: 3 stories of different people with different struggles, with a chorus that ties them together.  I think we shouldn''t do both of these songs because of that... They do have different messages though really.  Always is more "God can pull you through!  He will give you strength to survive the storm", while this one is God''s love giving you peace and identity.  ', 35, '2013-01-03 01:35:29'),
(842, 128, 'I personally never found this song convincing or powerful until I heard the story behind the author, because he wrote it after such personal tragedy.  So that personal testimony really made the lyrics powerful for me.  Without it, I had a hard time picturing myself actually being able to do this.  Also agree that blurbing can help people with understanding the lyrics.  Might be weird to change the wording for people that already know it...  I also like how it talks literally about Jesus'' return to earth.  Not something I feel like we''ve done much in our songs.  I like the re-arrangements too.  I already liked the Jars one, but really like the Kutless one too.', 35, '2013-01-03 01:41:50'),
(843, 128, 'Yes Rachel- story behind it- has anyone else heard the Adventures in Odyssey episode about this song? If we end up doing this song, everyone should listen to it :)', 37, '2013-01-03 01:43:05'),
(844, 128, 'The Kutless one I think has more of a feel that reflects the seriousness of the circumstances... but without it being somber.', 35, '2013-01-03 01:43:16'),
(845, 532, 'This song and your comment reminded me of another song, similar to this about learning to trust, Josh Wilson''s "They Just Believe."  That song was a favorite of mine as well.', 48, '2013-01-03 01:44:35'),
(846, 128, 'The story does give this hymn a lot of power, and I think that we can definitely share a background in the blurb, so I think this song is excellent for our setlist. :)', 48, '2013-01-03 02:02:12'),
(847, 532, 'I feel that this song doesn''t say a lot, but what it says is important and well-thought. Additionally, the target audience is both Christians and nonChristians alike. However, musically, I felt this song was somewhat boring standard Christian rock. \r\n\r\nSince it''s not arranged, I''d arrange it either with the purpose of increasing it''s level of musical depth or else make it really easy to learn so that it can become an easy-to-add mainstay for any set.', 19, '2013-01-03 02:03:39'),
(848, 532, 'True', 35, '2013-01-03 02:09:43'),
(849, 529, 'This is very similar to Via Dolorosa, which I think is a more powerful song. In this one, it bothers me that Jesus appears to not understand/remember the point of his sacrifice until God explains it to him/reminds him. Yes, Jesus suffered, but while he was fully human, he was also fully God and I feel like this song diminishes that.', 50, '2013-01-03 02:12:50'),
(850, 128, 'I feel that, given the plethora of XProd Christian rock songs and the lack of XProd hymns, we should consider this song as a candidate for the latter, as opposed to the former. Also, this song is one of my favorite hymns. \r\n\r\nBut this does pose one significant problem: the decided benefit of XProd singing hymns is that we can get away with singing anywhere, regardless of audience, and that our hymns are not subject to the same restrictions as our other songs (we can mention Jesus freely in a hymn). The problem is that given the archaic lyrics and strength of the blurb (we may not be able to blurb at our less-friendly gigs), we risk losing out on a significant portion of the strength of this song. ', 19, '2013-01-03 02:18:33'),
(851, 233, 'This song has tremendous energy, which makes me sad that it''s not Spring Break safe. However, I do feel that there are virtues in plenty to make up for this failing:\r\n1) The sheer energy and joy make it a promising pick for our concert even if we can''t reliably gig for it.\r\n2) The lyrics are actually deceptively deep while being accessible. It''s hard to think of the doxology as a creed to live by, rather than something we sing at church on Sundays. It might be worth slowing down to get the point across.\r\n3) XProd has reasonably few ska songs. This song will be virtually guranteed to add musical variety to any set. ', 19, '2013-01-03 02:24:08'),
(852, 551, 'I think this song is musically amazing. I would say the same for the lyrics except they''re not very friendly to non-Christians. If we can get a good blurb(er?)(ist?)(sperson?) on it, though, I would certainly be in favor of singing this song.\r\n\r\nWe really, really need a good arranger for this though.', 19, '2013-01-03 02:30:22'),
(853, 418, 'I love this song (only meh about our arrangement though). Good lyrics, spring break safe, and energetic music (if not particularly memorable).\r\n\r\nFor future reference, we need to put this next to "perfect people" in a set at some point.', 19, '2013-01-03 02:34:20'),
(854, 48, 'I really love the chorus of this song, but it''s going to be musically difficult because it doesn''t really pick up till the bridge, and even then it''s somewhat slow. So if we have a good soloist and a good arranger, I''d go for it.', 19, '2013-01-03 02:39:10'),
(855, 481, 'I really like the lyrics, and the fact that despite it''s a rap I can still hear them all clearly. They have a certain sort of unpolished charm which I think everyone can appreciate ("Some call it sovereign will, all I know is you the boss"), and this is strengthened by the fact that it''s a good Spring Break song. ', 19, '2013-01-03 02:42:59'),
(856, 9, 'I love this hymn, the lyrics are gorgeous, and manage to sum up our belief very well without just being a retelling of the gospel story.\r\n\r\nHowever, I think the original hymn is much better than this GLAD stuff...', 19, '2013-01-03 02:44:43'),
(857, 481, 'We had a hard time keeping the energy up on this song, so it ended up feeling like it was dragging a lot.  Perc would have to be very careful not to let it drag... as well as the group.', 35, '2013-01-03 02:44:46'),
(858, 9, 'Haha... better start arranging a competing piece then!  ;)', 35, '2013-01-03 02:45:28'),
(859, 534, 'Has good synergy with a transformation setlist (Perfect People, All the Broken Pieces). The lyrics aren''t complex but they make their point well. \r\n\r\nOne thing to note is that originally I was going to say that we could just edit the song slightly to be spring break safe, but in hindsight I think the song would suffer greatly as a result of that.', 19, '2013-01-03 02:51:23'),
(860, 554, 'One problem with this song is that it''s got almost nothing for non-Christians. I feel that only people who already know Jesus will understand why the artist is so worked up about disappointing him. Or, even worse, they might mistake the sin for not attending communion or reading the bible enough. We''d need a blurb.', 19, '2013-01-03 02:54:51'),
(861, 548, 'I really like this song.  I love this song.  It spoke to me as I heard it, especially the lines "Lord, you can have this life/That I have been holding for so long....Let my world crumble."  I think that is something that we as believers need to be reminded of often, because it is so easy to forget.  I needed that today. :)', 48, '2013-01-03 03:06:27'),
(862, 537, 'Several thoughts:\r\n1) I like how this song sounds different from much of the stuff we do. But I''m not sure we can do it. The pentatonix video was actually rather misleading because their video has SO MUCH PROCESSING that it''s hardly recognizable as a cappella. Anything we do is unlikely to sound anything like it.\r\n2) I REALLY don''t like the lyrics, to the point where I was bordering on putting "theological concerns" as my vote. I feel that if XProd is going to sing "who''s going to save the world tonight?" the answer to that has to be unequivocally "God is going to save the world," as opposed to the "we''re going to save the world" which comes a few lines later in the song. Similarly, I feel that if we''re going to say "heaven has a plan for you," we need to make it clear that we are NOT subscribing to some sort of prosperity gospel, and should talk about the things that we have been promised. But even if we fix this and similar lyrical problems in an XProd version, I''m still unsure as to where exactly the substance is coming from. There''s no biblical basis anywhere. \r\n', 19, '2013-01-03 03:07:56'),
(863, 539, 'I really like the lyrics, but the song is SO SLOW... All I keep thinking of is my design professor saying "you have 30 seconds to get their attention"', 19, '2013-01-03 03:11:47'),
(864, 521, 'I love how this song answers the question of suffering with more than just "have faith." It explains that our faith isn''t based in miracles, but in a God who loved us enough that he was willing to die to demonstrate it to us.', 19, '2013-01-03 03:14:45'),
(865, 437, 'I just love how it really puts out that line "You don''t have to feel safe to feel unafraid."  I think this song when given with God''s grace and love, can really sing to God''s power in us, that we are called to be a light in the darkness, a hope and refuge in the storm, and a beacon of his love.  I think it can really bring out the call God has for us, and in that say how much more he desires to do in us and through us.  I really like this song.', 48, '2013-01-03 03:15:28'),
(866, 302, 'Lyrically, I love this song. Musically? Naptime. ', 19, '2013-01-03 03:16:07'),
(867, 557, 'This song feels more like a workout song than a praise song to me. I really feel this song needs to have something about God in it before XProd can sing it.', 19, '2013-01-03 03:19:29'),
(868, 524, 'I feel like unless we made significant lyrics reworks the popularity of this song would actually hurt us. People are so used to this as a love song they''d look at us and go "why is XProd singing a love song?" But if we could get a good lyrics rework, I think it might get good value from the shock/parody value :)', 19, '2013-01-03 03:24:26'),
(869, 549, 'I love the simplicity of the song. It gives the listener time to think about the simple but deep lyrics.', 19, '2013-01-03 03:26:31'),
(870, 556, 'The ending reminds of me the part of the chorus in Lions by Lights where it says "You don''t have to feel safe to feel unafraid."', 50, '2013-01-03 03:27:34'),
(871, 541, 'So I pride myself on lyrical interpretation (perhaps too much), but I had no idea what this song meant before I looked it up. And even after looking it up, I am finding the connection to The Great Divorce tenuous. We would need a hella good blurb to make this one stick, and I''m not sure we could get a non-collegiate audience to understand it at all. ', 19, '2013-01-03 03:31:01'),
(872, 555, 'This song is spring break safe. I think it would make a really good paired song with a good gospel story/outreach song preceding it. Something that talks about God and that invites us to follow him (for example, All the Broken Pieces,).', 19, '2013-01-03 03:35:31'),
(873, 423, 'Wow, this song is direct and in-your-face about who God is and what he wants from you while not coming across too hard and even being spring break friendly. Why isn''t this an XProd classic already?', 19, '2013-01-03 03:40:14'),
(874, 438, 'I like how Natalie Grant threw in the Christ the Solid Rock reference. I feel it brings the whole song together, implying that not only are we trying to stand firm, but that with Christ empowering us, we CAN stand strong on a rock which will never be moved.', 19, '2013-01-03 03:45:52'),
(875, 550, 'And Lord I''ve come to know/The weaknesses I see in me/Will be stripped away/By the power of Your love.\r\nI really think just those lines capture what we try to do in every one of our set lists, that in this time we have come to see how much we need you Jesus, and now that we know we will accept your love, and live with you.  I think this is an excellent closing song.', 48, '2013-01-03 03:46:52'),
(876, 544, 'I like the message of the song, but as a whole I think that anecdote verses weaken the song if you don''t directly relate to any of the stories told.', 19, '2013-01-03 03:47:14'),
(877, 245, 'I think I like how this song can be a de facto mission statement without slapping the audience with the brutal honesty of it. The singer spends enough of his time making fun of himself that you don''t really notice how his example is both challenging and uplifiting.', 19, '2013-01-03 03:51:39'),
(878, 548, 'I feel this is a strong option for any set, with aspects of our failure, God''s mercy, and our redemption all thrown together.', 19, '2013-01-03 03:58:37'),
(879, 527, 'I think this is a beautiful song because it focuses on surrender in the light of his death and mercy, like a surrender focused on giving up our will and accepting his gift of salvation, rather than as a believer learning to continue our surrender as we seek to walk with him and not ourselves.  It is the call of worshipping him that just gives this song such a different light to me, I wouldn''t know how to best explain it.', 48, '2013-01-03 04:00:13'),
(880, 545, 'This song is such a powerful speaker to how empty all His gifts are a part from His love in us.  Without love, we have nothing.  I literally just started rocking out to this song as I heard it, seriously more than any other song I have yet heard on this list.  It is such a powerful speaker to me, the contrast of the power of his love to the emptiness of my pride.  I really feel this is a song that needs to be shared, for it tells the very basis of God''s calling on our lives.', 48, '2013-01-03 04:06:15'),
(881, 8, 'I see this song the same way I see the movie "the passion of the Christ." It''s a great song to hammer through the message "this is what Christ did for you," but it doesn''t actually say anything about what Christ did for you beyond the literal. By itself, my response to this song would be "so what." But when I''m hearing of how Christ was sacrificed to demonstrate God''s love and to save me from my broken life... all I can think about are the stripes on his back.', 19, '2013-01-03 04:06:19'),
(882, 546, 'It''s a great song for Christians, but I don''t really see the appeal towards nonChristians. ', 19, '2013-01-03 04:07:26'),
(883, 167, 'Except the soloist. Just kidding, but I do wish you had uploaded the DJWendel version instead. Seriously though, this song has very compelling lyrics if the blurb(er?)(ist?)(sperson?) can make them understood. That combined with the great musical content makes it a great song for most occasions.', 19, '2013-01-03 04:12:29'),
(884, 527, 'I love this song. It describes surrender perfectly. But I don''t know where it fits into a set/XProd ministry.', 19, '2013-01-03 04:14:42'),
(885, 536, 'This is a recording of XProd.', 19, '2013-01-03 04:15:00'),
(886, 536, 'I don''t like how the song sets up "man''s applause" as the chief contender for God''s love in our heart. But the description of God''s love is stunningly beautiful.', 19, '2013-01-03 04:17:46'),
(887, 526, 'I love this song especially since I hate being still. But despite this, every time I stop and am still and with God I feel better. And I know that when I am still, he is with me.', 19, '2013-01-03 04:20:52'),
(888, 246, 'The first time I heard this song was at the Logs Spring concert, and when I heard it, I was surprised by how the lyrics sounded very much like a song to God, and not to a earthly love interest.  The song''s actually been stuck in my head off and on since then, and I think if it sticks in anyone else''s head as much as it did mine, along with a good blurb, it might make a huge impression.  ', 44, '2013-01-03 04:22:03'),
(889, 542, 'I found this song somewhat meandery. Even though it was very pretty, I started losing focus on it after a while', 19, '2013-01-03 04:22:53'),
(890, 429, 'I love this song. "This is for my glory," indeed. And looking backwards, it''s easy to see God''s faithfulness through troubled times.', 19, '2013-01-03 04:24:54'),
(891, 218, 'I think this is the only song which XProd has scrapped due to musical difficulty during my time in this group. But this is an amazing song nonetheless and I would love it if we could redo the arrangement or even touch it up so that we could keep singing it.', 19, '2013-01-03 04:28:22'),
(892, 52, 'I just love the third story, I always have to sing to it, because it does hit me deeply, it relates to me.  I have never been in a cell, but that cry "Oh Lord, forgive me, I want to go home." is such a deep line, I feel it would resonate in so many people.', 48, '2013-01-03 04:29:48'),
(893, 545, 'I loved this song, both musically and lyrically. I think it needs a good blurb (Romans 5 comes to mind).', 19, '2013-01-03 04:30:51'),
(894, 556, 'I didn''t feel the message of this song except at the end.', 19, '2013-01-03 04:33:56'),
(895, 455, 'I totally agree with Rachel, especially the line "it feels like chaos, but somehow there''s peace."  That is where I am now.', 48, '2013-01-03 04:35:20'),
(896, 537, '"Don''t you worry child, heaven has a plan for you" reminds me of both Jeremiah 29:11 "For I know the plans I have for you," declares the LORD, "plans to prosper you and not to harm you, plans to give you hope and a future." and lots of do not worry messages, such as in Matthew "do not worry about tomorrow.." I agree that lyrically the lyrics to Save the World need to be changed like Kristina said (Who''s going to save the world tonight? Who''s going to bring you back to life? Don''t you worry child, because I''m going to bring you back to life).', 37, '2013-01-03 04:40:30'),
(897, 529, 'I had a lot of trouble with the verse of Jesus asking God why when he was at the cross.  Jesus pleaded with the Lord at the Garden of Gethsemane to take the cup away, but he always ended, not my will but your will be done.  The verse not ending with a line like that at the very least, just leaves me so troubled.  Jesus knew on that day what he bore, and he chose that cross out of love.  This song just makes me feel as if Jesus did not know why he had to bear that cross, as if all the pain he had endured, was not out of his love for us at all, but because he felt he had to.', 48, '2013-01-03 04:50:41'),
(898, 540, 'I am somewhat against this song because while it is true, there is almost no grace in the lyrics.  It would take a heavy lead into this song to make it not push away people who don''t know God or are new in their faith.  It is not easy to accept that our life is worthless a part from him, and then to really detail it to every moment, all that we can do, really pushes people away I feel.  It breaks the connection we are trying to build in their hearts through our ministry.  I feel this is a somewhat dangerous song to use.', 48, '2013-01-03 04:59:53'),
(899, 507, 'I think a mash up is a great idea, because we could never pull this off on our own as well as they do, just for the fact that they are so much younger.', 48, '2013-01-03 05:12:11'),
(900, 537, 'After seeing Kevin''s understanding, I do see what he is talking about.  Most especially the line about us saving the world is really conflicting, and in fact there is little in the song or the lyrics that do really point to God, more so pointing to ourselves saving and loving each other.', 48, '2013-01-03 07:57:08'),
(901, 537, '1- I remember a group at JMIB my freshman year during an arranging workshop saying that they tried to do the song "Saviour" by LIGHTS and it was impossible because of how electronic and processed the song is, and they said a lot to the fact that it couldn''t be done. And then the next semester Peter arranged it and it ended up sounding good. All this to say that doing a song like this isn''t impossible. 2- I would NEVER keep the lyrics "who''s going to save the world tonight? we''re going to save the world tonight" because that''s not Christ pointing. I did, however, like the Pentatonix addition of "Who''s going to save the world tonight? Who''s going to bring you back to life? Don''t you worry child, because I''m going to bring you back to life" to the Don''t You Worry Child lyrics because it felt to me like it brought the idea of God having a plan for our lives even through our struggles more full circle.', 24, '2013-01-03 13:07:22'),
(902, 540, 'Sorry still commenting on this song after the deadline... I like this song because of how provocative it is. I think xprod as a whole is very cautious when choosing songs and tries not to offend people, which is good, but when it compromises the message that we want to send as a ministry group, it is not good. As to the lack of grace Matthew mentioned, it does say "You know the state of my condition And yet you hold me anyway." I think this could be very powerful, especially to non-Christians, who may feel that their lives lack an ultimate purpose, and this song could help them realize what we have that we believe gives our lives a purpose.', 37, '2013-01-03 13:39:34'),
(903, 541, 'Here, I think this should help.  I was able to get in touch with my friend who gave the blurb on this song back in March, and I think it would help so much.\r\n"I think I said something about what the chorus means ("Would you fall to pieces in the High Countries?").  In The Great Divorce, Lewis presents an allegory for both heaven and hell.  The people from the Shadow Countries ("hell"), including the narrator, come via bus to the plains at the base of "the High Countries" (heaven).  They find that everything about the High Countries is so much more real, more solid, than they are, that even the grass of the plain cuts their feet.  The only way to reach the high countries is to agree to be be torn apart by this realness and be made real yourself.  Thus, when the chorus asks "Would you fall to pieces in the High Countries?" it calls us to ask whether we are willing to submit ourselves to the painful process of sanctification."\r\nHe also shared this link with me, which I really think goes into the entire depth of the song and Lewis''s image of the high countries.  It definitely gave me an idea on how to blurb it.\r\nhttp://www.covenanteyes.com/2009/04/20/cs-lewis-on-lust/', 48, '2013-01-03 16:32:25'),
(904, 537, 'The live version of Pentatonix doing that song is good too, btw.', 35, '2013-01-04 03:16:06'),
(905, 167, 'During those leaps of faith when everything falls apart, even then God is still there beside us, and this song highlights just that. It''s lively too, and a good Spring Break song (maybe if we bring it down a half or full step depending on our ranges next year).', 40, '2013-06-04 18:51:49'),
(906, 214, 'I agree with the previous comments on this song. Despite the possible boring nature of it, I feel it is a fantastic wrap-up song if it has a good soloist and blending :) I like how well it sums up the gospel, which is very important for the reason we sing. I see they did it at the 20th anniversary concert...', 37, '2013-06-06 18:44:46'),
(907, 558, 'I remember hearing CMU''s Joyful Noise sing this during Spring Break two years ago, and I remember how great I thought this mashup was (it was really good when they sang for us during that sing-off). A portrayal of God''s desire to love us enough to sacrifice Himself, and our realization and acceptance of God as our one love. ', 40, '2013-06-09 18:13:58'),
(908, 559, 'This song''s words really resonate and, I think, are really applicable. It''s a really pretty slow song!', 47, '2013-06-11 12:35:18'),
(909, 436, 'i can kind of see this being a good musical-kind of song :)', 47, '2013-06-11 14:01:25'),
(910, 397, 'i think this would be really nice for the musical! love how upbeat it is.curious about how the arrangement is like though!', 47, '2013-06-11 14:14:21'),
(911, 563, 'There are two versions posted, one is acoustic and the other one is in a live setting.', 38, '2013-06-12 19:05:15'),
(912, 564, 'I heard a song recently that made me think, "Wow, that would be perfect for our set next semester!" Of course, now I forget what song it was, so I''ve been listening to lots of Christian radio stations trying to find whatever it was. This might have been it (probably not, though, or you''d think I''d know). But I do really like the message of this song- I think the chorus says it pretty well: "I don''t wanna say a word unless it points the world back to You." That''s the reason we sing, right?', 37, '2013-06-12 20:25:24'),
(913, 408, 'As someone who sang our prearranged version of this song during Cross Linked last year... every syllable is different. It was rather difficult to memorize. That being said, it''s also an amazing song. I approve of this.', 40, '2013-06-14 02:37:52'),
(914, 563, 'I love the victory aspect of this song. It really praises God and gives Him glory throughout.  And also it highlights the fact that Jesus is alive and still saves during the bridge, as the climax of the song.', 38, '2013-06-16 09:17:51'),
(915, 562, 'The gospel in a nutshell. I can imagine this to be a "summary song" or something of the sort. Also love the fact that it highlights the Jesus is alive.', 38, '2013-06-16 09:18:46'),
(916, 561, 'I can see this song in a musical. It''s written in a very exposed, inner-thoughts-coming-out kind of way. Perhaps can be for a character that is waiting for God to show up in their life, since one of the motifs of the song is along the lines of "hope is coming for me".', 38, '2013-06-16 09:20:27'),
(917, 75, 'I really like Brooke Fraser''s way of putting first-person thoughts into songs, and I feel that we can incorporate this into a musical because of that reason. In the context of a musical, this can be for a character that has finally come to terms with completely surrendering their lives to God, even if they were struggling with doubt before. Love the way it emphasizes that God makes all things new-- because we are new creations in Christ. Also a pro: pre-arranged. ', 38, '2013-06-16 09:25:33'),
(918, 560, 'This song gives such strong imagery for me, and I think it''s very musically interesting, as well. The central idea is God''s love and how relentless it is (quite obviously, from the title). This fits into the direction of the musical because God''s love is what carries us and is ultimately the reason why we sing. Because of his unrelenting love, we stand here today whole and complete in Him.', 38, '2013-06-16 09:28:48'),
(919, 10, 'The first-person narrative in this song illustrates the character''s thought process of wanting to become something greater, and puts the need for a savior in the foreground. Of course, in the context of a musical, this could mean that this is a song near the beginning of the set finally figuring out that they need something more in this life. \r\n\r\nIf we do this song though, I''d personally rather have xprod take it faster than we have done in the past (according to the video). It gives a different, more energetic feel altogether-- which is more similar to that of the original.', 38, '2013-06-16 09:35:01'),
(920, 34, 'I feel this is a good summary-type song. It details God''s love for us and His death and resurrection. It focuses on the words, which would convey the message. And it''s a very pretty arrangement.', 37, '2013-06-17 13:44:36'),
(921, 424, 'This is a wonderful, happy song about the JOY God gives us! It is very energetic and would not allow our audience to get bored. Plus we already have choreo, though certain parts might need to be changed.', 37, '2013-06-17 13:46:21'),
(922, 467, 'This is a super pretty song. It''s spring break safe. Also I like Levi''s comment above. It could be a good song for someone to sing when they''re realizing all God has been doing in their life. ', 37, '2013-06-17 13:47:36'),
(923, 156, 'This seems to be a good typical conversion song. I like that it''s upbeat... comments on arrangement from people who sang it before?', 37, '2013-06-17 13:48:55'),
(924, 443, 'See my above comment :)', 37, '2013-06-17 13:49:26'),
(925, 408, 'This is a super good song for summarizing the reason we sing. It''s very xprod appropriate. Though I am still confused by the line "I wanna see from your side of the sky."', 37, '2013-06-17 13:50:24'),
(926, 30, 'We could ask if other aca groups have an arrangement we could borrow. We will praise God in every time of our lives, not just when the sun is shining. He is our refuge and our strength. Good for shipwrecks too...', 37, '2013-06-17 13:54:03'),
(927, 565, 'This song sounds like it would be fun to sing (ouh ooo oooh!) and perfectly describes how God will take care of us. And not only that, but it emphasizes how we need to put our trust in Him. It gives the singer/listener/protagonist an active role: "step out on the edge," but also it''s not to late for Him to "come to where you are."', 37, '2013-06-21 12:17:31'),
(928, 567, 'I suggest this song because for one, it fits perfectly with many of our skit ideas, but also because it perfectly hits the desperate cry of believers who are lost in their struggles and fears, which I know is an aspect being considered for the skit, and is so important for believers in similar struggles to hear.', 48, '2013-06-22 00:42:08'),
(929, 564, 'It''s funny you should suggest this song.  One of my non-Christian friends happened upon this song, really liked it, and told me XProd should sing it.', 44, '2013-06-23 10:53:13'),
(930, 568, '(oops! Hadn''t intended to add this to this year''s suggestions - I just meant to add it to the song database)', 26, '2013-06-23 22:08:47'),
(931, 568, '(...not that it''s a bad song, though! I remember the words encouraging me at least once during a hard time. Fun upbeat arrangement, too.)', 26, '2013-06-23 22:15:48'),
(932, 172, 'start 30 seconds in', 52, '2013-06-24 17:32:10'),
(933, 172, 'I love this song because it''s beautiful and it is a song of hope in hard times.', 52, '2013-06-24 17:34:02'),
(934, 464, 'I love this song because it gives a deeper meaning, a reason behind our trials and tribulations. God gives us joy, hope, peace, love, but he also allows pain in our lives, and things don''t always go right. But through it all, we learn to trust him, and give thanks for the rain', 52, '2013-06-24 17:36:44'),
(935, 420, 'I love this song because it puts all the focus on God. Our life revolves around Him because we need Him. He is all that is beautiful and good, and we are nothing without Him.', 52, '2013-06-24 17:39:25'),
(936, 416, 'Not only is this song uplifting and powerful, I love how the lyrics are the words of Jesus. When I was church hopping last year, I went to a service where the pastor challenged the congregation to pray nothing but the Lord''s Prayer for a week. During that week, I realized just how often I pray merely to ask God for things for myself -- but God isn''t here to just bless me and answer my prayer requests. We were saved so we could give glory to the Name of God, and so that His kingdom could come and His will be done on earth, as it is in heaven; we ask for His blessings and forgiveness so that He may be honored through our response of praise (Psalm 67).', 50, '2013-06-25 20:55:13'),
(937, 569, 'I just happened upon this video/song.. It''s not the kind of music I normally listen to, but it was pretty catchy and I particularly like the message of surrendering yourself to Jesus because He is worthy, He died for us, and has the power to hold us up.', 52, '2013-06-26 01:52:41'),
(938, 418, 'I don''t know, the arrangement isn''t bad (except maybe the personal high A for tenor''s "every BREAAAAAK" that I never hit :[ ). For me as well, multiple times during these past two years, listening to this song has broken me in times of brokenness. It''s a great song in our library. ', 40, '2013-06-26 04:01:05'),
(939, 418, 'Also, XProd Concert recording starts 1:10.', 40, '2013-06-26 04:01:45'),
(940, 566, 'As someone that constantly goes through struggles (as many of us do), a lot of the lyrics from the verses resonates with me. But even during moments when I feel abandoned and unsaved by those around me, I know that God is that light; God is that hope that can save me. \r\n\r\nA nice blurb can do wonders with this song, and it''s somewhat Spring Break friendly..', 40, '2013-06-26 04:09:45'),
(941, 36, 'The lyrics of this song are super poignant and i think it is very applicable to daily life. "I could live with many things but...I couldn''t face my life tomorrow without Your hope in my heart". in combination with a good blurb, i think this song can really touch our audience\r\n\r\nby the way, the youtube cover was produced by my good friend''s friend :)', 47, '2013-06-26 04:54:14'),
(942, 566, 'love this song! when tbt came to my high school, this song really encouraged the audience! i also agree with alvin that this is a very spring-break friendly song. simple, repeated lyrics "hope is alive" really makes the message clear', 47, '2013-06-26 15:20:55'),
(943, 172, 'this is definitely spring break friendly and i think it would really work in our 25th anniversary musical/skit. i''d be cool if we can have people take turns singing verses or something? mariah carey/whitney houston style :) if we go in that direction, we can venture toward more gospel-y genre music xD', 47, '2013-06-26 15:30:56'),
(944, 570, 'Appreciate each and every day, because God''s given us all these blessings, His son, and His love. I feel like it covers a lot of things that we aim to convey with our songs. Also, it''s relaxing to listen to :D', 40, '2013-06-28 16:37:55'),
(945, 414, 'I often confine God by thinking of Him in terms of what He does for me: He redeemed me, He loves me, He provides for me, etc. I forget that He is everything -- and still more awesome than I could possibly know.', 50, '2013-06-28 21:35:04'),
(946, 545, '1 John 4:7-21\r\nLove is at the heart of the Gospel, and our lives should be evidence of God''s love for the world. As we like to say, we are not a singing group that happens to minister, but a ministering group that happens to sing. The reason we sing is to point others to God, but "if I sing but don''t have love, I waste my breath with every song."', 50, '2013-06-28 23:46:43'),
(947, 513, 'I especially like the lines\r\n"So in times that are good, in times that are bad\r\nFor any times that I''ve had it all I will be glad.\r\nAnd I will boast in the cross. I''ll boast in my pains.\r\nI will boast in the sunshine, boast in his reign.\r\nWhat''s my life if it''s not praising you?"\r\nbecause our testimonies are filled with both the ups and the downs in our lives, and we should boast in Christ through everything. Should the LORD give or should He take away, we should still say, "blessed is the name of the LORD" simply because of who He is (Job 1:21).', 50, '2013-06-29 00:17:21'),
(948, 571, 'I feel like this song reminds me of the true scope of God, and how our infinite and loving God has a plan for me. He works for us who He loves, and it reminds us how we''re loved by Him.', 40, '2013-06-30 04:50:05'),
(949, 571, 'Also, just listening to this song reminds me of how God literally IS everywhere, in everything I do and all the things that go on in every aspect of my life.', 40, '2013-06-30 06:21:55'),
(950, 453, 'I think this song is a good fit for the "The Reason We Sing" theme, and it''s an xprod classic. Perfect for the anniversary concert :]', 38, '2013-06-30 09:19:47'),
(951, 462, 'Spring-break friendly, and it explains why we have the joy and the purpose in singing for God-- namely, because we were made to love Him and enjoy His presence. Upbeat and cheery. Could be fun to put into a musical.', 38, '2013-06-30 09:21:15'),
(952, 572, 'Under the assumption that we could actually pull it off, I could see a song like this reflecting our energy and joy as God''s people reborn through Christ. The type of song that makes people go, "Wow, I wonder why these kids are so happy and excited singing for this God".', 40, '2013-06-30 17:13:25'),
(953, 433, 'Combined with the XProd''s addition of "Holy is the Lord", this song talks about how grand and incredible our God is, yet still loves us as we are. ', 40, '2013-06-30 20:53:34'),
(954, 573, 'Matthew wanted to suggest this song but cannot due to lack of internet.', 37, '2013-06-30 23:12:34'),
(955, 14, 'I love this song, especially the last stanza ("[...] till He returns or calls me home, here in the power of Christ I stand"), which reminds me of my purpose here as a stranger on this planet until I go home at last.', 50, '2013-07-01 03:53:05'),
(956, 574, 'Although this isn''t a christian song, I felt that it could very well be interpreted as such, because the love mentioned in this song is really describing God''s love, and it''s a nice song(:', 52, '2013-07-01 04:36:17'),
(957, 575, 'I like the message about God having plans for you that are greater than what you could imagine, and that it is best to fully trust and rely on Him.', 52, '2013-07-01 04:40:31'),
(958, 429, 'I love this song because it is uplifting and inspirational as well as beautiful and catchy', 52, '2013-07-01 22:45:31'),
(959, 218, 'I LOVE THIS SONG!!! It is powerful and uplifting, although not exactly gospel oriented.. it would be great for spring break as well (: ', 52, '2013-07-01 22:46:23'),
(960, 248, 'So I went into the library and listened to all of the prearranged songs we have and this one really stuck out to me. I love how it paints a picture of someone choosing (key word!!) to have faith even in times of doubt. This song shows how we as believers struggle with not being able to answer all of our questions about God or life, but even through that, we still choose to say that God is in charge and that He knows what He''s doing. The bridge boldly proclaims verses from Romans 11:33-36.  Also, this song is a super easy/quick learn (check out the MIDI/sheet music) and sounds really cool.', 24, '2013-07-02 02:58:27'),
(961, 574, 'I think the lyrics could fit well for a shipwrecked-themed musical: When the waves are flooding the shore And I can''t find my way home anymore..." ', 37, '2013-07-03 13:25:23'),
(962, 453, 'It''s a good arrangement, easy to learn, and sounds good live!', 37, '2013-07-03 13:34:40'),
(963, 577, 'I like this song because it doesn''t claim that our troubles go away because we focus on God, just that the troubles seem to dim in comparison when we set our sights on Him. ', 17, '2013-07-04 04:12:07'),
(964, 578, 'A song talking about how during troubles, we can run to God and he will calm our heart, even when things are still falling apart. ', 17, '2013-07-04 21:36:44'),
(965, 579, 'I love this song because it clearly expresses that we are nothing, but before God, we can stand redeemed because of the blood of Christ.. I feel that it is a clear proclamation of Christ''s sacrifice and what it means for me.', 52, '2013-07-05 16:47:48'),
(966, 580, 'I love this song because it is a reminder that God is always with me and He is always working.. So stop trying to stay/get in control.. Sometimes the best thing to do is to stand still and let God move (:', 52, '2013-07-05 16:54:23'),
(967, 75, '"do you hear what I hear"- that is all', 17, '2013-07-06 03:20:08'),
(968, 397, 'no idea how our arrangement is, but I just found this arrangement from UC Berkley''s Xtian acappella group and their choreo was pure adorbs. their arr. is a little less full sounding, but take with that what you will. ', 17, '2013-07-06 03:43:14'),
(969, 214, 'I think this song is really beautiful and it really builds after the first chorus!! :D I like that it wonderfully conveys the gospel which I feel is an essential part of a successful xprod concert (: ', 52, '2013-07-11 02:35:39'),
(970, 573, 'I like this song!! It''s very upbeat(: and I think a very wonderful way to end the concert! Especially because it expresses so well how glorious it is to be saved by Christ (:', 52, '2013-07-11 02:50:04'),
(971, 453, 'I like that it starts with "I will seek You with my whole heart in the center of the storm" which goes well with the shipwrecked theme. I feel like this will be perfect for the duet between Christian 1 and Christian 2 :D especially because Christian 2 has doubts because of a lot of hurt in his/her heart.. plus they''re both stuck on an island b/c the cruise sank.. >.> lol ', 52, '2013-07-11 18:08:44'),
(972, 565, 'This is a beautiful song!! And I love that it is about trusting in God and His love, because He will find us even in the hurricane.. and that He is always there for us.. I think it''s perfect for the musical because there is an entire theme about trusting in God.. (:', 52, '2013-07-11 18:13:20'),
(973, 565, 'Normally I would think the lyrics to the verses are kind of stepping on the toes of the listener, and thus would not be a great choice. Since we''re doing a musical, however, I think it can be worked in well with the characters.', 38, '2013-07-11 18:27:17'),
(974, 214, 'Kind of a stylistic thing-- but if we end with this song, it''s a more somber tone than I would personally like. In my opinion, if it''s a song about the gospel, it should be happier sounding so that it''s more memorable and gives a better impression on the audience of the joy and life that comes from the gospel.', 38, '2013-07-11 18:31:28'),
(975, 464, 'I am ambivalent about this song. I feel like it glorifies problems/difficult situations more than it glorifies the Lord. That being said, if it is incorporated well into the musical, other songs may or may not be able to give it better context, especially for non-Christians to understand.', 38, '2013-07-11 18:36:56'),
(976, 581, 'beautiful song.. suggested on the skit outline by matthew.. no clue why he didn''t suggest it on here, but I listened to it and I love it (: I love all the references it makes, and building up to the fact that we are safe in his arms (:', 52, '2013-07-11 18:41:04'),
(977, 397, 'I like how this is a duet. Would lend well to a musical setting. I agree with Kristina though-- the melodies are lacking and I (as a listener) would be very bored if this song didn''t have really, really engaging choreo.', 38, '2013-07-11 18:49:19'),
(978, 580, 'I think this song runs the risk of being misinterpreted, especially for people who are new to Christianity. It gives off the impression of "okay, I''m just going to stand here and not do anything and see if God gives me what I want" type of deal. Also, the song itself is not compellingly interesting to me musically.', 38, '2013-07-11 18:54:31'),
(979, 579, 'Ambiguous: "When he looks at me/ he sees the nail-scarred hands that bought me my liberty". This implies that the nail-scarred hands are of the speaker, not of Jesus. I don''t like the arrangement of the song, and the lyrics are sort of self-condescending. I do like the theme of redemption, though.', 38, '2013-07-11 18:58:20'),
(980, 578, 'I like this song, except for the first two lines: "Wish it could be easy/ Why is life so messy?". Might just be me, but it kinda sounds like someone is up there just complaining. But it all evens out in the end, because I think the choruses are strong and catchy.', 38, '2013-07-11 19:06:37'),
(981, 576, 'Energetic and catchy. My concern is that since it''s sung from God''s perspective, it would be more difficult to incorporate into a musical.', 38, '2013-07-11 19:13:11'),
(982, 577, '^ ditto.', 38, '2013-07-11 19:15:07'),
(983, 574, 'I agree with Caitlin. I don''t the rhythm and the melodies are memorable though. I''m not sure I would want to use up a slot in the setlist with a song like this when we could have a catchier song with a similar theme.', 38, '2013-07-11 19:18:33'),
(984, 521, 'I like the imagery and metaphors in the lyrics. Would lend to interesting choreo for the musical.', 38, '2013-07-11 19:22:33'),
(985, 248, 'From a Christian standpoint, I think this song is okay... I''m more worried about what exactly is implied and what comes to mind for a non-Christian when they hear the line, "only God is God". They might not know about God at all, or maybe they have a negative view of God/the church and would just be really closed off to the message. ', 38, '2013-07-11 19:26:57'),
(986, 429, 'The imagery from this song would work well with our musical''s storyline about being shipwrecked.', 38, '2013-07-11 19:29:12'),
(987, 575, 'There are a lot of biblical references for this song. I don''t know how we could explain it clearly without blurbs (are blurbs even allowed in a musical?). Due to the point of view of the lyrics, I think it would be difficult to incorporate into a musical.', 38, '2013-07-11 19:34:25'),
(988, 558, 'It seems that the lyrics of "even if saving you sends me to heaven" are very unclear.  Is that supposed to refer to Jesus? It''d need a really good blurb and potentially some lyric changes to really reflect the singer as Christ.  But I do like the idea of using mainstream songs, although lyrics can be tricky. ', 44, '2013-07-11 21:58:46'),
(989, 562, 'I love the way this song gets the gospel across in a descriptive, poignant way, without using over-used words.', 44, '2013-07-11 22:25:05'),
(990, 561, 'Raw and real.  Which I think is kinda rare in a not worship song.', 44, '2013-07-11 22:30:34'),
(991, 577, 'I agree with Dorothy/Polly. It is kind of slow but still energetic and catchy. It''s a new way I never thought of to convey Jeremiah 29:11- ""For I know the plans I have for you," declares the Lord, "plans to prosper you and not to harm you, plans to give you a hope and a future."', 37, '2013-07-11 22:44:54'),
(992, 561, 'Pretty lyrics! Raw is a good word. It seems like it would be easy to arrange. Spring break friendly. I like it.', 37, '2013-07-11 22:47:06'),
(993, 424, 'Awesome lyrics. Awesome energy. I''m sold. :D', 44, '2013-07-11 22:51:12'),
(994, 408, 'I think that line might mean that the singer wants to get God''s perspective on things, as if he''s seeing how God''s seeing things from heaven.  Having said that, I''m not the biggest fan of the depth of the chorus lyrics.', 44, '2013-07-11 23:07:39'),
(995, 567, 'I like the message and think it fits in well with the skit idea, but the melody/music is somewhat mundane.  Maybe if arranged, more variance could be added?', 44, '2013-07-11 23:19:23'),
(996, 408, 'Comments from song listening party: Ruth: pretty! Caitlin: don''t understand "I want to see from your side of the sky." Alex: Similar to I Can Only Imagine (get God''s perspective -- see Dorian''s comment above). Alvin & Martin: Stanford has a gorgeous arrangement (but we also have an arrangement) Alex: nice, high energy song.', 50, '2013-07-11 23:47:20'),
(997, 172, 'I feel like this song puts too much emphasis on what "you can achieve when you believe" instead of what God can do.  And I''m not sure a blurb would be able to change that.  Maybe lyric changes?', 44, '2013-07-11 23:52:36'),
(998, 156, 'Although lyrics are good, I kinda got bored by the steadiness of the song, unfortunately.  ', 44, '2013-07-11 23:57:42'),
(999, 418, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Ruth: good for skit (scene about loss & God holding us together) Alvin: choreo didn''t match the song very well. He really likes the song -- hopeful message (God can take our brokenness and make it beautiful), spring break friendly. Caitlin: even though it''s God''s perspective, we can still do it in a musical.', 40, '2013-07-12 00:01:43'),
(1000, 416, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Ruth: fitting for 1st spot in skit (b/c talking about praying, joyful song about God''s love) Caitlin: in the skit, they''re talking about why you pray (it is a prayer). Alex: agree with Ruth -- good opening song. Jacob: tried and true, sounds good, spring break friendly, not in English (so maybe not as effective)', 40, '2013-07-12 00:08:46'),
(1001, 464, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Ruth: I love this song. Martin: I wonder who suggested this song...? Ruth: this song is about loss & how God blesses us through hard times (fits for song #4). The shipwreck may seem like a bad thing, but through it, many people who ended up on the island together are saved. Applicable to everyone''s life. Phoebe: can visualize this as a song in a musical. Alvin: I like this song, but it is very slow. How good the song is depends on the arrangement and the soloist.', 40, '2013-07-12 00:14:54'),
(1002, 513, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Martin: lyrics are great ("I will boast in the sunshine; I will boast in his reign"). Can see Matthew doing the rap & Polly on snare. Phoebe: whoever''s rapping, this needs a natural swag. Caitlin: we need to up our swag level (watch Dartmouth''s version on your own time). Ruth: it would fit in trust in God section of skit. Caitlin: Christian   #1 or #2 in skit. How easy is it to get another group''s arrangement? Jacob: Easy - just ask. Martin: rap songs have proven useful for spring break (but this one might be a little too explicit)', 40, '2013-07-12 00:22:28'),
(1003, 467, 'Audrey Assad blurbs this song at 10:25 of this video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rund7AqaqCU', 3, '2013-07-12 00:25:59'),
(1004, 467, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Pretty! Martin: Nice arrangement. Ruth: Song #5 (God''s work in our lives) and it''s really pretty. Martin: Xprod had a hard time memorizing this one (I don''t think it was due to the arrangement, though)', 40, '2013-07-12 00:29:13'),
(1005, 561, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Phoebe: I can hear Polly singing this. Martin: the perc is awesome. Caitlin: Easy to arrange. Lyrics are pretty, maybe hard to understand at times. Song #2 in skit (God keeps us safe in times of trouble). Alex: really like lyrics (not as cookie-cutter-ish as many others). Good variation between verses. Caitlin: spring break friendly. Ruth: could be a song about loss as well (in terms of skit). Caitlin: upbeat slow song (does it count as slow?)', 40, '2013-07-12 00:36:24');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(1006, 36, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Martin: can we have gospel choir come & guest group for us for this song. Alvin: I can see Phoebe soloing this song (jk). Phoebe: see the cover that is posted above (good electric, slow upbeat song). Good last song (reflection of what they''ve learned after being shipwrecked). Ruth: good first song? Non-Christian #1 asks Christian #2 why he prays.', 40, '2013-07-12 00:46:02'),
(1007, 453, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Ruth: Song #5 (God''s work in our lives); Emmanuel means "God is with us." "I will seek you with my whole heart in the center of the storm" = in the middle of a shipwreck. 2 characters talking in skit = soloist & duet?', 40, '2013-07-12 00:52:57'),
(1008, 414, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Phoebe: same message as Can''t Live a Day (work for the last song message-wise). Alvin: Musically, not a very good closure. Caitlin: musically not very entertaining. Martin: end is nice. Alvin: pretty easy to learn. Dorothy: duet (and third part)', 40, '2013-07-12 01:00:01'),
(1009, 521, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Martin: a lot of the energy is driven by the drums (would be hard to do unless we had a really good arrangement) or solid perc w/ cranked volume. Ruth: Song #4 in skit (God helping us overcome loss). Caitlin: similar to Blessings, but completely different style. Would end up sounding like Meant to Live. Dorothy: could be a really good arrangement. It''s a good/different guy song. Martin: would want to give it to a good arranger.', 40, '2013-07-12 01:05:25'),
(1010, 248, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Ruth: I really like this song. Song #3 in skit (trusting in God). Characters in skit don''t know why they''re stranded, but it''s all part of God''s plan to save them (physically and spiritually). Martin: arrangement is good. Caitlin: wants more safari part (maybe more perc?). Dorothy: casual listener might not get lyrics first time. Alex: slow, but high energy.', 40, '2013-07-12 01:13:12'),
(1011, 214, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Caitlin: could be either really boring or really amazing. Gospel-focused message. Good soloist & blending. Martin: and good intonation for key changes. Ruth: It really builds after the first chorus (reminds me of Before the Throne). Song #6 in skit (thank God for time together & keeping them safe). Martin: I like how it has a story-telling feel ("In the garden long ago" similar to "Once upon a time"). Conveys the sorrow of the Fall, which we tend not to focus on.', 40, '2013-07-12 01:20:42'),
(1012, 156, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Dorothy: at the time, Xprods complained that the arrangement was repetitive, but we''d just learned it the week before the concert... Jacob & Martin: good arrangement. Ruth: Song #7 in skit (last song). Dorothy: when I blurbed this song, I talked about Job. The only thing that matters is God is holy.', 40, '2013-07-12 01:26:22'),
(1013, 436, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Ruth: Song #1 for skit (praying after something bad happened). Prayer and singing are really interrelated. Caitlin: see Jacob''s comment above. Worship songs tend to be a little repetitive. Message is good. Dorothy: not sure it''s any more repetitive.', 50, '2013-07-12 01:33:02'),
(1014, 34, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Dorothy: Good Gospel-oriented song. Martin: Like the lyrics. Music is also really beautiful. Dorothy: nice that it doesn''t have a soloist (it''s different). Dorothy & Jacob: it''s a hymn (sort of spring break friendly). Phoebe: sort of slow. Martin: I like the variation (ex: the verses are different from each other). Jacob: has many different harmonies.', 40, '2013-07-12 01:40:42'),
(1015, 565, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Ruth: I love this song! Dorothy: I can see the a cappella arrangement being cool. Martin: might be hard to arrange a cappella. Alvin: Concern about sop blending on the "Ouh ooo oooh!"s. Caitlin: hurricane works with skit. Ruth: sinking ship. Song #3 in skit (trusting in God). Really upbeat (makes me want to dance).', 40, '2013-07-12 01:48:43'),
(1016, 172, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Dorothy: Good spring break song. Joyful Noise arrangement (see above). Caitlin: see Dorian''s comment (your own strength v. God''s strength). Ruth: Song #2 in skit (God keeps us safe in times of struggles). Martin: not a huge fan of "somehow you will". Dorothy: overall, very encouraging. Martin: Might be too much of a feel-good song without explicitly pointing to Jesus (could work in concert with a blurb, but not so good for spring break) - no strong theological issue, though.', 40, '2013-07-12 01:58:18'),
(1017, 429, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: see Tufts Anchord version. Alvin: I like the song, but am slightly disappointed by the song not explaining who the Voice of Truth is for a non-Christian audience. Seems too much like "do this because we said so." Dorothy: Christianese. It has boat imagery, but not all the songs should have boat imagery.', 40, '2013-07-12 02:06:30'),
(1018, 545, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Martin: Musically, reminded me of The Motions... Dorothy: I like how this song is aimed at Christians from an introspective perspective and challenging them. It''s telling us how to live out our faith. Very appealing message for non-Christians, as well. It''s good to have faith, but not dead faith.', 40, '2013-07-12 02:12:39'),
(1019, 498, 'musical! and at the beginning i thought it was caitlin haha!\r\ni agree that extra thought be put into this arrangement to avoid cheesiness', 47, '2013-07-13 01:21:35'),
(1020, 570, 'I really like this song ! :D I feel like it could fit in multiple places in our skit, and that it has a lot of wonderful content, extensive lyrics and its an overall beautiful song (:', 52, '2013-07-13 17:42:19'),
(1021, 570, 'I like also :]. Finally, a song that brings diversity musically. I like how it talks about how the gospel impacts the singer''s life in tangible ways. If we do this, perhaps we can do a duet between the verses and the chorus. Depends on what the arranger/pitches want, though!', 38, '2013-07-13 18:32:11'),
(1022, 408, '', 50, '2013-07-13 19:01:30'),
(1023, 418, '', 50, '2013-07-13 19:02:09'),
(1024, 416, '', 50, '2013-07-13 19:03:38'),
(1025, 436, 'Ditto with Kevin ^. Fits in with the "The Reason We Sing" theme for the musical.', 38, '2013-07-13 19:03:39'),
(1026, 408, '', 50, '2013-07-13 19:04:28'),
(1027, 408, 'I have the same concern as Shion (see top comment), but I think we might be able to incorporate it into a musical setting without much friction. I don''t find the chorus particularly compelling (except the last line)... I think it might be a little abstract for most people. Would rather not have this song take a space in our setlist when we could have something that''s more concrete and effective, with the same message. I do like the a cappella arrangement though.', 38, '2013-07-13 19:09:10'),
(1028, 156, 'I think the concept of God being holy is really abstract for non-Christians, and probably some Christians too. I personally can''t really see this being well-integrated into the musical because of the chorus. Verses are alright though. Repetitive is also a concern.', 38, '2013-07-13 19:14:06'),
(1029, 36, 'I think this song fits "The Reason We Sing" theme well. I like the lyrics and the arrangement.', 38, '2013-07-13 19:20:01'),
(1030, 513, 'dangggg it was this song where the perc was insane! I don''t have enough swag for that, man. ;] But yeah I agree- brings diversity to the set (rap), catchy, quite Jesus-explicit lyrics (which I think is a good thing in this case). I also like how X.ado took it slow enough that people can understand the rap lyrics.', 38, '2013-07-13 19:25:27'),
(1031, 558, 'Mashup! I like it! And I really like Joyful Noise''s arrangement. I remember this song from spring break and being moved by it, especially during the "my heart beats only for you" part.', 38, '2013-07-13 19:33:34'),
(1032, 571, 'I like this song''s energy and lyrics. I think it can be incorporated well into a musical.', 38, '2013-07-13 19:43:01'),
(1033, 246, 'Pub-ing this song again...I think this could be a great musical song, and would work well as a song of worship and surrender in Scene 5.', 44, '2013-07-13 20:10:30'),
(1034, 564, 'Mmm... its message is good, but I think it puts the focus on words itself, and not on God, for most of the song. IIt sor of beats around the bush for a while before it gets to the chorus that relates to our theme. I would prefer to have a stronger, more explicit song from the beginning in our set.', 38, '2013-07-13 21:35:26'),
(1035, 464, 'I really like the line "What if my greatest disappointments or the aching of this life is the revealing of a greater thirst this world can''t satisfy." James 1:2-4, 12: "Dear brothers and sisters, when troubles come your way, consider it an opportunity for great joy. For you know that when your faith is tested, your endurance has a chance to grow. So let it grow, for when your endurance is fully developed, you will be perfect and complete, needing nothing...God blesses those who patiently endure testing and temptation. Afterward they will receive the crown of life that God has promised to those who love him."', 37, '2013-07-14 04:50:20'),
(1036, 559, 'I think this fits in the "The Reason We Sing" theme. It''s a gospel song, but not explicitly so. The reason we sing is because of His love and His sacrifice for us, because now we''re sons and daughters in Christ. I think this is a really good option for our set.', 38, '2013-07-14 09:00:38'),
(1037, 457, '', 40, '2013-07-14 20:36:37'),
(1038, 582, 'I love this song because it focuses on Jesus Christ who rose from the dead, and is alive and working in our lives today. And that is the reason we sing.. because God is not a God who just sits by and lets things happen however.. he intervenes, he answers prayer, and he is alive.', 52, '2013-12-24 04:28:37'),
(1039, 582, 'I love this song because it focuses on Jesus Christ who rose from the dead, and is alive and working in our lives today. And that is the reason we sing.. because God is not a God who just sits by and lets things happen however.. he intervenes, he answers prayer, and he is alive.', 52, '2013-12-24 04:28:41'),
(1040, 583, 'This song is super catchy, and I feel like the audience would be humming this on their way out ;) I also love this song because it talks about how God still cares about us, and is faithful, even when we can''t see Him, because he gives every trial and temptation for a reason...', 52, '2013-12-24 04:32:43'),
(1041, 219, 'ditto Kevin''s comment (:', 52, '2013-12-24 04:36:56'),
(1042, 420, 'The reason we sing: because Christ is everything (:', 52, '2013-12-24 04:43:07'),
(1043, 416, 'Baba Yetu was one of the first songs that came to mind. It''s a solid and (as Shion mentioned above) nice arrangement. We also have this clapping thing we "borrowed" off of CMU''s Joyful Noise. It''s great. \r\n\r\nOne of the reasons we praise God is because He is our good provider. Not that He has some obligation or anything to do so, but because out of His grace He listens to our prayers, and out of His grace we''re forgiven of our trespasses and given daily bread. He''s a good and graceful God, and a very worthy reason for us to give praise. ', 40, '2013-12-24 05:06:55'),
(1044, 584, 'Yup, another Tim Be Told song :P Anyways, I twiddled with the idea of closing a concert with a song like this. I''m a fan of this song musically, and how it trades off soloists while building up the huge exclamations of Hallelujah and praise. The song essentially calls the broken, the sinner, the weary, to come be set free through Jesus. Especially if the rest of our set were spiritually solid, it could be a cool song to wrap up our messages/end with a bang.\r\n', 40, '2013-12-25 05:09:51'),
(1045, 533, 'i like how the more "a cappella" style that this song has! the lyrics talk about God''s love and spreading God''s love, which could match the "Reason We Sing" theme\r\n\r\nit''s also prearranged!', 47, '2013-12-27 17:52:11'),
(1046, 470, 'i see this as a song of thanks and praise. really pretty and a nice duet solo. i am a little confused about the second verse, though', 47, '2013-12-27 18:17:06'),
(1047, 558, 'love the mashup! The lyrics "We could sing our own but what would it be without you?" seems to match the "Reason we Sing" theme well. these songs are also more "mainstream" so it might appeal to a larger audience', 47, '2013-12-27 18:29:34'),
(1048, 585, 'Very upbeat and catchy which is awesome (: and I love the message: Every sinner saved by grace, has a purpose, has a place; Inside the bigger plan, we might not understand. But if we just keep walking on, we will see the Kingdom come, so don''t lose hope, and let the light of the holy spirit within us shine.. etc ', 52, '2013-12-27 18:49:02'),
(1049, 586, 'This song is very beautiful and I can see this becoming a wonderful a cappella arrangement.. (: This song focuses on the power of faith, believing, dreaming.. etc.. It would be a great spring break song..', 52, '2013-12-27 18:53:56'),
(1050, 587, 'This is a popular secular song that has lyrics that sound oddly christian.. at least chorus wise.. (:', 52, '2013-12-27 19:02:17'),
(1051, 587, 'It''s also catchy', 52, '2013-12-27 19:02:38'),
(1052, 589, 'just an idea- i was thinking the mashup could start with someone praying, asking God to "say something", and then the chorus of Beloved would come in. not sure if it matches this semester''s theme as well, but just wanted to put it out there!', 47, '2013-12-27 19:43:04'),
(1053, 589, 'there could possibly be changes to lyrics, too', 47, '2013-12-27 19:47:23'),
(1054, 397, 'i think there''s a bug on this website? i meant to suggest another song with the same name.... *confused phoebe*', 47, '2013-12-27 20:10:50'),
(1055, 590, 'found this randomly on youtube.. possible secular song that can be viewed from a Christian perspective', 47, '2013-12-27 20:13:11'),
(1056, 583, '(Just a tiny nitpick re. Ruth''s comment: God allows us to be tempted, but doesn''t tempt us himself... James 1:13. =)', 26, '2013-12-29 03:10:10'),
(1057, 590, 'I''ve sung this with Boston Found before, actually... it''s a really fun arrangement! Good memories =) Check out the Youtube video of X.Ado doing it (not sure if it''s their arrangement or ours, but I expect we can get hold of it either way).', 26, '2013-12-29 03:25:51'),
(1058, 582, 'The words in this song are so potent with the weight of His Resurrection.  I really love this song, and believe that it is an excellent song for making the message of His love for us and Christ''s death on the cross very clear and powerful.', 48, '2013-12-30 04:09:57'),
(1059, 591, 'I have never heard a song that better describes the vast expanse of glory and love that we walked away from, with such a simple and well known story.  With a small blurb, I am certain the power in this song would come out clearly for how much we left behind when we left God, and the founded hope that He is bringing us back to it again.', 48, '2013-12-30 04:24:14'),
(1060, 34, '"This is how God showed his love among us: He sent his one and only Son into the world that we might live through him. This is love: not that we loved God, but that he loved us and sent his Son as an atoning sacrifice for our sins.[...] We love because he first loved us." 1 John 4:9-10, 19 We love God because He loved us first, and we boast in Jesus Christ because of His death and resurrection - these are the reasons that we sing. (also, see my comment from last year)', 50, '2013-12-30 16:03:03'),
(1061, 167, 'This is a cool, easy arrangement that is good for spring break and generally happy! Trusting God and having faith is always a good message. And this song contains my favorite quote according to the xprod website!', 37, '2013-12-31 02:11:09'),
(1062, 463, 'I feel that this song is good for the theme because we are able so sing because of God''s love. Like Brad said in 1/3/12 this song addresses how it is so essential to our very existence that God loves us. I also felt that it was from the perspective of when we''ve run out of rope and are turning back to trust fully in God rather than only partially on Him and partially on ourselves. ', 53, '2013-12-31 03:47:13'),
(1063, 443, 'This song really addresses how great God''s grace to us is despite us being so undeserving. It both speaks to the glory of God and to how He has redeemed us. ', 53, '2013-12-31 04:46:31'),
(1064, 592, 'This is borderline cheesy, but it''s basically the footprints in the sand story in song form. It''s always an encouraging song to hear :]', 38, '2013-12-31 07:52:00'),
(1065, 593, 'This one might be a bit of a stretch... but I perceived the lyrics to this song as being sung from God''s perspective or from a Christian friend''s perspective to either a Christian or a non-Christian, suggesting that we all need a savior. The message is similar to Saviour by Lights, but in a different point of view.', 38, '2013-12-31 07:54:44'),
(1066, 594, 'I love the lyrics to this song, especially because of its focus on Jesus and joy. The song is a continual reminder that our identity is in Christ alone.', 38, '2013-12-31 08:00:48'),
(1067, 595, 'This would make for a really interesting a cappella arrangement, haha. I love how this song comes from a posture of adoration of God''s grandeur and His creation. It talks about the characteristics of God and His awesomeness in a way that keeps the focus on Him.', 38, '2013-12-31 08:04:45'),
(1068, 596, 'I love the simplicity of this song, and the theme of how God makes beauty from ashes. Though it is simple musically, I feel that we can create an a cappella arrangement that is interesting-- or it can be used as part of a mashup if we find another song that goes together with it.', 38, '2013-12-31 08:08:11'),
(1069, 597, 'I like how this song portrays a cray of keeping an outward perspective fixed on God while being in the valley (i.e., the not-so-pleasant times of life). On a musical note, I think this would be a really fun song to do because xprod doesn''t tend to do folk-y songs that much, and there''s lots of room for creativity for the arranger when translating this song to a cappella. It''s also a bonus that The Civil Wars are widely known as a folk duo in the "secular" realm.', 38, '2013-12-31 08:13:44'),
(1070, 598, 'This song centers on Jesus'' crucifixion, and how Jesus is our hope because of the promises of His word. Despite its simplicity, it has the potential to be a powerful song because it speaks the reality of Jesus'' sacrifice for us and how it feels to wait on the Lord. ', 38, '2013-12-31 08:19:21'),
(1071, 598, 'I posted the live performance video version because I feel that it shows the intensity of the emotion behind the song more effectively. I would also like to add that the "it is well" part near 2:50 would be a cool way to mash it up with the "It Is Well With My Soul" hymn or something like that. Just an idea :]', 38, '2013-12-31 08:23:36'),
(1072, 599, 'Super strong lyrics w/ gospel presentation and the Lord''s Prayer.  Delivered with conviction could be really powerful.', 44, '2013-12-31 19:03:21'),
(1073, 600, 'I was scouting around the top 40 list for songs that might have a redemptive message, and I came across this one.  These lyrics beautifully share Christ''s love for us, and I think this would be an amazing addition to our set, not only that it might have a wide recognizability factor, but that God is a God of loveout of this it''s possible to share Christ''s sacrifice, shed out of his unconditional love. "All your insecurities, all your dirty laundry, never made me blink one time"\r\nI also believe that the world needs to hear that we as Christians aim to mirror that unconditional love  to them.\r\nThis could be an thought-provoking song for spring break as well.', 44, '2013-12-31 19:16:16'),
(1074, 600, 'Never thought I''d be okay with a Katy Perry song in an XProd pool before o_o. I like it. After quickly listening to it, I think an arrangement could be pretty straightforward, upbeat and fun to sing, and this song could be a nice pick, depending on what messages the rest of the set focuses on.\r\n\r\nCool blurb highly recommended.', 40, '2013-12-31 23:53:13'),
(1075, 601, 'This is such a powerful song, that really just pours out so much of our raw need for Christ.  It has brought me basically to tears many times, and it can even be used as a Spring Break song!', 48, '2014-01-01 05:19:19'),
(1076, 415, 'this could also be a stretch but...what if we mashed this up with Sara Bareilles'' Brave? the lyrics of both seem to fit the Reason We Sing theme (being so excited to share His love and to praise Him..to be "brave" in this world)', 47, '2014-01-01 20:29:27'),
(1077, 559, '*resuggesting* i agree with polly! and see my comment above', 47, '2014-01-01 20:46:58'),
(1078, 603, 'So I really like this song because it talks about the conflict between faith and rationality and that even though we constantly come up with things to explain away God, there are still things that we feel and experience that we can''t understand. I think it''s a good song for an MIT audience and it''s spring break friendly.', 57, '2014-01-02 20:38:34'),
(1079, 604, 'Yay, more Brooke Fraser! So you can read about the story of Hosea''s wife in Hosea chapters 1 through 3. Israel is basically compared to a prostitute and God shows how he continues to love Israel even though they keep turning away from Him and running towards other loves/idols. \r\n\r\nAnyway, I think this song is really powerful and even without the Hosea''s wife context it still hits on the question of whether or not there is any purpose to our lives.', 57, '2014-01-02 21:09:12'),
(1080, 605, 'I think this song is really powerful. I don''t know how it would turn out in an arrangement though. We would probably have to shorten it a little since it''s kind of long.', 57, '2014-01-02 21:16:47'),
(1081, 606, 'I haven''t thought about this song in a while, but it popped into my head last night (when I was trying to think of possible mashup songs for One Direction''s Story of My Life lol). Then tonight, I was cleaning the basement and found the Leeland CD with this song on it. It''s a little on the repetitive and slow side but might be good for a mashup. It summarizes the reason we sing well.', 37, '2014-01-03 01:48:12'),
(1082, 600, 'yesyesyes! The only part that doesn''t really work is the bridge ("Will you do the same for me?" unless someone has a different interpretation than me...) which we could easily get rid of. ', 37, '2014-01-03 01:51:18'),
(1083, 607, 'This connects because it speaks about how God rescued us like a super hero and how He did so much other cool stuff. This compels us to sing and praise Him and His mighty deeds. \r\n\r\nPersonally, I like that it is upbeat. Also, though the lyrics are explicit it doesn''t sound like it. ', 53, '2014-01-03 02:12:09'),
(1084, 433, 'Connects because: This is all about how amazing and glorious God is, and that is really why we sing: to worship our indescribably awesome God. \r\n\r\nI really like the lyrics because they talk to this fundamental aspect of our relationship with God. We worship God for all His majesty and awesomeness. For Christians in the audience and maybe nonChristians too it brings into perspective how everything should be about God, not us. also, dido Alvin. ', 53, '2014-01-03 04:17:14'),
(1085, 608, 'Connects because: It addresses how God fulfils and completes us through Christ. On a day to day basis, this fulfilment makes us worshipful of the God who brought us out of nothingness to be given meaning.\r\n\r\nI feel like this can be really poignant for so many college students who pursue success and other things in order to find meaning and fulfilment but so often find themselves devoid of it. I guess that it is because as prodigal children we often come back to God when our situations are dire and we fall short. ', 53, '2014-01-03 04:51:32'),
(1086, 609, 'Connects because: Apart from the obviously perfect choruses this is all about how we worship God because of His awesomeness and decision to choose to love us.\r\n\r\nI like this because it gets at the idea of our purpose in this life is to experience the magnificence and love of God. ', 53, '2014-01-03 05:06:36'),
(1087, 610, 'Connects because: We rejoice at the sight of all things indicative of Christ''s presence in our lives and the promise we have in Him. \r\n\r\nThough this song was inspired by the Chronicles of Narnia, it is really true in the life of a Christian. In the world around us we can see the workmanship of God and the assurance of His promise. Also, it is eye opening to those who think of God as either hands off or a tyrant. This shows how we long for God who found and raised us out of darkness. ', 53, '2014-01-03 05:41:08'),
(1088, 205, 'Connects because: Granted it says testify to love not God (making it unexplicit - "give thanks to God" is not poignant), but 1 John 4:7 "for love comes from God. Everyone who loves has been born of God and knows God." This is not to be misquoted, but all these acts of love in the world are testaments to the fact that we are created by a loving God and created to know and be like Him. \r\n\r\nReally, "testify to love" is at the core or the Christian ministry. We cannot testify except because we have the love of God which is all fulfilling and overflowing out of us as a testimony. (1 Corinthians 14 too). So, in all we do, we cannot help but testify to the love of God and this is the testimony that has meaning at all.\r\n', 53, '2014-01-03 06:08:40'),
(1089, 469, 'Connects Because; We sing for joy because we know that we have security in a God who is strong enough to save us from anything. In conjunction with the fact that He loves us, we have nothing to fear even if life is rough.\r\n\r\nThis song is very clear that it is not the salvation gospel. It doesn''t say that God will save you from every trial, but it does say that God can save you from any trial and that He is there to catch us even when He lets things go wrong. ', 53, '2014-01-03 06:23:41'),
(1090, 611, 'This song expresses the desperate desire we have for Christ. ', 53, '2014-01-03 06:44:10'),
(1091, 481, 'Ahhhhhh I love the lyrics.. couldn''t resist re-suggesting it even though I know xprod lacks rappers.. XD', 52, '2014-01-03 18:57:12'),
(1092, 227, 'Echoing the comments of past xprods, this is a great arrangement. I like the metaphors in this song as well as the Bible references. It shows what great lengths God went through to save us and how much He loves us.', 37, '2014-01-03 23:38:10'),
(1093, 506, 'I think this is a really good song to explain the reason we sing. Clearly, we as xprod are not in the position where we are afraid to say the name Jesus, but this definitely applies to me outside of music. It''s much more difficult for me to have a conversation with someone about my faith than to sing about God in xprod. Leading by example is good, but God calls us to do more than that. And singing in xprod is one way we can do more!\r\nIn response to Rachel''s comment, I believe only the first two lines are from God''s perspective, while the rest of the song is a person. In my opinion, "Jesus, why''s your name offensive" means why are we (some of us) afraid to speak the name of Jesus? When He is the reason for our salvation and when "all of the hope of this world''s in [His] name," meaning that only accepting Jesus can save us? I interpret the line "if I avoid to speak Your name Tell me would You do the same to me" as if I abandon (talking about) You, will You also abandon me?', 37, '2014-01-03 23:56:04'),
(1094, 613, 'Funny, this was actually a song on my mind that I had considered suggesting too (A few weeks before Mighty Sound came out actually). The gist of the song (you can watch it in the video too), is that our faith is not a culture of exclusivity, but rather, founded from the fact that our loving God came to save everyone, whether you''re an outcast or from different backgrounds. One concern I had was that the directed audience might be pretty narrow, but upon looking at it a few more times, I can see it reaching out to a wide range of audience, both Christian and non-Christians.\r\n\r\nMusically, it''s this "epic, anthemic" song. Especially the part that has us singing, "You will be like Jericho, and I will sing with a mighty blow till the walls come down". As if we''re trying to blow the walls down. It''s super great.', 40, '2014-01-04 03:43:29'),
(1095, 615, 'Not the most explicit song ever, but I think this paints a beautiful picture of our relationship with God especially "I am the moon with no light of my ownI can''t be a light unless I turn my face to you".  This it be a good spring break option.  Although it''s not super musically complex, I think the song has a sweet simplicity.', 44, '2014-01-04 03:47:43'),
(1096, 590, 'Yesss I was just about to suggest this again because I thought it was the FFH version.  Love this version!', 44, '2014-01-04 03:51:42'),
(1097, 564, 'I know that it doesn''t start out strong with the message, but as Caitlin said above, it really is the reason we sing...', 55, '2014-01-04 03:53:04'),
(1098, 617, '"Your love makes me sing" is very literal to "the reason we sing".  I don''t know if it is too much of a direct correlation, but it is straightforward.', 55, '2014-01-04 04:00:45'),
(1099, 494, 'I think these songs together really capture one of the aspects of God''s nature that inspires me to worship. Go''d persistence and his constant love and availability. It''s times when we''re broken that God''s grace and love become so much more precious to us, and I think these songs capture the fact that God''s love is greater than our imperfections and goes so much farther than we sometimes even want to admit, because it means looking at our own failures in the eye for what they are, nails in the hands and feet of a God who endured that pain for us. It''s when we see our own sinfulness juxtapositioned with God''s infinite grace that our hearts rejoice in his holiness.  ', 56, '2014-01-04 04:03:43'),
(1100, 618, 'This song is super powerful, I''m not 100% sure how well it''d transfer to a cappella.', 44, '2014-01-04 04:08:45'),
(1101, 619, 'I think this song captures that feeling you get when you get a little glimpse of where you''d be if God hadn''t saved your butt all those times, or when you look around and realize that you go to MIT, you live in America, or [insert huge blessing here] and you just feel this great joy and you know that you''d be so so screwed if God wasn''t always saving your butt. ', 56, '2014-01-04 04:10:09'),
(1102, 620, 'I wanted to suggest this song since the theme is the reason we sing, and I thought this song captures that by talking about who we as the Church are and what we seek to do, which is fundamentally the reason we sing. To lead the world to Jesus. :)', 56, '2014-01-04 04:18:01'),
(1103, 621, 'Kinda a short song, but musically really interesting. I love the message of the hope of heaven.', 44, '2014-01-04 04:22:00'),
(1104, 622, 'I think this song captures a person''s individual story of their reason for following Christ. I like the way the singer captures the way they can see God having always been in their life. I especially like the line \r\n"\r\nI hear these people asking me\r\nHow do I know what I believe\r\nWell, I''m not the same me, and that''s all the proof I need"\r\n\r\nbecause that goes beyond the reason we sing and addresses the question of why we follow Christ in the first place. \r\n\r\nAlso as a side note I''m embarrassed about the amount of pop music I listen to. Sorry guys.', 56, '2014-01-04 04:26:10'),
(1105, 625, 'I think the singer of this song captures the truth that God > the world and that God is the only one who can truly satisfy us. \r\n"All the things I thought would fill me up inside\r\nLeft me empty here and now I know why"\r\n\r\nI''ve been deeply moved my this song, but just looking at it lyrically I have some concerns that it''s not clear enough that the singer is talking about God. It kind of verges on the Jesus is my boyfriend side of things. \r\n\r\n', 56, '2014-01-04 04:34:07'),
(1106, 469, 'I''m Nursen Ogutveren and I approve this message! I love how much this song captures God''s power and his abundant, crazy, irrational, prodigal love for us, which are two reasons we praise God. Even better, this song doesn''t overlook the trials we face or our iniquities, it''s not a purely happy/sappy/corny song. It says crap this world is really hard but ZOMAGAH God is capable of overcoming ANYTHING, so call on Him! Praise Him! It''s the smart thing to do, duh. :P', 56, '2014-01-04 04:38:19'),
(1107, 418, 'I actually think this song is a really great one for the theme of the reason we sing. I don''t know if I''m just weird, but a lot of the times when I''m feeling really hurt, one way I talk to God about it is listening or singing songs that reflect that and praying that He would bring me healing. I think that''s a reason that''s not typically thought of when we talk about the reasons we sing. But David did this a ton in the Psalms, we don''t only have to sing songs of praise when things are going well, we can also cry out to God for faith and healing in the troubled times, and, like the person who sings this is encouraging us, God also encourages this. ;)', 56, '2014-01-04 04:47:08'),
(1108, 605, 'It would be hard to get an arrangement to sound similar to this song, but I think that is the case with  many songs of this style. I really like all the lyrics, but it is slow to get through all of them. I wouldn''t want to cut any out either though...but it does repeat the chorus many times.', 37, '2014-01-04 04:55:31'),
(1109, 363, 'I love the contrast between us and God in the lyrics, and it could make a cool arrangement.', 44, '2014-01-04 04:57:12'),
(1110, 433, 'I really like this song. It captures how amazing and awesome God is. When I look at the sky, I am in awe at how God created everything and how He still loves me individually. In addition to saying how great God is, it also reminds me that my little problems aren''t really that significant. I like all the descriptions of nature and seeing the glory in God''s creation.', 37, '2014-01-04 05:01:59'),
(1111, 481, 'Haha I agree with the lack of rappers... the lyrics are really nice but they lose the intensity of the message if we don''t have a legit rapper. :)', 37, '2014-01-04 05:03:37'),
(1112, 36, 'If we did this song, I would really like our arrangement to end in everyone singing the chorus and clapping :) or somewhere towards the end', 37, '2014-01-04 05:07:37'),
(1113, 205, 'Brian, that is a perfect, to the point blurb for this song! With that blurb it is great, but without that background, it seems kind of wishywashy and overly repetitive. Does anyone have a recording of our arrangement?', 37, '2014-01-04 05:13:33'),
(1114, 467, 'I really like this song! It''s super pretty, as I also said above. And it is also a Brad arrangement.', 37, '2014-01-04 05:25:26'),
(1115, 467, 'I loved singing this song sophomore year. Brad created such a great arrangement that is both fun to sing and hear. This song is sung by a person who willing admits that she has no profound understanding/observation of God, but even so she can see God working. It highlights the ability of God to show Himself and display his beauty and grace in even the smallest things. ', 24, '2014-01-04 05:25:30'),
(1116, 631, 'This song connects all of our weaker moments with the identity we have in God. When we are ashamed of ourselves, when we feel like we can never amount to being "enough" for God, we are reminded that we are the forgiven sons and daughters of the heavenly King who died to save us, and that nothing can make us more deserving of that because it is simply our identity in Christ. Also a plus... it''s upbeat and spring break friendly!', 24, '2014-01-04 05:47:44'),
(1117, 632, '(interesting interpretation to follow)I love this line in the song: "She knows all the answers And she''s rehearsed all the lines And so she''ll try to do better But then she''s too weak to try". I think this line can resonate with a lot of MIT students. Often we can get into a cycle of feeling like we have all of the answers, but when we don''t succeed, we promise ourselves that next time we''ll work harder... only by then we''re so burnt out that we can''t work any harder. I think that we often forget how challenging and damaging academic idolatry can be, including loss of friends and self-worth. This song gets at that (but is also general enough to fit other sins) and then turns it back to how we''re remade in Christ. **to note, we can probably borrow UC''s arrangement**', 24, '2014-01-04 07:04:40'),
(1118, 613, 'I think this song can add some great emphasis to our "Reason We Sing" theme. It points to how we so readily turn away from keeping God as the center of our attention. While HE should be where we focus all of our praise, so much of our thoughts goes to our OWN praises and to feeding our pride. I love how this song, after calling us out on our self-idolatry, we see the perfect picture of love, represented by God.', 24, '2014-01-04 08:28:34'),
(1119, 613, 'If you''re listening to the youtube video, start at 5:48. If you''re interested in hearing the studio version, go to http://timbetold.bandcamp.com/track/temple-of-stone. ', 24, '2014-01-04 08:30:14'),
(1120, 613, 'I also uploaded the studio version mp3 up there. Just hit play.', 40, '2014-01-04 08:47:43'),
(1121, 633, 'No matter what has happened, what is happening, or what will come to pass, we will continue to sing the praises of the Lord. "For all Your goodness I will keep on singing, Ten thousand reasons for my heart to find"', 24, '2014-01-04 08:50:31'),
(1122, 558, 'One thing after reflecting for a while on mashups was that I would feel weird using another group''s arrangement of one. Though groups DO borrow arrangements, personally it''d feel weird for me if another group asked us to borrow the Child mashup, for example. I do really like their arrangement though. ', 40, '2014-01-04 23:53:28'),
(1123, 604, 'Marked as pre-arranged since we could probably borrow Stanford Testimony''s arrangement.', 26, '2014-01-06 20:25:14'),
(1124, 615, 'Marked as pre-arranged since we could probably ask Stanford or Yale for their arrangements.', 26, '2014-01-06 20:28:44'),
(1125, 615, 'I love this song!!! Especially the chorus that Dorian pointed out... sooo cool and so beautiful! (I actually bought one of Stanford Testimony''s CDs largely because it had this on it; their arrangement is really nice, and streamable for free on Spotify.)', 26, '2014-01-06 20:33:07'),
(1126, 34, 'YESSS I''m so glad Meiji suggested this (I was thinking of it and then missed the deadline).', 26, '2014-01-06 20:35:23'),
(1127, 408, 'It felt repetitive and not just at the parts which are supposed to. I kind''ve zoned it. ', 53, '2014-01-07 02:06:06'),
(1128, 585, 'I like the song, but I''m not sure how it would sound to a nonChristian. It sounds as if it is meant more to encourage Christians.', 53, '2014-01-07 02:12:59'),
(1129, 589, 'This is a really cool idea. I never thought about how Say Something could work as a prayer to God. And Beloved makes for a really beautiful response to the doubt in Say Something. Though I''m not sure it really addresses the reason we sing. ', 53, '2014-01-07 02:20:17'),
(1130, 591, 'Love the song Matthew! (Chose the artist because the name similarity, right? jk) Only thing is that I don''t know how well it relates to the reason we sing. ', 53, '2014-01-07 02:36:41'),
(1131, 416, 'I really like this song, but I am not sure how the audience will equate this to why we sing. Unless we have the full translation of the Lord''s prayer it will be impossible to explain, and even if we do, I feel that it is a bit of a stretch. ', 53, '2014-01-07 03:11:45'),
(1132, 600, 'I can see this as a song from God to us. (which makes it strange to have a female soloist ?) As for the bridge: "acceptance is the key" sounds a little too much to me like being in acceptance of this world ( = bad/unChristian). I agree with Caitlin that "Will you do the same for me?" feels a little weird given our context.\r\n', 53, '2014-01-07 14:53:51'),
(1133, 600, 'Brian: I think "acceptance is the key" could be viewed as accepting Christ as your savior if you were to interpret the song as a Christian, God-talking song.', 37, '2014-01-07 19:31:51'),
(1134, 600, 'I agree with Caitlin about the "will you do the same for me", otherwise I really like this song! ', 57, '2014-01-07 20:08:59'),
(1135, 416, 'I like this song, it is definitely different than anything else in our potential set in both language and genre.  To address concerns with the different language, I think a well written and well presented blurb would clear up most language issues along with translation.  Essentially, this song is prayer, one of the many reasons we praise God, and there is no better way to praise God then through the Lord''s prayer, the way he himself taught us to pray.  I would guess that a fairly significant portion of potential audiences have heard of the Lord''s prayer, and this song is a unique way of praising him through what he taught us.  Perhaps, with the Lord''s prayer in such a different format, members of the audience may see the prayer, and by extension, God himself in a different, and happier way.  Our happiness, like all things, comes from God, and he is the reason we sing.', 55, '2014-01-08 07:05:56'),
(1136, 612, 'Slightly different genre then what xprod generally seems to sing; a lot of freedom as far as a solo/duet goes.  As for the message of the song, it focuses on saying Thank You to God for his love, for everything that he has given us- it is a part of our praise to Him and part of why we sing.', 55, '2014-01-08 07:10:27'),
(1137, 587, 'I like the lyrics to the chorus, and yes it is catchy... for the rap parts is this a piece of which the lyrics could either be changed or rewritten?  Also, the chorus of this piece would be good in a mash-up (unfortunately, I don''t know what song to do a mash-up with).', 55, '2014-01-08 07:24:17'),
(1138, 618, 'Arranging in a cappella:\r\nI think that we could actually break this song up by individual instruments rather than try to separate it chorally. It might make it even feel more like a cappella:\r\n\r\nIt would be cool if the sounds and rhythms were fused into all the parts. eg Altos/sops. could have the half-note syllable "shing" for the sleigh bells and then get acoustic guitar. Basses could get the toms and bass drum lines with "dum"s with the same progression inside measures and maybe with a general chord progression. Then they could continue to sing the bass guitar line etc.. You would still need a perc from 1:00 on but maybe only to sing snare and hi-hat. Or something like that.       ', 53, '2014-01-08 16:12:40'),
(1139, 618, 'Arranging in a cappella:\r\nI think that we could actually break this song up by individual instruments rather than try to separate it chorally. It might make it even feel more like a cappella:\r\n\r\nIt would be cool if the sounds and rhythms were fused into all the parts. eg Altos/sops. could have the half-note syllable "shing" for the sleigh bells and then get acoustic guitar. Basses could get the toms and bass drum lines with "dum"s with the same progression inside measures and maybe with a general chord progression. Then they could continue to sing the bass guitar line etc.. You would still need a perc from 1:00 on but maybe only to sing snare and hi-hat. Or something like that.       ', 53, '2014-01-08 16:12:43'),
(1140, 619, 'This song doesn''t have any explicitly Christian material. ', 53, '2014-01-08 16:51:03'),
(1141, 629, 'Really great song, but do you think that it might be a little too much for nonChristians, even seekers?', 53, '2014-01-08 17:22:02'),
(1142, 630, 'This is a worship song, but might it be a little over the top for nonChristians in the audience?', 53, '2014-01-08 17:24:06'),
(1143, 605, 'I love this song! Only thing is that "Spirit lead me..." will be really strange for a nonChristian. Also, since when was this song nine minutes long?', 53, '2014-01-08 17:27:00'),
(1144, 613, 'I like the song, but what portion of the audience will this actually be able to speak to?', 53, '2014-01-08 17:57:47'),
(1145, 603, 'I definitely agree, I can really relate to this song, and I think it''s one that has really thought provoking lyrics.  I think this would be a great opportunity for a really honest blurb that many non-Christians could relate to.  It''s also pretty catchy, and would add a good diversity to our set, likely.', 44, '2014-01-08 20:01:02'),
(1146, 205, 'This sounds like a song that would be really fun to perform musically, I like all the different parts.', 56, '2014-01-08 23:07:13'),
(1147, 633, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Phoebe: Don''t like the arrangement. Martin: might get boring if it''s that slow. Maria: Powerful if arranged for a cappella because it''s so well known, esp. paired with a blurb. Dorian: would like a choral arrangement.', 50, '2014-01-08 23:14:38'),
(1148, 633, 'I love this song. But listening to the arrangement, it seems kind of slow and   choir-y, and I''d be interested in trying to make it in some way faster.', 56, '2014-01-08 23:16:48'),
(1149, 408, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Ruth: liked that it''s upbeat. Martin: Stanford has an amazing arrangement. Alvin: Our arrangement''s hard to remember (overall ok). Similar feel to Emmanuel, but more upbeat. Maria: good worship song, but not sure if it''s applicable for us as a ministry. Dorian: simple lyrics are ok as long as they make a point. Ruth: praise God v. making a point.', 50, '2014-01-08 23:23:26'),
(1150, 408, 'I kind of agree with Brian, I think that I''d need some really interesting dynamics to stay engaged with this song as a listener. ', 56, '2014-01-08 23:25:08'),
(1151, 582, 'DANG NATALIE GRANT. I love this song. I think the lyrics are beautiful and so gospel-filled and I feel like this song is musically very interesting as well. It''s good at building and resolving tension.', 56, '2014-01-08 23:29:10'),
(1152, 582, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Nursen: Lyrics are great - full of the Gospel. Matthew: powerful song (see comment above). Dorian: explicit without hitting you over the head with it. Maria: romantic, in the best possible way. Everyone: likes it musically. Matthew: builds well - good energy. Dorian: slow at the beginning (just have to make sure the arrangement is dynamic).', 50, '2014-01-08 23:29:51'),
(1153, 625, 'I think the message of the song is good, but the repetition and the vagueness of the lyrics kind of concerns me. It''s slightly on the boring side. I would be find having another song with more poignant in its place in the set with the same message would be favorable.', 38, '2014-01-08 23:33:56'),
(1154, 625, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Martin: might need to be contextualized as a Christian song (blurb, being in a Christian set list). Matthew: more general song. Maria: relate-able & powerful worship song, esp. for seekers. Simple message. Dorian: forgettable, might slip past people if arranged too similarly to original. Maria: can see it as a tagline that is reiterated throughout skit. Dorian: Can see it as a good mashup.', 50, '2014-01-08 23:34:42'),
(1155, 625, 'I love the idea of this being in a mash-up, I think it could add substance and musical interest while maintaining the passion-evoking message of the song.', 56, '2014-01-08 23:35:49'),
(1156, 612, 'I''d be interested to hear this as an a cappella arrangement :]', 38, '2014-01-08 23:36:28'),
(1157, 612, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Maria: good worship song. How does it fit in the MIT context - all good things come from heaven, but doesn''t say why. Matthew: slow, takes a while to build up. Message may be lost because it''s so slow. Dorian: might be cool with a super gospel-vibe (as long as we take it seriously).', 50, '2014-01-08 23:38:47'),
(1158, 418, 'ALSO ZOMAGAH THE ENERGIES! :D This would be so fun to perform. ', 56, '2014-01-08 23:40:07'),
(1159, 418, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Ruth: liked the message. Matthew: (see comment above). Agree with Kevin that the arrangement is "meh".', 50, '2014-01-08 23:46:43'),
(1160, 622, 'Yeah, I agree with Nursen about that line. It stood out to me, because I feel like people at MIT tend to ask those kinds of questions. This song is an interesting take on that.', 38, '2014-01-08 23:51:36'),
(1161, 622, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Dorian: Christian version of Taylor Swift. Martin: Theological concern - "I''m not the same me, and that''s all the proof I need" but that''s true for many other religions, as well. It''s not incorrect, but it''s not sufficient to explain why Christ is the true way. Dorian: it''s interesting how Nursen picked out that same line.', 50, '2014-01-08 23:53:26'),
(1162, 630, 'I like it as a worship song, but I''m not sure if it''s necessarily aligned to what the pitches want as a direction for this set. Also agree with Brian.', 38, '2014-01-08 23:55:38'),
(1163, 630, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Dorian: I agree with Brian. Matthew: repetition makes it over-the-top, but might be good as a mashup. Good energy. Alvin: not too attracted to the song musically. Kind of forgettable, but it kept repeating.', 50, '2014-01-08 23:56:41'),
(1164, 416, 'I love how this song is spring break friendly because it''s in a different language ;]', 38, '2014-01-08 23:59:03');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(1165, 622, 'Hm, I definitely see that other religions leave people experiencing changes within themselves, but I guess I kind of felt that the song evokes the personal nature of our Christian God, since He''s the kind of God who enters into our existence and walks with us. And I think that the leap I made listening to this was to connect it with all the changes in my heart I saw God make, things about myself I''d tried to change on my own and failed to, that he changed, and to me it was so clear that it was God responding to my prayers and amazing me with His capacity to change things I never could on my own. But I don''t think that connection is necessarily there in the lyrics, especially for a non-believer. At the same time, I don''t think I could be the only person who has had that kind of experience with God.', 56, '2014-01-08 23:59:54'),
(1166, 416, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Alvin: you can sing it anywhere, but it has power. Matthew: well known (Martin: amongst nerds). Dorian: It''s nice because if people don''t know what it is/haven''t heard it, they''re likely to ask about it.', 50, '2014-01-09 00:02:50'),
(1167, 481, 'I''m black!!! I could provide the necessary swagger!!!', 56, '2014-01-09 00:09:08'),
(1168, 481, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Alvin: I don''t actually like Background. Martin: rap is nice for variety, but we have other rap songs (ex: Never Change). Maddie: rap is a little slow (nice to hear the words) - it dragged. Martin: hard style to arrange without making it boring. Alvin: background of the arrangement was dull.', 50, '2014-01-09 00:11:54'),
(1169, 481, 'Also I think it would be cool if DanceTroupe or some dance group on campus would like to do something appropriate (emphasis on APPROPRIATE) to this, since it''s hip hop. It''d be a cool way of kind of expanding how people think of xprod. Or maybe even some people from our fellowships who like to dance for the glory of God?', 56, '2014-01-09 00:12:15'),
(1170, 596, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Dorian: good for a mashup. Alvin: too repetitive, wouldn''t appreciate it if I was in the audience. Phoebe: might not be a performance song b/c of the repetition. Hard to maintain energy with the same words.', 50, '2014-01-09 00:16:30'),
(1171, 591, 'I like how these lyrics convey a different perspective on the Adam and Eve story than most people think of. ', 38, '2014-01-09 00:17:52'),
(1172, 591, 'I love this song, I think the lyrics are beautiful, but I''m concerned that the meaning would be really lost on a nonbeliever.', 56, '2014-01-09 00:19:16'),
(1173, 591, 'definitely builds on top of an existing theological foundation. Must be careful not to assume that people already know Adam and Eve story (literary perspective and Christian perspective). This song is kind of that third layer on top of those previous two that would make it difficult for a nonbeliever to understand.', 38, '2014-01-09 00:22:58'),
(1174, 591, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Matthew: it''s a song about Adam & Eve wishing they could turn back time. Talks about us wanting to go back to how God wants us to be. Biggest concern - audience might not be familiar with the story - blurb would help. Nursen: How would a nonbeliever take this song? Polly: nonbelievers might know it as a story, but not understand it on the level of this song (theologically). Nursen: don''t overestimate what nonbelievers know - might be too hard. Polly: blurb would help, but might still be too hard to understand. Alvin: musically - good duet, but was there a background? Martin: cool musically, but would need a good arrangement (would have to put the drums into the background).', 50, '2014-01-09 00:23:10'),
(1175, 600, 'I think the "will you do the same for me" works... unless I''m interpreting it wrong? Were you guys thinking this was from a Christian''s perspective or from God''s perspective?', 38, '2014-01-09 00:25:23'),
(1176, 600, 'I think it works from God''s perspective! I really like this one.', 38, '2014-01-09 00:30:51'),
(1177, 600, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Dorian: cool to sing it to nonChristians. Polly: love the idea of a pop song in our set. What did people mean about the acceptance thing (see comments above)? Ruth: "Will you do the same for me" is weird b/c it''s in God''s perspective, and we don''t love him unconditionally. Phoebe: He doesn''t need our unconditional love b/c he''s perfect. Nursen: Love the Lord your God with all your heart (etc) - how is that different from unconditional love? Phoebe: Unconditional love implies that there''s something wrong with the other person (you love them despite their flaws). Nursen: unconditional b/c we love God despite our circumstances. Matthew: that line comes just after "acceptance is the key," so it''s asking if we will accept God and love him too. Polly: emphasize that God loves us unconditionally, but it''s our choice whether or not we accept him.', 50, '2014-01-09 00:33:15'),
(1178, 600, 'THIS SONG IS AWESOME!!! The first verse is so profound, I mean, personally, that''s like the story of my Freshman year, not wanting to let God in too far, because I didn''t want Him to see the mess I made of myself and my life, and I was so ashamed. And it wasn''t until I understood that He saw it all on the cross and never even blinked that I realized the depth of His love for me was great enough to cast out the shame. Not to mention that I often felt growing up that love was conditional on performance, and I feel like that''s a common thing people at MIT have believed at some point, Christian or not, so communicating the unconditional love of God in an accessible way is so critical to our ministry on this campus.', 56, '2014-01-09 00:36:31'),
(1179, 601, 'Stylistically very different from xprod repertoire. It''d be interesting to see how this arrangement sounds a cappella. The lyrics reminded me of the verse from "Come Thou Font" that starts with "O to grace how great a debtor", etc. Maybe a mashup idea? haha\r\n', 38, '2014-01-09 00:37:13'),
(1180, 601, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Matthew: I like how he slightly changes the notes in the verses. Also like how he emphasizes the need, then God''s response. Phoebe: style might bore the audience. Dorian: more traditional hymn style. Martin: arrangement in style of "How Beautiful" would work.', 50, '2014-01-09 00:39:05'),
(1181, 36, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Dorian: only concern is that I''d lose interest in it pretty quickly b/c of the current tempo. Martin: do other groups have an arrangement of this already? Ruth: really pretty. Martin: gospel-choir style. Alvin: arrangement-wise, might be challenging.', 50, '2014-01-09 00:43:18'),
(1182, 589, 'wow... I love the emotion and simplicity of the first song. There''s definitely an emotional pull that we need to keep if we have an a cappella arrangement of it.', 38, '2014-01-09 00:48:30'),
(1183, 589, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Phoebe: mostly the song from God''s perspective, but then "Say Something" is the human''s perspective. Polly: lyrically, these 2 songs work together.', 50, '2014-01-09 00:49:32'),
(1184, 34, 'one of my favorite xprod hymns :]', 38, '2014-01-09 00:50:19'),
(1185, 34, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Ruth: love the lyrics. Dorian: like the swell from the quiet to the loud part. Alvin: simple, straight-forward, need to be especially in tune (or it''ll sound bad b/c it''s choral), harmonious (not a lot of different textures), sounds great. Polly: Gospel, in a nutshell.', 50, '2014-01-09 00:54:41'),
(1186, 603, 'I like the musical style of this song. I think it would be interesting to have a guy/girl duet on the choruses in harmony, because the melodies in this song are interesting.', 38, '2014-01-09 00:56:29'),
(1187, 603, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Martin: can''t picture a cappella version, sounds like Coldplay- ideas from previous Coldplay arrangements;', 55, '2014-01-09 00:58:11'),
(1188, 602, 'I love how this song talks about the relentless love of God in such a way that highlights the power of God. It shows that God pursues us because he loves us that much. Good message.', 38, '2014-01-09 01:00:39'),
(1189, 602, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Dorian: relatable for Christians, non Christian perspective is questionable, confusing... ; Alvin: outside of Christian context sounds "really weird"; Ruth: "really likes it"', 55, '2014-01-09 01:02:38'),
(1190, 590, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Alvin: don''t use X.ado''s arrangement, could be inproved; Martin: It''s super fun to sing though (with Boston found); Dorian: Tweak their arrangement? Phoebe: I love Kelly Clarkson, popular, listened to it in 5th grade and still remember the lyrics;  ', 55, '2014-01-09 01:08:52'),
(1191, 13, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Ruth: I like this, I really like the message, although I feel it''s more for Christians; ', 55, '2014-01-09 01:14:27'),
(1192, 592, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Alvin: Really slow; Phoebe: I don''t know if we could do it... solo like her.', 55, '2014-01-09 01:18:54'),
(1193, 584, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Ruth: I like the message, but how relavent will people find it?  Too literal? Apply to our audience? Alvin: Closer in a set, more songs are more relatable, go out with a bang!; Martin: Reason as a close song because the concert is "The Reason We Sing"', 55, '2014-01-09 01:23:22'),
(1194, 585, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Maddie: It''s really upbeat and motivating :); Phoebe: definitely translate to a cappella (and Martin); Ruth: really upbeat, like it, too much worship in song suggestions', 55, '2014-01-09 01:26:58'),
(1195, 613, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Alvin: my dislikes is that... narrow audience, then reasoned that this would be straight up to Christians and be to nonChristians we would be like examples of not, examples of people who aren''t exculsive... ', 55, '2014-01-09 01:39:46'),
(1196, 615, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Martin: I really like that song, I listened to it several times.. listened to the lyrics... OH I GET IT THAT''S SO COOL!!!!!; ', 55, '2014-01-09 01:45:11'),
(1197, 615, 'Love the lyrics!: I am the moon with no light of my own\r\nStill you have made me to shine\r\nAnd as I glow in this cold dark night\r\nI know I can''t be a light unless I turn my face to you... ', 52, '2014-01-09 01:45:49'),
(1198, 624, 'ooh I really like this... especially during the instrumental parts, we can have a male voice speak bible verses, like it does in the video but aloud.. I think it could be really cool and impactful.. :D', 52, '2014-01-09 01:47:56'),
(1199, 624, 'Comments from Song Listening Party: Ruth: is like Via Doloroso, very strong Gospel :); Martin: interesting arrangement, changing style in verses.', 55, '2014-01-09 01:50:02'),
(1200, 625, 'My only concern is that this song seems to be focused more on the singer seeking than on why God is the answer -- it says "You''re so much more," etc., but doesn''t elaborate (what makes God more?).', 50, '2014-01-09 17:06:08'),
(1201, 622, 'I like how this song addresses both believers and nonbelievers by saying how  God has been with us all this time, whether we knew it or not. Like Martin, though, I''m a little concerned with that line ("I''m not the same me, and that''s all the proof I need"). I''d have liked it to have focused more on God in that line, instead of focusing on "me." I definitely agree with Nursen that I have seen God do amazing things in my life, and it is convincing proof for me, but I wouldn''t say that it''s "all the proof I need," and I don''t think someone who hasn''t been transformed by God would be able to relate to it. We believe in God and embrace the cross before the Holy Spirit comes and changes us; here, it kind of sounds like Christians have the proof, but if you''re a nonbeliever, you can''t know until you''ve tried it.', 50, '2014-01-09 17:39:05'),
(1202, 596, 'Mashup idea: Empty My Hands by Tenth Avenue North. Empty My Hands is about us coming from our brokenness, asking God to come empty us of ourselves and fill us with Him and Beautiful Things is about God making beauty out of brokenness. Musically, they seem to work pretty well together, too.', 50, '2014-01-09 17:58:21'),
(1203, 494, 'I liked the 2 songs together when we sang the mashup last year, but the arrangement was hard to memorize.', 50, '2014-01-09 18:29:07'),
(1204, 587, 'UC did a mashup of Coming Home & Go the Distance at their Fall 2013 concert. (http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NVo_SkRHgXY)', 50, '2014-01-09 19:30:25'),
(1205, 506, 'I think the first two lines are still from the person''s perspective. They''ve tried hard to bring God''s message of love & salvation to earth (or they feel like they have), but every time they bring up the name of God, they feel like people get offended. This person does want to be a witness; they''re just scared of the consequences of being explicit. My concern with this song is that although it''s an important challenge to Christians, it''s not friendly to non-Christians (us v. them vibe).', 50, '2014-01-09 19:48:51'),
(1206, 620, 'This song is really sweet, and I think good for a Christian audience. However, even though we, as the Church, should ideally be the hands and feet of Christ sharing his love on earth, the Church isn''t usually seen that way from an outside perspective. I''m concerned that us claiming that this is what we do may come off as a little pretentious.', 50, '2014-01-09 19:59:55'),
(1207, 605, 'I think UPenn''s Full Measure sang this at the UC concert Fall ''13, if we want to ask them about their arrangement. My concern with this song is that it''s slow, and slow songs tend to drag (especially since this one repeats so many times).', 50, '2014-01-09 20:44:49'),
(1208, 605, 'We can always take out repeats, right? Up to the arrangers and pitches'' discretion. I love this song as a worship song, but I agree with Brian''s comment above.', 38, '2014-01-10 01:02:55'),
(1209, 620, 'Yeah, I agree with Meiji. I can imagine some nonbelievers who were previously hurt by Christians being more and more convinced that Christians are hypocrites because we mess up and don''t follow through with loving as Christ loved us.', 38, '2014-01-10 01:06:18'),
(1210, 506, 'I feel like this song puts the focus on people too much, instead of putting the focus on God. I agree that it fits in the "The Reason We Sing", but I also feel like other potential songs in the set can have more power in declaring that we sing for the glory of God.', 38, '2014-01-10 01:10:09'),
(1211, 624, 'This song has a really somber tone, which may or may not be a challenge to keep in the tone of an cappella arrangement. Though I like the lyrics, it may be a little deep for some (especially nonbelievers) due to the theological/biblical references throughout. It''s cool that it''s a different style than we normally sing, though.', 38, '2014-01-10 01:14:45'),
(1212, 587, 'Strange mashup, but it works. I thought they could maybe integrate the songs together more, rather than just at the end. It helps with interpreting this song as a Christian song. I like the idea of having secular songs in our set, but if we were to use this song, I''d go with making it a mashup to remove lyrical ambiguity. (Or we can just ask UC if we can use their arrangement, haha)', 38, '2014-01-10 01:23:37'),
(1213, 615, 'I like the lyrics and the Yale arrangement. So pretty :]', 38, '2014-01-10 01:31:24'),
(1214, 615, 'spring break friendly, as well', 38, '2014-01-10 01:32:52'),
(1215, 585, '"Keep on pushing back the dark" implies that we''re oppressed by the darkness. In reality, God already has victory over that and has given us that authority. I am not listing this as a theological problem, but I don''t fully agree with the posture that the songwriter comes from. Aside from that line, I think the rest of the song is alright. Super upbeat and happy sounding, though :]', 38, '2014-01-10 01:40:46'),
(1216, 592, 'If we do it, we can do it at a faster tempo. It would help make it more doable for the soloist, too.', 38, '2014-01-10 01:44:14'),
(1217, 590, 'I love Kelly Clarkson too! I would like to hear xprod create their own arrangement of the song also.', 38, '2014-01-10 01:50:39'),
(1218, 583, 'love how it''s upbeat and positive! could be a very good spring break song. i wonder how it sounds in a cappella though', 47, '2014-01-10 02:06:46'),
(1219, 620, 'agree with the above 2 comments', 47, '2014-01-10 02:12:48'),
(1220, 614, 'i like this! part of it reminds me of After the Music Fades', 47, '2014-01-10 02:16:56'),
(1221, 506, 'i agree with polly: i understand what they''re trying to say when they say "if I keep quiet, they''ll never see I''m different" but it makes it seem like the purpose is to show people that *we* are different, thus skewing the focus away from God ', 47, '2014-01-10 02:23:40'),
(1222, 606, 'i really like this song! a blurb explaining the Christianese would be good, i think', 47, '2014-01-10 02:26:39'),
(1223, 628, 'i understand what the artist is getting at but i feel like this also kinda puts the focus more on people and less on God- i think the comments for Legacy by Nicole Nordeman would apply here too', 47, '2014-01-10 02:31:01'),
(1224, 593, 'oooh cool! this could work :D i''m just really confused about the first verse though (i don''t even know what it means from the secular/intended perspective) any thoughts?', 47, '2014-01-10 02:38:12'),
(1225, 24, 'i like the lyrics but i''m not a fan of the arrangement- agree with above comment that it would need a really strong soprano soloist ', 47, '2014-01-10 02:46:03'),
(1226, 632, 'i love the message of this song-i think it''s very applicable to MIT life as Kristina said. i''m not sure it fits the "reason we sing" theme exactly but it would still be nice to have a song like this in our set', 47, '2014-01-10 03:06:26'),
(1227, 102, 'this fits the reason we sing theme very well. the a cappella version would require a lot of energy to make it sound less repetitive', 47, '2014-01-10 03:11:27'),
(1228, 633, 'I think this is a bit hard to pull off in xprod because it is a full-out worship song. Non-Christians may find it hard to relate to.', 38, '2014-01-10 23:17:02'),
(1229, 593, 'omg haha I copied inaccurate lyrics, sorry. It should be "You wore it so much longer / it made sense". I interpreted the first verse to be about how people strive for virtues like patience and doing "Christian things" instead of being in a relationship with Him. ', 38, '2014-01-10 23:25:24'),
(1230, 628, '^ agreed. That point alone makes me more inclined to choose another song that''s more potent and focused on God in the set instead of this one. Message is good, though.', 38, '2014-01-10 23:27:23'),
(1231, 606, 'Agreed with Phoebe. Also another thing to note is that the negative connotation of a "thief in the night" may spark some negative reflections about who God is and about His heart towards us. We need to be super clear that God is not malicious and that He loves us; it may be a pitfall that people fall into when listening to this song for the first time, with certain faith backgrounds and theologies that they don''t interpret the song''s meaning as the author(s) intended.', 38, '2014-01-10 23:31:16'),
(1232, 583, 'Haha I love how it''s such a power song, even while being upbeat and so happy-sounding. The only part I''m a bit worried about are the "Oh, lift your head it''s gonna end\r\nGod''s right there\r\nEven when you just can''t feel Him\r\nI promise you that He still cares" lines, because the happy music behind the lyrics almost feel like it''s trivializing the problem. Small price to pay for such a positive song though. It would be a good spring break song with a few lyrical tweaks.', 38, '2014-01-10 23:36:59'),
(1233, 622, 'I actually feel that this song is very clear and straightforward in it''s message, just speaking of God''s presence in our life.  People could take it other ways, but we will not be directing it other ways.  We as a group, as a ministry, will do all that we do to point to God and His transforming power, so I am not nearly as worried about the clarity and message here.', 48, '2014-01-10 23:39:13'),
(1234, 627, 'I actually really like the lyrics of this song. It''s very encouraging to believers, and is scripturally grounded. It''s an exhortation to people but still very focused on God, which is a delicate balance to achieve but I think this song has achieved it.', 38, '2014-01-10 23:46:02'),
(1235, 618, 'or a double perc, haha.', 38, '2014-01-10 23:53:04'),
(1236, 618, 'I must admit I''m not a huge fan of this song because the focus is a lot on man and not on God, especially since the focus is on how the man was before God saved him and not as much on how God is living or changing his life.', 38, '2014-01-10 23:54:34'),
(1237, 607, 'Musically interesting, and lyrically solid.', 38, '2014-01-11 00:03:57'),
(1238, 604, 'I love the bridge. It counters some of the philosophies I''ve seen and heard from people at MIT, where they hold a rather scientific and purposeless view about why we as humans are here on earth.', 38, '2014-01-11 00:05:53'),
(1239, 631, 'This song totally fits "The Reason We Sing" exactly because of what Kristina said above. I like the message and the song lyrically, but musically I feel it is very not exciting (lol). Maybe the arranger can add some cool riffs or rhythms or something like that to make it sound more exciting in a cappella.', 38, '2014-01-11 00:11:04'),
(1240, 363, 'I agree with Dorian, but I also feel that it''s a bit difficult to relate to for nonbelievers because of the "You are holy" lyrics. Would need a blurb to provide some context, but a lot of the song''s power is lost in that transition.', 38, '2014-01-11 00:13:43'),
(1241, 621, 'I like this song - my only concern is that without a blurb, it doesn''t seem to connect to God/Christianity.', 50, '2014-01-11 00:27:19'),
(1242, 621, 'I like this musically, but not sure how this fits in with "The Reason We Sing" theme.', 38, '2014-01-11 00:28:13'),
(1243, 227, 'I really enjoyed singing this song, but since we did it both semesters last year, I would prefer if we waited a bit longer before singing it again.', 50, '2014-01-11 00:37:04'),
(1244, 600, 'God is the author of love, and the only being capable of perfect unconditional love. It would be cool to connect this idea with society and humanity''s obsession/search for love and acceptance (especially since this is a pop song).', 50, '2014-01-11 00:50:56'),
(1245, 415, 'YESSS to the Sara Bareilles'' "Brave" mashup idea! That was the first thing that popped into my mind after I saw this in the song suggestions list again. I feel like this verse out of the other "Brave" fits better in a Christian context: \r\n\r\n"Everybody&#146;''s been there, everybody&#146;''s been stared down\r\nBy the enemy\r\nFallen for the fear and done some disappearing\r\nBow down to the mighty\r\nDon&#146;t run, stop holding your tongue\r\nMaybe there&#146;s a way out of the cage where you live\r\nMaybe one of these days you can let the light in\r\nShow me how big your brave is" \r\n\r\nI think the interplay/perspectives between "I wanna see you be brave" from the Bareilles song and the "You make me want to be brave" from this song would be interesting to mash up.', 38, '2014-01-11 00:53:36'),
(1246, 586, 'I don''t like the line "miracles just happen" and the emphasis on our faith instead of on God. God is the one who makes these things happen. Our faith in God allows the Holy Spirit to work through us, but our faith alone doesn''t do anything. People can have faith in many different things (including other religions).', 50, '2014-01-11 01:26:36'),
(1247, 533, 'No offense, but I feel like this song washes out Christianity too much in the choruses, which makes the song kinda cheesy. It matches the theme to a certain extent, but I feel like other songs can also fill this void.', 38, '2014-01-11 01:46:12'),
(1248, 533, 'I really like the arrangement of this piece!  It''s a different style than everything else I''ve heard on here. ', 55, '2014-01-11 02:08:04'),
(1249, 632, 'Connection to The Reason We Sing: "Therefore, if anyone is in Christ, the new creation has come: The old has gone, the new is here! All this is from God, who reconciled us to himself through Christ and gave us the ministry of reconciliation: that God was reconciling the world to himself in Christ, not counting people''s sins against them. And he has committed to us the message of reconciliation. We are therefore Christ''s ambassadors, as though God were making his appeal through us. We implore you on Christ''s behalf: Be reconciled to God. God made him who had no sin to be sin for us, so that in him we might become the righteousness of God." 2 Corinthians 5:17-21', 50, '2014-01-11 02:09:55'),
(1250, 621, 'I like this song and the arrangement, but I agree with Meiji- a connection to God/Christianity is not obvious.', 55, '2014-01-11 02:18:57'),
(1251, 615, 'When I first heard this song, I thought of the quote by C.S. Lewis: "I believe in Christianity as I believe that the sun has risen: not only because I see it, but because by it I see everything else." Also, "Those who are wise will shine like the brightness of the heavens, and those who lead many to righteousness, like the stars for ever and ever." Daniel 12:3.', 50, '2014-01-11 02:19:42'),
(1252, 627, 'I love the line "if God is for us, who can be against us"... and he is alive, living for us... this is the reason we sing', 55, '2014-01-11 02:29:30'),
(1253, 558, 'Their arrangement is really pretty. However, I''m not a huge fan of the Your Guardian Angel lyrics "now that I''m strong I have figured out," as if God is neither omnipotent nor omniscient.', 50, '2014-01-11 02:31:43'),
(1254, 626, 'I think this is a gorgeous song but I really can''t imagine it in an a cappella setting...', 55, '2014-01-11 03:22:02'),
(1255, 634, 'Lina Kim requested this song.', 53, '2014-05-17 01:46:42'),
(1256, 635, 'So... musical theater again.\r\nFirst- a few edits to the lyrics I would make- like just removing "let''s have some wine"\r\nI think It could be arranged in a really cool way to have multiple solo lines and full chords (but not wall of sound).\r\n\r\nIn terms of the lyrics, it''s pretty much Matthew 5:13-16- Gospel in song.\r\n\r\nAlso, it may be cool to mash this up with This Little Light of Mine- I don''t know if chord progressions work or anything, but Caitlin has the idea of This Little Light of Mine in a mashup and this could be a potential partner song since the themes are essentially the same.\r\n', 55, '2014-05-17 06:20:09'),
(1257, 636, 'This is a super upbeat song... I marked as pre-arranged because it is an a cappella choral piece, however, it could possible use edits.  \r\nI don''t have much to say except it''s a happy song... different genre than we''ve been singing- which I think would be cool for next semester.\r\nThe arrangement I''m familiar with I believe has some emphasis on male voice parts, but could be rearranged to change this.\r\n\r\n', 55, '2014-05-17 06:27:07'),
(1258, 637, 'XPROD GOES GOSPEL!!!!!\r\nFirst: This song is SO FUN TO SING...  I sang it my junior year in high school.\r\n\r\nSecond: It is not nine minutes long.  It is like 4 or 5.  The video I added shows a lot of repeats, but is also one of the best videos on YouTube in terms of performance soulfullness.\r\n\r\nThird:  It would be a challenge.  Not super boy requirement (tenor part easily covered by females), but tough to arrange the piano part, tricky chords, and requires a very full sound.  Opportunity for multiple soloists- probably a quartet with background... \r\n\r\nIf we can pull off an arrangement for this song, it would sound so cool!!!!!', 55, '2014-05-17 06:41:28'),
(1259, 638, 'New idea...  This song is a giant Thank You to God (in 15 languages).  I don''t know if this is too explicit/ not enough meaning for our concert, but there''s a couple of options for this arrangement...\r\n\r\nWe could actually have a call and response, however this may be weird for any non Christian members in our audience.\r\n\r\nWe could also do call and response among the group.\r\n\r\nPoint being, arrangement options are open.  I think it''d be cool to include more languages in xprod again, especially after Baba Yetu...\r\n\r\nSome input on the message/lyrics would be greatly appreciated.  I don''t really know how it would work in a skit/concert setting, but it would be a really cool song to sing!', 55, '2014-05-17 06:49:12'),
(1260, 642, 'This is not specifically Christian, but it is from the perspective of someone caught by the realization that their life is meaningless. The song could not stand alone that well, but it sets up someone searching for God. \r\n\r\nI like it because it is a different genre, and because even as a Christian sometimes my heart yearns to know what my purpose here is. This song would probably be best used in a skit. ', 53, '2014-05-19 21:07:27'),
(1261, 643, 'While the beginning might need a blurb, the bridge definitely would not.  I feel that this is a song that powerfully describes the agony of our separation from Christ and how far we have fell and even scorned Him.  And over it all, how powerful His love for us is. (:', 48, '2014-05-20 01:24:43'),
(1262, 640, ':D I like this.', 57, '2014-05-21 00:46:53'),
(1263, 646, 'I think this song could be a picture of someone turning back to God after trying to find meaning/understanding in other things. I just really like the image here.', 57, '2014-05-21 01:33:44'),
(1264, 647, 'I like the Addison Road song. I feel like it''s a little vague, so depending on how explicit we would want to be, we could do a slight mash-up with Gungor''s "We Will Run" as a way to say who we are running to. ', 57, '2014-05-21 01:46:02'),
(1265, 649, 'Ok...so this might just be me trying to make this song work, but I really like "Rather Be" musically. I''m not really set on all of the lyrics though. But then I thought it would be cool to mash up with the lyrics from "Set a Fire." Thoughts...?', 57, '2014-05-21 02:26:42'),
(1266, 465, 'I can''t remember which group it was, but at BIDB this year a group sang this song and changed it to "He gave His life to fix you."', 57, '2014-05-21 02:30:16'),
(1267, 650, 'yay oldies! i think the lyrics can totally be applied to a Christian context- maybe with a couple of easy verse changes (like the one about the phone)', 47, '2014-05-23 18:40:08'),
(1268, 641, 'including spanish version cuz it''s awesome :3', 47, '2014-05-23 18:41:25'),
(1269, 651, 'i love love love this song! it''s lyrically simple, but powerful and declares God''s Holiness! i also love the Digital Age''s rendition of it- but i''m not sure how this would translate to a cappella.. \r\n@5:00 in video: borderline screamo ^_^\r\n', 47, '2014-05-23 18:52:47'),
(1270, 652, 'since our fall concert is a little bit before Christmas, it''d be super awesome to do a Christmas song... especially this arrangment ahhhhh', 47, '2014-05-23 19:44:54'),
(1271, 640, 'ooooooooooooh !!!!!!!!!! me too!!', 47, '2014-05-23 19:58:34'),
(1272, 653, 'some parts of this song are definitely like prayers recognizing that God is present, loves us, and gives us strength, while other parts i''m not so sure about (at the end of the song, it seems like it''s an emphasis on what God does more than who He is...)\r\n\r\nthoughts?', 47, '2014-05-23 20:30:48'),
(1273, 638, 'I personally don''t like it. I found it rather dull and repetitive. But objectively, for a set with only a limited number of slots, I can''t imagine a song that just has us singing different forms of "thank you" for several minutes. Also, pronunciation struggles. "Baba Yetu" works out well because of its content as the Lord''s Prayer, its musically interesting progression, and its selling point as the title track of a popular video game. ', 40, '2014-05-24 09:51:11'),
(1274, 484, 'Cool song, high energy, super happy, prearranged. High tenor solo though, if that ends up being important. Also, a straightforward key change: something good for the group to get used to and better with. Otherwise, look above for other reasons I''d reiterate.', 40, '2014-05-24 09:57:45'),
(1275, 17, 'Party notes: 6 part split (SMATTB) + Solo/Duet + Perc.', 40, '2014-05-25 18:58:16'),
(1276, 639, 'I love the lyrics: "You liberate me from my own noise and my own chaos," combined with the fact that it''s so simple musically. Especially at MIT, there are so many things to do, and I feel like I need to be a busy bee and be productive and not rest. Skit anyone? Also "From the chains of a lesser law You set me free." Though it is slow and slots for slow songs are highly competitive. But I love it.', 37, '2014-05-26 02:26:40'),
(1277, 542, 'I like message "but even though You know, You will always love me." God knows everything we go through (even when we think we can hide things from Him), but He still loves us. Unconditionally. Downside is that it is slow. Woooohoo ballads. The soloist needs to be engaging. Also: spring break friendly, without compromising the message.', 37, '2014-05-28 01:57:00'),
(1278, 655, 'This song is really encouraging to Christians. It is a reminder of how God is always with us, before and behind, and that He is the God of angel armies. I know that a lot of people in different fellowships know it and if we want a song specifically for them (not so much for nonbelievers) then this one is great. \r\n\r\nMusically, I think that to avoid it sounding repetitive we would maybe want to split the solo (like what Princeton did with Oceans) Also, sending some of the verses/choruses to the group or parts of the group could add power.\r\n', 53, '2014-05-29 15:11:17'),
(1279, 656, 'This is a really beautiful song purely worshipping God. \r\n\r\nI said that it is prearranged because Princeton has an arrangement which we might be able to borrow. ', 53, '2014-05-29 16:40:23'),
(1280, 657, 'My TBT submission quota for the semester. Also yes, that''s not a mistake. Prearranged. \r\n\r\nIf Christ has not been raised, then we are fools. If only for this life we have hope in Christ, we are of all people most to be pitied. Our faith would be useless, our sins still not forgiven, and we''d be false witnesses about God. Fools to be pitied. But here''s the thing. Christ has indeed been raised from the dead. The "wise" man: whether that be the world, the devil, or our inner demons, says to give up. But there''s a reason to bear our pains and continue to march through the unknown: there is already certain victory ahead. Our God has risen, He''s with us through the dark, and our heavenly home isn''t too far off. ', 40, '2014-05-30 04:40:29'),
(1281, 658, 'Popular song: everyone knows it which is good in terms of inviting nonChristian friends (they always ask will I know anything you guys sing) also in a journey, I think it makes a good intro song.. it clearly depicts a broken person in a broken world that is in dire need of Christ. This would not be a standalone song though', 52, '2014-05-30 13:37:16'),
(1282, 21, 'This song is very catchy and upbeat and I like the message of the song.. the message of freedom and peace and joy in God (: also I kind of want to ask Columbia for their arrangement and modify some of the chords so that it doesn''t clash.. I really like the things that they brought together in their arrangement..', 52, '2014-05-30 13:43:27'),
(1283, 659, 'It''s a good transition song.. a broken person realizing how weak and broken they are and desiring God.. it makes me think of Savior by Lights.. in that it''s asking for God and only God.. being in His presence etc', 52, '2014-05-30 13:47:53'),
(1284, 660, 'I love the lyrics to this hymn!! If we can find/make a good arrangement I feel like it would be a very applicable song, applicable to us and life in general because we all look for something to satisfy us, but only Christ can fully satisfy, he is the unquenchable living water', 52, '2014-05-30 14:08:47'),
(1285, 661, 'explicit gospel within this song (: Love it! ', 52, '2014-05-30 14:11:20'),
(1286, 662, 'really spring break friendly :)\r\npossible lyric change: "My love will only get stronger & stronger" -> "my love is so much stronger & stronger"', 47, '2014-05-30 15:07:33'),
(1287, 663, 'i think this song is a cry for mercy; recognizing one''s own vulnerability and yearning for hope. the bridge is really powerful! a mashup/medley of this song with positive songs proclaiming that Jesus is the Savior would be an interesting juxtaposition', 47, '2014-05-30 15:15:27'),
(1288, 113, 'WHAT IF WE DID IT IN MULTIPLE LANGUAGES??? :D :D', 47, '2014-05-30 15:26:41'),
(1289, 517, 'So often I feel like I''ve failed or lost so many battles. But God doesn''t care about results. He simply wants me to continue to strive, and continue to be molded in His hands. Also, especially in the context of Cross Products, "if I never sing again, my soul will be my song" is really comforting. ', 53, '2014-05-31 13:30:20'),
(1290, 665, 'This is a simple, powerful worship song (another one). It is musically a little boring, but I love the lyrics. I especially think that the third chorus (bridge ?) is powerful.', 53, '2014-06-01 02:44:15'),
(1291, 666, 'This song is technically a Christmas song, but it is of a different genre than other Christmas songs. UPenn sang this at BiDB 2014 so I said that it is prearranged (if we can get it from them). \r\n\r\nThis is a really beautiful song that speaks to the need of this world for redemption (in the sense that this world hungers and waits for redemption of its brokenness). And how that is found in the beauty and glory of our king. ', 53, '2014-06-01 03:10:06'),
(1292, 635, 'ignore this: I the website resubmitted the Godspell "Light of the World" instead of Lauren Daigle''s "Light of the World"', 53, '2014-06-01 03:12:06'),
(1293, 667, 'As people and even Christians we have been programmed to put on a face. It has been ingrained into us that we should bear some level of trial purely on our own before we reach out for help. The problem is that we are made to be wholly dependent on God. Moreover, too often, that threshold of what we "should" bear is far above our heads. \r\n\r\nThis songs speaks to how God wants us as we are, wherever we are. He doesn''t want us to wait until we achieve perfection but wants us to come to Him in all our brokenness and allow for Him to make us perfect. And as Christians we are still broken people, but it is so easy of us to come with a facade that we are not.', 53, '2014-06-01 14:14:35'),
(1294, 138, 'For both Christians and nonChrisitians we get into the patterns of life and cease to live. Rather, we simply exist, but God gives us so much more than this. \r\n\r\nI love the line:\r\n"''Cause just ok is not enough" because it is so easy to back down and accept OKness and give up on the promises that we were made for so much more than this.\r\n', 53, '2014-06-01 14:22:25'),
(1295, 466, 'While this song is written about a friend lost to drugs and is often associated with suicide, as Christians this song has even greater significance. \r\n\r\nWe all know friends who lost their faiths. They slowly callous and fall away, and there are no words we can give them because part of them has died and everything outside is just noise. Yes, we stay up all night, and yes we pray to God He hears them, and yet, we still lose some. And we wonder where did we go wrong because we lost a friend. \r\n\r\nThis past year we lost Andy Sun to suicide. I didn''t know him personally, but I was told that he was active in Harvard''s Christian community. I pray that somehow he held onto his faith despite giving up on life. But there are so many others unnamed and unnoticed who continue to exist, but cease to live. ', 53, '2014-06-01 15:22:38'),
(1296, 248, 'Personally I think the arrangement is really awesome, especially if the group performs it solidly music-wise. Also see stuff that Kristina wrote up there. \r\n@Polly: I think it''s talking more like, I''m only man BUT since God is God, He''s awesome and stuff. It did take me a bit to figure out that interpretation, but that also might be because I only listened to chunks of the video at a time and never the full song.', 40, '2014-06-01 16:05:44'),
(1297, 603, 'What exactly does the song end with? "I feel his hope running through me... but I can''t be sure, and that''s just the way I am?" I might be confused, but that doesn''t sound right. Help me out?', 40, '2014-06-01 16:12:08'),
(1298, 542, 'Strongly advise listening to the MIDI first. Yes, it''s slow AND not a flashy arrangement, which... is a huge detriment to be honest. On the flip side, songs with actual chords and key changes, woo. And it''s really pretty, yeah.', 40, '2014-06-01 16:29:29'),
(1299, 659, 'It sounds very... difficult to arrange. Mostly because IMO the arranger would have to pretty much compose the background. That or keep it as one with mostly whole notes and a perc, with vocals sometimes. Though someone can correct me, please. ', 40, '2014-06-01 16:42:50'),
(1300, 138, 'I''m very amused by the choreo, particularly by how into the shuffle Dorothy is at like 1:01 and no one else is :( ', 40, '2014-06-01 16:47:23'),
(1301, 590, 'Yeah... just a reiteration. Still not a big fan of the X.ado arrangement. ', 40, '2014-06-01 18:23:37'),
(1302, 668, 'Another Choral song! I''ve sung it before and pronunciation is not difficult.  The two melodies are really cool in mashup.  In a choral arrangement, but would require some arranging for the basic pioano part (and there is a lot of parts in the end, 1 or 2 people per part) and more of a trio and less of a soloist (male/female).  ', 55, '2014-06-02 04:06:28'),
(1303, 596, 'Mashup? :]', 38, '2014-06-02 04:51:14'),
(1304, 669, 'Harvard UC version! Maybe we can borrow their arrangement/lyric changes. It''s a well-known and recognizable secular song that works really well in a Christian context.', 38, '2014-06-02 04:56:50'),
(1305, 670, 'Spring break friendly song, musically different style than a lot of the other repertoire xprod does. I love how this song is a song of surrender to God and talks about the inner transformation of the heart when we allow God to change our lives; He gives us the peace, strength, and endurance to make it through. Drawback is that we may need a blurb to explain that this love is God''s love and no other kind of love.', 38, '2014-06-02 05:04:11'),
(1306, 671, 'Spring break friendly song, without compromising the transformational power of the gospel. I love the juxtaposition between our old life and the new life we have in Jesus, which is so present throughout the lyrics. Musically, this is really stripped down. I''d imagine that if this song is chosen for a cappella, we can make it more musically interesting (or keep the vibe, if we can pull it off ;]). ', 38, '2014-06-02 05:23:37'),
(1307, 41, 'Similar message to "Meant to Live". I think this confronts the question of why we''re here on earth that a lot of students at MIT (and the world at large) are wondering. It doesn''t necessarily give a blatant answer, but I interpreted the lyrics of this song to suggest that we were put on this earth to worship God and give Him glory. And this song is already arranged :]', 38, '2014-06-02 05:42:56'),
(1308, 672, 'Spring break friendly? This is a worship song that I think a lot of Christians would recognize. It centers around the strength and unfailing nature of the love of God, which is ultimately what has saved us and sustains us every day. In the bridge, it unashamedly proclaims the power of the cross. I also included a stripped down version in the youtube videos to show that there are many arrangements that could work for this song, musically.', 38, '2014-06-02 05:52:25'),
(1309, 603, 'That doesn''t sound right to me either. :)\r\n\r\n"See a world full of beauty\r\nAnd I feel his hope running through me\r\nBut I can''t reconcile\r\nWith the doubts in me\r\nWith the doubts in me\r\n\r\nCan''t be sure\r\nThat''s just the way I am anymore"\r\n\r\nHe''s talking about how he had trouble reconciling that hope with his doubts but now he''s not sure he feels that way anymore (as in, he''s transitioning to a place where he does find a reconciliation). The chorus is just one sentence: "I can''t be sure that''s the way I am anymore.", not "I can''t really be sure, but whatever, that''s just the way I am. Let''s move on with life and forget about it."\r\n\r\nThe pattern of the song is more like:\r\nVerse - Here''s how I used to feel\r\nChorus - Not so sure I feel this way anymore\r\n\r\nSo it''s not like the song goes into any details about how he got to that place, but I feel like with a good blurb that dealt with something along those lines, the lyrics could be really powerful.\r\n', 57, '2014-06-02 21:07:41'),
(1310, 521, 'I like how this song talks about how God''s love and what He has done for us change how we look at our lives.', 50, '2014-06-03 03:29:15'),
(1311, 207, 'I came across this when listening to the xprod Live 2002-2004 CD and I really liked the energy of the song. Also, one of the lessons God taught me this year was about rejoicing in the Lord ALWAYS - a life of rejoicing is a life of praise.', 50, '2014-06-03 03:55:07'),
(1312, 673, 'Like How Deep the Father''s Love for Us, this is a modern hymn; I love the musical style. I also like how the lyrics draw a parallel between who God is and who we are.', 50, '2014-06-03 04:24:57'),
(1313, 674, 'I love this tribute to God''s goodness - not only celebrating His character, but also all that He has done for us, we who have nothing to offer in return. I also love how the song has parts of "It Is Well" winding through it.', 50, '2014-06-03 04:55:16'),
(1314, 438, 'Over and over, the Bible tells us to stand firm (Eph 6:10-18, 1Cor 15:58, 1Cor 16:13, 2Cor 1:21-22, etc). We can stand firm, not because we are strong, but because Christ is our firm foundation.', 50, '2014-06-03 05:22:47'),
(1315, 598, 'Mm, I love the duet in this song. And the I like how it builds too. I also like the image of "standing empty handed, shattered by the cross." And how basically when we realize how we have nothing, what we do have is that promise which gives us everything. I like the mash up idea too! ', 57, '2014-06-03 19:21:49'),
(1316, 438, 'Lol, "rockin'' girl songs." I like the power in this song.\r\n', 57, '2014-06-03 19:32:23'),
(1317, 673, 'I like the style too,  and we could do some really beautiful harmonies.', 57, '2014-06-03 19:37:29'),
(1318, 41, 'I love songs that deal with those kind of questions and I really like this song musically and lyrically and was definitely jamming out when they sang this at the concert. ', 57, '2014-06-03 19:56:42'),
(1319, 41, 'And yeah, it doesn''t give a blatant answer, but it''s still very thought provoking and gets people to think about deeper questions we tend to shy away fom.', 57, '2014-06-03 19:57:59'),
(1320, 596, 'I reaaaally like the mashup idea.', 57, '2014-06-03 20:11:14'),
(1321, 639, 'I feel like bits of this song could be really cool in a mashup or something.  But yeah the lyrics are really beautiful and meaningful. ', 57, '2014-06-03 20:20:08'),
(1322, 675, 'I feel like if we just replaced some words ( like baby with Jesus etc) lyrics are very relevant... We always seek to satisfy ourselves elsewhere but Jesus has been here for us all along, and we come running back to Him.. He fills the vacancy in our hearts and we have become one with Him... ahhh :D', 52, '2014-06-04 02:30:39'),
(1323, 676, 'This song reminds me of Paul (in Philippians 3) saying how his identity in Christ is worth far more than anything on this earth. We''re all created with a God-shaped hole in our hearts that nothing else can fill, not even all the fame and glory of the world. It''s especially impactful to hear AJ Michalka, an artist identified in popular culture rather than in Christian music, performing such a song.', 50, '2014-06-04 22:35:11'),
(1324, 11, 'I like how this song is saying that God is our deliverer, He rescued us, but that this isn''t just a past-tense thing. Even now, after being saved, we depend on Him totally, and He''ll find us watching, waiting, praying, and praising Him in every moment.', 50, '2014-06-04 23:49:20'),
(1325, 677, 'This song talks about what is waiting for us beyond death. Although the lyrics are simple, I love the harmonies.', 50, '2014-06-05 00:22:40'),
(1326, 678, 'God is so glorious, yet we can''t possibly comprehend all of who He is and what He does. It''s such a waste when we let ourselves be content with mediocrity instead of enjoying all of God''s glory!\r\n\r\n**You can find the xprod version on the CD "...And Then He Found Me", track 12 ("Take My Hand"), at ~7:40. (Sorry -- I''m having trouble uploading it)', 50, '2014-06-05 00:49:13'),
(1327, 5, 'This is really poignant, even for Christians.', 53, '2014-06-05 02:10:18'),
(1328, 445, 'The lines saying "And they don''t know anything else / They don''t know they''re breathing bad air" really strike me because I once was blind, but now I see. Before God started to transform me, I didn''t know what I was missing; similarly, now when I look at my non-believing friends, it hurts me to see them living their lives not knowing that they''re dying with every breath.', 50, '2014-06-05 02:23:29'),
(1329, 679, 'I really love how this song sounds, though I have no musical terminology to describe it. I also feel that our campus and our hearts are hungry for revival and redemption of the brokenness. \r\n"When you come to where you''re broken within / The light meets the dark" I''ve personally been feeling a need for healing, and it always comes to digging up the brokenness and bringing it to light. And we know that the light casts out darkness, never darkness casting out or even resisting the light. God wants our brokenness that He can take it from us and give us back a wholeness in Christ.', 53, '2014-06-05 02:24:06');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(1330, 262, 'I love how this song speaks of how our lives are dedicated to God, fully in surrender, fully in praise, and fully in witness to others.', 50, '2014-06-05 02:33:46'),
(1331, 680, 'I''ve been thinking a lot about having this song as a potential to our setlist.  I think there''s a lot of potential within the song, especially because it ends with "And even though it all went wrong, I''ll stand before the Lord of Song, With nothing on my tongue but Hallelujah"-and it shows that even after going through times of trouble, in the end, God is still there, and we are there praising Him, because without Him, we would be nothing, and he has helped us survive our struggles and hard times.  I''m not sure what perspective to take it from, however and it is really long.  I think with some verse elimination and maybe some potential lyric edits, and with a strong blurb, it would be a good addition to our setlist.  It is well known, and maybe some people could see it from a new perspective. ', 55, '2014-06-05 03:05:22'),
(1332, 664, 'This song is interesting in that it tells the Gospel from a couple different perspectives.  I think it would need a blurb discussing what is the beginnning.  Probably would be a duet for the different people in the song.  Also, has cool mysterious beginning that I think would sound cool in a cappella and a powerful ending.', 55, '2014-06-05 03:15:52'),
(1333, 218, 'So reading the above thread, this song apparently as a very difficult arrangement (which can be fixed).  Seconding what Ruth said last year.  It never explicitly says God or Jesus, and would be excellent for Spring Break.  It has such a powerful ending, and powerful lyrics: "You Raise Me Up, to More than I can be".  We can be nothing without God, but through God, and with living our lives through him, we can do amazing things.', 55, '2014-06-05 03:20:06'),
(1334, 681, 'GOSPEL!!! (I really want xprod to sing some Gospel this semester).  There is a choral arrangement that exits, but the piano part would have to become a cappella.  Tenor part on this is high if I remember correctly (female range easily).  And while it is meant for a full choir, a small group can pull it off (see second video).  Solos would be fairly short (2- one male, one female probably) and I see the arrangement as a quartet (or octet) singing the choral parts and the rest of the group on the piano turned a cappella part.', 55, '2014-06-05 03:33:46'),
(1335, 597, 'I like how the metaphors all point to our longing for God in different ways: the desert longs for water like our souls long for Living Water, the outcast longs for acceptance like we long for redemption, etc.', 50, '2014-06-05 03:40:55'),
(1336, 684, 'Previous comments:\r\n\r\n----- I think this song is really powerful. I don''t know how it would turn out in an arrangement though. We would probably have to shorten it a little since it''s kind of long.\r\nBecky @ 2014-01-02 16:16:47\r\n\r\n----- It would be hard to get an arrangement to sound similar to this song, but I think that is the case with many songs of this style. I really like all the lyrics, but it is slow to get through all of them. I wouldn''t want to cut any out either though...but it does repeat the chorus many times.\r\nCaitlin @ 2014-01-03 23:55:31\r\n\r\n----- I love this song! Only thing is that "Spirit lead me..." will be really strange for a nonChristian. Also, since when was this song nine minutes long?\r\nBrian @ 2014-01-08 12:27:00\r\n\r\n----- I think UPenn''s Full Measure sang this at the UC concert Fall ''13, if we want to ask them about their arrangement. My concern with this song is that it''s slow, and slow songs tend to drag (especially since this one repeats so many times).\r\nMeiji @ 2014-01-09 15:44:49\r\n\r\n----- We can always take out repeats, right? Up to the arrangers and pitches'' discretion. I love this song as a worship song, but I agree with Brian''s comment above.\r\nPolly @ 2014-01-09 20:02:55', 38, '2014-06-05 06:13:35'),
(1337, 685, 'Previous comment:\r\n\r\nSo... musical theater again. First- a few edits to the lyrics I would make- like just removing "let''s have some wine" I think It could be arranged in a really cool way to have multiple solo lines and full chords (but not wall of sound). In terms of the lyrics, it''s pretty much Matthew 5:13-16- Gospel in song. Also, it may be cool to mash this up with This Little Light of Mine- I don''t know if chord progressions work or anything, but Caitlin has the idea of This Little Light of Mine in a mashup and this could be a potential partner song since the themes are essentially the same.\r\nMaddie @ 2014-05-17 02:20:09', 38, '2014-06-05 06:18:06'),
(1338, 686, 'I enjoy this song for just how well it paints how hard we can run away from God, and even when we recognize the emptiness of our idols, we still get stuck listening to their voices over and over again.  The chorus is a beautiful prayer just proclaiming how when we turn from those voices, God can speak and will give life, and in face of his love we cannot help but ask for Him to take them away so we can come closer.', 48, '2014-06-07 17:40:29'),
(1339, 687, 'So this isn''t a song that is directed to unbelievers, but I do believe the call to believers is just as valuable and necessary, and I love this song as a proclamation of the faith we are able to act on because of the God we are able to stand on.  It gives a beautiful feel of joy that this is our God, and this is what he has not only allowed us to do, but called us, and purposed us, to do.', 48, '2014-06-07 23:12:59'),
(1340, 676, 'I love the second verse of this song. It''s a confession that I''m sure a lot of Christians can relate to; being caught up in the world and realizing that our sole identity is in the love of God. I think this is such a pretty song :]', 38, '2014-06-08 06:31:08'),
(1341, 651, 'I love this song as a worship song! My only concern is that it''s not very accessible to non-Christians, especially with words like "hallelujah" and "holy" that are crucial to understanding the song. Not sure if a blurb would mitigate the problem entirely.', 38, '2014-06-08 06:54:18'),
(1342, 667, 'I like how the song sings about both man and God, from God''s perspective. I am not entirely comfortable with the lyric "I need your hurt/ I need your pain", if this song is interpreted as being sung from God''s perspective. I think I can see where the writer is getting at (namely, that God needs us to surrender our hurts and pains to him), but it''s easily misinterpreted as God needing our hurts and pains in order to be God. I hope that makes sense. It''s kinda hard to explain in words, haha. Maybe a lyric change would help, but we would also have to be careful with the misinterpretations that can come with the line following that, "It''s not love any other way", because we don''t want to give off the impression that God''s love is conditional.', 38, '2014-06-08 06:56:27'),
(1343, 634, 'Oh man, this is one of my all-time favorite worship songs! I love the journey it takes from pure adoration of God''s creativity and power, then to the fact that Jesus died and rose again for us, and then to the triumphant day when we enter heaven''s gates in eternal life. The verses all have the same melody, so the audience can focus a bit more on the words. This also means that dynamics are super important in this song, to keep it engaging. Maybe we can even try multiple soloists for this song, one for each verse or something.', 38, '2014-06-08 07:02:28'),
(1344, 511, 'I like the mashup idea ^', 38, '2014-06-08 07:16:23'),
(1345, 658, 'The lines, "This is my kingdom come" and "It''s where my demons hide" do not sit well with me, since I feel like they''re not easily changed to something that makes sense theologically with this song (or maybe I''m not thinking hard enough lol. I''m open to ideas). We aren''t out to make the world "our" kingdom, per se; it''s about the kingdom of God. I also don''t think it makes sense to sing about demons living inside of us when we have the spirit of God living inside of us. Feel free to ask me more about my theological views on this, if you would like more explanation. I agree with Ruth''s point about pop and reaching non-Christians, so I''m all for lyric changes that make sense.', 38, '2014-06-08 07:26:21'),
(1346, 656, 'I think this is a relatively accessible song to non-Christians because there''s less Christianese in it, even though it''s a worship song.', 38, '2014-06-08 19:49:16'),
(1347, 637, 'haha this would be awesome if we could get a good a cappella arrangement together. I just wonder how the message of this song can tie into an overall set/skit message because it''s very specific. Definitely not against it being in the set if it works, though.', 38, '2014-06-08 19:54:34'),
(1348, 656, 'It''s pretty okay, in my initial opinion. Decent, but not striking. It''s madly repetitive and narrow scoped, which I find to be one of the bigger reasons why I''m not fond of this choice, and I do wonder if some other songs in the suggestion pool may perform the role better. Otherwise, I''m never much of a fan of borrowing another group''s arrangements, but that''s more of a personal preference.', 40, '2014-06-09 00:37:14'),
(1349, 675, 'I''m not sure where the whole analogy comes in. I can see a few places here and there that seem to follow what you put down, but some of those are also sort of confusing/convoluted. But who knows if lyric changes fix that (a lot would be necessary). My real problem would be that I think the main theme of the song, "mirrors", doesn''t actually have any place here. God''s the other half that we''re missing? God''s a reflection of ourselves? Not sure. I''m not sure if that could be resolved without singing pretty much another song. ', 40, '2014-06-09 04:03:34'),
(1350, 509, 'Our current version is a 4 part GLAD arrangement with solo. Can''t be fully considered a hymn for practical purposes, but it''s still really cool. Funky chords though. ', 40, '2014-06-09 04:15:34'),
(1351, 676, 'I agree, it''s pretty. I can also envision different layering/rhythmic changes that could make this song go at a more energetic pace if desired (still mellow at the right places). ', 40, '2014-06-09 05:47:24'),
(1352, 641, 'Kristina (Meiji): I feel like this would be a boring arrangement. Lyrics are cool, but very repetitive. Maddie: Also worried about a cappella translation. Caitlin: Columbia''s Jubilation sang this at BIDB! *listen* Kristina: eh. ', 37, '2014-06-09 22:50:25'),
(1353, 593, 'Song Listening Party Comments: Kristina: I''m in love with the chord progressions, musically I''m in love with it. Lyrically, I''m having difficulty seeing how this is Christ pointing. Blurb required. Meiji: I think it would get a little apathetic, and people would just start dragging.', 37, '2014-06-09 22:57:16'),
(1354, 636, 'Song Listening Party Comments: Ruth: I wonder if it might be confusing to the audience (lyrically).', 37, '2014-06-09 23:00:51'),
(1355, 598, 'Song Listening Party Comments: Caitlin: It sounds like a country song. Ruth: It sounds really pretty! Like compose me. Kristina: I was thinking more Like an Avalanche. I really like the lyrics- going from Jesus''s death to his resurrection is common, but people don''t really talk about that time in between. I think that''s a cool perspective. Maddie: I really love the duet, but I''m worried because the essence of the song is in the bass. Kristina: Oh, I thought it was in the perc, so I was worried.', 37, '2014-06-09 23:06:13'),
(1356, 262, 'Caitlin: I love it. I hate that it''s a ballad, but I think it''s a good different take on the reason we sing. Kristina: If this were done, it would be nice if it was a girl solo- there are other songs that we need to use the guys on. Meiji: We could speak more to what Jesus as a treasure is in the skit if need be. I think this could work well as arrangement- it''s really pretty.', 37, '2014-06-09 23:11:38'),
(1357, 11, 'Song Listening Party Comments: Ruth: I really like it! Kristina: If I was still in Cross Products... Our arrangement is good and really fun- Kellie arranged it. ', 37, '2014-06-09 23:16:19'),
(1358, 590, 'Song Listening Party Comments: Kristina - The prechorus is the same chord progression as The Start of Something New. #justsayin. Ruth: I like the music, the energy, and the lyrics. It''s one of those semi-secular songs that we sing. I think it''s pretty fitting. Maddie: I like the fact that it''s secular. People know who the artist is, and it will be interesting for our audience to hear it from a Christian perspective. Alvin: My positive comment is that people will recognize it. I don''t know what you''re talking about with the chord progression. Kristina: It''s a girl power song.', 37, '2014-06-09 23:21:23'),
(1359, 653, 'Song Listening Party Comments: Meiji: We need a really good soloist, and I''m not sure we have one of those. Caitlin: People scream at riffs at BIDB. Maybe xprods could do them if given the opportunity. Alvin: It''s maybe too slow. Double time is feasible. Still slower than other songs. I could get bored within the first minute. ', 37, '2014-06-09 23:29:06'),
(1360, 484, 'Song Listening Party Comments: Caitlin: This is a happy song I sing to myself (on my way to finals)! Alvin: Out of the songs we''ve gone through in the past few years, this is the epitome of a happy, joyful, praise song. This fills the happy praise song slot better than other songs of its type. This has energy and words and is not secular. I hope we sing it better.', 37, '2014-06-09 23:37:49'),
(1361, 542, 'Song Listening Party Comments: Alvin: It''s slow. It''s repetitive. It''s a bit boring. Caitlin: Depends on the arrangement.', 37, '2014-06-09 23:41:31'),
(1362, 650, 'Song Listening Party Comments: Kristina: Theological concern: It is not God''s job to make us happy. I would not want Cross Products preaching the prosperity gospel. Alvin: If there are lyric changes necessary, we need to have them by the time song suggestions end so that people vote on the version of the song that would sing. ', 37, '2014-06-09 23:49:40'),
(1363, 689, 'I think the lyrics really paint a picture of what life is like without God.. and how He is the answer (:', 52, '2014-06-09 23:51:51'),
(1364, 648, 'Ruth: I do like the fact that this makes me think of the fact that God is both personal and absolute. Kristina: I really like the lyrics. I think one of the things that it addresses is that people could think that Christians are brainwashed and believe everything they hear. But this says that Christians do question it. Caitlin: I think of this as the message of God is God and I am not- I can''t completely understand it. But that might sit the opposite way with NCs.', 37, '2014-06-09 23:57:03'),
(1365, 643, 'Song Listening Party: Ruth: I really like the lyrics before the bridge/during the bridge. It reminds me of HDTFLFU. Maddie: They are really powerful statements, but I''m not sure if everyone will understand them.', 37, '2014-06-10 00:03:58'),
(1366, 689, 'Ruth and Caitlin: I like the lyrics of the last verse. Alvin: If you guys are looking for massive diversity and happen to have 17 songs...otherwise don''t take up a slot for it.', 37, '2014-06-10 00:10:30'),
(1367, 651, 'Ruth: The lyrics are very worship-filled, but there''s no explanation for an audience (not good for performance). ', 37, '2014-06-10 00:17:52'),
(1368, 511, 'Song Listening Party: Kristina: I''m not convinced an a cappella arrangement could do this song justice. *Listen to Jubilation''s arrangement BIDB 2012. Kristina: I''m not feeling it. People would like it because they know it, not because it''s a good arrangement. It''s a great song though. ', 37, '2014-06-10 00:23:22'),
(1369, 445, 'Song Listening Party: Kristina: Alvin and I have concerns with this song. It''s petty. Okay, so it''s not really petty, it''s more... personal? Never mind. Alvin: It''s poorly worded. Kristina: Yes.', 37, '2014-06-10 00:31:00'),
(1370, 687, 'hmm.. I wish it didn''t keep saying like.. live like He''s alive, pray like He''s listening.. etc.. He IS alive and He IS listening... ', 52, '2014-06-10 00:34:04'),
(1371, 676, 'Song Listening Party: Ruth: I really like it... the chasing a million things. How she gave her heart to the world but wants it back Maddie: agrees with Meiji''s previous comment. Caitlin: Ughhh all the ballads... I really like this though. It''s super pretty. And it would be a great solo for many xprod girls. Alvin: For one of those slower songs, I actually like it a lot.', 37, '2014-06-10 00:39:07'),
(1372, 462, 'Song Listening Party: Consensus: It hasn''t been done too recently (xprod, not xlinked). Alvin: high tenor or power alto.', 37, '2014-06-10 00:46:36'),
(1373, 657, 'Caitlin: I like this song musically and message-wise. I feel like I am marching in the dark a lot. But you keep going, because hope is alive.', 37, '2014-06-10 00:58:37'),
(1374, 664, 'Song Listening Party: Ruth: I really like it! I like how it recounts the gospel and the lines Don''t you see, He did all this for you. Kristina: I think it''s a weird mismatch between the music genre and the message. Alvin: It''s very much like a song you would sing at church camp.', 37, '2014-06-10 01:05:09'),
(1375, 642, 'Song Listening Party: Meiji: It reminds me of Meant to Live... but I don''t like the part "is there more than what I''ve been handed" because God gave it to us in the first place?', 37, '2014-06-10 01:10:56'),
(1376, 642, 'Song Listening Party: Kristina: It''s a really fun arrangement. Alvin: You heard the alums sing it. Kristina: They were having a good time.', 37, '2014-06-10 01:16:23'),
(1377, 679, 'Song Listening Party: Kristina: Isa pretty. Alvin: Maybe as a mashup? Kristina: I think it''s really cool. I like the lyrics All the walls you built up Are just glass on the outside because people think of walls as solid- you can''t see through them. The person who''s singing it says I know you have this exterior, but we see through it, and we want you to know that there''s something more. We don''t judge you by it. Alvin: I wish it were more interesting. That''s why I initially suggested it as a mashup. Maybe it''s just because I can''t see how I would arrange it, but someone else might be able to. ', 37, '2014-06-10 01:25:16'),
(1378, 646, 'Meiji: I don''t get it. Ruth: I was looking for Becky''s interpretation, but..."it''s such a shame for us to part." But something that''s this famous, people would want to hear. Alvin: theological concern until proven otherwise.', 37, '2014-06-10 01:30:02'),
(1379, 670, 'Song Listening Party: Caitlin: It feels very romantic to me... love, thy will be done. Alvin: I just find it boring. Agreement.', 37, '2014-06-10 01:34:50'),
(1380, 138, 'Song Listening Party: Kristina: Choreo. Never again. It''s very meh. 3. Alvin: It''s okay. 3.4.', 37, '2014-06-10 01:38:27'),
(1383, 24, 'Song Listening Party: Alvin: People over spring break were really touched by this song. After the homeless shelter gig, a lot of the guys said this was really cool. Ruth: I thought it sounded exciting.', 37, '2014-06-10 01:46:31'),
(1384, 597, 'Song Listening Party: Kristina: I''m meh about it. Some of the lyrics...I''d have to think about it. Caitlin: I think this could be really cute a cappella style.', 37, '2014-06-10 01:50:53'),
(1385, 207, 'Kristina: I''m worried about the exposed parts. Martin: But they are mostly words. Alvin: I wasn''t very impressed by the arrangement. It sounds like Kindred Spirit.', 37, '2014-06-10 01:59:17'),
(1386, 650, 'added changed lyrics! tried my best', 47, '2014-06-10 03:00:20'),
(1387, 248, '@Alvin: yeah, I totally get that. I''m just worried part of our audience will not understand that intention.', 38, '2014-06-10 04:08:23'),
(1388, 686, 'I think this would be a fun arrangement when translated to a cappella', 38, '2014-06-10 05:03:56'),
(1389, 667, 'Interesting... I''ve never thought of that interpretation before. I always took this song to mean that we can only have true intimacy when we let ourselves be vulnerable (in this context talking about our relationship with God, but it really applies to all relationships). I can see how the other interpretation would be misleading, though.', 50, '2014-06-10 21:07:38'),
(1390, 687, '^ ditto. Could we change the lyrics?', 38, '2014-06-11 05:02:48'),
(1391, 688, 'Man... I like the verses. It''s a shame that the first thing I thought of when hearing the chorus was the cultural connotations of "rainbows" (and my second thought was about leprechauns lol). Good overarching message, though.', 38, '2014-06-11 05:47:03'),
(1392, 649, 'I like the mashup idea, especially if we just sample parts of "Rather Be" to fit into "Set a Fire" or change the lyrics to be more relevant.', 38, '2014-06-11 05:51:17'),
(1393, 113, 'THAT WOULD BE SO COOL. That being said though, I think it would require a blurb (perhaps) to explain to non-Christians what "holy" means and stuff like that. I feel like without that basic understanding, a large part of the meaning behind the song would be lost.', 38, '2014-06-11 05:58:26'),
(1394, 248, 'Ahhhh mashup with Human by Christina Perri?', 37, '2014-06-12 16:07:19'),
(1395, 248, 'Ahhhh mashup with Human by Christina Perri? Maybe too late now though', 37, '2014-06-12 16:08:14'),
(1396, 640, 'I really like this idea!!!!!  I was actually thinking about the song Burn during Church this morning, and how the lyrics of the chorus (When the light started out-gonna let it burn burn burn burn) really seem to be the idea of Pentacost and the Holy Spirit given to all His disciples to spread His word, similar to what we do in Cross Products', 55, '2014-06-16 04:45:52'),
(1397, 655, 'I love the images this song brings up with the angel armies with us... showing that he is always there to help us.  It reminds me of a prayer at my church: "May the Lord walk ahead of you to guide you, may He be at your side, giving you strength, and may He walk behind you should you fall."', 55, '2014-06-18 02:36:11'),
(1398, 641, 'Xprod goes multicultural?! I can totally envision an arrangement that allows for Spanish to be in the mix.', 38, '2014-06-18 04:31:02'),
(1399, 21, 'We would need a really energetic and compelling soloist to pull this off', 38, '2014-06-18 04:35:22'),
(1400, 659, 'we would need a really engaging soloist, especially if the arrangement is whole notes and perc. I like the vibe, though.', 38, '2014-06-18 04:47:39'),
(1401, 262, 'agreed with Caitlin. Musically, I was bored by the second verse. But it could have a potentially pretty a cappella arrangement.', 38, '2014-06-18 05:12:31'),
(1402, 648, 'Ehh... I can see where the songwriter is coming from, but I would much rather have a song that has a same message but keeps the focus on God instead of on the singer.', 38, '2014-06-18 05:17:13'),
(1403, 634, 'We would need a blurb to explain the church as the bride of Christ (might be a bit confusing for non-Christians). I also think the repetition might lose some people, depending on the arrangement.', 50, '2014-06-18 15:56:55'),
(1404, 598, 'Christ''s death wouldn''t mean much if He didn''t then rise.', 50, '2014-06-18 16:36:23'),
(1405, 683, 'What words are the background parts saying?', 50, '2014-06-19 17:21:03'),
(1406, 658, 'I''m not sure minor lyric changes would fix the theological problems I see in this song. The main message seems to be that the singer is hell bound because of the demons inside him, so he doesn''t want the other person to get too close and become corrupted (it''s all about protecting this other person''s innocence, which is not aligned with the message of God we''re trying to convey). Also, the singer keeps saying things like "I say it''s up to fate / It''s woven in my soul" and "I can''t escape this now," which seems to exclude God''s power to save. Also, +1 for everything Polly said.', 50, '2014-06-19 17:49:03'),
(1407, 664, 'At first, I thought the repetition of the chorus was a bad response to the non-Christian''s continuing concerns, but now I think the repetition serves to show that Christianity is more than just about what a man did 2000 years ago. If Jesus was just a historic figure who lived and died, it wouldn''t mean anything. However, that is just the end of the beginning of the story -- Jesus is so much more than that (God himself who walked among us, our savior & redeemer who died for our sins, the one who conquered the grave so that we too might live again). My only concern is that this song doesn''t really go deeply into that whole other aspect of who Jesus actually is, so it would need to be paired up with another song to explain it.', 50, '2014-06-19 18:00:01'),
(1408, 465, '@Becky: Adoremus (Johns Hopkins)', 50, '2014-06-19 18:15:20'),
(1409, 465, 'I like how Adoremus added "Kyrie Eleison" (meaning, "Lord have mercy") in the background parts. +1 on Martin''s comment. Also, one Christian interpretation of the lines "When you''re too in love to let it go / But if you never try you''ll never know / Just what you''re worth" is "you''re too in love with this world, so you''ll never know just how much you''re worth to God."', 50, '2014-06-19 18:23:04'),
(1410, 248, 'The lyrics remind me of God''s response to Job (see Job 38-42).', 50, '2014-06-19 19:08:16'),
(1411, 665, 'I''m concerned that this song might be too slow to be engaging, but I can see parts of it being worked into the background parts of another song.', 50, '2014-06-19 19:12:28'),
(1412, 680, 'I''m really confused by the lyrics. What perspective is this song from and to whom is it sung? Is it a song about human love & relationships, or about God? I looked up many interpretations online and while there are obvious references to Biblical characters (David, Samson, etc), it''s unclear whether the message is supporting Christianity, mocking Christianity, or just using the imagery to describe lust / love / heartbreak. If this song is not about God, then what is the meaning behind using the word "Hallelujah," meaning "praise the LORD"? I have theological concerns with other parts of the lyrics, as well. "Maybe theres a God above" questions the very existence of God. "You say I took the name in vain / I don''t even know the name / But if I did, well, really, what''s it to you?" describes a total lack of respect for the name of God. These, along with sexual references (according to some interpretations) and other things, make it hard for me to understand this song and deem it theologically sound. Someone please clarify if you have a better understanding.', 50, '2014-06-19 19:56:29'),
(1413, 466, 'Yes, as Christians and friends in community, we are supposed to build each other up and carry each other''s burdens, and I agree that we should be bearers of light to those who live in darkness. However, I would prefer to sing a song that points the audience back to Christ and what he has done / can do, and is not as focused on what we have failed to do.', 50, '2014-06-19 20:22:44'),
(1414, 666, 'I really like the repetition of "Emmanuel," which means "God with us." It''s so beautiful that God came to be with us; we longed for Him, we needed Him, we called for Him, and He came.', 50, '2014-06-19 21:17:59'),
(1415, 640, 'It seems like this mash-up addresses many different aspects of the fire (representing the light of Christ/the Holy Spirit) in our lives: it burns brightly to show the world that we are His witnesses (Matthew 5), it burns our sins away to purify us (Isaiah 6), it burns to guide us (Exodus 13:21-22, Psalm 119:105)... A good blurb would be needed to explain this, especially to a secular audience who would probably just identify it as a mash-up of popular music.', 50, '2014-06-19 21:36:08'),
(1416, 687, 'Changing lyrics might be a bit awkward because the lyric we''re changing is the title of the song... but I agree with changing it.', 50, '2014-06-19 21:43:33'),
(1417, 609, 'Concern for our non-Christian audience: I think it may come across as a pushy to say "You and I embrace surrender / you and I choose to believe" to someone who doesn''t actually believe.', 50, '2014-06-19 21:58:45'),
(1418, 675, 'Ditto what Alvin said. One of the confusing parts of trying to make this song apply to our relationship with Jesus is that I can''t figure out whose perspective this is supposed to be from. For example, it seems to be us talking to God, but then God doesn''t reflect us (we reflect Him)...', 50, '2014-06-19 22:09:42'),
(1419, 680, 'I see where you''re coming from Meiji.... I''m trying to think of lyric edits, however I''m not having much success in coming up with something cohesive.  There''s a few lines in this song that I really like, but I think that this song might require too much lyric change..  I''m open to any proposed lyric changes... but I was hoping when I suggested it that I could think of something. and I''m stuck...', 55, '2014-06-19 23:56:54'),
(1420, 666, 'Especially since our concert is so close to Christmas... and during Advent... the word Emmanuel has always been associated with Advent for me, due to a hymn at my church. "For all who wait For all who hunger For all who''ve prayed For all who wander" really reminds me of Advent, followed by the words of Christmas.', 55, '2014-06-20 00:20:34'),
(1421, 662, 'I like the lyrics of this song, and I agree with Phoebe about the lyric change.  I don''t really know how the melody of the "I"s in the chorus will work in an arrangement however, but I really like the idea of this song that God is always with us through everything.', 55, '2014-06-20 00:29:45'),
(1422, 609, 'i love this song! but yeah i agree with meiji', 47, '2014-06-20 04:05:42'),
(1423, 597, 'I really like this one... the message is good, to always keep our eyes on God.  I also really like the duet within the song...', 55, '2014-06-20 21:28:30'),
(1424, 670, 'I like how this corresponds to the Lord''s Prayer with "thy will be done", however, I have a difficult time of seeing how it can be arranged for a cappella...', 55, '2014-06-20 21:32:40'),
(1425, 218, 'This song has a good message and all, but I don''t know if we can pull it off... it always sounds cheesy to me, no matter who sings it :/', 38, '2014-06-22 00:46:24'),
(1426, 644, 'Recognizable pop song, which has an underlying Christian message. I like how the lyrics deal with apathy, being burnt out, and needing purpose but saying that He has the love to see us through. Spring break friendly if we do minor lyric changes.', 38, '2014-06-22 00:53:46'),
(1427, 688, 'There''s not really any background melody/harmony.', 50, '2014-06-22 22:03:41'),
(1428, 649, 'I would be agree to a change of lyrics.', 50, '2014-06-22 22:10:08'),
(1429, 645, 'This sounds like a combination of Fools Marching + Sailing on a Ship, just less hopeful. I also am not a fan of the lines "Only change I see / Lost or found at sea / The only difference / Is believing I''ll make it in" because the difference between being lost and found isn''t blind belief. Also, our belief in Christ doesn''t end with vague hope for the future, but transforms our lives and changes the journeys that we are on in the present -- it''s about the journey more than the destination.', 50, '2014-06-22 22:38:41'),
(1430, 593, 'My interpretation of the lyrics (first verse & chorus): You had a problem and thought patience was the answer, so you were taken in and lulled into apathy. Now you need to be honest with yourself that you need saving.', 50, '2014-06-22 23:05:20'),
(1431, 595, 'The background is pretty cool, but we''d want an engaging soloist to really sell the song.', 50, '2014-06-22 23:10:59'),
(1432, 603, 'hmmm I definitely interpreted it more as "I can''t really be sure, but whatever, that''s just the way I am"...', 50, '2014-06-22 23:39:40'),
(1433, 688, 'Yeah I really like the first verse! Otherwise though...', 37, '2014-06-23 00:50:01'),
(1434, 637, 'I WANT TO SING THIS SO MUCH!!!!!!!!! (see comments from last semester)', 55, '2014-12-09 05:19:15'),
(1435, 218, 'Re-suggesting, because I think it''s a gorgeous song and spring break friendly.', 55, '2014-12-09 05:20:31'),
(1436, 692, 'Pre-arranged because I sang an a cappella version of this song in High School and we could use that.  4 part, gorgeous, easy to learn (like really easy to learn), dynamics do a lot for it.\r\n\r\nLyric-wise, praise/worship song acknowledging the great miracles of the Lord and how he died for us to save us from our sins.', 55, '2014-12-09 05:26:17'),
(1437, 693, 'I am picturing this song lyrically as a dialoge between us and God.  The parts like ''I won''t give up on us'' are coming from God''s perspective, and the ''I''m still looking up'' could be from our perspective, talking to God.  I can also see parts like "God knows I''m tough enough" etc. as us and our relationship with God, knowing that through Him, we can handle everything he throws at us because He is with us to guide us.  I see this song as a duet.  It''s well known, and I think we could put an interesting spin on the piece by introducing it as God''s perspective.', 55, '2014-12-09 05:38:37'),
(1438, 694, 'This song was actually recommended to me for xprod to sing by one of my friends.  I see some potential issues with specific lyrics (which could probably be changed), but overall I think the essence is pretty true.  I''m not saying that you don''t have to try to be loved by God, but I think the idea that is the essence of the song, and the essence of why I''m suggesting this is that you don''t have to change every aspect of your personality to be loved by God.  God loves who you are, and you only have to listen to his plan for you.  Also, God sees all of who you are, so you can''t put on a better face for Him.  He knows everything, and God loves you just the way you are.', 55, '2014-12-09 05:53:14'),
(1439, 696, 'Here comes the Disney Song! I think the lyrics itself is not really powerful but has somewhat straightforward Chirstian truth. Also it''s Disney-theme popularity and African-style beat can add some variety of genre of our performances.', 54, '2014-12-09 06:57:58'),
(1440, 697, 'I love how catchy this song is- it just gets better as you listen to it more and more. I also love how it shows how much joy we can have in trusting God. It''s not just that we are putting all our trust in Him in an intense "Oceans" way, but that we can rejoice in His promise.', 37, '2014-12-10 23:08:53'),
(1441, 695, 'BC-ATC did it and it was absolutely great. The context was that we love and we love one another because God first loved us. \r\n\r\nIf y''all ever end up choosing to expand the set beyond those that mostly focus on ''self to God'' or ''God''s glory'' and instead decide to look for songs that apply more of this ''love your neighbor because God first loved us'' type of message, I think this song could potentially sound good and be impactful (arranged in a non-xprod style). +1 girl solo bonus', 40, '2014-12-12 23:27:59'),
(1442, 443, 'Psalms 8. It also speaks to how we are so small and insignificant compared to God, and yet He still loves us. I know that even nonchristians feel overwhelmed and insignificant at times when they look at what looms against them, and I feel that this song speaks of how God loves lost and unlovable. ', 53, '2014-12-15 18:46:57'),
(1443, 699, 'This is a worship song. Thus, its focus lies more on the Christians in the audience. I like it because I feel that the biggest stumbling block for Christians at MIT is not oppression and persecution, but distraction. I''m referring to the "This pset is too important" "My future depends on this presentation" "I have to study" which get in the way of us and our friends going to church, being in fellowship with believers, reading the Bible, praying, etc. \r\n\r\nI also like that, in the key it is written in, the highest note is an E', 53, '2014-12-15 18:58:38'),
(1444, 700, 'Part of it is a duet (in the bridge) I think that it probably would work best with two guys, so we might not be able to do this song this semester...', 53, '2014-12-15 19:05:10'),
(1445, 700, 'MIT is certainly a place in which we all feel helpless at times. For some of us, all the time. This song is addressed as the desperate prayer of a Christian in a time of trial. Thus, I feel that its message is mostly for Christians. However, I find that, with myself, it is often my prayer, because we have confidence in this: that we can come before God and confess our weakness and plead Christ''s strength over us. ', 53, '2014-12-15 19:11:29'),
(1446, 132, 'I love this song! It speaks to anyone, Christian or not because we all know what it feels like to be alone and wanting someone to hold us as we fall apart. I particularly am touched by how it speaks, from the perspective of God, inviting us back into His loving embrace while we search for meaning in other things than Christ. We''re all searching for something, and the only one who can fill that God shaped hole is God. \r\n\r\nBTW I particularly like the bridge in this song. \r\n\r\nPS Dartmouth X.Ado also has an arrangement of this song', 53, '2014-12-15 19:59:14'),
(1447, 164, 'This song is thematically similar to Baba Yetu and Revelation song, not because the lyrical meaning or tunes are similar, but because the role it plays in our set. It is a song involving the uniting of Christians across the board to worship God. In many ways, it is the foretaste of heaven where we shall worship God together with the peoples of all times, places, races, and cultures for forever. ', 53, '2014-12-15 20:11:22'),
(1448, 30, 'They say above that this needs to be REarranged...\r\n\r\nCaitlin captures the heart of the message well, but I want to add this:\r\n\r\n"And I''ll praise You in this storm\r\nAnd I will lift my hands\r\nFor You are who You are\r\nNo matter where I am\r\nAnd every tear I''ve cried\r\nYou hold in Your hand\r\nYou never left my side"\r\n\r\nWe praise God for who He is: worthy of praise. His grace is sufficient for us, but, as the beginning of the song states, God''s grace is given according to His goodness, not our need. That said, our circumstances, our suffering, even our failure as Christians and the failure of the church do not change who God is ("For You are who You are, No matter where I am"). \r\n\r\nAnd yet, though God owes us nothing and gives grace according to His goodness, not our need, He chooses to be with us in the storm and He holds every tear we cry in His hands. I can''t convey the tears in my eyes as I write this. His grace does not come in a faucet which we can open and close, but we can "say Amen" even in the rain because we know that our God is good, and that His love for us would move the sun, moon and stars to bring us home. ', 53, '2014-12-15 20:24:35'),
(1449, 619, 'Clarifying the comment above: This means that we can sing this in venues where we aren''t allowed to be explicit. \r\n\r\nI think that the line which holds it to Christ even outside of context is: "I''d be building my kingdom just to watch it fade away."  For the Kingdom of God is an everlasting kingdom, and "the kingdoms of this world has become the kingdoms of our Lord"', 53, '2014-12-15 20:35:28'),
(1450, 619, 'I also think that we might want to change this to a girl solo. Except, in our culture, guys are more commonly thought of as wanting to forage their own way, making their own kingdoms, etc. (in a dramatic external fashion)', 53, '2014-12-15 20:37:27'),
(1451, 701, 'I feel that we could do the type of a cappella arrangement that Alvin wants to do...', 53, '2014-12-15 20:58:51'),
(1452, 702, 'I suggested this song because it is really beautiful, and already has a choral feel. (ie I think that it would be easier to make a more traditional a cappella arrangement for it, even just by transposing what we can hear). \r\n\r\nI like the song because I find it as the desire of my heart often. \r\n\r\nHowever, it does use a lot of Bible references, and it is a prayer (of sorts) so it might not be so good for our non Christian audience. That said, it is really pretty, so I imagine that they would still appreciate it if done well.', 53, '2014-12-15 21:09:32'),
(1453, 703, 'This goes right into the message of grace. Grace alone is not the full gospel, but this covers the topic of grace pretty well.\r\n\r\n', 53, '2014-12-15 21:21:37'),
(1454, 15, 'I feel myself praying this song because it is our mission here on earth. Our mission is not fundamentally to increase the size of our churches or have more people wear crosses. Our mission is to shine the love of Christ into everyone that we encounter, and this cannot be accomplished without wanting to see our friends and enemies brought into direct contact with the God. It is God who''s love makes our love look like muddy puddles in comparison to the ocean. \r\n\r\nAnd how can we love unless God gives us His eyes for our brothers, those He loves.', 53, '2014-12-15 22:11:57'),
(1455, 26, 'This song is from the perspective of God. It is, IMHO, the corollary to Indescribable. Here we have God saying look at all the universe which proclaims how great I Am and how small you are. And yet, I chose to love you  and to exalt you as the pinnacle of all My creation. ', 53, '2014-12-15 22:20:49'),
(1456, 420, 'Echo Ruth: This is the reason we sing: because Christ in everything! :)\r\n\r\nThis song sets my heart on fire. Because it is our purpose and greatest joy proclaim the Christ is everything.', 53, '2014-12-15 22:25:21'),
(1457, 138, 'I love the song, but it relies mostly on the heavy bass line and drum set. From Caitlin''s commentary it looks like we need a new arrangement. (And such an arrangement would not be possible to do in the traditional a cappella style as it would kill the rock feel of the song)', 53, '2014-12-15 22:37:17'),
(1458, 704, 'This is derived from the Apostles Creed. I''m not entirely sure what sort of a role it would play in a set, but it is really a uniting point if we were going to sing something at a church, for instance.', 53, '2014-12-15 22:52:37'),
(1459, 705, 'Pentatonix arrangement can be purchased online...\r\n\r\nOr rewritten\r\n', 53, '2014-12-15 23:49:49'),
(1460, 705, 'As you can hopefully tell, this is a love song, not a Christian song...\r\n\r\nThat said, I think that if we were willing to sing it baptized it could fit in to our set. (See suggested edits to the lyrics)\r\n\r\nI suggested this because using pop music allows for us to better engage our non Christian which, generally speaking, does not listen to much Christian soft rock and pop. "Let it Shine" and "Unconditionally" were generally appreciated more, in part, because our audience recognized the songs. ', 53, '2014-12-15 23:53:12'),
(1461, 706, 'This is a song praising who God is.\r\n\r\nIt might not be so interesting if we arranged it as it could be arranged more chorally (?)', 53, '2014-12-16 23:21:08'),
(1462, 669, 'ditto polly!\r\nadded another link of this baptized version :3', 47, '2014-12-17 02:46:43'),
(1463, 679, '"When you come to where you''re broken within, the light meets the dark"\r\n\r\nSo good!', 53, '2014-12-18 23:09:28'),
(1464, 28, 'This is about how we find our identity and worth as children of God. It is made more poignant by juxtaposing this message with the ever present voice that condemns us as failures. I think that this idea of feeling unworthy, and feeling the weight of real and false failure is very relatable and pertinent to all MIT students.\r\n\r\nAlso, apart from "Christ" once, this song is "clean" for secular gigs. ', 53, '2014-12-18 23:32:49'),
(1465, 471, 'That God would go through such lengths to find and save us who are so helpless is amazing.\r\n"You called and you shouted\r\nbroke through my deafness"\r\n\r\nI feel that this song speaks to depression: people trapped in darkness, unable to get out. But even if it is self inflicted lostness and confusion, God finds us and calls us back to life.', 53, '2014-12-18 23:37:58'),
(1466, 707, 'this would be really spring break friendly! i''ve been trying to think of a good thing to mash it up with though (something that points to God more explicitly) but can''t think of anything.. but this is totally crying out "mashup" to me, especially at the end with the oh''s!\r\nideas?', 47, '2014-12-19 20:13:00'),
(1467, 117, 'This song reminds me of "Lifesong" by Casting Crowns, in that it''s a cry for our lives to be a life of worship completely surrendered to the Lord, that it might be a sweet sound to the Lord when we meet face to face. "Therefore, I urge you, brothers and sisters, in view of Gods mercy, to offer your bodies as a living sacrifice, holy and pleasing to Godthis is your true and proper worship." -- Romans 12:1', 38, '2014-12-19 20:20:42'),
(1468, 709, 'This is a very straightforward worship song that encapsulates the gospel and what it means to be saved by the cross. I love the position of victory that it takes, and the juxtaposition between the humility and the grandeur of God.', 38, '2014-12-19 20:27:12'),
(1469, 708, 'This is a beautiful arrangement of a traditional song/chant. This prayer is very sweet and simple, especially since TAN decided to shorten it to only include two stanzas of the original lyrics. Idea: if we want to have a guys/girls only song, I can see this being one of them.', 50, '2014-12-19 20:31:45'),
(1470, 710, 'I love the juxtaposition between heaven and earth in this song, between God and man. It''s a song that flows out of a place of intimacy and head-over-heels love for God, and I think it''s rarely captured in such a poignant song.\r\n\r\nMusically, I really like the acoustic version because it shows the emotion and has less cheesy (in my opinion) instrumentation. I honestly can''t really stand the album version lol. I included it here for completeness, though.', 38, '2014-12-19 20:33:15'),
(1471, 711, 'This song is a lament for the fall of man and all that we lost; I think the chorus repetition of "In the cool of the day we walked together" emphasizes that the greatest thing we lost was our communion with God himself. This genre is different from xprod''s normal style, but I think it could be a very cool a cappella arrangement. (Note: I marked it as having no soloist, since that''s how I would arrange it.)', 50, '2014-12-19 20:39:36'),
(1472, 712, 'I absolutely LOVE the power behind this song! It''s such a great testament to God''s unrelenting passion and love for us, and we can''t run away from it even if we tried! I also love how it rephrases verses from Romans 8 into such a singable, anthemic bridge.', 38, '2014-12-19 20:41:00'),
(1473, 713, 'This song reminds me of John 15:5, Jeremiah 17:7-8, and the parable of the prodigal son. If we are not rooted in Christ, we die. However, the beautiful thing about Christ and His love, is that He forgives us for leaving Him and welcomes us back with open arms.', 50, '2014-12-19 20:45:50'),
(1474, 714, 'Musically, I think this would be a really pretty translation into a cappella. I love this song because of the posture of faith it takes, no matter whether we understand what God is doing or not. God is the anchor for our souls, and this writer is truly coming from that stance. It''s an intimate, steadfast love that isn''t weathered by external circumstance.', 38, '2014-12-19 20:47:14'),
(1475, 715, 'This song is about the journey and process of following God. His presence is the treasure that we seek, and even though we''re just a work in progress, it''s the pursuit and hunger for God that keeps us going. I love that this song comes from a posture of victory and positivity. I feel like this could serve as a good song to encourage Christians in the audience to pursue God wholeheartedly.', 38, '2014-12-19 20:53:02'),
(1476, 716, 'This song is sung from God''s perspective and comes from a place of such love and intimacy, which sets it apart. Sometimes we''re so reluctant to give God the parts of our hearts and lives that are too difficult or painful to confront, but God relentlessly pursues us despite that. This song is about transformation, and hope that God will bring beauty from pain.', 38, '2014-12-19 20:59:08'),
(1477, 717, 'love these lyrics "But You are a Savior and You take brokenness aside and make it beautiful"', 47, '2014-12-19 21:33:16'),
(1478, 718, 'Not all the lyrics work, but it could work in a mashup about us pursuing God/vice-versa. For Nursen :p', 37, '2014-12-19 22:08:01'),
(1479, 75, 'Bravery. It takes a lot of courage to step out on shadowfeet and start walking toward a land you''ve only ever heard of, to push through distractions and fears, and to have enough faith to trust that in the end you''ll be found in Christ. This is the calling of every one of us.', 50, '2014-12-19 22:17:31'),
(1480, 720, 'I love the lyrics for this song -- God, please take everything that I am and everything that I have for Your glory. We are not our own. We are  just stewards of everything God has given us: our money, our talents, our time, our intellect, our bodies. This could be really pretty if done more like the original hymn, but I''ve put the Chris Tomlin version since the hymn might be too repetitive (would depend on the arrangement).', 50, '2014-12-19 23:30:52'),
(1481, 721, 'MC Jin is so awesome! He is a secular rapper-turned Christian. his lyrics are very real and his flow is so good :) \r\n\r\ndownsides to this song: we need a rapper, and the lyrics may be a bit personal to him (and therefore a little weird to do an a cappella cover unless we change the lyrics)', 47, '2014-12-19 23:41:49'),
(1482, 722, 'Just because we weren''t made for this world and this life doesn''t mean that this life isn''t worth something. I also think this song would be really fun to sing!', 50, '2014-12-19 23:46:46'),
(1483, 723, 'can be viewed as singing from God''s perspective; changed that one line about not knowing how life will be(see lyrics above) to make it work better', 47, '2014-12-19 23:57:09');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(1484, 724, 'john legend''s "favorite church song". lyrics recognize that life is not easy and struggles come. even amidst the struggles, though, God is there! i uploaded the john legend version (not as good quality) and a slightly different version by fred hammond', 47, '2014-12-20 00:24:51'),
(1485, 725, 'i''m not 100% about this song but i thought i''d suggest it to see what you guys think. it''s a song of repentance (though christina aguilera''s specific repentance.. could change the 2-3 lines to generalize if needed)... doesn''t musically sound like the kind of prayers you usually hear, and it''s a pretty powerful song... strong soloist is a must', 47, '2014-12-20 01:50:05'),
(1486, 725, 'also if it gives context, christina aguilera has a catholic background (which explains the language she uses in this song)', 47, '2014-12-20 01:54:46'),
(1487, 726, 'God is higher and stronger than any and all of our fears and problems. He is the Rock!\r\n\r\nUCSD, USC, TCNJ (from bidb), and BU''s mustard seed have all done this song so we could probably ask for the arrangement if we decide to do this song', 47, '2014-12-20 02:42:51'),
(1488, 727, 'one of my favorite hymns!', 47, '2014-12-20 03:11:04'),
(1489, 728, 'if we want to do a multilingual thing again... :)\r\ncornell''s measureless has done this before so we would probably get the arrangement (and korean/english lyrics from them)', 47, '2014-12-20 03:29:03'),
(1490, 694, 'to reinforce that message i think a mashup with something more explicit would help!', 47, '2014-12-20 03:41:32'),
(1491, 649, 'i love rather be! but i can''t seem to think of ways to make it work without making major major lyric changes, unless we only use a couple lines from this song and intertwine a bit of it into another (a "one-sided" mashup)', 47, '2014-12-20 04:00:50'),
(1492, 596, 'ooooooh the mashup works pretty well!', 47, '2014-12-20 04:08:36'),
(1493, 431, 'since we learned this song a little bit already this would hopefully be quicker to learn this coming semester. but the reason we dropped it was the message seemed somewhat redundant with indescribable (was that the reason..?) if that was the reason, i''m not sure if we want to learn it for next semester if we have indescribable already.\r\nas for spring break, even for places that allow us to sing about God explicitly, a blurb would help a lot to clarify that this is sung from God''s perspective (may not be as obvious to some).. and i''m not sure how often we will be able to blurb this spring break', 47, '2014-12-20 04:20:39'),
(1494, 729, 'I was watching Hairspray a couple weeks ago and this song struck me as something that may be applicable for xprod.  I see it kind of as the journey we have to heaven, and the struggles being those of life that God helps us through.  Also, new musical genre...', 55, '2014-12-20 04:23:16'),
(1495, 705, 'thanks for putting the effort in rewriting the lyrics brian! i like :D', 47, '2014-12-20 04:25:24'),
(1496, 712, 'love this! "unstoppable love that never ends"', 47, '2014-12-20 04:30:33'),
(1497, 164, 'good news from university of michigan did this! linked above if you want to hear their a cappella version', 47, '2014-12-20 04:38:34'),
(1498, 672, 'I think when we''ve sung this within prayer, it always seems to be really powerful to me, and this song could express a lot of unspoken feelings if we could translate that power through an arrangement.', 55, '2014-12-20 04:46:45'),
(1499, 698, 'oooh i expected something kinda generic.. but it''s not! :)\r\nlyrics are representative of my personal prayer for the year! \r\n"everything my heart desires, Lord I want it all to be for You"', 47, '2014-12-20 05:27:11'),
(1500, 706, 'hmm perhaps, no soloist? it would be a different (more traditional a cappella -y) feel', 47, '2014-12-20 05:29:50'),
(1501, 695, 'HOLD UP. MAYBE WE COULD MASH THIS UP WITH ALICIA KEYS'' WE ARE HERE..?! \ni like this by itself too but i think it works well!!!', 47, '2014-12-20 10:07:17'),
(1502, 695, 'except idk if i like the repetitive "we''re only human"...song needs a bit more Jesus/a little more emphasis of how God first loved us', 47, '2014-12-20 05:54:35'),
(1503, 722, 'i like this a lot! maybe have it be a mashup with we are here or some other song to give a more specific idea of what having our lives "shine" in this broken world means!', 47, '2014-12-20 06:00:51'),
(1504, 726, 'Ahh my friend from my home church is in that UCSD video! :]', 38, '2014-12-20 07:43:21'),
(1505, 726, 'I just added the original Laura Hackett version to the Youtube links, for reference', 38, '2014-12-20 07:44:29'),
(1506, 730, 'I love the vibe of this song. So much soul! A huge plus is that this is a very different musical style from the rest of our repertoire. Would be a fun challenge to translate this to a cappella. Solid lyrics about the journey of following Jesus-- starting from darkness, encountering Jesus, and having a life transformed completely for His glory.', 38, '2014-12-20 10:03:30'),
(1507, 707, 'Hmm this might be a stretch musically and lyrically... maybe a mashup could be with "God of This City" by Chris Tomlin? The idea would be that God is ruler of the nations but also our city, and we''re here in this place and time to make an impact for God.', 38, '2014-12-20 10:14:19'),
(1508, 477, 'Ed Sheeran does an awesome a cappella loop pedal version, too. Different stylistic interpretation of a beautiful classic.', 38, '2014-12-20 10:22:30'),
(1509, 731, 'A well known hymn, with a message proclaiming how great and awesome God is.  i think this could be quote powerful if we managed to get an arrangement similar to the one above!', 58, '2014-12-20 16:34:00'),
(1510, 732, 'I think would be a great song to sing and we could get make and interesting arrangement.  Theologically, I think this song would be good to convey the message - particularly to non-Christians - of how Jesus died for our sins and why we rejoice in this.', 58, '2014-12-20 16:46:04'),
(1511, 697, 'lol she''s holding a fishbowl in the boat xD \r\nespecially love the first verse!', 47, '2014-12-20 18:04:09'),
(1512, 733, 'Crufty Alum here!  So take or leave this suggestion :).  I was home for break and my mom had been talking to me about how I can''t just try to be a Christian alone (had been talking about how I haven''t plugged myself in a church at a new city.)  When I started driving today, this song came on the radio.  Thought it was a unique but very true message compared to most CCM songs.  In college whenever I was overcome with sin I would just try to hide it from my friends, but I truly found help when I started to reach out to my Christian brothers and sisters for prayer and support.  I feel like this song communicates that message. ', 17, '2014-12-21 00:28:28'),
(1513, 0, '', 50, '2014-12-21 03:19:40'),
(1514, 738, 'The poetry of these lyrics are a compelling depiction of desiring and encountering God, and knowing that there''s more to this life than just life on earth. Reminds me of Romans 8, where it says that all creation waits in eager expectation of liberation.', 38, '2014-12-21 04:20:17'),
(1515, 742, 'Really this is just for the chorus. I think it could work as a mashup with a "God is God and I am Not" message. Thoughts/ideas?', 37, '2014-12-21 04:57:08'),
(1516, 746, 'bossa nova christian music?! what what? i love this type of music!\r\nlyrics are short, but echoes the reason we sing!', 47, '2014-12-21 05:15:22'),
(1517, 746, 'take that comment back about the short lyrics- i copied the wrong ones xD', 47, '2014-12-21 05:19:52'),
(1518, 700, 'maybe a minor detail, but maybe instead of "i''m asking You to be strong enough for the both of us", change to "i recognize You are strong enough for the both of us"', 47, '2014-12-21 05:25:14'),
(1519, 595, 'agree with meiji^', 47, '2014-12-21 05:43:37'),
(1520, 742, 'mashup with something like that would be awesome!', 47, '2014-12-21 05:49:17'),
(1521, 302, 'agree with kevin and rachel^ the musical "boredom" i think can kinda only be fixed if we add the skit to our set...\r\nnot relevant but when the guy says "and" and "again" he says "wand" and "wagain" it bothers me a lot lol\r\n', 47, '2014-12-21 05:57:28'),
(1522, 714, 'i really really love this!', 47, '2014-12-21 05:59:24'),
(1523, 733, 'sorry i keep trying to make a mashup happen, but i think this might work with We Are Here by alicia keys?!\r\n\r\n"our souls were brought together so that we could help each other" and "please don''t try to fight me, i am for you. we are not meant to live this life alone" work pretty well', 47, '2014-12-21 06:13:29'),
(1524, 719, 'love the music, and love the lyrics!', 47, '2014-12-21 06:34:27'),
(1525, 719, 'the music makes me want to listen to the lyrics- which is a good thing!', 47, '2014-12-21 06:36:06'),
(1526, 730, 'mmmm<3 ', 47, '2014-12-21 06:45:22'),
(1527, 733, 'some parts of the background sound like the "oh''s" in katy perry''s roar  :O', 47, '2014-12-21 07:09:42'),
(1528, 746, 'and one last comment: to give you all a sense of what this may be a cappella:\r\nbossa nova perc (perc explanation starts at 3:00 ish) : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mFKvpr6Seys\r\n\r\nimagine this background bossa nova line, but slower: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fy80kXxJsTI\r\n\r\nlastly this frank sinatra (?) song, a slower background bossa nova line: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_ALhQcpDo-g', 47, '2014-12-21 08:17:12'),
(1529, 719, 'I''m a melody person, so I really like this song because it''s fun to sing. More importantly, I like the message. To me, it''s about the "who is in the throne of your life" question and putting God in the driver''s seat, not just for most things but for every detail of your life. My alternative interpretation is someone who''s frustrated, angry even, that they can''t see how God is working through them but realizes that they don''t need to see the fruits of God''s work in their own life because it''s not about them. Back to the throne question.', 37, '2014-12-22 02:55:20'),
(1530, 703, 'I like how it''s a spin on the traditional Amazing Grace and might make people think more deeply about its lyrics. I can see it working with a hymn lead in/out like Never Change. ', 37, '2014-12-22 04:51:27'),
(1531, 443, 'Hmm... despite my above old comments, I don''t think they apply to next semester- I don''t think Brad''s SSATBB + Solo/Duet would be a good thing for our small group. It''d have to be a new arrangement. Still love the lyrics though. I think the chorus lyrics'' flow make the message really clear.', 37, '2014-12-22 04:55:56'),
(1532, 471, 'It''s a more positive version of "Bring Me To Life" since the singer has already been saved and isn''t searching.', 37, '2014-12-22 05:23:28'),
(1533, 597, 'Ditto Maddie. Love the duet, especially the a cappella part. And I like that the one part of the lyrics people can''t forget is "pray, pray, pray."', 37, '2014-12-22 05:27:10'),
(1534, 117, 'Soooo prettyyyyy. Reason/Testify/Lifesong message yes. I love the opening lyrics. It''s definitely a sweet sweet sound :)', 37, '2014-12-22 05:29:02'),
(1535, 708, 'YES Gregorian chants are my favorite. I can also see it as a guys/girls only song. Or tacked onto the beginning/end of something else.', 37, '2014-12-22 05:33:03'),
(1536, 711, 'Ahhhh harmony! Meiji, what are these crazy beautiful songs you have found? Musically I really like it, but it would need a blurb to explain it. I wouldn''t get it.', 37, '2014-12-22 05:37:31'),
(1537, 708, 'And it''s basically already arranged if we want to do it exactly the way they did. Someone just needs to transcribe it.', 37, '2014-12-22 05:49:52'),
(1538, 596, 'Another thought about the mashup: Nothing I Hold Onto by Will Reagan also works really well with Empty My Hands and Beautiful Things (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ma6syhsYvKw).', 50, '2014-12-22 23:31:29'),
(1539, 537, 'We sang this Spring 2013 -- it ended up being a mashup of Don''t You Worry and Child of Mine. (I''ve added the youtube).', 50, '2014-12-22 23:37:51'),
(1540, 734, 'Absolutely love the lyrics, I feel that it really speaks to me and I feel that it can be quite powerful for the listener (:', 52, '2014-12-23 00:29:52'),
(1541, 734, 'Absolutely love the lyrics, I feel that it really speaks to me and I feel that it can be quite powerful for the listener (:', 52, '2014-12-23 00:30:00'),
(1542, 719, 'Beginning sounds like Katy Perry''s ''Roar'' and Sara Bareilles'' ''Brave'' :)', 61, '2014-12-23 01:16:41'),
(1543, 657, 'Mashup with The After''s Light up the Sky?', 61, '2014-12-23 01:25:38'),
(1544, 537, 'Thanks Meiji! I meant to resuggest the mashup :)', 55, '2014-12-23 03:27:16'),
(1545, 750, 'sorry it''s past the deadline for suggestions but my roommate asked me to suggest it and i had forgotten about it! if it''s too late for this semester, maybe another? :)', 47, '2014-12-23 04:20:15'),
(1546, 590, 'I take it back. X.ado arrangement is cool. I''m bad. \r\nHowever, there''s up to an 8 part split + solo in that arrangement.', 40, '2014-12-23 09:07:27'),
(1547, 590, 'I take it back. X.ado arrangement is cool. I''m bad. \r\nHowever, there''s up to an 8 part split + solo in that arrangement.', 40, '2014-12-23 09:07:29'),
(1548, 619, 'This song is upbeat and sounds happy :) seems like it would be great for spring break, and it really presents an amazing message, the face that we really cannot live without our God.', 55, '2014-12-23 21:01:44'),
(1549, 702, 'I agree with Brian that this song is gorgeous, however I think that there''s too many bible references that could distract from the essence of this song, that we want God to hear us in our prayers, particularly to a non Christian audience.', 55, '2014-12-23 21:09:42'),
(1550, 730, 'A little concerned because this is largely driven by the bass, but it''s a cool style.', 50, '2014-12-23 23:34:43'),
(1551, 750, 'I REALLY LIKE THIS- the message is what I often need to hear.  Also, sounds like it could possibly translate to a cappella well??', 55, '2014-12-24 01:01:25'),
(1552, 596, 'o0o yes ^', 38, '2014-12-24 07:18:24'),
(1553, 717, 'Personally, I think this might be a bit slow on its own -- but it is another song that would work really well in the Beautiful Things / Empty My Hands mashup!', 50, '2014-12-24 20:06:40'),
(1554, 695, 'I like the message: a call to action, as well as a statement about what it means to be Christian. Like Phoebe said, though, I''d prefer more about God first loving us. Message-wise, this song reminds me a bit of The Proof of Your Love.', 50, '2014-12-24 20:17:44'),
(1555, 596, '...and Brokenness Aside by All Sons & Daughters (which was also suggested as its own song this semester).', 50, '2014-12-24 20:19:57'),
(1556, 633, 'I agree with other people that it is a little slow and repetitive which lends itself well to the genre of a cappella arrangement that Overflow made (see second youtube video) However, it is a genre that Cross Products has diverged quite far from over the last many years. \r\n', 53, '2014-12-24 20:32:06'),
(1557, 717, 'I like the message, but there are not that many lyrics total. It might be better in a mashup.', 53, '2014-12-24 20:57:40'),
(1558, 750, 'I find Owl City''s feel to be quieter. By this I mean, there is not too much background, nor is the solo making a show. Additionally, the way the rhythms are do not lend to smooth flow, but rather rely on the drum line cutting through. Additionally, Owl City is high for a guy solo; however, I guess that it could be changed into a girl solo.\r\n\r\nOverall, it might be so easy to replicate in a cappella.', 53, '2014-12-24 21:04:28'),
(1559, 619, 'Pray for guys and hope that we can nail down the bass line.', 53, '2014-12-24 21:15:55'),
(1560, 657, '1 Corinthians 1:18-31', 50, '2014-12-24 21:18:02'),
(1561, 537, 'I think that we could add a guy to sing an octave below the girl''s "jum-jum-jum"s because it feels a little hollow to me. ', 53, '2014-12-24 21:27:07'),
(1562, 749, 'I love this song! Thanks Hans for suggesting it. \r\n\r\nI think that this would work best as an all guys song though. That said, if the girls want to have a song this could be the guy corollary. ', 53, '2014-12-24 21:42:10'),
(1563, 749, 'Sorry: my comment immediately above refers to the quartet arrangement for these lyrics (see video three)', 53, '2014-12-24 21:49:07'),
(1564, 0, '', 50, '2014-12-24 21:51:09'),
(1565, 715, 'Spring Break friendly! In addition to being a reminder for Christians that this life is meant for us to live to the full, this song can also speak to non-Christians that life is a journey and that God has a role in it (God has plans for each of us, even those who are not Christian). I also really like the background music of the chorus.', 50, '2014-12-24 21:57:31'),
(1566, 708, 'I find this hard to fit into our set list (whatever it may be) but I think that it would be cool to sing on Spring break or something. ', 53, '2014-12-24 22:11:48'),
(1567, 721, 'I like the song, but personally don''t relate to the lyrics too much. I''d also prefer that there was more emphasis on God and His role in the change of heart.', 50, '2014-12-24 22:17:18'),
(1568, 732, 'Solid Gospel message. Might be a bit repetitive (depends on our arrangement) but I like how the Newsboys arrangement has the classic lyrics of a hymn but with more upbeat and modern music.', 50, '2014-12-24 22:29:07'),
(1569, 696, 'I actually thought about suggesting this at one point because it is a well-known song that sounds very Christian. I agree with Dongho, though, that I''m a little concerned with the lyrics; I''d feel better about it if it were mashed up with a Christian song for a more powerful message.', 50, '2014-12-24 22:43:28'),
(1570, 738, 'This is a beautiful song about our yearning for what comes after this life. However, I''d rather sing something that talks about life with God here and now, as Christians are meant to live for Christ in this life, as well as the next, and it would probably be a more powerful message for those who don''t know Christ yet.', 50, '2014-12-24 23:01:48'),
(1571, 555, 'This song was my first solo in xprod -- it was really powerful over Spring Break that year. I agree with Kevin''s comment, though, that I would like to see it paired with a song that answers the question "Can You hold me together?"', 50, '2014-12-24 23:08:20'),
(1572, 714, 'It would be cool to cascade the "duns" but it would be pretty hard for us to get them right...', 53, '2014-12-24 23:09:45'),
(1573, 731, 'This reminds me of a GLAD arrangement. We''d have to be very careful with it because it has naked harmonies that would sound bad if not perfectly tuned.', 50, '2014-12-24 23:22:50'),
(1574, 742, 'I was actually thinking this could work in the Beautiful Things / Empty My Hands mashup (lol, so many songs work in that mashup).', 50, '2014-12-24 23:28:31'),
(1575, 431, 'The reason we dropped it was because we had to readjust for the new group balance. Yes, the message is similar to Indescribable, which made it an ideal song to drop, but that wasn''t the main reason. (Hopefully that clarifies it!) Because of what Phoebe brought up concerning blurbing, this would probably not be a song we''d take on Spring Break; that also means we wouldn''t have to worry about it being redundant.', 50, '2014-12-24 23:35:38'),
(1576, 729, 'I can see what you''re saying, Maddie, but I would still prefer that the lyrics were more specific. I feel like it''s saying "Life is rough, but it will all be ok in the end," which isn''t the whole truth of the message that Christ brings.', 50, '2014-12-24 23:41:48'),
(1577, 736, 'I''m worried about how non-Christians would feel when listening to this song, since they may or may not be familiar with notions of church/kingdom, etc.', 38, '2014-12-25 07:34:44'),
(1578, 713, 'Omg this is one of my faves. I love the lyrics! It''s such a display of vulnerability before the Lord, with a different perspective. I also am a huge fan of the acoustic version of this song. If the arranger wants to do a version from her original album (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bPHkhrkSAWM), that can also be a stylistic choice in a different direction. ', 38, '2014-12-25 07:39:45'),
(1579, 695, 'Yeah... for me, there is a disconnect between the "I am loved" and "let''s love others" that isn''t really filled by the lyrics. It takes a lot of effort from the audience to sit there and piece it together. Would definitely need a blurb to clarify.', 38, '2014-12-25 07:43:04'),
(1580, 721, 'Upsides: spring break friendly, rap and lyrical content can help us relate to different audiences at various gigs. Same downsides as Phoebe mentioned.', 38, '2014-12-25 08:04:14'),
(1581, 496, 'I actually have the opposite opinion as Rachel about this song-- I love how the verses as written, and I feel that the choruses are powerful in a worship setting because they''re repetitive. The challenge with this song is to keep this song interesting, because there''s so much repetition. Personally, I''m not sure if this would translate well to a cappella unless the arranger does something clever and keeps it interesting for the audience.', 38, '2014-12-25 08:23:34'),
(1582, 742, 'whoa we can have another gigantic mashup this semester! haha. I like this song with Beautiful Things / Empty My Hands though :P A huge plus for this song: this is a pop song that even non-Christians would recognize. Lyrically, reminds me of "Hold Me Together"', 38, '2014-12-25 08:30:09'),
(1584, 729, 'Mmm yeah I agree with Meiji on this. Also, the lyrics don''t come from a perspective of the victory that Jesus already died for us on a cross and won the battle. Though I understand where this song is coming from, the way it talks about pride is something that we need to be cautious about, especialy when we may not necessarily have a chance to blurb and clarify that we must lay down our pride in order to follow God.', 38, '2014-12-25 08:36:27'),
(1585, 705, 'o0o yeah I like the gist of the lyrics! I''d suggest some minor lyrical changes if this ends up going into the setlist, but looks good overall :]', 38, '2014-12-25 08:42:01'),
(1586, 724, 'This song is so real. It exposes the hardships and acknowledges that life isn''t all rainbows and butterflies all the time, but God is always good and he chooses to thank Him.', 38, '2014-12-25 08:47:37'),
(1587, 693, 'Hmm... do you mind marking which parts you imagine to be God and which are from the human''s perspective? It would give a better sense of understanding exactly what you''re going for', 38, '2014-12-25 08:49:23'),
(1588, 708, 'omg this is so pretty! <3 I actually think this message is very relevant to pretty much anything we sing haha. It''s just that stylistically it''s obviously quite different than what we''re used to.', 38, '2014-12-25 08:52:09'),
(1589, 718, 'mmm yeah. Would only like it for xprod if it was in a mashup', 38, '2014-12-25 09:02:08'),
(1590, 619, 'Soloist would have to be engaging. I currently imagine this would be hard to pull off with a cappella unless we have an imaginative arrangement.', 38, '2014-12-25 09:04:17'),
(1591, 712, 'This song is really powerful, and I like the song''s tension and lyrics about God''s love. I''m not sure about converting this song into a cappella arrangement, though. ', 54, '2014-12-25 22:22:22'),
(1592, 693, '^ ditto what Polly said.', 50, '2014-12-26 00:21:36'),
(1593, 710, 'This song is really powerful because it''s our outpouring of love for God. Non-Christians won''t relate to it, but I think it would give them a taste of the joy that we have and maybe cause them to ask why we feel this way. I really like how this doesn''t focus on our brokenness and our love as a direct response to what He has done for us, but on God''s beauty and our love as a direct response to who He is.', 50, '2014-12-26 00:34:20'),
(1594, 748, 'I love the lyrics of this song! The hardest part about choosing God is letting go of our rights to ourselves. We are not our own; the reason we fail is because we choose ourselves and what we want over God. I know it scares me to give everything to God because I''m afraid of losing control. However, when we ask God to take this life, He doesn''t take advantage of us -- He lets us shine!', 50, '2014-12-26 00:44:42'),
(1595, 733, 'Would need a lyrical change to "The struggle makes us new", if the song is sung from the perspective of God', 38, '2014-12-26 06:38:34'),
(1596, 735, 'Would have to be paired with a song that answers with what he''s looking for', 38, '2014-12-26 06:47:52'),
(1597, 75, 'I love this arrangement! ahhh <3', 38, '2014-12-26 06:53:11'),
(1598, 723, 'I feel like this would be a good song to mash up with another song, as one of those God/human conversations', 38, '2014-12-26 07:00:36'),
(1599, 711, '^ ditto Caitlin. I know this song isn''t suggested, but it would be cool to mashup with Eden by Phil Wickham (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HGlLL_m4dWQ), to give it context. ', 38, '2014-12-26 07:13:38'),
(1600, 703, 'It also puts a different spin on the reason we sing. I love how this song paints a picture of who God is, and also comes from a stance of God''s victory.', 38, '2014-12-26 07:20:48'),
(1601, 712, 'ah, I forgot to attach an album version also. Could be easier to arrange from that version, but definitely has a different feel.', 38, '2014-12-26 07:27:06'),
(1602, 743, 'Hmm... I think it might be isolating for non-Christians to hear a lyric that says, "Hands up, oh hands up\r\n/ Hands up all believers / Take up your cross, carry it on"', 38, '2014-12-26 07:32:15'),
(1603, 748, 'I think this could work well, because us giving ourselves to God is an important message.  It would be great if we can blurb this to explain how it is sometimes difficult and scares us and how we overcome this and I feel it could have a big impact on non-Christians who might struggle with this idea.  Also, musically it''s pretty upbeat and interesting. :)', 58, '2014-12-26 20:59:37'),
(1604, 696, 'I actually read that the composer is a Christian who may have drawn inspiration from his love of Gospel. \r\n\r\nHowever, I must agree that I''m not sure that our audience would understand us singing it unless we mashed it up or made sure to blurb it. ', 53, '2014-12-26 20:59:49'),
(1605, 723, 'Do you think this could work in a mashup with I Won''t Give Up - Jason Marz? I could see it working well  with the God/Us conversation with him saying that he''ll always be there for us. ', 58, '2014-12-26 21:05:53'),
(1606, 693, 'I like this idea. :) Do you think this could work in a mashup with John Legend - Shelter? I could see it working well  with the God/Us conversation with him saying that he''ll always be there for us. ', 58, '2014-12-26 21:05:56'),
(1607, 714, 'I really like this message! :) Especially with the idea of  trusting in God''s plan, even when we are struggling and do not know what the future holds.  I also feel this would make a good arrangement.', 58, '2014-12-26 21:09:38'),
(1608, 712, 'I really like this!  I think it could definitely be very powerful if we could pull it off! :)', 58, '2014-12-26 21:13:12'),
(1609, 619, 'I love this! The message works really well and I feel that we could definitely have an interesting arrangement that could make this work.  I think it would be effective, because it''s so upbeat and catchy that people would remember it :)', 58, '2014-12-26 21:17:27'),
(1610, 718, 'I can see this as a duet. The main singer is a Christian struggling to find God, but continuing to follow. God comes in the chorus saying how He is there even though the Christian struggles in his faith. \r\n\r\nI have tentative lyrics/split here: PLEASE LOOK AT THIS!!! https://docs.google.com/document/d/1sGHoYP5muZzh2esfLtmZM03e4DDCy_7o2VStDu0_dbs/pub\r\n', 53, '2014-12-26 22:11:52'),
(1613, 718, 'In general, I prefer that we change as few lyrics as possible -- otherwise it seems like we''re trying too hard to force it to work. Especially, with non-Christian songs, which we use to try to appeal to our audience, it''s weird to change too many things.', 50, '2014-12-26 22:19:29'),
(1614, 739, 'I really like this song! However, it emphasizes our own impact and legacy more than the importance of God and His kingdom. "Will I be remembered?" isn''t our purpose in life - making God''s Name known is. (see comments on Legacy by Nichole Nordeman)', 50, '2014-12-26 23:17:21'),
(1615, 697, 'I agree with Caitlin -- it''s so joyful! It can also easily become a Spring Break friendly song.', 50, '2014-12-26 23:32:20'),
(1616, 733, 'I''ve always thought of this song as a song from one Christian to another, calling them to join in Christ-centered community. I think it''s a really powerful message in that context (Ecclesiastes 4:9-12), but for non-Christians, the message seems very secular.', 50, '2014-12-26 23:39:56'),
(1617, 749, 'I can see it as an all guys song, especially if we have a strong bass section. It''s a little repetitive, so I would cut a few of the choruses at the end, though.', 50, '2014-12-26 23:54:40'),
(1618, 716, 'This song is so personal and pure. I especially love the chorus. This reminds me of Oh Child by Nevertheless, but more emphasis on God yearning for us, His children, to come home to Him.', 50, '2014-12-27 00:04:11'),
(1619, 477, 'Vision (UDel) did this for BIDB 2014 (see youtube), if we want to borrow their arrangement.', 50, '2014-12-27 00:12:33'),
(1620, 698, 'The Cornell''s arrangement is really good and I like the song! I''m not sure about how non-christian audience will think about this song', 54, '2014-12-27 06:27:49'),
(1621, 724, 'The first youtube video version of this might be very difficult to arrange. ', 53, '2014-12-27 14:31:07'),
(1622, 694, 'Ditto Phoebe:\r\nThe mash up would have to make it clear that this is God telling us this not because we are good enough, but because His love surpasses how unlovable we are. (Forgive the poor grammar)', 53, '2014-12-27 14:49:36'),
(1623, 735, 'I''m a bit uncomfortable with the line that says "I am the one you left behind" -- he''s probably talking about Jesus literally leaving earth, but it sounds more like he''s saying that God left him behind.', 50, '2014-12-27 15:02:13'),
(1624, 723, 'I''d also be a fan of changing "I will get to wherever you are" to "I am with you wherever you are."', 50, '2014-12-27 15:11:38'),
(1625, 714, 'I also appreciate the positive vibe, even though she''s talking about weathering storms. Trusting in God can be scary, but He is steady, so therefore we can rejoice with assurance that He will provide. Also, this song is Spring Break friendly and carries a message that I think even non-Christians can find comforting.', 50, '2014-12-27 16:49:12'),
(1626, 725, '"I''m so lost, and I need You to help me repent" is a perfectly legitimate thing to pray in my opinion. /// And the devil inside me is torn ///\r\nGod bless the lives that I have scorned', 53, '2014-12-27 17:09:46'),
(1627, 700, 'I really like the 2nd verse: usually, we think we''re strong enough to handle our problems, so we don''t turn to God. It''s in our weakness, though, that God is proved strong and we rely on Him the most. I also like how this admits that Christians aren''t themselves better people than others; it''s not by our own strength, but by God''s strength. Even after being saved, we''re constantly relying on who God is and what He has done for us. Proverbs 30:7-9.', 50, '2014-12-27 17:17:00'),
(1628, 117, 'Heart of worship.', 50, '2014-12-27 17:20:34'),
(1629, 723, 'While this does match one aspect of who God is, I feel that it neither makes it specific enough nor broad enough to really convey that this is God to us. IE: It doesn''t sufficiently address the relational aspect between God and us, nor does it address more of who God is. Thus I feel that it is neither able to stand alone, nor does it do an exceptional job of sharing our message.', 53, '2014-12-27 17:22:26'),
(1630, 745, 'This is the proclamation of our faith. It is not a song of us turning to God when we are struggling. Rather, it is a promise that we will hold on in faith whatever may come. ', 53, '2014-12-27 17:29:56'),
(1631, 205, 'Lyrically similar to The Proof of Your Love, but from the angle that all creation testifies to God''s love.', 50, '2014-12-27 17:30:44'),
(1632, 729, 'I''m not sure how the theme: "I know where I''ve been" ties into the Christian walk...', 53, '2014-12-27 17:35:05'),
(1633, 693, 'Hmm... Splitting up stanzas will be hard to do without it becoming disjoint. ', 53, '2014-12-27 17:48:46'),
(1634, 704, 'I''m not sure how much non-Christians would take this. This song states what we believe, but I would prefer a "show, not tell" approach.', 50, '2014-12-27 17:49:59'),
(1635, 731, 'This is a really beautiful arrangement, but I don''t think that we will be able to arrange this, and we would definately not be able to split into this many parts...', 53, '2014-12-27 17:57:28'),
(1636, 714, 'I REALLY REALLY like the song both message-wise and musical-wise. I agree with Brian about how to sing this song beautifully but still this song and lyrics are just so beautiful! :D', 54, '2014-12-27 19:16:43'),
(1637, 719, 'Girly girly pop song! I also like the part ''write YOUR STORY on my heart''!', 54, '2014-12-27 19:31:36'),
(1638, 637, 'I like the song but I''m not sure about changing piano lines into a cappella arrangement. Also I think the song itself is hard to deeply relate our internal relationship with God (how God work through into our hearts). But still it is definitely cool, straightforward, and reeallly powerful worship song!', 54, '2014-12-27 19:50:39'),
(1639, 619, 'Ditto with Polly. I can''t think how electronic sound can sound beautifully into a cappella arrangement. Still, this song is really fun to sing with straightforward message!', 54, '2014-12-27 20:14:37'),
(1640, 9, 'I love the lyrics, but I think we need more guys to sing this beautiful hymn...', 54, '2014-12-27 20:17:57'),
(1641, 28, 'I really like this song. :)  I also love the mashup with Don''t You Worry Child.  I think it''s good to combine it with  a song the non-Christians might have heard so they may be able to relate to it more.', 58, '2014-12-27 22:21:07'),
(1642, 694, 'I agree with both Phoebe and Brian. Currently, the song is talking about how you don''t have change your physical appearance in order to try to fit in; unless we change the message, I don''t think this song would work for our ministry.', 50, '2014-12-27 22:26:26'),
(1643, 712, 'The first verse is very confusing grammatically, since they don''t specify the subject of the sentences beginning with "Try [...]."', 50, '2014-12-27 22:34:37'),
(1644, 740, 'Because of the genre (worship) I''m not sure how relatable it will be to our nonchristian audience.', 53, '2014-12-27 22:38:46'),
(1645, 736, 'I agree with Polly. While I think that Christians who hear it will really like it, it isn''t very friendly to nonchristians due to the large amount of "christianese." Not that it uses a lot of bible references, but I don''t think that nonchristians would be able to understand what we are singing about. ', 53, '2014-12-27 22:49:09'),
(1646, 741, 'I like it. Two things: Phil Wickham''s songs all sound similar so we probably wouldn''t want to do more than a few. Also, his voice is pretty high for a guy, so it might have to be made into a girl solo.', 53, '2014-12-27 22:53:36'),
(1647, 676, 'I like how she, a success in many people''s eyes, says that her success has not given her the satisfaction she needed. Especially for MIT students this message is or will be very relevant. My only concern is that people might not relate to it because it is only after you catch what you''re chasing that you find that it wasn''t what you wanted. That said, I don''t think that there is any elegant solution to relatability. ', 53, '2014-12-27 23:40:22'),
(1648, 701, 'I''ve often been at this point, where I''m just worn from this life and wish God would come make it all right. However, I''d rather we sang a song with a more positive spin on the same message that focuses on God coming and making it all right rather than our weariness of this world. Also, 2 Peter 3:9.', 50, '2014-12-27 23:42:53'),
(1649, 496, 'However this is arranged, can the line please be: "unforeseen kiss" rather than "sloppy wet kiss." I don''t want this to sound like a dog slobbering someone or a drunk person trying to kiss someone. ', 53, '2014-12-27 23:43:41'),
(1650, 420, 'I like the lyrics. I''m concerned that it will drag / become boring because it has a slow beat.', 50, '2014-12-27 23:51:56'),
(1651, 637, 'I feel that gospel is very different than much of what Cross Products sings. I wonder if it would clash with the rest of what we sing.', 53, '2014-12-27 23:52:19'),
(1652, 615, 'Also, John 15:1-8 (The Vine and the Branches).', 50, '2014-12-27 23:54:56'),
(1653, 164, 'I''m not actually a huge fan of Good News'' performance of this. I''m not sure if the sound mix is simply unbalanced or if the arrangement is not what I was expecting.', 53, '2014-12-27 23:58:43'),
(1654, 750, '*might NOT be so easy to replicate in a cappella', 53, '2014-12-28 00:25:04'),
(1655, 750, 'This is mostly driven by the percussion, so I''m not sure how well it would work when translated to a cappella.', 50, '2014-12-28 00:28:40'),
(1656, 749, 'I really like this!  I also think it could work well as an all guys song! :)', 58, '2014-12-28 00:29:24'),
(1657, 699, 'I definitely love the message and think it is very applicable to MIT students, but I worry that it''s a little too repetitive/even-keeled and think other songs might get the same message across more easily via a cappella.', 37, '2014-12-28 00:30:59'),
(1658, 749, 'One of my favorite songs! Well, the chorus at least. I could also see it as a lead in/out song for another arrangement, Never Change-style. ', 37, '2014-12-28 00:32:09'),
(1659, 750, 'I can actually see it working well as a soulful a cappella song! It wouldn''t have the same type of Owl City-feel, but I think it would sound just as cool. And I like the lyrics. And a non-cheesy key change!', 37, '2014-12-28 00:37:36'),
(1660, 672, 'It is a great worship song, but I''m not so sure that it is a great performance song. ', 53, '2014-12-28 00:40:27'),
(1661, 672, 'If we did it, I''d want to make it a short & sweet song so the lyrics don''t lose their edge when it''s sung a cappella.', 37, '2014-12-28 00:42:48'),
(1662, 701, 'I agree with Meiji about the positive spin, but I love the melody of the chorus.', 37, '2014-12-28 00:47:02'),
(1663, 723, 'I can potentially see this as a mashup with Human, but it would take some manipulating.', 37, '2014-12-28 01:08:26'),
(1664, 649, 'Keep in mind that our Fire mash-up already uses Set a Fire.', 53, '2014-12-28 01:11:19'),
(1665, 562, 'I think that this could be soloed by either a girl or a guy.', 53, '2014-12-28 01:20:33'),
(1666, 641, 'Columbia''s Jubilation sang this at BiDB last year (2014). We might be able to get an arrangement from them. ', 53, '2014-12-28 01:27:47'),
(1667, 748, 'Love "There''s no life apart from you."', 37, '2014-12-28 01:40:20'),
(1668, 604, 'Testimony''s arrangement needs to be fixed for high range of sops. Also, I think it needs more context of how God shows purpose to our lives!', 54, '2014-12-28 02:40:48'),
(1669, 725, 'yeah i guess i was confused since the whole song seems to already be demonstrating repentance, and so asking God to help her repent in her song of repentance seemed redundant? (not sure if that''s the right word); i could just be overthinking semantics though', 47, '2014-12-28 03:01:32'),
(1670, 749, 'God really is awesome, which is why this song is so powerful. I really like the Praise & Harmony a cappella version. I don''t think it would need to be all guys; it works well with girls too in the recording. ', 62, '2015-05-30 18:57:57'),
(1671, 751, 'I loved this song when I heard it at BIDB. It''s cool because it''s a popular song but it has a very Christian message.', 62, '2015-05-30 18:59:55'),
(1672, 714, 'This song is beautiful, and I like the message. I think it''d translate to a cappella well. The arranger might need to shorten the instrumental part a bit, though.', 62, '2015-05-30 19:24:50'),
(1673, 754, 'this song was in pitch perfect 2! i think it can be applied to God''s light in our lives with relatively little lyric changes. thoughts?', 47, '2015-05-30 23:28:34'),
(1674, 484, 'Philippians 4:4-7. I love how this song is our declaration to choose joy over fear and anxiety -- we choose to rejoice in Christ, for the joy of the Lord is our strength!', 50, '2015-05-31 00:20:14'),
(1675, 167, 'At church, the pastor said, "God can do amazing things with us when we''re outside of our comfort zones." I think God does amazing things with us when we''re in our comfort zones, too, but at those times, we usually take the credit for them. It''s when we''re outside our comfort zones that we''re forced to admit that it''s God and not us -- but if we live our lives looking to and relying on God and not ourselves, He gives us wings to fly.', 50, '2015-05-31 00:27:28'),
(1676, 754, 'Not crazy about the song itself, having not seen the movie, but I''m sure people will recognize it, and I definitely see the applicability. Anybody have problems with the "it''s a sweet life" line?', 62, '2015-05-31 17:12:00'),
(1677, 753, 'This song is super popular on Christian radio, so a lot of people in the audience will recognize it. I think it''s so beautiful, and there''s a lot going on in the background that would be fun to arrange with. I love the line "I found my life when I laid it down" -- that our true purpose is only found when we surrender to God''s love and stop living for ourselves, and this is something to rejoice over.', 62, '2015-05-31 17:18:42'),
(1678, 755, 'I''m sorry, I don''t really like this song. I''m not saying I have theological issues with it, but I don''t think it''d be a smart pick. A lot of the audience (particularly the non-Christain audience) is probably thinking "God, why don''t you do something?" Saying that God''s answer is us only gives them the opportunity to ask what exactly we are doing to fight poverty and human trafficking, now that we''ve brought it up. At our concerts we''re more trying to be a light to the campus, and this song isn''t really doing it. It''s a battle cry to Christians but not applicable to anyone else.', 62, '2015-05-31 17:27:36'),
(1679, 652, 'If we were to do any Christmas song, I''d vote this one. This is my favorite Christmas song. Not a fan of this particular arrangement. I feel like this is a more solemn song.', 62, '2015-05-31 21:02:19'),
(1680, 724, 'Yeah, I like the song, but arranging it would be a real challenge, and it doesn''t really sound like something xprod would usually sing.', 62, '2015-05-31 21:16:43'),
(1681, 719, 'Very catchy. I think it''d easily mash-up with a pop song too.', 62, '2015-05-31 21:19:39'),
(1682, 756, 'This is a "secular" band, but this is totally a worship song. God is love, and his love has defeated us and given us a way to know him, even though we''re broken. It''s such a happy song that proclaims the the joy found in God''s love and the changes it works in our lives.', 62, '2015-05-31 22:31:24'),
(1683, 757, 'Not the most well-known Phil Wickham song, but it''s one of my favorite. Usually I associate him with worship songs, but this one''s a little different. This is one of those songs that I like to sing at the top of my lungs when I''m going through things I can''t handle on my own and realize that literally the only thing that can get me through life is God''s grace. It''s an act of surrender when we admit that we''re clueless, powerless, and hopeless on our own and ask God for his grace. But, yet, it''s happy and awesome because he gives it to us!', 62, '2015-05-31 22:44:35'),
(1684, 167, 'I loved when we did this song a couple years ago over spring break.  It''s really fun to sing, I think it''s a good option to maybe have choreo (with a cool arangement), Spring Break Friendly :)', 55, '2015-06-01 03:32:10'),
(1685, 758, 'I will work on finding a choral recording of this... it''s a really gorgeous hymn (the band recording 0:00 - 0:47 doesn''t do it justice) that I have sung in chamber choir. We only sang the first two verses. It is a little weird/unintuitive/tricky, but it''s super short, so I''m sure xprod would have no problem learning it. I love how the music supports the message of the words in really unexpected but beautiful ways. It''s really awe-inspiring and establishes a sense of wonder, fear of the Lord, and reverence that I haven''t found in any other hymn, particularly in the first two verses. But it also feels very intimate and personal, as God is.', 37, '2015-06-02 02:59:21'),
(1686, 431, 'More than half of the group will still mostly know this one, so it might be nice. Also, I love the message. ', 53, '2015-06-08 11:55:08'),
(1687, 508, 'This is such a powerful song, both lyrically and musically. I love the contrasts between glory and brokenness. And the xprod arrangement is really pretty, too.', 50, '2015-06-08 17:21:11'),
(1688, 766, 'It''s been suggested several times that we do Christmas songs at our fall concert. This song is one of my favorite carols. I love how it portrays Jesus as both fully man and fully God, and how ridiculous / miraculous that can sound, especially to the one who held God as a baby in her arms.', 50, '2015-06-08 21:29:38'),
(1689, 759, 'I love the lyrics and feel of this song.  The message is about how everything, even the forces of nature that we see as much much bigger than we can ever hope to control, belongs to God and that the universe unstoppably "declares the glory of God" (Psalm 19:1) and sings of His praises.  It reminds me of the verse "''I tell you,'' he replied, ''if they keep quiet, the stones will cry out.''" (Luke 19:40) The lyrics are really poetic, but still simple.  The beginning of the song is very delicate - makes me think of a child in awe, and it matures into an intense praise to God.', 61, '2015-06-09 04:14:59'),
(1690, 752, 'So I''ve really come to love this song (and the video).  I think it could work with a blurb.  Through God, he forgives our original sin. We are all made in his flawless image and likeness.  No matter what you are going through in life, God is there, with you.  He died for us to save us!', 55, '2015-06-09 05:36:03'),
(1691, 751, 'I also like how Amazing Grace is a part of this song.  It''d be really cool to work that in more as a mashup!', 55, '2015-06-09 05:37:04'),
(1692, 759, 'I think this would work well as a worship song in the set, and it''s not too repetitive. I like the juxtaposition of the earth trembling and rejoicing in God''s presence.', 62, '2015-06-09 05:39:40'),
(1693, 508, 'Oooohh this is really pretty. And it has a darker feel to it, which is nice when a lot of Christian songs tend to sound super happy.', 62, '2015-06-09 05:43:51'),
(1694, 513, 'This song is super cool. I know I can relate to the theme--even being at MIT, nothing I do matters if I''m not living for God. ', 62, '2015-06-09 05:54:42'),
(1695, 751, 'I''m not sure I''d like that as a mashup, but maybe do something similar to the beginning/end of our Never Change arrangement :)', 62, '2015-06-09 06:23:37'),
(1696, 769, 'I found this song on social media, and I think it''s really cool. God reaches out to us, and it''s when we reach back and it becomes a relationship that we experience his love.', 62, '2015-06-09 06:48:00'),
(1697, 773, 'I really like this version and I feel like we could do some cool things with it.', 57, '2015-06-09 13:55:36'),
(1698, 774, 'James 1:2-4. I like how it talks about God working through difficult times and suffering (rather than in spite of them), and how our limited perspective isn''t what God sees. Gold can''t be refined without fire, and diamonds can''t be made without pressure. This song is also really catchy and I can see it having a powerful bass line.', 50, '2015-06-09 16:12:38'),
(1699, 430, 'It''s such a beautiful hymn that clearly states the Gospel -- how great our God is, and how great His love is for us, that He chose to die for people like us.', 50, '2015-06-09 16:22:48'),
(1700, 771, 'I like this song, but it''s super repetitive so we''d probably need to do a mashup. Still, I think few songs express love for God so sweetly.', 62, '2015-06-09 19:43:54'),
(1701, 5, 'I''ve never considered this to be one of Switchfoot''s best songs, but reading the comments above I think it could be cool. The arrangement sounds good, and I can definitely see the lyrics in the chorus being thought provoking.', 62, '2015-06-09 19:49:05'),
(1702, 467, 'Great song, great arrangement. I like how it highlights the simple act of faith.', 62, '2015-06-09 20:08:58'),
(1703, 772, 'This song is super cool and exemplefies the sort of positive feedback loop that comes with chasing after God. It''s kinda electronic, though, so it might be hard to do. It needs energy.', 62, '2015-06-09 20:22:31'),
(1704, 555, 'Haha "male" solo and then I see Meiji. This is a pretty cool song though. I like how the lyrics are honest about Christianity: sometimes I don''t know what to pray besides, "God help me, because I sure can''t!"', 62, '2015-06-09 20:29:32'),
(1705, 774, 'I feel like I''d prefer this as a female solo', 62, '2015-06-09 20:36:03'),
(1706, 773, 'I''m surprised we don''t already have a Come Thou Fount arrangement. This is one of my favorite hymns.', 62, '2015-06-09 20:37:38'),
(1707, 775, 'Really like this hymn, particularly how Jesus washes us clean of our sins. The first video is more of a modern recording, but it could be arranged however.', 62, '2015-06-09 20:47:30'),
(1708, 11, 'mm<3 ', 47, '2015-06-10 02:06:29'),
(1709, 776, 'I think it would be awesome if we had a mashup of a bunch of different Bethel songs or something - like Holy Spirit+Set A Fire+You Make me Brave+Your Praise Will Ever Be On My Lips.  I know Bethel songs can be quite repetitive, so it might be hard to do well in an acappella setting.  However, if we put in in a mashup, it could be pretty exciting :)', 61, '2015-06-10 03:13:09'),
(1710, 767, 'See my comment on Ever Be about doing a Bethel mashup!', 61, '2015-06-10 03:14:41');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(1711, 768, 'See my comment on Ever Be about doing a Bethel mashup!', 61, '2015-06-10 03:16:03'),
(1712, 778, 'I like this song musically and lyrically, but I fear it might be hard for non-Christians to relate to it.  That being said, the lyrics are rich with Biblical symbolism, which I think is incredibly powerful and clear.  It basically talks about the aftermath of the Gospel - that because of Jesus''s sacrifice and crucifixion, we are a new creation, dead to our sinful nature, and risen like Christ.  It is suppose to be the turning point of our life, the pivotal moment that we claim changes the way we interact with others, conduct our daily life, and even the way we think.\r\n\r\nI don''t mean this song in particular, but I think it would be really sad to dismiss a song with an important and truthful message just because we don''t think it would resonate well with the audience.  I have faith that God can provide divine understanding to even our non-Christian audience members if He chooses to. :)', 61, '2015-06-10 04:51:09'),
(1713, 783, 'I see this song as an admittance of a past without God, and the realization that God is everything (but now I tell a single truth There''s you in everything I do).  I think it could work with a blurb.  I''d probably want to change the chorus lyrics to something like ''I know that I was wrong, I''ve walked that road before.  But you never left me on my own. and please believe me when i say That it''s left for yesterday And the records that I''ve played Please forgive me for all I''ve done''', 55, '2015-06-10 05:41:35'),
(1714, 776, 'I agree with the mashup.  I have a hard time seeing some of these stand alone in our set because of the repetitveness but together it could bring a lot of messages together :)', 55, '2015-06-10 05:43:09'),
(1715, 652, 'Definitely my favorite Christmas song!!!!!  I think it would be really cool to have in our set. I''m curious about a skit connection :)\r\n', 55, '2015-06-10 05:45:58'),
(1716, 784, 'From BIDB.  I love singing about HOPE!!!!!  Especially at MIT where hope is hard to find.  But our HOPE is in GOD and this is a great song to say that. ', 55, '2015-06-10 05:48:16'),
(1717, 783, 'Ooohh interesting pick. I was trying to think of popular songs that could relate to Christianity, and this one definitely could. But, yeah, I''m not really sure how I feel about the bridge. Admittedly, I''m not the best with interpreting lyrics, so I''m not really sure what the original meaning is supposed to be. I know the song was about his parents though.', 62, '2015-06-10 23:53:32'),
(1718, 776, 'Don''t forget Fall Afresh ^_^  I like this Bethel mashup idea.', 62, '2015-06-10 23:55:36'),
(1719, 785, 'See Hans''s comment on Ever Be about doing a Bethel mashup! ;)', 62, '2015-06-10 23:57:39'),
(1720, 736, 'One of my favorite songs to sing in church ^_^  I could maybe see it being less good at a concert, though.', 62, '2015-06-10 23:59:32'),
(1721, 783, 'oh yeah I meant change the bridge lyrics... not the chorus lyrics.', 55, '2015-06-11 02:16:01'),
(1722, 205, 'Harvard Under Construction also has an arrangement of this if we want a second. See the audio file.', 53, '2015-06-11 03:30:01'),
(1723, 584, 'I wouldn''t worry about reliability too much for this one...I mean, at some point, we have to expect non-believers in the audience to not "relate" to some of our music. That said, I think this one''d be set dependent. I like how it trades solos and builds throughout, although interestingly it sounds kinda the same throughout the song too if you get what I''m saying.', 62, '2015-06-11 03:53:00'),
(1724, 657, 'So in the middle of last semester, I listened to this song A LOT.  I think that no matter what, there are are always times when we feel lost and God is always there to help us.  This song helps me when I don''t know where to turn, and with that point, I think it can be relatable for everyone.  Plus, it''s really pretty!!!! and I can see how it could be a cappella', 55, '2015-06-11 04:03:44'),
(1725, 472, 'I heard this song live once. Awesome. Might not have the same presence a cappella style though.', 62, '2015-06-11 04:47:31'),
(1726, 786, 'Yeah, I can feel these flowing into each other. Interesting, turning two non-Christian songs into one that is. Not sure how I feel about calling God darling, but that could be omitted. I noticed how you altered the chorus of Rather Be slightly.', 62, '2015-06-11 04:54:53'),
(1727, 471, 'Not sure why people don''t like the lyrics. Sure, it''s praise-oriented, but it''s a good song.', 62, '2015-06-11 05:02:15'),
(1728, 157, 'I can''t comment on the arrangement, but I really like the song and haven''t heard it anywhere in a while.\r\n', 53, '2015-06-11 12:01:49'),
(1729, 787, 'This song is not very explicit, though it is by Skillet, a Christian band. It might not be the best for this semester, but it is a different genre from songs we typically do. ', 53, '2015-06-11 12:12:14'),
(1730, 157, 'The arrangement seems fine. Honestly, you could just kill the ending; I''m not sure where it came from. Might be a fun pick.', 62, '2015-06-11 23:32:58'),
(1731, 787, 'I agree, it could add variety to a setlist. It''s interesting because it''s by a Christian band but you''d kind of need a blurb to make sure people know it''s about Jesus. I''m skeptical as to how well this sort of song would translate to a cappella; none of us really sing like this.', 62, '2015-06-11 23:38:08'),
(1732, 151, 'This in not a Christian song, but I feel like for a love song it relates pretty well to a Christian''s testimony. "And be the one who catches all your tears/That''s why I need you to hear" would need to be changed, but otherwise whenever it references "all the pain I put you through" it is like how "I Will Glory in My Redeemer" says "Mine was the sin that drove the bitter nails." ', 53, '2015-06-12 12:05:31'),
(1733, 5, 'Party notes: the final chorus is fairly high for solo, especially if you do the adlib.', 40, '2015-06-12 15:04:44'),
(1734, 151, 'I loveeeee this song!', 47, '2015-06-12 21:32:40'),
(1735, 788, 'I am suggesting a Harvard Under Construction arrangement of a baptized "Incomplete." The old lyrics (where changed) are in parentheses. I said that it is prearranged because Harvard has an arrangement, but I don''t know if we can use theirs.\r\n\r\n', 53, '2015-06-13 13:57:14'),
(1736, 788, 'This has an interesting message because it is akin to the story of the prodigal son. Likewise, some of the psalms are like this. It is about the reaffirmation the God is worth more than anything else in this world. More than that, it is testament to the reality that once we experience the reality of God, we can''t go back to the way things were before. The rest of the world simply is not real enough to compare to the memory.', 53, '2015-06-13 14:02:48'),
(1737, 718, 'Please see baptized version via above comment from me. Lyrically, not much has changed. Instead, rather than having one soloist expressing both the push and pull experienced in the relationship, it splits it into a duet in which the christian pushes and God pulls.\r\n\r\nThe baptized version of this song comes back to me some times because of the poignancy of paradise lost. Also, the chorus is so true of many times in faith where we are desperate and angry to know how He could have let things unfold the way they did. But God''s rebuttal of being there for us in our darkest times. is all we need to know. (Think footprints in the sand)\r\n', 53, '2015-06-13 14:11:51'),
(1738, 789, 'This is a Baptized song by Harvard''s Under Construction. They really only change the raps. (They keeps some of the original rap too) I think that the goal was to use the message of the song''s chorus: the futility of our human efforts mixed with a message about the gospel rather than a bad relationship. What I really like about the rap is the way that they use parallel structure to juxtapose what we did to separate ourselves from God with what Christ did to bring us back. ', 53, '2015-06-13 14:41:00'),
(1739, 790, 'It is upbeat and catchy. I also really like the message of the bridge.', 53, '2015-06-13 14:46:53'),
(1740, 791, 'The a cappella version by Harvard Under Construction is very similar to the original. (There are a few noncritical word changes) This is another example of a love song which describes pretty well the romance between us and God. ', 53, '2015-06-13 15:06:08'),
(1741, 752, 'You''re right, this song is growing on me too. It''s so comforting, and musically nice too.', 62, '2015-06-13 16:04:15'),
(1742, 176, 'I didn''t care much for this song until I heard the xprod arrangement. Now I think it''s really awesome. It''s an interesting perspective, how God feels when we stray from him, and it''s done really well. This could round out a setlist very well.', 62, '2015-06-13 16:07:06'),
(1743, 151, 'Ooohh I like this song. I think it could work if we changed that one line. Could be as simple as "You''re the one that catches all my tears"', 62, '2015-06-13 16:09:39'),
(1744, 789, 'Personally I''m not a fan of changing songs to this degree.', 62, '2015-06-13 16:16:13'),
(1745, 790, 'Oh wow, yeah I like it when a song''s bridge is the best part rather than something that felt obligatory. I can definitely relate to the message: sometimes I feel like there''s something between me & God and I just need to ask him to break that down.', 62, '2015-06-13 16:29:08'),
(1746, 792, 'We''d probably never get a more perfect entry into rap for our group, with how this song so wonderfully implements so many choral aspects in it.  This song moves well, and ends powerfully as a declaration of just how much God is meant to be, and is.  There are a few hard parts for those who will do the rap, but we have to start somehow if we ever want to, and I have found personally that it is actually easier to develop a solid rap style and sound with faster parts, as the slow parts are easy to just sound like us talking.  And we got a slew of guys who can do this.', 48, '2015-06-13 19:24:06'),
(1747, 584, 'I really do like the build up.  I think it ties well to the message of redemption - humble beginning, but strong ending.', 61, '2015-06-13 20:29:02'),
(1748, 793, 'I love the message of the original hymn, especially after hearing about the story of the songwriter, Horatio Spafford.  I think this could be a good modern twist of the original that might be more suited to our generation.', 61, '2015-06-13 20:37:17'),
(1749, 784, 'I really liked the choral arrangement by Mustard Seed!  Would it still sound good with a smaller (understatement) group? :)', 61, '2015-06-13 20:40:33'),
(1750, 781, 'Awesome sounding song - how to translate to acappella?  Who knows.  Pertinent message - about the steadfastness of God''s love.  It''s something I think MIT students particularly struggle with, especially when we feel inadequate.', 61, '2015-06-13 20:56:54'),
(1751, 128, 'I''ve never found the lyrics to be inaccesible, but maybe you would if you didn''t grow up in the church. I''ve never liked any "modern" renditions of this song because, knowing the story behind it, it''s not exactly a happy, bubbly song. As a slow hymn, though, I think it''s really powerful, but maybe you would need a blurb to explain it.', 62, '2015-06-13 22:47:39'),
(1752, 731, 'Same comment as last semester.  Arrangement wouldn''t have to sound exactly like this - just that kind of style.', 58, '2015-06-14 18:52:41'),
(1753, 799, 'I know Revelation Song went down well with all the languages and I thought this might be good to do something like the version above.  There is a chance it would be too similar, but I think it would sound good.', 58, '2015-06-14 19:04:10'),
(1754, 749, 'Mmm, this takes me back...I like Caitlin''s comment about the lead-in/out thing. Or as an all-guys "jesu dulcis" kind of thing. ', 57, '2015-06-14 21:40:00'),
(1755, 472, 'I feel like this could be a very tender and honest song in our set. I like the idea of having a song that addresses the tougher stuff. I also agree with Shion''s comment and I think it could make the follow-up song even more meaningful in light of this one.', 57, '2015-06-15 00:08:55'),
(1756, 769, 'I like this song - it''s super catchy and I think it translates pretty well to a cappella.  We can copy the clapping beat and the duet!', 61, '2015-06-15 17:06:22'),
(1757, 756, 'I think there a few parts in the lyrics that I don''t think fits as a worship song - maybe we can adjust slightly? \r\n\r\nAlso, just a note (haha), Bono sings really high, at least for my range.', 61, '2015-06-15 17:18:06'),
(1758, 680, 'Check out the third Youtube link - it''s a really awesome (definitely Christian) version of the song.  ', 61, '2015-06-15 17:40:16'),
(1759, 680, 'I updated the lyrics to Cloverton''s Christian version.  It basically tells the nativity story in a really powerful way.  The melody is also super popular and almost everyone will recognize the song.  In short, it would be a great song for caroling! :)', 61, '2015-06-15 18:00:46'),
(1760, 787, 'I feel like this would go well with Evanescence''s Bring Me to Life.  If anything, our a cappella version of Bring Me to Life would give a glimpse at how we could arrange it for a cappella.', 61, '2015-06-15 21:01:55'),
(1761, 619, 'Actually, I think I can envision a very catchy a cappella version of this song!  We can finally use the syllable "bap" :P', 61, '2015-06-16 01:41:06'),
(1762, 756, 'Maybe it''s not exactly a worship song, but I think this song is a first rate example of a secular song that can be turned to God with little to no changes (actually I believe it was written about God, although it''s not explicit). Jesus is a "window in the skies," a way we can see and be with God in heaven. The refrain "oh can''t you see what love has done, what it''s doing to me" is so cool because it expresses this unrestrained urge to share God''s love and the changes in our when we encounter it.', 62, '2015-06-16 02:10:21'),
(1763, 680, 'I actually heard a baptized version of this song live once. The singer used some of the same lyrics (the first verse I remember was unchanged) but changed others and turned it to God. I agree with Meiji--this is definitely not a Christian song--and I generally don''t like changing song lyrics, but with this particular song it might be appropriate. I''ll see if I can find a recording of what I''m talking about.', 62, '2015-06-16 02:19:33'),
(1764, 680, 'I believe it was Leonard Cohen''s "Another Hallelujah" that I was remembering. Eh, maybe it isn''t a good idea, but I remember the song being cool when I heard it at a Greg Laurie festival. As much as I would like to turn this ironic hallelujah to God, I could see people saying it''s a cheap parody of a "great song."', 62, '2015-06-16 03:29:20'),
(1765, 680, 'Edit: Lincoln Brewster, sorry', 62, '2015-06-16 03:30:07'),
(1766, 800, 'Reading the lyrics, they''re actually pretty cool. No matter who the world tells us we are, we can assert that we are God''s children.', 62, '2015-06-16 03:33:48'),
(1767, 799, 'Mhm, definitely. I was actually thinking of this song when I heard your version of Revelation Song.', 62, '2015-06-16 03:37:43'),
(1768, 800, 'I actually really like this song as well - it''s catchy and I think the lyrics are witty and easy to understand.  I like how it starts with the identities of regret and defeat and ends with "child of the one true king."  It''s a clear, relatable, and clever progression of verses.', 61, '2015-06-16 04:42:47'),
(1769, 752, 'It''s really catchy :)', 61, '2015-06-16 05:39:34'),
(1770, 596, '... Or "This is What You Do" by Bethel!', 61, '2015-06-16 08:09:50'),
(1771, 596, '"This is what you do, this is what you do ooh ooh ooh"  "You make beautiful things!" lol', 61, '2015-06-16 08:10:53'),
(1772, 792, 'I feel like the lyrics in the rap are pretty hard to understand at a first glance - even for me.  I fear it might be even harder for non-Christians to relate.', 61, '2015-06-16 08:12:44'),
(1773, 471, 'At first listen, the lyrics seem a little vague, but they actually have several important messages inside -- God heals & restores us (physically and spiritually), our faith is counter to "reality"/the world but we don''t have to see it to believe it, God''s great love for us and our response (bridge).', 50, '2015-06-16 12:34:18'),
(1774, 651, 'I agree that it would probably be hard to listen to for a non-Christian audience, especially since the lyrics are solely focused on how everyone will come worship.', 50, '2015-06-16 12:40:37'),
(1775, 157, 'My favorite line: "But the beauty of grace is that it makes life not fair." I love and need God''s grace, but I struggle with it at the same time, and this line puts it perfectly.', 50, '2015-06-16 12:52:21'),
(1776, 596, 'This is What You Do -- I like how that would add energy to the mashup.', 50, '2015-06-16 12:55:49'),
(1777, 778, 'I like how this song focuses on how we not only died with Christ, but also rose again to new life. I feel like a lot of songs talk about guilt and forgiveness, but here the emphasis is on a life of worship. I''m not sure how this will translate to a cappella, though. @Hans: I agree that we shouldn''t censor our setlist to eliminate everything that could be hard to relate to. It''s important to consider our audience in the setlist overall, as we are a ministry that''s trying to reach people, but having God at the center of our focus is definitely most important.', 50, '2015-06-16 13:29:49'),
(1778, 790, 'I like the bridge, too. I also like how we''re asking God to break us down with His mercy because He does it out of His love for us rather than out of His wrath.', 50, '2015-06-16 13:35:18'),
(1779, 772, 'A love song to God! I love how the beat complements the lyrics in showing our excitement and joy. It can very easily become a SB friendly song, which is nice, but I would pair it with a more explicit song, since (except for "Lord" in the 2nd verse) it''s not super obvious that we''re singing to God.', 50, '2015-06-16 14:03:32'),
(1780, 794, 'I love this as a worship song, but I''m not sure it would translate to a cappella.', 50, '2015-06-16 14:10:11'),
(1781, 777, 'Lyrically: Psalm 23, Deuteronomy 31:6. Musically: it''s really repetitive.', 50, '2015-06-16 15:53:08'),
(1782, 785, 'I agree -- this would probably work better for a cappella in a mashup.', 50, '2015-06-16 16:06:31'),
(1783, 794, 'Mashup?', 62, '2015-06-16 16:10:56'),
(1784, 754, '@Barry: I would interpret it as "life with Jesus is sweet." I can see this being popular with our audience and lyrically it works pretty well even without changes.', 50, '2015-06-16 16:22:05'),
(1785, 752, 'The line "Thinking there''s worth in what you do" edges a little on the faith v. works debate, which I think would be clarified with a good blurb. I get what he''s saying (we''re made flawless because of God''s grace, not anything we did/can do), but the way he phrases it makes it seem like he''s disregarding the value of righteous behavior altogether. On a completely separate note, I like how flawlessness here isn''t just being made perfect in spite of the sin you''ve committed, but also being made perfect in spite of the wrongs done to you.', 50, '2015-06-16 18:42:03'),
(1786, 770, 'It''s so joyful and light and celebratory! I could totally sing and dance to this song. Musically, the style / energy reminds me of My Lighthouse, and I like the duet. Also, it''s SB friendly.', 50, '2015-06-17 23:55:44'),
(1787, 798, 'I can hear this translating well to a cappella (especially the perc / clapping).', 50, '2015-06-18 00:23:55'),
(1788, 786, 'For the most part the lyrics work. I''d prefer that they weren''t so questioning (won''t you understand? if you gave me a chance). Would need a good blurb / a song paired with it saying how God is always with us. Also, I''m not really sure how the prechorus of Rather Be relates.', 50, '2015-06-18 00:52:07'),
(1789, 510, 'I like the Christmas feel. And I like our arrangement- very choral :)  ', 55, '2015-06-18 04:47:28'),
(1790, 773, 'ooooooo I like :) I agree with Becky on the cool things (personally, I hear some toned down body perc as a super simple choreo.  Also, syncopation!!  ', 55, '2015-06-18 05:13:35'),
(1791, 731, 'This is one of my favorite hymns.  Looking ahead to spring, this would be a great song for Spring Break because a lot of people would probably know it.  Also agree with Meiji- it sounds very hard to do well.', 55, '2015-06-18 05:16:50'),
(1792, 0, '', 50, '2015-06-18 20:59:36'),
(1793, 737, 'I like this as a worship song. I''m not sure it would translate well to a cappella, though, since it''s pretty repetitive and doesn''t really "go" anywhere (other than a slow dynamic build to the bridge).', 50, '2015-06-18 21:00:47'),
(1794, 128, 'I think the hymn carries the emotion of the lyrics much better than the other versions.', 50, '2015-06-18 21:22:00'),
(1795, 782, 'Very snazzy. Also SB friendly.', 50, '2015-06-18 21:48:07'),
(1796, 795, 'I love this line: "When my days are few and death is near I run to you and you alone ''Cause you''re my light in the dark and I sing with all of my heart." In life, we run to God in our times of joy and times of fear. Really, though, our entire life is one long marathon run toward God. On our deathbed, we''re on the final sprint through the last bit of darkness before we reach the light.', 50, '2015-06-18 22:13:18'),
(1797, 652, 'I can''t decide whether the arrangement detracts or adds to the lyrics. On the one hand, people tend not to pay attention to lyrics of songs they know really well so a different arrangement of a common Christmas song might make them stop and listen. It could also be distracting, though. Thoughts?', 50, '2015-06-18 22:20:24'),
(1798, 781, 'A lot of songs like this are from the human perspective, where we talk about our struggles and then declare in faith that God''s steadfast love is there for us through it all. Coming from God''s perspective is so much more reassuring because He has indeed promised us this and constantly reminds us of this! "I''m here to remind you my love remains." Isaiah 41:13-14. Matthew 28:20.', 50, '2015-06-18 22:34:22'),
(1799, 792, 'I really like the use of Psalm 1/Jeremiah 17 and what they did with the extended metaphor of being a tree firmly rooted in Christ! I agree with Hans, though, that it''s kind of hard to understand because the lyrics/meaning is so dense, especially if you''re not familiar with it already.', 50, '2015-06-18 22:46:20'),
(1800, 584, 'For some reason I can''t get the youtube video to show on this site, so here is the URL: https://youtu.be/L9X2Xm1jq3U?t=3730 (1:02:10). A Caitlin Kerr arrangement.', 50, '2015-06-18 23:09:14'),
(1801, 753, 'Oh, the irony that we keep trying so hard, when in reality it''s not about what we can grab for ourselves, but the beauty of what God gives freely to us. Also, SB friendly.', 50, '2015-06-18 23:30:28'),
(1802, 758, '@Caitlin: Yeah, if you could find a recording, that would be great. I''m not really sure I get what it''s supposed to sound like from the instrumental recording.', 50, '2015-06-18 23:35:27'),
(1803, 767, 'I can also see this standing by itself with a message reminiscent of Like An Avalanche + Oceans.', 50, '2015-06-18 23:54:58'),
(1804, 782, 'I really like this song! I don''t know how it could translate to a cappella but it''s super upbeat and happy! (Also, is that an airplane at the beginning?!?)', 55, '2015-06-19 00:45:30'),
(1805, 782, 'I agree, this is so upbeat and groovy!  Stylistically it might offer a nice variety in our set list.  It may be difficult, but I think we could come up with a pretty cool arrangement.', 58, '2015-06-19 02:24:14'),
(1806, 786, 'I like this idea and think this could work out well if we mash them together and take out the parts that are less relevant.  I think using popular songs like this can really help us to convey our message. (I''m thinking every time people here this after our concert, they''ll think of it from a new perspective) :)', 58, '2015-06-19 02:57:39'),
(1807, 751, 'I also really like the Amazing Grace part.  I think it could work really well even if we do something as simple as what''s done here!', 58, '2015-06-19 02:58:57'),
(1808, 766, 'I think this would be a really good song to incorporate into our concert.  I like the link to Christmas while it still conveys so much about our belief of who Jesus is.', 58, '2015-06-19 03:01:53'),
(1809, 798, 'I love the message that this song that we are all ''famous in our Father''s eyes.''  I feel that this is really applicable to MIT that we aren''t defined by our GPA - every one of us is valued by God.', 58, '2015-06-19 03:05:57'),
(1810, 619, 'I''ve listened to this song so so much in the past months.  I agree with Hans - I think we could get a pretty cool arrangement!', 58, '2015-06-19 03:07:15'),
(1811, 176, 'I love this song so much! I''ve listened to the xprod arrangement so much.  I think it could bring some really interesting diversity to our set', 58, '2015-06-19 03:08:28'),
(1812, 30, 'I think this song really expresses one of the hardest things about being Christian- praising God no matter what.  Personally, I find it hard to praise God through times of hardship.  But even in the hard times and the storm, we know that God is with us.', 55, '2015-06-19 03:28:09'),
(1813, 794, 'love the idea of a bethel mashup!', 47, '2015-06-20 03:25:24'),
(1814, 424, 'Considering how we only sang this two years ago (including at GBIS) I think it might be best to wait on.', 53, '2015-06-20 19:39:39'),
(1815, 513, 'I really like this too. One thing to keep in mind is that you need to have a really well enunciated rapper in order for the audience to have any hope of hearing the message. IE For me rap takes a couple of listens with lyrics to really appreciate.', 53, '2015-06-20 19:55:07'),
(1816, 768, 'I was thinking that this could be really cool to do if we host BiDB. In many ways, calling forth God''s presence is what BiDB is all about.', 53, '2015-06-20 20:12:21'),
(1817, 779, 'I feel like we could arrange this as a more traditional style hymn, kind''ve like some of our GLAD arrangements. ', 53, '2015-06-20 20:13:50'),
(1818, 783, 'We''d definately have to rewrite the bridge, which I think would be ok. (It could be bad if we just picked and chose parts) I also think that we should replace "So" with "Now" in the chorus to show that there is a difference between our past and present attitude.', 53, '2015-06-20 20:20:32'),
(1819, 607, 'Sorry, I accidentally suggested it this time around.', 53, '2015-06-20 20:25:41'),
(1820, 796, 'Some of the rocked up worship songs from the Newsboys are pretty cool, but this one just brings me back to kids church. Sorry. ', 53, '2015-06-20 20:42:51'),
(1821, 472, 'It''s poignant and straight from the heart. It is especially so because it is really easy to start asking if God is so great that He doesn''t care about our relatively insignificant existence. \r\n\r\nI guess to contrast this from Praise You in the Storm: (See Shion''s comment) This doesn''t soften the pain by making any promise to God. It doesn''t really seek to comfort the speaker or resolve the issue. Rather, it is straight from the heart. In this sense, it is really authentic, but also needs another song to resolve it. ', 53, '2015-06-20 20:50:43'),
(1822, 769, 'This sounds like a worship song. After hearing it, I''m actually surprised that I have never sung this at Cru or Aletheia. ', 53, '2015-06-20 20:54:51'),
(1823, 800, 'I have listened to this song a lot and I liked it even more after fully reading the lyrics.  I think that it''s great that it proclaims that we are children of God', 58, '2015-06-20 21:01:19'),
(1824, 680, 'Reading the comments from the Christmas one, the Christians tend to like it, but the nonChristians hate it. From what I have read, the original song draws reference from the Bible to write about a dark love. Taking something written to look like a Christian song but actually not, and then making it actually about God can seriously detract from the original artistry which people tend to not like.', 53, '2015-06-20 21:06:54'),
(1825, 800, 'Blurbing this could be pretty cool.', 53, '2015-06-20 21:08:19'),
(1826, 157, 'I think that some of the syllables could be changed. ', 53, '2015-06-20 21:18:01'),
(1827, 776, 'I love this idea of a mashup!  I''ve always thought these songs could be quite powerful, but it''s difficult to have them standing alone', 58, '2015-06-20 21:19:32'),
(1828, 790, 'I love how it addresses that even our desire to believe is by the grace of God. Really, each and every day we are asking God to put to death in us the part of us which won''t let us belong to God. This song is aimed exactly for this. ', 53, '2015-06-20 21:26:17'),
(1829, 777, 'I''m not so sure how we would fit this style of song into our concert.', 53, '2015-06-20 21:33:07'),
(1830, 796, 'Don''t know why we couldn''t do it as a hymn though.', 62, '2015-06-20 21:37:30'),
(1831, 769, 'I think it''s pretty new, that''s why ^_^', 62, '2015-06-20 21:44:21'),
(1832, 773, 'I''m personally not a huge fan of this version. The background kind of just drones on, and the way that they break every verse to stand alone and be repeating the tune of the ones before makes this song really boring for me. Also, again personal opinion, I find the different rhythm to feel strangely off balance.', 53, '2015-06-20 21:59:35'),
(1833, 731, 'I totally rediscovered this guy on my own and really like his arrangements. ', 53, '2015-06-20 22:01:00'),
(1834, 737, 'I listen to this kind of worship song when I am trying to pray or meditate, so I personally like it, but really can''t see us singing it to an audience.\r\n', 53, '2015-06-20 22:02:19'),
(1835, 773, 'Yeah, I''d prefer it as a hymn.', 62, '2015-06-20 22:02:41'),
(1836, 128, 'I also much prefer the original hymn. In addition to the fact that this is not a "happy, bubbly song" (Barry) because the hymn is much more familiar to audiences it might be weird for them unless the new version manages to really add depth to the meaning or something. I don''t really think that this version accomplishes that. ', 53, '2015-06-20 22:06:43'),
(1837, 795, 'I like the lyrics, but something about the style doesn''t sit great with me. Maybe it is that Owl City''s style clashes with his message, or that I just can''t imagine singing it a cappella. I''m not sure.', 53, '2015-06-20 22:09:56'),
(1838, 652, 'I love this Christmas song! No comment on the arrangement. ', 53, '2015-06-20 22:10:38'),
(1839, 781, 'This would be an interesting a cappella conversion because you can''t just steal the instrument parts, but I''m sure that the feel can be replicated otherwise. ', 53, '2015-06-20 22:13:19'),
(1840, 792, 'I really like the song after listening a few times. That said, I didn''t get it either the first several times. I like the sound of the rap part, and the chorus is stuck in my head, but it doesn''t help if the audience doesn''t get more than music.', 53, '2015-06-20 22:19:35'),
(1841, 584, 'Keep in mind that we sang this just over one year ago...', 53, '2015-06-20 22:20:49'),
(1842, 782, 'It is interesting because this song is indirectly directed toward the audience. ', 53, '2015-06-20 22:29:39'),
(1843, 786, '"Replace" darling with "Jesus" LoL no longer SB friendly', 53, '2015-06-20 22:34:16'),
(1844, 766, 'This Christmas song manages to really delve into some of the great realities of Christianity which was why I was so surprised when I heard PTX (a secular group) sing it. It is so explicit, but because it is a Christmas song you can sing it anywhere around Christmas. \r\n\r\nIn general, I feel like you would need a Christmas element supported by several songs in order to incorporate any. Otherwise they clash a bit with all the rest of the songs.', 53, '2015-06-20 22:38:30'),
(1845, 798, 'I''m not living for applause\r\nI''m already so adored\r\n\r\nI feel that MIT Christians really need to hear this message, but it will be completely glossed over without a convicting testimony. Specifically, we tend not to think it sufficient to exist solely for God to delight in us. As in, if God decided to never show us off before other people then most MIT students would have a serious fit. ', 53, '2015-06-20 22:42:08'),
(1846, 176, 'One really nice thing about this rap is that you can actually understand it without too much difficulty. ', 53, '2015-06-20 22:47:02'),
(1847, 791, 'was listening to this song on spotify the other day on throwback thursday and was thinking the same thing ^ ! :)', 47, '2015-06-21 01:06:13'),
(1848, 769, 'cute song!', 47, '2015-06-21 01:59:10'),
(1849, 781, 'beautiful song, beautiful message! arrangement could be interesting!', 47, '2015-06-21 02:04:43'),
(1850, 758, 'I added a sketchy recording of me singing it! It''s too late for this semester but might be helpful for the future. I didn''t put the bass/tenor down an octave because the distortion was too weird, but hopefully it gives you an idea of the pretty chords. It sounds a lot better when you add the richness of real tenors and basses.', 37, '2015-07-11 22:33:08'),
(1851, 749, 'Suggesting this one again because God is awesome. I think the a cappella version is really cool. It provides multiple things to a setlist at once (it has choir/hymn elements as well as a hinting of rap influences in the verses--and it would be fun to sing)', 62, '2015-12-08 23:41:15'),
(1852, 803, 'The first time I listened to this song, it gave me chills, and at this point I would probably list it in my top 10 favorite songs of all time. The lyrics are incredibly powerful in a humbling sort of way. I mean, how often is God the last thing we think about, how little do we deserve His love, yet He gives it to us anyway. It''s powerful musically too--the chords, the high note...it would take a good arrangement and a good soloist who could do it justice, but I think we are capable of having both of those things.', 62, '2015-12-08 23:50:30'),
(1853, 758, 'This sounds really pretty! I think it''d be fun to do because it''s different from most of what we have (no solo, all singing the same words, could focus more on blend/chords), like Jesu from last year but with everyone and in English. I agree with Caitlin about the sense of reverence, but I also like that juxtaposed with the intimacy of the lyrics.', 62, '2015-12-09 05:47:35'),
(1854, 477, 'I added yet another video because Yale performed this at BiDB last year, and their arranement is incredible. Far from being boring/old-fashioned, it was probably one of the most impressive songs at BiDB.', 62, '2015-12-09 06:03:14'),
(1855, 561, 'So this was done in Fall 2014, but that''s just as recent as Be Thou My Vision was last year, so it''s not too early to recylce it. From what I understand the arrangement is really good, and Caitlin herself said that this was her favorite song Xprod did during her four years. I absolutely love this song. It serves as a reminder that this world is broken, and that Earth is not our true home but a mere pitstop on our way to God''s kingdom in Heaven. But it explains this in an agaty sort of way, in a way that resonates with me whenever I''m feeling crushed by the weight of the world.', 62, '2015-12-09 06:11:51'),
(1856, 245, 'My mom and I used to sing this song all the time. It''s sort of funny (which I think people listening will enjoy) but it''s also true that we should praise God no matter how we or the world perceive we are. And sometimes we just need to be reminded that we aren''t cool--it''s not about us, it''s about God.', 62, '2015-12-10 00:23:24'),
(1857, 804, 'I think this would be a great choice for a rap song. It''s pretty chill/sonic for rap, and it''s an honest, humble declaration of faith. Even though we aren''t perfect, and trusting in God may be hard, we keep on following Him. He is greater than everything, and without him we are nothing.', 62, '2015-12-10 01:00:16'),
(1858, 218, 'Based on past comments, I un-marked as pre-arranged due to a hard past arrangement.  That being said, I think this song shows the power of what God can do, it''s fairly well known, and just always makes me happy.', 55, '2015-12-11 17:08:36'),
(1859, 222, 'I feel like this song would be a good first or second song in our set. It is very explicit, but it''s said well- that we need Jesus, and he saves us- and we can''t do it on our own.  Also, country song (new genre??)', 55, '2015-12-11 17:24:11'),
(1860, 444, 'This song hits like a truck. I think it''d cause audience members to think, in a good way. You may never be convinced intellectually, but what if the gospel is true--that changes everything.', 62, '2015-12-12 15:14:48'),
(1861, 731, 'Not necessarily resuggesting the arrangement, just the hymn in general. (but I also really like the arrangements)', 55, '2015-12-12 21:05:54'),
(1862, 805, 'This song is another "give your worries to God" song, but I think it''s different from most in how freeing it feels, especially in the chorus. Somehow it gets my heart involved every time I hear it. It''s a proclamation of who God is and how that allows us to cast our cares on him alone. I also think it could translate to a fun a cappella arrangement well.', 37, '2015-12-13 23:02:20'),
(1863, 805, 'Also with some fun body perc.', 37, '2015-12-13 23:10:22'),
(1864, 758, 'I just relistened to my recording from July and cringed, so I recorded another version that is hopefully more close to how xprod would sound singing it. Sounds weird with the bass down an octave though because I can''t sing that low :) Happy listening!', 37, '2015-12-15 02:53:10'),
(1865, 584, 'If you sing this again, please let me edit the arrangement to make it more singable :)', 37, '2015-12-15 03:10:36'),
(1866, 808, 'Mmm brings me back. Always loved this tune. It''s a love song to God and a declaration of his glory and might all at once.', 62, '2015-12-16 15:17:54'),
(1867, 810, 'I could see this as a fun closer to a setlist (especially if we opened with "Jesus Take the Wheel" haha)', 62, '2015-12-16 15:48:28'),
(1868, 208, 'I always seem to associate these two songs with each other, and musically, I think they work for a mashup.  I think there''s something really powerful in saying both, God is Everlasting, and he is our everything, we live through his power.', 55, '2015-12-18 02:38:14'),
(1869, 813, 'This is one of my favorite worship songs. The idea of realizing how broken our world is and how God is the only one who can save it is something I sometimes forget to call out to God about. I know it''s slow, but I think with well-placed perc it could be made more lively or we could keep it as a slow point in the set.', 64, '2015-12-18 17:42:58'),
(1870, 814, 'one of my favorite hymns! added a non-GLAD arrangement above :P', 47, '2015-12-18 21:38:28'),
(1871, 815, 'simple, clear lyrics!', 47, '2015-12-19 01:45:38'),
(1872, 817, 'I think this song would be good for xprod to sing for several reasons: 1. The message of stopping the fight and resting, giving God control, and choosing to worship him, 2. It has that battle hymn drive which I like, and 3. It tiptoes the line between worship and not worship. By that I mean it is a worship song, but it tells a story, so it isn''t awkward to listen to if you are also not actively worshipping.', 37, '2015-12-19 01:56:02'),
(1873, 816, 'prearranged by UC; paints a picture of feeling hopeless, broken and lost- but finding revival and healing through Jesus. british rock band mashup fit for a trip to the UK ;) \r\n\r\nminor qualm is the lyric ''try to fix''.. something more along the lines of ''i am already here'' and ''i have the power to transform you'' might be better. thoughts?', 47, '2015-12-19 02:04:03'),
(1874, 818, 'I heard this song on the radio and was mesmerized by the pre chorus. I could listen to it all day long (0:51-1:07, 1:59-2:15) The rest of the song is just eh, but I have some ideas for how this could translate to a really fun a cappella arrangement. Think logs popping out of the clump. Can also use Amazing Grace as an intro/outro/overlay on bridge. Grace wins is an important message! And the chord structure (and also the rhythmic patterns) helps bring out that tension and then revel in the victory.', 37, '2015-12-19 02:05:25'),
(1875, 819, 'different from our usual style, but yay moar rap! the rap is slightly slower which i like- easier to understand the lyrics. the chorus is definitely a prayer i pray often', 47, '2015-12-19 02:11:42'),
(1876, 820, 'simple honest lyrics, catchy, soulful melody. a bit repetitive but i think it can give way to a pretty creative arrangement', 47, '2015-12-19 02:44:03'),
(1877, 821, 'was on the top 50 spanish billboard charts a couple months ago haha; lyrics are not too deep and kinda repetitive, but thought i''d suggest it anyway :P it''s pretty good edm in my opinion!', 47, '2015-12-19 03:22:25'),
(1878, 822, 'We are dearly beloved by God, held close to His heart, and that is what we place our identity in. What He says is truth, and what He believes about us is who we are.', 50, '2015-12-19 22:16:58'),
(1879, 823, 'We know that God is there with us through tough times, but we often turn to ourselves or others to help us, instead of surrendering completely to Him and asking Him to come rescue us. Also, I think this song could work well in an a cappella arrangement.', 50, '2015-12-19 22:36:23'),
(1880, 816, 'Ignoring any potential theological qualms, I''m really a fan of the arrangement. Clocks is taken too slow, and Fix You is too fast, since they''re not the same tempo, and there''s very little overlap in the mashup since the cords are different too. Not a fan of the soloist being an alto either.', 62, '2015-12-20 17:48:03'),
(1881, 484, 'Random unnecessary backup vocals and key changes are two pet peeves of mine, and this arrangement commits both of them. But beyond that it seems like a song that everyone would like to both hear and sing. Kind of like "Joy"', 62, '2015-12-20 17:54:13'),
(1882, 15, 'It''s more of a song for Christians I think. I''m not sure how it would be perceived by a secular audience.', 62, '2015-12-20 17:58:46'),
(1883, 14, 'I really love this hymn. It tells the story of Jesus really well and affirms our place with Him. But the arrangement is sort of pulsing and not really hymn-like. Maybe it''s just the recording, but I''m not crazy about the way the background sounds. Bass solos galore though ^_^', 62, '2015-12-20 18:04:08'),
(1884, 172, 'I agree with some of the above comments. I could completely see this song being in a Disney movie or something and having nothing to do with Jesus. That said, singing it would be not different from singing most secular songs that we do--we''d just want a blurb. And it sounds good, provided you can nail the dissonant chords.', 62, '2015-12-20 18:09:55'),
(1885, 508, 'And it''s going to be on the EP we''re releasing around the time of the concert! I''d want to do it with one soloist the whole way through though.', 62, '2015-12-20 18:22:33'),
(1886, 751, 'It was Rutger''s First Light that has the arrangement', 62, '2015-12-20 18:32:49'),
(1887, 443, 'Amherst TI also has an arrangement which they sang last year at BiDB. (Solo only - no duet). This song might be good for this year''s group, as its highest solo note is only a Gb. ', 53, '2015-12-20 19:47:23'),
(1888, 526, 'This is a beautiful song which could be arranged for either a male or female solo. I imagine that we would leave out the perc and trumpet solo (make that almost all the instrumental solos). The background will probably be focussed on the chords rather than on super interesting moving parts. \r\n\r\nThat said, this would be best arranged ground up, rather than stealing the instrumental parts. (ie from chords to dynamically and rhythmically varying moving chords)', 53, '2015-12-20 19:55:58'),
(1889, 826, 'This song is a call to arms, to fight on the side of love. We, the people of God, are told to love our enemies and do good to those who hate us. We fight the battle against hate, each and every one of us standing up for the kingdom of God.', 50, '2015-12-20 20:01:01'),
(1890, 827, 'This song describes how God is Lord over all creation. \r\n\r\nI like how the background is interesting without being crazy. With this song it would be entirely straight-forward to simply transcribe the instruments into voice parts. Admittedly, a good arrangement goes far beyond just this. (for instance, the background should probably jump in to support the soloist at some points)\r\n\r\nMy feeling is that this song is all about captivating the audience by building suspense, so dynamics and solo quality are essential. ', 53, '2015-12-20 20:05:58'),
(1891, 828, 'This song is really heavy, but it has an incredible message of triumph while acknowledging a lot of today''s problems. It reminds us that though things are falling apart, one day God will triumph over all of that.', 63, '2015-12-20 20:10:36'),
(1892, 829, 'I love how this song is a celebration of life and life abundant. Christ has called us into a beautiful romance, an adventure that takes us beyond the familiar and transforms us into wholehearted, brave, and free individuals. Also, I think this song could be a lot of fun to sing musically!', 50, '2015-12-20 20:17:03'),
(1893, 585, 'This has been suggested before, I''m just suggesting it again. I love this song and it always helps encourage me!', 63, '2015-12-20 20:22:01'),
(1894, 830, 'Great celebration song!!! Reminds us that we have been saved and that we have something to dance about.', 63, '2015-12-20 20:31:03'),
(1895, 832, 'This song has an incredible amount of swag and Christian pride. The raps are a bit difficult, but with practice I think we can get them.', 63, '2015-12-20 20:36:58'),
(1896, 834, 'I have no idea if we could find this already arranged, but it is already in a capella format, making it easier to arrange regardless. This group was my first intro to a capella, so give them a listen even if you don''t want to use this song.', 63, '2015-12-20 20:58:05'),
(1898, 836, 'This one is all about living a life with nothing held back, utterly given over to God''s purpose, it is challenging personally and also very fun to sing.', 63, '2015-12-20 21:04:57'),
(1899, 216, 'The lyrics are directly from Philippians 4:4-7. Rejoice! God''s been teaching me a lot about joy through all circumstances, and how living with joy is a choice. This more traditional style could be really pretty to sing and would contrast a lot of our more contemporary music.', 50, '2015-12-20 22:26:50'),
(1900, 838, 'I found this arrangement whilst digging through the xprod Athena locker. It''s so beautiful! It has a solid Gospel message and imagery.', 50, '2015-12-20 22:57:28'),
(1901, 839, 'So many times I find myself going to God for me instead of for Him. This song is a powerful reminder that He is first.', 50, '2015-12-20 23:59:22'),
(1902, 841, 'This arrangement is really cool! I like how the soloist is layered over the chanting of the background (reminds me of Baba Yetu for some reason). Lyrically, it''s speaking of our desire to be near to God through all things.', 50, '2015-12-21 01:24:07'),
(1903, 745, 'I love this song - it''s musically interesting and the words are really powerful.  Whatever life throws at us - and it will - we will not be shaken because our God goes with us.  For me, personally, what a fitting song for the conclusion of a tough semester.', 61, '2015-12-21 01:33:21'),
(1904, 807, 'I think this song is really musically interesting, especially as an acapella (see the second youtube link).  It''s a strong message to do our work in bringing restoration to a broken world - kind of like Make a Move, but more explicit.', 61, '2015-12-21 01:40:51'),
(1905, 842, 'secular song, but i feel like some parts of it could potentially be sung from God''s perspective', 47, '2015-12-21 01:46:51'),
(1906, 842, 'certain verses would definitely need to be revised/ mashed up with something else', 47, '2015-12-21 01:47:57'),
(1907, 172, 'Throwing out an idea out there: changing a couple of the "you"s to "He"s.  Could help to bring back the focus to God.  I personally think that''s a pretty innocuous change and I seriously doubt anybody in the audience would have qualms with it, since we are a /Christian/ acapella group.  What y''all think?', 61, '2015-12-21 01:49:32'),
(1908, 810, 'Lol, Barry.  But yes, it could be a cool closer :)  \r\nI do also think this is a very musically interesting, but somewhat-difficult-to-arrange, song.  The lyrics are almost unexpectedly down-to-earth and relatable (Got my iPhone bumping like "dom da dom").', 61, '2015-12-21 02:33:47'),
(1909, 825, 'Probably my favorite hymns - the words are just soo... alksjdkfjlaskjdfw... good.  dat third verse.  However, as a hymn, we have to somehow make it musically interesting and not feel repetitive - we gotta "GLAD" it up.', 61, '2015-12-21 02:34:24'),
(1910, 128, 'I suggest this as a hymn, since it''s pretty recognizable.  I think it''s hard to understand every word, but I think people will get the overall meaning, especially with a good blurb and (for our concert) the lyrics in front of them.', 61, '2015-12-21 02:38:06'),
(1911, 812, 'I stumbled onto this song on Spotify Radio, and the message really hit me in my grief.  We hold on to the hope that there will indeed be a day with no more tears, no more pain, and no more fears.  The world will be restored and whole - perfect in every measure.  But until then, cling on to Jesus, who comforts us when we are at our lowest points.\r\n\r\nI envision this song to be very choral - with most of the background parts singing the melody with the soloist, at least during the climax.  I think it would be powerful when we sing (as loudly as we can) together.', 61, '2015-12-21 02:50:26'),
(1912, 844, '50s style, meghan trainor-esque. lyrics aren''t too deep but it''s interestingly different from anything we''ve every done', 47, '2015-12-21 02:54:43'),
(1913, 845, 'pretty pop-y style; not a humongous fan but thought i''d suggest it anyway', 47, '2015-12-21 03:00:32');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(1914, 809, 'This song really spoke to me when I did feel especially broken and scattered.  I think our audience everywhere would find this song interesting because almost everybody knows the original Amazing Grace.  It could capture their attention by pulling the ol'' switcheroo, but with a song that, I think, is equally beautiful.', 61, '2015-12-21 03:04:32'),
(1915, 846, 'montell jordan was the guy who sang ''this is how we do it''; he left his music career and is now a worship minister at his church :O', 47, '2015-12-21 03:06:40'),
(1916, 808, 'Such a majestic song - tries to capture the glory of who God is.  I love the refrain of "The moon and the stars declare who you are", almost like Psalm 19.  Great melody as well - although maybe has a bit of that typical-contemporary-praise-song feel.  I feel like we could arrange it to be a lot more musically interesting - thinking something like Harvard Under Construction style.', 61, '2015-12-21 03:17:01'),
(1917, 843, 'A very powerful song - both lyrically and vocally.  It''s a very personal take on the Gospel story - that we sinned against God, but God loved us and saved us.  Love the intimacy in the song - it really focuses well between God and the singer.', 61, '2015-12-21 03:25:15'),
(1918, 66, 'It''s pretty interesting how it tells a story inside the song - almost like a mini skit (but without the props, please).  The first verse is super relatable to other Christians.  The song overall is a call to go outside of our comfort zone to be a blessing for the world.  ', 61, '2015-12-21 03:28:20'),
(1919, 824, 'It''s a modern take on an old (very solemn) hymn.  I really like the lyrics.  The imagery of light really convey the message of hope.', 61, '2015-12-21 03:34:10'),
(1920, 436, 'This is how we should be! We shouldn''t sing for our own glorification or our joy or to entertain other people. Rather, praise should burst from us in response to how amazing God is.', 50, '2015-12-21 03:40:56'),
(1921, 856, 'former Destiny''s Child member; the lyrics are a pretty familiar prayer..', 47, '2015-12-21 03:57:28'),
(1922, 218, 'I just added the youtube to Yale Living Water''s arrangement.', 50, '2015-12-21 04:00:48'),
(1923, 537, 'Resuggesting the Mashup', 55, '2015-12-21 04:13:05'),
(1924, 857, 'Who is our God? Behold, He is awesome and worthy of praise!', 50, '2015-12-21 04:29:12'),
(1925, 859, 'This would be really cool to do, since Tori Kelly is well known outside of the Christian circle, but wrote this song about her faith. It would definitely need a powerful female soloist, but I think the background would be really interesting as well!', 50, '2015-12-21 04:35:40'),
(1926, 861, 'I think this song can be very powerful in proclaiming the freedom Christ offers by His death.  It is clear in its lyrics, and the song moves rather well with power.  I love it.', 48, '2015-12-21 04:44:44'),
(1927, 17, 'Stanford Testimony did this song, and I think it sounds beautiful.  I appreciate just how the music reflects the call to Jesus, waiting to hear him come back, to answer.', 48, '2015-12-21 04:48:38'),
(1928, 867, 'I love the proclamation of Victory in this song.  This is an excellent finale song, speaking to our weaknesses, and claiming victory over all of them.  The third verse is definitely a powerful one to sum up the theme of this song.  And, it is a simple rap song with a beautiful ending for A cappella, I would think.', 48, '2015-12-21 04:55:41'),
(1929, 870, 'I love the way this song just sings personally to its audience.  It is an excellent song for catching people''s attention, and pouring love all over them.  To call them beloved.  (:', 48, '2015-12-21 05:04:02'),
(1930, 871, 'This song is a strong call to our brokenness (as even the title suggests) and to our need for Christ to put us together again.  I love the flow of the song, especially during the chorus/hook, interplaying our faults in the rap, and his glory in the chorus and bridge.', 48, '2015-12-21 05:10:54'),
(1931, 826, 'ooh i kinda like this!', 47, '2015-12-21 20:46:52'),
(1932, 828, 'oh wow, that''s really heavy.. really relevant though', 47, '2015-12-21 20:54:37'),
(1933, 817, '"You taught my feet To dance upon disappointment And I, I will worship" mm', 47, '2015-12-21 20:58:24'),
(1934, 872, 'This has been one of my favorite songs from when I was little, and it always reminds me that we are created in God''s image, which is something we always need to remember!', 64, '2015-12-21 22:20:42'),
(1935, 873, 'This is our purpose! To do everything in life for His Glory! Just like we want to always sing for His Glory, we should want to do all things for His Glory!', 64, '2015-12-21 22:24:19'),
(1936, 875, 'Sometimes all we can do is fall at His feet. This was me during the 18.02 final. He is always the ultimate solution no matter what we are going through, and often we can best understand that at His feet.', 64, '2015-12-21 22:32:19'),
(1937, 811, 'The message of this song is that we shouldn''t forget that this world is not where we belong.  We should live in the world but not live for it.  If we were given the choice between the world and Jesus, would we take Jesus?  I think it can make an interesting acapella arrangement.', 61, '2015-12-22 23:39:46'),
(1938, 815, 'This could be a pretty fun song to sing :)', 61, '2015-12-22 23:41:50'),
(1939, 828, 'Yah, agree with Phoebe...', 61, '2015-12-23 06:35:53'),
(1940, 875, 'This sounds like something that Xprod would sing...which is not necessarily good or bad', 62, '2015-12-23 17:48:23'),
(1941, 874, 'I think this is really relatable to MIT students. People want to do so much and frequently feel like failures, when really we are just incapable on our own and need God', 62, '2015-12-23 17:50:38'),
(1942, 873, 'I think it''d be cool to rewrite the verses to make them more MIT-relatable. Not many of us have babies, but if we talked about coding or bacteria or something...', 62, '2015-12-23 17:54:12'),
(1943, 676, 'Wait, I think this song meshes really well with "Give Us Clean Hands" by Chris Tomlin.  They both sing about not letting idols take God''s place.  And of course, both choruses (chori?) are (kinda) four chord songs and mesh perfectly: I''ll trade it all right now / Leave it all and lay it down / To get back to where I belong -> So give us clean hands / Give us pure hearts / let us not lift our souls to another...', 61, '2015-12-23 18:31:11'),
(1944, 859, 'Oh wow, this is really good. I''ve never heard of her, but apparently she''s new and Grammy-nominated, so I believe that people will know her. It''s a simple message but very beautiful.', 62, '2015-12-23 20:18:00'),
(1945, 537, 'So, I really like this mashup, but I don''t think we have the numbers to do this. This is the sort of thing that you want loud, and with 2 solos + perc at a time...I think this may be best left for another year.', 62, '2015-12-23 20:32:02'),
(1946, 851, 'This seems more like a love song to me than a worship song--at least from the video', 62, '2015-12-23 21:08:10'),
(1947, 850, 'Hey somebody else besides me knows this song! I really like it, but it''d take a lot of creativity with the arrangement considering it''s supposed to basically be guitar + vocals.', 62, '2015-12-23 21:13:50'),
(1948, 222, 'Not my favorite Carrie Underwood song *coughcough* but this is pretty good', 62, '2015-12-23 21:58:16'),
(1949, 834, 'My late grandfather used to love this song. It''s different than what we normally do, but it''s pretty cool. I kind of don''t think it was written about God, but we could totally sing it as such.', 62, '2015-12-23 22:33:49'),
(1950, 205, 'Stanford said we could use their arrangment. Although I heard it has like eight parts or something. The UC one sounds simpler. Beyond that, this is basically our purpose, and it''s a crowd pleaser.', 62, '2015-12-23 22:36:42'),
(1951, 851, 'I agree with Barry-  I really like the song and how it could translate to a cappella, but it seems like only the chorus can really be sung from a human to God perspective.', 55, '2015-12-24 17:56:43'),
(1952, 245, 'Added a recording from a concert of the xprod version.  Looking back into old concerts, I think it may be cool to make the lyrics more MIT.  Also, I feel like this song would have a decent impact on the skit if it was in our set.  But I think it gives a good message :)', 55, '2015-12-24 18:04:50'),
(1953, 561, 'See xprods arrangement. about 4:14 in the 3rd video.', 55, '2015-12-24 18:25:50'),
(1954, 828, 'This song definitely gives a lot of perspectives... especially when thinking outside of the MIT bubble.', 55, '2015-12-24 18:37:46'),
(1955, 852, 'I can''t really tell how I feel about this song.  I like it as it is, but I''m kinda having a hard time seeing how well it would translate to a cappella.', 55, '2015-12-24 19:40:18'),
(1956, 831, 'This style would be so cool to do! My main concern is that we''d need a really powerful soloist to carry this, and I''m having a hard time envisioning any of our current female soloists being able to pull it off.', 50, '2015-12-24 20:46:37'),
(1957, 837, 'Amazing Grace is one of the most well-known hymns, which makes it a great opportunity to reach out to a lot of people! That being said, sometimes songs that are too familiar are tricky because people zone out and don''t listen to what we''re saying. I think having the more upbeat / modern arrangement (like BYU''s) could help avoid that, but I wouldn''t want to lose the traditional hymn sound. Thoughts?', 50, '2015-12-24 20:56:12'),
(1958, 814, 'I''ve also added Columbia Jubilation!''s arrangement.', 50, '2015-12-24 21:12:16'),
(1959, 827, 'For a Christian audience, this resonates strongly, but I''m not sure how a non-Christian would respond to hearing this. Maybe it would be better if the lyrics spoke more about who God is rather than our response to who He is?', 50, '2015-12-24 21:27:35'),
(1960, 749, 'The Praise & Harmony a cappella arrangement is pretty simple, so we''d have to focus a lot on dynamics and style to keep it engaging. The Glad arrangement is more interesting, if y''all are down for more Glad... :P', 50, '2015-12-24 21:37:55'),
(1961, 810, 'I agree with Hans about it being a complicated arrangement (both to arrange and to learn). I think it could be a good option, but I''m not confident we have enough swag to pull it off.', 50, '2015-12-24 21:43:53'),
(1962, 749, 'I feel like if we could mash this up with another song, it would be the ultimate BIDB group song...  And I say we should mash it up because I just don''t know how group rapping would sound.', 61, '2015-12-24 21:48:00'),
(1963, 874, 'This could be a really fun arrangement to sing. I love how happy this song is, especially juxtaposed with the lyrics. Usually hearing that we are incapable is terrifying and discouraging, but here it''s a celebration of God and His strength. What we think is wrong is right in the middle of God''s plan for us.', 50, '2015-12-24 22:03:04'),
(1964, 473, 'I really love this song and how it speaks to our desperate need for God to come rescue us. Just as a heads up, the Chorallaries just covered it this fall (so they''ll probably also do it in the spring).', 50, '2015-12-24 22:09:55'),
(1965, 871, 'I really like the message, and the hook / chorus and bridge parts! I''m admittedly not a huge fan of rap in general (sorry Matthew)... I''m not sure how well this would translate to a cappella because it''s so reliant on the bass/perc. Maybe a good arranger could do it, though.', 50, '2015-12-24 22:28:55'),
(1966, 692, 'I also shared the Living Water Arrangement of this song, which I thought flowed well, and with strong dynamics gives the song a lot of power.', 48, '2015-12-24 23:43:53'),
(1967, 818, 'I love this song. That first verse is so good, so well placed to how everyone feels over so much as the semester rolls to an end, as finals and projects reach their deadline.  This song is perfect for MIT, a place that is built on making people who can stand on their own, and lead others.  We can''t stand on our own, we fall every time, but thanks be to God, grace wins every time.', 48, '2015-12-25 01:53:52'),
(1968, 822, 'I think that one phrase, "closer than the angels" is a powerful way to describe how close we are to God and how loved we are by God.  No one pictures us as closer to God, but to told that we are, is huge.', 48, '2015-12-25 02:31:15'),
(1969, 823, 'I love the last verse, or bridge if that is what it is.  A perfect song to fill out any setlist, just making our cry to Him that we need him, so clear.', 48, '2015-12-25 02:37:09'),
(1970, 816, 'I don''t remember who did the arrangement in BIDB during my sophomore year, but one group sang Coldplay''s song "Fix You."  They made an excellent change to that line, by instead singing "He gave his Life to Fix You."', 48, '2015-12-25 02:40:37'),
(1971, 809, 'I''m imagining it with an Oceans-esque arrangement.', 50, '2015-12-25 05:46:56'),
(1972, 561, 'That awkward moment when you have to watch yourself soloing... :P In all seriousness, though, the first time I ever heard this song, it made me cry. I love this song -- the lyrics that resonate so much with me and my walk of faith, and the haunting melody. That being said, I''d prefer to let it lie a little longer before xprod sings it again.', 50, '2015-12-25 06:07:48'),
(1973, 808, 'I can see the arrangement having higher moving parts and lower long held notes. It would have to have a more dynamic background, since the solo is pretty slow.', 50, '2015-12-25 06:12:42'),
(1974, 805, 'I love the line "You''re the anchor of my hope," for God is the one who grounds us so we can sail through the storms with confidence in the coming of the dawn. Why do we hold onto our worry when we could have God''s peace instead? Musically, it would be cool to have an interplay between the background and the solo.', 50, '2015-12-25 06:42:32'),
(1975, 475, 'None of the current xprods knows this, so it would be cool to do, especially since it''s easy to learn!', 50, '2015-12-25 06:46:26'),
(1976, 816, '@Matthew It was Adoremus from Johns Hopkins (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MMAfZac6u3k). @Barry, I agree that it seems a little disjointed between the 2 songs.', 50, '2015-12-25 06:59:12'),
(1977, 821, '^^I agree that I wish there was more to the lyrics, but I like the style!', 50, '2015-12-25 07:03:52'),
(1978, 831, '@Meiji, then leave it to the guys :P  Jkjk... But anyways, I think this would be a really awesome acapella arrangement.  It''s really dynamic and groovy, lots of interesting parts that would make a lot of cool voice parts.  I agree that it does require a powerful soloist, but I think we have the (wo)manpower to do it.  It''ll take a bit of workshopping to help people come out of their shells, but I think it''s worth it to train the next generation of divas who could project their voice not only during solos, but also for their background parts - especially since we''ve been having trouble with volume because of our small group size. Overall, I think this song will push our soloists, but that''s not necessarily a bad thing.', 61, '2015-12-25 07:15:23'),
(1979, 819, 'I think we have to be creative with the arrangement for this song because it''s repetitive and the background is pretty simple.  However, I do like the message of the song, and the chorus has awesome vocals.  ', 61, '2015-12-25 07:20:59'),
(1980, 828, 'I wish it answered the question "until that day" with more than just "this won''t be forever." We have hope in Christ for today, and victory now, not just for the future someday. Yes, ultimately these things too shall pass, but in the meantime God isn''t passively letting these things happen. I feel like this song mentions these terrible things and instead of addressing them, just says this is how it''s going to be until later.', 50, '2015-12-25 07:22:56'),
(1981, 858, '^^ I added the not-acoustic version for reference.', 50, '2015-12-25 07:28:56'),
(1982, 803, 'This song...  Musically, it reminds me of Like an Avalanche. Lyrically... God''s love for us is so overwhelming and beautiful, and it''s so much more powerful *because* it''s undeserved. I fight to walk my own way and be strong without God, but He brings me to my knees with His quiet gentle voice that has the force of a deep ocean current.', 50, '2015-12-25 07:47:43'),
(1983, 537, 'Also, as a note to add to Barry''s comment, we seriously considered having 2 percs, but since 2/3 of our percs were soloing, Martin ended up doing half body perc to have all the perc parts still there.', 50, '2015-12-25 07:57:07'),
(1984, 852, 'I think this actually translates pretty well to an acapella arangement.  I envision it as an especially awesome song for smaller groups, like Tuft last year.  It''s sounds really intimate, and doesn''t need too many voice parts to keep the feel of the song.  It has the feel of a folk/call and response song/chant.  It''s kinda short and the lyrics are a bit repetitive to expand as is, but we could probably do some creative arranging to keep it interesting.  I like how simple the message is: There is no safe place but to be in God.', 61, '2015-12-25 07:57:58'),
(1985, 840, 'I''m not entirely sure I understand the lyrics...', 50, '2015-12-25 21:39:52'),
(1986, 820, 'The harmonies would be cool to do a cappella. How could we make it less repetitive (other than like a mashup)?', 50, '2015-12-25 21:44:14'),
(1987, 872, 'This has a fun beat and could be cool to sing.', 50, '2015-12-25 21:57:04'),
(1988, 807, 'I love the line "It takes a soldier who knows his orders to walk the walk I''m supposed to walk." It''s so tempting to live the way we want to, the way that the world tells us to, but we''re called to not be of this world. When we keep our eyes fixed on God, we''re able to live the way He wants us to, in freedom and in confidence, because in Him we have nothing to fear. Also, the a cappella arrangement of this is really cool!', 50, '2015-12-25 22:06:50'),
(1989, 834, 'Oooh this is a cool style. Reminds me of a Glad arrangement. It would be a challenge piece if we chose to do it.', 50, '2015-12-25 22:16:42'),
(1990, 818, 'This song is so joyful musically, pointing to the victory we have in God''s grace rather than on our guilt and shame.', 50, '2015-12-25 22:22:10'),
(1991, 861, 'Solid Gospel message: our guilt, Christ''s sacrifice and God''s forgiveness, resulting restoration of our relationship with God.', 50, '2015-12-25 22:25:54'),
(1992, 800, 'Our identity is in God''s love for us alone. It''s not based on anything we did to bring us guilt, or on anything we do to build ourselves up. Also, that bass line could be fun to sing...', 50, '2015-12-25 22:33:29'),
(1993, 845, 'I like how it has both who God is and how we respond in light of that. I like the style; it would be cool to try.', 50, '2015-12-25 22:37:47'),
(1994, 817, '@Phoebe +1 ...and those cool runs in the background of the chorus! The soloist has a lot of room to play around musically as well.', 50, '2015-12-25 22:44:01'),
(1995, 692, 'Reminds me of 2 Corinthians 12:9-10, and Matthew 5:3-12.', 50, '2015-12-25 22:55:42'),
(1996, 843, 'God''s love for us and His infinite forgiveness and restoration is mind-blowing, isn''t it?', 50, '2015-12-25 23:14:02'),
(1997, 731, 'I just added an acoustic version, to give options.', 50, '2015-12-25 23:30:47'),
(1998, 844, 'This is really catchy!', 50, '2015-12-25 23:35:26'),
(1999, 804, 'Ahhh those lyrics... We like being so independent, and we''re so scared of trusting someone other than ourselves that we choose bondage over freedom. I would like a blurb to clarify what we will "keep on" doing -- I''m assuming it''s that we''ll keep on trusting God and trying to live for Him and not that we''ll keep on doing what we''ve been doing without Him, but it''s a little ambiguous.', 50, '2015-12-25 23:43:23'),
(2000, 222, 'The lyrics are pretty specific; I''m not sure how many people can empathize.', 50, '2015-12-26 00:18:36'),
(2001, 832, 'LOL: "I''m so rich and I ain''t talking bout cheddar"  This is pretty much a solid rap song, which might be challenging for our current group.  It relies heavily on solid rapping skills and a strong perc with little to no voice background, which might be okay if we choose to change it up a bit for one song.  Otherwise, I think we would need a creative arrangement to make it work.  Lyrically, it''s witty and very Christian explicit.  Just a little hard to understand - maybe we could slow it down just a bit...', 61, '2015-12-26 00:26:43'),
(2002, 841, 'This is a really awesome arrangement!  Can we do it though?  I think it requires a big chorus unless we rearrange it.', 61, '2015-12-26 00:37:21'),
(2003, 854, 'Human love is so imperfect, but God''s love is so inhuman. The problem is that when we experience God''s love, our imperfect hearts don''t know how to accept it because we''ve been hurt so many times before. But perfect love casts out all fear -- and our love for God should be childlike in purity and complete trust. One concern I have for this song is that when I first heard the chorus, I thought it was confusing that we''re asking God to keep us as children, almost like God is trying to keep us dependent and stifle us. I know that''s not what they''re saying, but it could play into the whole faith = ignorance misconception.', 50, '2015-12-26 00:44:27'),
(2004, 835, 'It''s like a combination of Fire Mashup + Joy + Make A Move!', 50, '2015-12-26 00:58:01'),
(2005, 836, 'Living for God instead of for the world/yourself is so freeing! I can almost hear the background "jen jen jen jen jum jum"s...', 50, '2015-12-26 01:08:31'),
(2006, 608, 'John 4. Also, Matthew 7:7-11. Random thought: this could mashup really well with Tenth Avenue North''s other song Satisfy, which is a song from our perspective asking God to come satisfy us and be our all, since He is more than this world could ever give. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KZHvXJmaVgA', 50, '2015-12-26 01:24:45'),
(2007, 837, 'I tend to prefer hymns as hymns, but I think maybe a blurb could give meaning to a song that people haven''t paid much attention to before.', 62, '2015-12-26 01:29:14'),
(2008, 860, 'This seems like a pretty standard worship song. The background reminds me of In Christ Alone a little bit, especially right after he says, "amazed by who you are."', 50, '2015-12-26 01:33:21'),
(2009, 749, 'I''ve definitely thought of using this song for BiDB ^_^ We''d want something simple for that and something that would sound fine with 200 people singing it. You could potentially have soloists for the group song (I was thinking maybe have like eight people each sing a couple of lines or something), but mashing this up with something else would be cool as well. Any ideas?', 62, '2015-12-26 01:35:14'),
(2010, 802, 'It''s like Oceans with the message from When I Am Afraid! It''s a bold celebration of the confidence we have because of our solid foundation, our sure anchor.', 50, '2015-12-26 02:36:26'),
(2011, 820, 'a bible verse/some spoken word/rap-like portion over the verse instrumentals would be kinda cool! \r\n\r\ni could also see this having multiple soloists, each one singing it with a different flair unique to their own voices/emphasis on a certain phrase of the verse', 47, '2015-12-26 02:44:41'),
(2012, 561, 'ditto meiji''s entire comment^', 47, '2015-12-26 02:49:53'),
(2013, 814, 'oh wow they''re so cute ahhh totally different feel- i like how they start off and end with a solemn style, too so it''s not completely jazz''ed up', 47, '2015-12-26 02:59:13'),
(2014, 824, 'I love this arrangement! It makes my heart so light and happy. I also really like the lyrics, how our whole lives are changed in light of what God has done -- His love, light, joy, and sacrifice redefine me and how I live my life.', 50, '2015-12-26 03:37:34'),
(2015, 862, 'I like the line "I want to be reckless ''cause you are endless." We live freely and fully, without fear, not to serve ourselves and our desires, but because our God is so much greater than anything else and we have confidence in His ultimate authority over it all.', 50, '2015-12-26 03:46:01'),
(2016, 863, 'I like the lyrics! We are redeemed and no chains can hold us. I''m concerned that it''s a slow song, which is hard to do engagingly in a cappella.', 50, '2015-12-26 03:49:38'),
(2017, 849, 'It''s jarring to me that the song is so happy/bouncy musically, but so hopeless lyrically. Maybe I''m interpreting this wrong, but the first verse sounds like he''s saying that he''d rather commit suicide now than live longer...', 50, '2015-12-26 04:02:45'),
(2018, 864, 'Cool musical style that could be fun to do in a cappella.', 50, '2015-12-26 04:07:10'),
(2019, 855, 'Oooh this sounds like so much fun to sing. Concern about how non-Christians will receive this, though. Human free will vs. God''s sovereignty -- if God says yes, can humans say no?', 50, '2015-12-26 04:13:04'),
(2020, 830, 'I don''t think you could possibly sing this song without dancing... :)', 50, '2015-12-26 04:17:30'),
(2021, 848, 'I''m not sure I understand the "Take from vandals" verse.', 50, '2015-12-26 04:27:34'),
(2022, 751, 'It''s not the best quality video, but I added an arrangement that works the Amazing Grace part into the beginning more, if we want to do something like that. I like this style better than a lot of the other a cappella arrangements for this song that try to have the background sing more of the electric guitar parts.', 50, '2015-12-26 04:53:41'),
(2023, 853, 'This is our testimony! Every week, we share our highs and lows and one thing that God has been doing in our lives. Moment by moment, God brings the little pieces together to create the beautiful story of our lives. We share with each other how God is with us each step of the way, molding and shaping us, so that we can go out and tell the world.', 50, '2015-12-26 05:09:38'),
(2024, 469, 'We have hope and confidence in God because He is so much greater than anything we could ever face, and He will not abandon His beloved children.', 50, '2015-12-26 05:12:37'),
(2025, 867, 'Faithful endurance to the end. Stand firm! 1 Corinthians 15:58, 2 Timothy 1:6-14, Ephesians 6:10-20', 50, '2015-12-26 05:22:07'),
(2026, 833, 'Completely new, different, changed, remade, reborn. 2 Corinthians 5:14-21', 50, '2015-12-26 05:31:24'),
(2027, 584, '@Caitlin haha yeah, it was a beautiful arrangement, but not the most "rememberable." :)', 50, '2015-12-26 05:36:31'),
