(2055, 824, 'I really love this arrangement too. Definitely a top contender for a hymn piece for me.', 64, '2015-12-26 18:47:34'),
(2056, 814, 'I really like the Jubilation arrangement :)', 64, '2015-12-26 18:51:52'),
(2057, 561, '^^yep', 64, '2015-12-26 18:56:23'),
(2058, 820, '^^Yes, Phoebe!', 64, '2015-12-26 18:57:09'),
(2059, 803, 'Wow....okay..yep...so much agreement with Barry', 64, '2015-12-26 19:02:31'),
(2060, 837, 'I agree with both of you.', 64, '2015-12-26 19:05:40'),
(2061, 854, 'Wow, I love this one a lot too. I think a blurb would be key though to clear up the confusion possibility Meiji outlines.', 64, '2015-12-26 19:21:53'),
(2062, 841, 'This one is so cool! I think we can do it Hans if we focus on strengthening our voices and volume!', 64, '2015-12-26 19:29:40'),
(2063, 844, '^^+1', 64, '2015-12-26 19:37:09'),
(2064, 807, 'This one is great! The a cappella arrangement is awesome! Also my sister, Elise, says we should definitely do this one :)', 64, '2015-12-26 19:58:22'),
(2065, 475, '^^+1', 64, '2015-12-26 20:17:00'),
(2066, 841, 'Ok Riley, you gotta teach us then :)  But yes, I do think this would be spectacular if we could pull it off.  Last year I remember that our Gregorian chant, Jesu Dulcis Memoria was super popular.', 61, '2015-12-26 20:49:45'),
(2067, 842, 'I agree with Phoebe-  some parts of it would work really well, but a lot of the verses seem like they would need to be changed.  I think this song would work better in a mashup.', 55, '2015-12-26 21:24:35'),
(2068, 832, 'This could be an interesting song to do.  What if the chorus part was mashed up with When the Saints Go Marching In (the spiritual)?  this could also add background to the a cappella and maybe slow the rap down.', 55, '2015-12-26 21:40:00'),
(2069, 216, 'This song almost seems a little Christmasey to me.  I think I''d prefer it in a fall semester.', 55, '2015-12-26 21:58:20'),
(2070, 66, 'I also think this really applies to MIT. (and maybe we could add/change a verse to show this more) of the fact that when we''re within a semester, at least for me, I generally have not much idea of all the things going on outside and I think that makes this song relatable for most of our MIT audience. Not sure about spring break applicability though.', 55, '2015-12-26 22:15:56'),
(2071, 810, 'I love TobyMac!! :)  I was actually thinking about suggesting this one.  I agree with the lyrics being relatable.  We would need to have swag to make this song work, but I think if we commit and get an good arrangement it could pay off.  Would be a interesting song to arrange!', 58, '2015-12-26 22:17:45'),
(2072, 205, 'Love this one.', 64, '2015-12-26 22:17:46'),
(2073, 676, '@Hans YAAASSSS', 64, '2015-12-26 22:18:57'),
(2074, 873, '@ Barry YAAAASSS', 64, '2015-12-26 22:21:06'),
(2075, 731, 'I was actually also thinking about suggesting this again!  We could definitely make our own arrangement for exactly what we are looking for.  Maybe something more typcical, but also interesting (perhaps less GLAD-like).', 58, '2015-12-26 22:21:52'),
(2076, 798, 'Suggesting again for the same reason as before.  I feel that this song is particularly applicable for the audience to which we will be singing.', 58, '2015-12-26 22:23:48'),
(2077, 835, 'I know!  It''s so groovy, catchy and happy.  It also has a really great strong message!', 58, '2015-12-26 22:26:01'),
(2078, 837, 'I was thinking that this is a popular one that we could reach out to a wide audience with, although that is a good point that it may be too familiar.  It is something that we could also perhaps mash up with something else.  I also suggest it, because it would give us a chance to make our own arrangement for it (similar comment to How Great Thou Art).  I think it would be great to make an arrangement that fits really well with our group (in terms of balance/soloists) and is exactly how we want to do it (maybe a few interesting bits, but not as much as GLAD-style arrangements)', 58, '2015-12-26 22:30:18'),
(2079, 837, 'Also as a side-note would be a good one for spring break.  This may just be me, but I feel Amazing Grace is particularly popular in Scotland (an extremely common bagpipe song)', 58, '2015-12-26 22:31:32'),
(2080, 831, 'I agree with both of the above - it would maybe take a bit of work for the soloists - but I reckon we could pull it off.  I must say that I wanted to suggest this as soon as I heard it.  The verse lead-in I feel would work well a cappella and I feel we could have a lot of fun with the style.  The rap section also adds more variety (and we now know we have several people who are willing to rap).  I really like the message as well - the rap section talking about God being relevant in our everyday lives ("if I''m not talkin'' bout the newest Nikes or releases","I can''t speak about my Jesus?") resonated with me a lot, as well as the turning away aspect ("I can be a little punk sometimes").  I do think that it would be good paired with a song answering the plea, saying that God is always there and never leaves us alone.', 58, '2015-12-26 22:38:08'),
(2081, 750, 'I love the message in this song (particularly in relation to those rough weeks that we all have).  In regards to arrangements, it is true that it is driven by perc and less happening in the background, although we did manage My Everything and I feel that this is somewhat similar (if we decided to go down the Owl City route).  Also as a side-note I love the cheesy key change :D', 58, '2015-12-26 22:51:23'),
(2082, 218, 'I LOVE THIS ONE', 64, '2015-12-26 22:52:35'),
(2083, 874, 'Very much agree with the relatability to MIT students.  There is just so much that we cannot comprehend about God and the ways he works.  @Meiji I love the point about the happiness along with the lyrics.  I never thought of that!  Would definitely be a cool arrangement to sing!', 58, '2015-12-26 23:03:27'),
(2084, 172, 'I think that''s a good idea, Hans.', 64, '2015-12-26 23:04:21'),
(2085, 809, 'I think it would be cool to have and arrangement of this with the traditional Amazing Grace melody at the beginning or end or incorporating it in some way.  Would definitely grab people''s attention.', 58, '2015-12-26 23:11:27'),
(2086, 837, 'And if we sing it, now they can hear the words! Good thinking!', 62, '2015-12-27 00:57:35'),
(2087, 868, 'This is an amazing worship song! I''m not sure it would be the best for outreach, though.', 50, '2015-12-27 01:14:48'),
(2088, 849, 'Mmm, yeah, I see your point, especially when I imagine an a cappella arrangement. It''s also easy to misinterpret...', 57, '2015-12-27 01:39:30'),
(2089, 815, 'If you think about it, according to a human metric, God is so foolish for trading all of His awesomeness for our brokenness, but God''s wisdom is foolishness to the world. Love makes you do stupid things, and His love for us is so amazing!', 50, '2015-12-27 01:45:53'),
(2090, 850, 'I like how this song isn''t just a recitation of the Lord''s Prayer, but a very real prayer from a human heart that God would come and reign sovereign in His love.', 50, '2015-12-27 02:44:30'),
(2091, 781, 'This is so good!', 64, '2015-12-27 04:10:41'),
(2092, 619, '^^I AGREE', 64, '2015-12-27 04:11:11'),
(2093, 619, 'If we keep the spirit of the song, then it will definitely be very catchy. This one may need a bit of a blurb for some people, but I think it has a solid message and it is one of my favorites on that album. I like it!', 63, '2015-12-27 06:19:43'),
(2094, 781, 'This sounds really nice and I like the catchiness of the song. But I could also take these same lyrics and sing them to my girlfriend. I like this song, but I wish it was more explicit about being the relationship between us and God.', 63, '2015-12-27 06:26:05'),
(2095, 781, 'I heard that the singer actually wrote this song for his wife. Nevertheless, I think it makes even more sense as God singing to us. Only God can say that he''ll be with us through everything and have it be completely true. And songs like this are useful because they''re Spring Break friendly.', 62, '2015-12-27 07:25:32'),
(2096, 753, 'I found that TCNJ''s Voice of Hope has an arrangment of this song. I''m not crazy about what they did with it (could just be the recording quality though), but it might be an option if we want to do the song but don''t want to arrange it.', 62, '2015-12-27 18:36:03'),
(2099, 849, 'Yeah... not sure how this would sound for nonbeliever''s ears.', 63, '2015-12-27 20:41:16'),
(2100, 868, 'This song is more of an encouragement. If anything, we could save it for an encouragement of some kind (this is if we learn everything else). It would be good to sing in a place with a large concentration of believers.', 63, '2015-12-27 20:46:06'),
(2101, 172, 'I like it!', 63, '2015-12-27 21:09:57'),
(2102, 874, 'Yeah, failing and feeling like you are in out of your depth is a huge part of MIT life, and this song says it''s okay, and that God is right in it!', 63, '2015-12-27 21:13:16'),
(2103, 832, 'Oh man, that would be so cool! @Maddie, I love the idea of a mashup. Yeah, I agree that the raps are hard to understand, But I think we could do this well.', 63, '2015-12-27 21:15:23'),
(2104, 854, 'Hmm, I was thinking more along the lines of Matthew 18:1-4, but I see the possible confusion.', 57, '2015-12-27 21:26:48'),
(2105, 218, 'I love It!!', 63, '2015-12-27 21:35:22'),
(2106, 873, 'That sounds great!!', 63, '2015-12-27 22:06:25'),
(2107, 676, 'This song is meant for Christians coming back and being redeemed, but it also definitely has a place to speak to the lost, showing them, particularly at MIT, that whatever they are chasing will not satisfy, and that they can turn to God with whatever they have done and he will accept them. I like it, and the medley sounds like a cool idea as well.', 63, '2015-12-27 22:12:20'),
(2108, 810, 'I think Squad ''19 can work on the swag factor if the arrangement is solid. Come on, take a chance! This song is soooooo cooool!!!!', 63, '2015-12-27 22:14:09'),
(2109, 834, 'This is definitely about God, (I think all their songs were) but yeah, it''s a bit different, we could still try it though.', 63, '2015-12-27 22:22:21'),
(2111, 830, 'This song reminds me exactly of Footloose (the song from the movie).  So much dancing :)', 55, '2015-12-27 22:32:39'),
(2112, 849, 'Okay, if we change it to die to myself that might help, I''m pretty sure that''s what they meant anyhow, that would make it better I think', 63, '2015-12-27 22:50:57'),
(2113, 815, 'That guitar will be pretty hard to replicate, our rendition would have to have a bit of a different feel', 63, '2015-12-27 23:23:45'),
(2114, 841, 'Woah! This does sound really super awesome!  I think it would be very powerful if we could pull it off.', 58, '2015-12-27 23:26:53'),
(2115, 832, 'I do think the mashup is a good idea and perhaps slowing it down.  Maybe the lyrics could be clarified with a good blurb, but I definitely see the potential problem with understanding the lyrics.', 58, '2015-12-27 23:36:44'),
(2116, 205, 'I loved it when they did it, and I''m excited for it!!', 63, '2015-12-27 23:57:13'),
(2117, 862, 'I know this isn''t what the song is going for, but I kinda see a bit of a theological issue with this song.  When I first heard the line "I want to be reckless ''cause you are endless.", while I know that is truth, it almost seems like God will be with us no matter what we do, but we''re not supposed to test God''s boundaries (Think Jesus tempted by Satan).  It''s just the one line, but as it is the title of the song, I worry it can be misinterpreted', 55, '2015-12-28 00:17:05'),
(2118, 841, 'I found the score! http://www.acasongs.com/uploads/5/2/0/4/5204591/nearer_to_thee_-_james_stephens.pdf', 61, '2015-12-28 00:39:19'),
(2119, 831, 'This could be paired with something like Owl City - ''You''re Not Alone''.  Might be a bit too much, but I think it would be cool to have this saying ''please don''t leave me alone'' and then ''I hear you say You''re not alone''', 58, '2015-12-28 02:43:07'),
(2120, 873, 'This song is so cool!  I definintely like the idea of changing up a verse or two to make it MIT (or general college student/young adult) relatable  :)', 58, '2015-12-28 02:44:23'),
(2121, 749, 'Wait.  I got it!!  How about mash it up with the bridge of Mighty to Save??  The "Shine your light and / Let the whole world see, we''re singing / For the glory / of the Risen King" and "Our God is an awesome God /\r\nHe reigns from heaven above /\r\nWith wisdom, power, and love /\r\nOur God is an awesome God" simultaneously?  They both have the same chord progression! :)', 61, '2015-12-28 03:41:02'),
(2122, 831, 'I''ve definitely thought about that, although I think pairing it with something like Remain might be a bit more tasteful.', 62, '2015-12-28 04:33:02'),
(2123, 745, 'I love this song!', 63, '2015-12-28 05:02:39'),
(2124, 749, 'Here''s a quick demo: https://www.noteflight.com/scores/view/a3b619ddf97ece11c048c9e8037a80c986e53c53', 61, '2015-12-28 07:16:19'),
(2125, 749, 'Woah that''s really cool! Those work well together--chordwise and themewise', 62, '2015-12-28 07:32:50'),
(2126, 876, 'Pre-arranged, that''s not a mistake. The audio file is the arrangement. I''m probably going to use this for Xlinked but wanted to put it out here as well. I really like this song because it''s so joyful--especially in the chorus--which is exactly the response we should have to God''s love. ', 62, '2016-05-10 14:49:12'),
(2128, 859, 'Basically my comment from last semester and Meiji''s as well. This song is one of my favorites, but is also a break through to secular audiences because Tori Kelly is well known outside the Christian circle as well.', 64, '2016-05-10 15:36:08'),
(2129, 878, 'This song is so awesome. It points to God clearly without being overly explicit or preachy. It''s personal but at the same time it doesn''t dwell on the individual but gives everything up to God. It''s a bit more, well, rap than some of the raps we''ve done recently, but I still think it would have wide appeal. It''s just so good!', 62, '2016-05-10 15:40:34'),
(2130, 809, 'I really like what TCNJ did with this song at BIDB. I''ve added the youtube video of that here. It should start with them.', 64, '2016-05-10 16:48:17'),
(2131, 809, 'It didn''t start with them for me, but I added the recording of just TCNJ.', 62, '2016-05-10 19:44:25'),
(2132, 859, 'Added the recording of CMU from BiDB. I really really like this song. My main concern would be that I''m not sure we have anyone to solo it.', 62, '2016-05-10 19:47:52'),
(2133, 859, 'I really liked this song last semester and those feelings still stand.  I''d love to to this song this semester.', 55, '2016-05-10 22:25:54'),
(2134, 879, 'I was a little confused when I first heard this song. "When You dont move the mountains Im needing You to move" ... it sounds like God isn''t there. But that''s just it. Life can get confusing, and we don''t always understand God''s plan and why he does or doesn''t answer our prayers. But, still, we trust Him because He knows everything. He is always loving and good, and He is so much stronger than anything on Earth.', 62, '2016-05-11 13:40:52'),
(2135, 415, 'An xprod classic that hasn''t been done for awhile. It''s like You Make Me Brave but more upbeat--which is cool because we haven''t had enough upbeat female solos recently.', 62, '2016-05-11 13:46:24'),
(2136, 753, 'Not quite as new as when I originally suggested it, but I STILL love this song. We find true purpose and joy when we surrender our lives to God.', 62, '2016-05-11 19:59:27'),
(2138, 881, 'Hi Xprod, old-as-dirt alum checking in with a song suggestion. This is a fun little choral piece that some friends and I are performing at my church in a few weeks. There''s a brief solo line that is in a pretty singable range for just about anyone- could be sop, alto, tenor, or bass (a male soloist would just sing it down an octave). Pretty straightforward message about giving up control to God and asking Him to shape our lives.', 3, '2016-05-14 20:56:32'),
(2139, 462, 'Hey, thought I would throw out a couple favorite songs from yesteryear that haven''t been done for a while afaik. This arrangement is pretty fantastic. Unless you have an alto who can pull it off (like Dorothy in the Youtube video I just added), you will probably want a tenor soloing.', 3, '2016-05-14 21:28:19'),
(2140, 21, 'Another old favorite! Portrays a life devoted to Christ as something that is super joyful.', 3, '2016-05-14 21:38:00'),
(2141, 879, 'Wow, this is basically my struggle as I become a more chill Riley. This is just as great and powerful as "First". I think it could be a good option.', 64, '2016-05-16 02:30:46'),
(2142, 880, 'Matthew 28:20\r\n"And be sure of this: I am with you always, even to the end of the age."', 64, '2016-05-16 02:40:15'),
(2143, 882, 'I love this song. I remember thinking about suggesting it last semester and then forgot somehow. Then Cru did it at worship and reminded me about it. The expression of faith in and reliance on God is so real in this one. I had never thought about it as a worship song, but if you read the lyrics it actually is.', 62, '2016-05-16 14:21:14'),
(2144, 883, 'This song is very powerful, raw, and painful.  It''s not like anything we''ve ever done, but I think it would be an amazing song to share with all those who come to hear us, and relate to this kind of pain.  I know I relate to this song strongly, and just hearing that someone else understands begins to work freedom and healing in my life, and I am confident in the lives of all who hear it.', 48, '2016-05-17 21:30:28'),
(2145, 884, 'I think this song is kinda a combination of Hello My name is (verses) and it sounds like the lighthouse/from the day energy.  I''ve heard this song before, but it showed up on a random playlist I was listening to and the first thought that crossed my mind is that xprod should sing it.  I think it would work fine a cappella wise.  And I think this message is one that''s important to hear- God is greater, he lives inside of us, and he takes us no matter how we come.', 55, '2016-05-18 04:41:36'),
(2146, 885, 'Side note: I think Adele is super strict about copyright and stuff so you cant find any studio recordings of her on YouTube, at least her new stuff (hence the concert recording). Good enough quality to get the gist of the song though.\r\n\r\nI was listening to this song while packing and I was like, oh we could totally sing this! (tooootally) I can see it as a song praising and celebrating God for His devotion to us and turning our lives upside down. \r\n\r\nIts one of her few upbeat/happy songs. I made some veeeery slight changes to the second verse and bridge (changed a few pronouns/added a preposition or two). Anyway I like the joy and power behind this song and I like how its a different style than what we normally do. Also Adele is pretty well-known and it''s SB friendly.', 57, '2016-05-21 19:45:03'),
(2147, 715, 'Ditto the above comments! Love how victorious and confident this song is.', 57, '2016-05-21 19:48:39'),
(2148, 886, 'I love the intimacy of this song. It reminds me of how tender and gentle God is. It helps remind me to pause and enjoy Gods presence and who He is, not just be asking for things all the time.', 57, '2016-05-21 19:56:33');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(2149, 887, 'Mainly suggesting this song for the different style/music (I really like the guitar intro). The message is basically a love song to God. <3', 57, '2016-05-21 20:03:04'),
(2150, 141, 'I like how spunky this song is, haha. I also like the idea of MIT-izing (?) the lyrics. Could be funny!', 57, '2016-05-21 20:08:03'),
(2151, 888, 'Trying to get a slow song for a guy solo out there. Dat falsetto.', 57, '2016-05-21 20:16:39'),
(2152, 889, 'There''s not too, too much substance in the lyrics, but I like the energy a lot. It celebrates the freedom we have from our cages and the victory we have in God.', 57, '2016-05-21 20:21:33'),
(2153, 890, 'This song is soooo beautiful! It''s about taking risks, going out into the unknown and trusting in God, the beauty of being completely overwhelmed and surrendering in that moment.', 57, '2016-05-21 20:31:03'),
(2154, 891, 'I really like the tension in this song. We live in a pretty messed up world and it''s easy to point the finger and blame everyone except ourselves. But the truth is we are all broken and our only hope is God coming and bringing His rule and His kingdom to earth where the first shall be last and the last shall be first. (Matthew 19:16-30)', 57, '2016-05-21 20:40:23'),
(2155, 892, 'The lyrics might be too artsy - theyre not very straightforward. But I love the energy of this song. Were waking up to Gods reality and finding we are his children (the kings and queens imagery reminds me of Narnia :D ).', 57, '2016-05-21 20:43:00'),
(2157, 893, 'A really beautiful song about finding satisfaction in God and God alone.', 57, '2016-05-21 20:50:38'),
(2158, 894, 'This song is about freedom and grace. The lyrics have been very inspirational to me of late, and the message will fit in well with most setlists. It is the Gospel in a song, about how we are free from sin and darkness and made new. It would need arranging, but it doesn''t seem to be overly difficult. ', 63, '2016-05-22 20:51:48'),
(2159, 833, 'Really upbeat, incredibly strong Gospel message. Seems like a fun song to do!', 63, '2016-05-22 20:53:06'),
(2160, 830, 'Much fun, let''s do it!!!!', 63, '2016-05-22 20:53:58'),
(2161, 895, 'I added the link for God''s Not Dead because most of the songs I listed as mashups are in a similar style. If we were to decide to do this, it would be a mashup of probably 3 of the above songs. This would be tricky to arrange, but if we pulled it off it would be a lot of fun. Their songs are upbeat and have a powerful message. A mashup would be quite fun. I''m going to suggest some of the songs I have listed, but a medley would be exciting!', 63, '2016-05-22 21:29:22'),
(2162, 896, 'This song is a pretty bold declaration, and one that suits MIT campus well. We all know how MIT is, how it can be a pretty discouraging place for people of faith. Boldly proclaiming that God is not dead would be a great way to counteract that discouragement. This song is really drum heavy and might be hard to do a capella, but the lyrics alone make it worth a second glance.', 63, '2016-05-22 21:41:31'),
(2163, 897, 'This song is a great one for MIT. We have a ton of challenges in our path that seem utterly insurmountable, but God is bigger than all the giants in our way. We often hear the whisper of doubt that we can''t get through all the challenges ahead, but if God brought us to it, He will get us through it. This song reminds us of that.', 63, '2016-05-22 21:45:58'),
(2164, 898, 'This song is focused on mission. It provides an attitude that rejects the fear of going out and evangelizing and instead provides an attitude that the message of God is coming whether the world is ready or not. It replaces fear with confidence, and has an upbeat feeling to boot. Fun song, really perc heavy.', 63, '2016-05-22 21:52:09'),
(2165, 10, 'Discovered this when going through old songs and boy is it catchy. I was a bit disappointed to realize that it was done not too long ago, but I guess anything I don''t remember is kind of old enough to re-do now. Weird. Anyhow I agree that the xprod arrangement lacks the original feel, but I think with a slightly faster tempo, perc, and possible tweaking of the arrangement we could get it.', 62, '2016-05-23 04:09:14'),
(2166, 210, 'A bit of a throwback now, but an all time favorite song for me. I always felt this song was a cry out to God, so it doesn''t surprise me that Xprod covered it years back. It''s a bit different than what we''ve tended to sing lately, but I think it''d add both musical and lyrical variety if we did it.', 62, '2016-05-23 04:25:44'),
(2167, 5, 'Xprod classic. Poignant message. Awesome arrangement with some fun syllables. How to get around the high solo problem? Key change? Bass solo down the octave? Pray for high tenors? :)', 62, '2016-05-23 04:30:21'),
(2168, 648, 'I really like this song. It reminds me that whenever I think I have God figured out, I definitely don''t. He will always be bigger, and greater, and more good and holy than I can ever imagine. But I can also see where Polly is coming from with her earlier comment as well. Other people have thoughts?', 64, '2016-05-23 14:02:50'),
(2169, 899, 'This song is an anthem for what we are to do when we come upon dark times. It is a bit repetitive; maybe it could be mashed up with something?', 64, '2016-05-23 14:25:56'),
(2170, 577, 'I agree with everything in the above comments. Wanted to bump this one back in the running. This one really resonates with how I became a Chill Riley over the past year.', 64, '2016-05-23 14:34:22'),
(2171, 900, 'This is just a song about living in the joy of the Spirit! This is my jam when I need dancing around the house music. But on a more serious note, it also talks about the importance of taking time everyday to meet and talk with God.', 64, '2016-05-23 14:40:57'),
(2172, 577, 'You say that like you''re totally chill now :P\r\nWould''ve been fun if we had Fix My Eyes in the set, but still a good song.', 62, '2016-05-23 20:25:40'),
(2173, 900, 'This is pretty cool. The lyrics are that of a worship song but it''s pretty energetic and fun as well', 62, '2016-05-23 20:30:04'),
(2174, 885, 'Added the studio recording (shhh). Thanks for suggesting this song, I''d forgotten about it.', 62, '2016-05-23 20:36:49'),
(2175, 21, 'Good song, although it was just done in Fall 2014.', 62, '2016-05-23 22:00:19'),
(2176, 430, 'Hasn''t been done since Spring 2010. Solid hymn with a simple but beautiful gospel message.', 62, '2016-05-23 22:42:04'),
(2177, 898, 'Fun song. Might be hard without the funky skip/slow/whaterveryoucallit effects in the original', 62, '2016-05-23 22:49:27'),
(2178, 901, 'So I''d love to do a Christmas song at concert this year and I found this song (see BYU version).   I love how it also talks about our journey to God and what life with him looks like.', 55, '2016-05-25 02:24:53'),
(2179, 902, 'This song has a more gospeley feel to me that I think we could pull off.  With a quick blurb about the significance of a river, I think that it would be received well and understood well.  In addition, I think it''s fairly well known.', 55, '2016-05-25 02:37:59'),
(2180, 584, 'I think this is probably my favorite song I''ve ever sung in xprod (done Spring 2014).  Every time I listen to it, I just want to cry at it''s beauty.  God can do anything!', 55, '2016-05-25 02:41:59'),
(2181, 873, 'I still think it''d be fun to MIT-ize this song.', 62, '2016-05-25 05:14:51'),
(2182, 619, 'This is actually not crazy high for a tobyMac song. It''s within the baritone range in the original key.', 62, '2016-05-25 05:17:04'),
(2183, 910, 'Musical comments: Rutgers First Light sang this at BIDB - you can ask them for their arrangement!  Also, you could possibly mash this with the traditional "Down to the River to Pray" to make something kind of like Never Change!  That would be exciting!', 61, '2016-05-25 14:20:06'),
(2184, 914, 'Very simple and beautiful lyrics!', 62, '2016-05-25 15:41:42'),
(2185, 916, 'I''m failing to see how this is more than a song about self-empowerment...', 62, '2016-05-25 15:47:00'),
(2186, 917, 'This song is incredibly soulful, and incredibly simple. We could do a lot of things with it, mash it up, throw in some cool remixing, or just jam out and worship to it. The message is solid, and there''s a lot of room to play with.', 63, '2016-05-25 17:13:21'),
(2187, 910, 'It''s musically interesting, although perhaps a bit lacking on the message side', 62, '2016-05-25 17:15:57'),
(2188, 216, 'I''ve heard a gospel version of this song too, so if we want to play with that a little bit? Maybe alternate between this and something a bit more rhythmic?', 63, '2016-05-25 19:21:21'),
(2189, 919, 'This song is about motivations. For worship mostly, but also for life. It''s more serious and very challenging, but it would be something we could do well. It has a strong ballad feel, which is right up our alley. ', 63, '2016-05-25 19:32:26'),
(2190, 920, 'This hymn captures the beauty of Christ''s sacrifice, what life redeemed is like, and the reason that we sing. I''m envisioning Verse 1 as a 4-part harmony (like HDTFLFU), Verse 2 as a bari solo over background oo''s, and Verse 3 with layered exaltations building and ending in FF (think Hallelujah chorus / Revelation 7 / Luke 2:14).', 50, '2016-05-25 20:03:24'),
(2191, 457, 'This song is so sweet and gentle. I often struggle thinking I have to be good enough for God, but these words remind me that I am loved by God not because of anything I have ever done, but because I am a dearly cherished child.', 50, '2016-05-25 20:12:03'),
(2192, 922, 'I see this as a conversation between us and Christ, our brother (Romans 8:29). We declare our need (verses) and Christ answers that we just need to let Him in (chorus). Musically, this style would be really fun in a cappella.', 50, '2016-05-25 20:20:53'),
(2193, 921, 'I grew up on this song.  It is a beautiful spanish hymn with a simple and powerful message.  I know that we do not usually sing spanish songs, and the only spanish song we have sung in my time was both spanish and english, but I still think this a worthy addition to our music, and we can provide a translation in the pamphlet.  There is one translation error in the video though.  It should be: "In return you receive this humble offering, this humble offering Lord Jesus, of my heart."', 48, '2016-05-25 20:25:19'),
(2194, 923, 'Both of these songs are talking about God''s faithful and unfailing love for us, and how much we don''t deserve Him. While they''re both amazing songs individually, I felt like I had to suggest them as a mashup since they work so perfectly together musically and lyrically. (Listen to the chorus of Loyal and sing on top of it the chorus to Don''t Deserve You: "I don''t deserve your love" and "Your love is, Your love is / Your love is loyal." "More faithful than the rising sun / This grace for me I can''t outrun" and "And when I walk away / You take off running and come right after me.")', 50, '2016-05-25 20:33:10'),
(2195, 34, 'One of my favorite hymns. Really powerful lyrics. I wonder if it''s old enough to take advantage of the spring-break friendly hymn loophole. From what I understand the arrangement we have sounds pretty when sung correctly, but it has a lot of harmonies that are hard to tune and sounds really bad if you can''t get them.', 62, '2016-05-25 22:09:21'),
(2196, 922, 'Interesting. I like the song but I didn''t suggest it because I didn''t see how it would fit into one of our sets message-wise. I can see your interpretation, but I don''t think it''d be immediately apparent without a blurb.', 62, '2016-05-25 22:26:04'),
(2197, 216, 'So this is what''s on RHR...might be interesting to bring a song like this back. Very celebratory in a traditional way.', 62, '2016-05-25 22:30:50'),
(2198, 923, 'Hmm...I think I like Don''t Deserve You too much to be able to appreciate this.', 62, '2016-05-25 22:34:54'),
(2199, 457, 'Very engaging for a slow song. It reminds me of Out of Hiding, sung from the Father''s perspective. (By the way I was listening to the Xprod video without looking and I thought I heard Brian singing...it was Kevin!)', 62, '2016-05-25 22:40:45'),
(2200, 871, 'Very real lyrics, and I think relatable too, despite not all the lines probably applying to one person. And I like how the outro brings closure--that we are not left to be broken on our own but are restored in the unleaving presence of God. I could see it being difficult to arrange though, as well as give a convincing performance. I mean, I can kind of think of how to do it, but it''d be tricky to pull off.', 62, '2016-05-25 22:47:15'),
(2201, 919, 'It''s got fair amount of words and a strong, clear message (albeit one that is maybe more for us than for our audience) which I think could counteract it being on the slower side. I could see an arrangment happening similar to Out of Hiding. It''s a good song for Xprod regardless of if we actually sing it.', 62, '2016-05-25 22:53:31'),
(2202, 920, 'Is FF fortissimo?', 62, '2016-05-25 22:55:18'),
(2203, 477, 'Oh I wanted to suggest this one too!  I love this song :) ', 55, '2016-05-25 23:00:52'),
(2204, 924, 'I think this song speak powerfully to our desperate failures to satisfy ourselves, and equally desperate need for God.  The bridge is so powerful, and I think the song will be very relatable.', 48, '2016-05-26 01:22:56'),
(2205, 925, 'This song could be great for us!!! It''s got rap, a strong message, powerful vocals. This could be a cool one for us. I don''t think it would be terrible to arrange either. I like this one!', 63, '2016-05-26 01:47:17'),
(2206, 927, 'This song is more in the style of rap than almost any I''ve heard us do. It''s a lot of fun to listen to, and has a really strong almost club type of beat to it. It may not be applicable to all audiences, but it is definitely worth a listen!', 63, '2016-05-26 01:50:50'),
(2207, 928, 'This song is hard, speaking to a lot of pain from verbal abuse and possibly more as a child.  I think the title perfectly fits the message of it, speaking to how the pain from such hurt lasts for a lifetime.  This would definitely be a powerful song to share with our audience, and a very personal one.', 48, '2016-05-26 02:09:20'),
(2208, 925, 'It''s a good message, although I wish God was more explicit. He''s "the one who can liberate your soul" but without a blurb that may not be super clear.', 62, '2016-05-26 02:24:05'),
(2209, 841, 'I don''t know how it would sound with a smaller group, but it is musically so powerful. We''d need to creatively arrange in a soprano line too. ', 53, '2016-05-26 03:23:37'),
(2210, 843, 'UPenn sang this at BiDB, so we could probably ask them for an arrangement. https://www.dropbox.com/s/tum8m7ftyra9k5v/How%20Can%20It%20Be.mp3?dl=0 I love the song - the way it captures the awesomeness and glory of God''s saving grace juxtaposed against our brokenness. By this I mean that the song is slightly lamentful but primarily it captures an expression of awestruck worship. That said, I feel like it relies on a really powerful solo, so we''d have to see. ', 53, '2016-05-26 03:32:00'),
(2211, 157, 'I don''t know about rearranging, but it''s been four years since we sang this.', 53, '2016-05-26 03:34:51'),
(2212, 227, 'I love this song, how it comes from God''s perspective calling us away from our brokenness because He has traversed the distance to bring us home. If you want to see an example blurb (note above discourse) please view the second youtube link.', 53, '2016-05-26 03:38:03'),
(2213, 929, 'When I was in Mexico over IAP, my host family had several songs they were prepping for a church festival and this was one of them.  I think this song is gorgeous, both in melody and lyrics.  I''ll add a more elegant and (probably) accurate translation to english in the next day or two, but the essence of this song says essentially this: "God, I love you, and I want to give myself to you, forever.  Help me overcome my fears, and help me to live a life for you and to understand your love".', 55, '2016-05-26 03:45:59'),
(2214, 581, 'Becky soloed this our freshmen year. I think that three years is sufficient if this song piques your interest. This is a beautiful song with a powerfully encouraging message. Truthfully, I tend to tear up listening to this as I viscerally remember that this is the God who saves and holds me. One of my favorite lines is in the bridge: "These are the arms that were nailed to a cross / To break our chains and set us free." (Not to discredit my love of the verses) ', 53, '2016-05-26 03:46:30'),
(2215, 930, 'Another one that I''m pulling from my high school choir- a Swahili folk song.  This song talks about us, those who are Christians and what God gives us.', 55, '2016-05-26 03:52:19'),
(2216, 920, 'Aughhh! This song kills me (in the good way). It''s the way it captures the attitude of the worshiper and the beauty of the worshiped. The attitude that we are totally captivated by Christ, as we fix our eye unwavering on Him. The beauty of Christ in that it captures the full character of how He redeems us. \n\nI agree with Meiji that this song shouldn''t be done with a single solo. I''d actually love for it to be solo-less, as I see this as something deeply personal and yet completely shared with all believer. (Envisioning  all the saints in heaven singing this side by side, each with his eyes fixed on our redeemer). \n\nI feel like one of the other a cappella groups must have sung this before. You could probably ask around for an arrangement to work off of. (EG This seems like Princeton KS''s genre)', 53, '2016-05-26 04:35:34'),
(2217, 841, 'What I''ve found with a lot of these all-male arrangements is that there''s often a Tenor I or Countertenor line which is basically in the soprano range XD\r\nNot sure about this one of course.', 62, '2016-05-26 04:15:58'),
(2218, 843, 'This was probably my favorite song at BiDB this year. But, yeah, that probably had a lot to do with how good the soloist was. Their arrangement was pretty cool incorporating the bridge of Switchfoot''s "Dare You to Move" toward the end, although it''s possible it has a very repetitive female line (listen to it). ', 62, '2016-05-26 04:19:50'),
(2219, 227, 'This song confused me when I first heard it, and I found the tune mildly annoying. Now I like it a bit more, but I''d worry about singing it sans blurb.', 62, '2016-05-26 04:27:08'),
(2220, 14, 'We could probably rearrange it to be more hymn-like. I don''t think we should perpetually not do a hymn because we don''t like the way it was done in the past.', 62, '2016-05-26 04:34:51'),
(2221, 758, 'I had the insight to google the first line of the hymn, and, voila, recordings! I added a Youtube link, and there''s an even better recording on Spotify by Choir of the Abbey School Tewkesbury. I also found sheet music, in case Caitlin doesn''t have hers anymore.', 62, '2016-05-26 05:21:16'),
(2222, 878, 'I see it really hard to replicate the electronic feel of this song in a cappella, but I really like the words, and I think the rap is slow enough that people could still understand the words.', 55, '2016-05-26 14:47:30'),
(2223, 880, 'I thought I remembered hearing this on secular radio, but I see now that the artist is Christian. So if I did, great, more people will know it!', 62, '2016-05-26 15:40:59'),
(2224, 919, 'I''m not sure how familiar potential audiences would be with idols.  It''d work with a blurb (and I think it''d be amazing) but I worry about us singing in a place where we wouldn''t be able to blurb.', 55, '2016-05-28 02:57:27'),
(2225, 919, 'That''s true. I guess you have to remember that not everyone is familiar with terms like that.', 62, '2016-05-28 05:44:22'),
(2226, 919, 'I really like the message of this song, but I agree that it could be more for us than for our audience if they aren''t familiar with the terminology. Definitely a style right up our alley though and a piece to keep in mind.', 64, '2016-05-28 18:56:41'),
(2227, 929, 'Personally, I really like singing in other languages :) (and other a cappella groups at MIT do it), but I''m not sure exactly how well it will transfer to our audience. I think it could be cool though. Maybe a shortened version? Anyone have further thoughts?\r\n\r\nThanks for translating this, Maddie! :)', 64, '2016-05-28 19:00:00'),
(2228, 14, 'I like the idea of switching solos, but I agree the background could be revamped.', 64, '2016-05-28 20:20:09'),
