(2236, 881, 'I like it as our hymn for the semester, but maybe we could funk it up a bit? Add some gospel to it? Just an idea.', 63, '2016-05-29 04:11:59'),
(2237, 462, 'I love the song, but I honestly am not sure if I could handle the solo. Maybe? Either way love this song, grew up on it. Pre-arranged is always a bonus.', 63, '2016-05-29 04:14:51'),
(2238, 218, 'Still love this song from last year. But do we have a soloist for it? Good one though, love the powerful tenor!', 63, '2016-05-29 04:24:36'),
(2239, 876, 'I don''t think it''d be a problem; I was just explaining why I made it. It''s a simple arrangement, but the solo gives a chance for a girl to belt without needing to go super high. It''s interesting because it''s sung outward to other people (yet still about God), but it''s sung from our perspective, which is a focus that not many of our songs tend to have.', 62, '2016-05-29 06:15:59'),
(2242, 925, 'I found it a bit hard to see the message at first, I had to look really closely at the lyrics in order to find it.  Once I found it, I agree, it is a good message, but I''m a bit worried it could be missed by some.', 55, '2016-05-29 14:05:35'),
(2243, 926, 'ooooooo I like this! it''s catchy!  My concern is that it''s a bit repetitive and maybe we could mash it up with something or shorten it?', 55, '2016-05-29 14:12:49'),
(2244, 879, 'Yeah this is definitely a message I need to hear.  Even when it doesn''t seem like God is there, He is, and He knows what''s best for you.', 55, '2016-05-29 14:44:21'),
