(2289, 473, 'I definitely think this song has a really cool style (I think a little different to other songs) and a great message.  I do think it would good for CD pub.  I''m not sure how much it matters about the Chorallaries doing it.  It will be a year and I''m not sure how much of an audience crossover we actually have.', 58, '2016-05-31 17:07:49'),
(2290, 918, 'So I was actually thinking about arranging this over the summer anyway just for fun.  (I''ve literally been listening to it all semester and have so many thought about how it could be a cappella with cool flourishes and everything - slightly different to our normal style.)  It has a really clear message which is pretty memorable, but I also don''t think it''s too shallow. ', 58, '2016-05-31 17:11:12'),
(2291, 751, '^^^Repeat of what past Riley said :P', 64, '2016-05-31 17:12:45'),
(2292, 837, 'Similar comment to last year.  I think it would be cool to do something like this that people are familiar with, but then twist it up to give it more effect.  Also if we blurb, we can really make people focus in on the message and then they''ll hopefully remember it whenever they hear the song.', 58, '2016-05-31 17:14:41'),
(2293, 756, 'Hmmm...The whole second verse and parts of the bridge would have to be altered, I think, for this to work...those parts seem to me very guy-girl relationship sounding.', 64, '2016-05-31 17:16:10'),
(2294, 841, 'I don''t know if this is even possible and might have to be organized in advance, but I think it''d be super awesome if we could do a joint thing with concert choir :D It would definitely be worth looking in to.  I''m sure we could pull it off with a group our size, perhaps if we tweak the arrangement slightly.', 58, '2016-05-31 17:19:36'),
(2295, 926, 'That is true, it would perhaps be worthwhile mashing up.  I think the imagery is really effective and helps to emphasize God''s love and power.  I feel that it is something pretty different from most stuff that Cross Products has done before, but definitely worth considering and trying.', 58, '2016-05-31 17:22:32'),
(2296, 756, 'I actually think it''s more metaphorical (Since I do believe U2 wrote this song about God. The single artwork even has a cross on it.) -- e.g. "Soul and its striptease" meaning shaking off the shackles of sin, "The sky over our head/We can reach it from our bed" referring to prayer. But I see how it could be interpreted...erm, differently.', 62, '2016-05-31 17:23:07'),
(2297, 798, 'Love this one :) I totally agree that it would be very applicable to our audience!', 64, '2016-05-31 17:24:39'),
