(2304, 643, 'Loved the arrangement we heard at BIDB for this, especially the handoff style bridge. It''s an incredibly powerful song lyrically and very emotional.', 63, '2016-05-31 18:30:36'),
(2305, 52, 'I''ve loved this song since I first heard it. It''s really powerful because it talks about real stories and struggles people have, and how God can answer all of them. Comments before mention that it''s good for spring break and missional gigs. So if we do it this semester we might want to save it over for spring too.', 63, '2016-05-31 18:37:05'),
(2306, 883, 'This is a great song, and I really like it, but I''m not sure if it would be good for us to perform. I hate to say that it is too raw, but I''m just not sure audiences would react positively. Maybe I''m wrong though.', 63, '2016-05-31 18:50:38'),
(2307, 884, 'I love this song!! The message is perfect for anyone struggling with past sins and regrets. It is joyful and amazing. It would be way fun to perform too!', 63, '2016-05-31 18:53:46'),
(2308, 886, 'The beginning might need some blurbing, the second verse and bridge clear it up nicely though.', 63, '2016-05-31 19:05:11'),
(2309, 715, 'Oh, I really like this!', 64, '2016-05-31 19:31:02'),
(2310, 886, 'Mmmm. So good, and such an important reminder to simply rest in the joy of His presence.', 64, '2016-05-31 19:37:28'),
(2311, 883, 'Wow. Yeah. I like this a lot, but I think I agree with John that it might be too raw. If we did decide to do it we''d need a really personal performance by the soloist.', 64, '2016-05-31 19:52:19'),
(2312, 882, 'Thanks for suggesting this, Barry! It really is an amazing worship song.', 64, '2016-05-31 20:01:58'),
(2313, 851, 'I actually think most of this song is easily translated to a relationship between us and God.  The only issue I possibly see is when they sing "Strong arms get too weak to hold her", but even then that could easily be understood as talking to God, asking for support to carry us through as we hold each other, which is what I think the song is literally doing.  Really, I don''t think this song needs translating at all except for the chorus, as it speaks of our need of God in order to love and support each other, especially those most dear to us.', 48, '2016-05-31 21:32:20'),
(2314, 927, 'Definitely very different to anything we''ve done before, but I think it would be nice to try it out and expand our style.  I''m sure we could have fun with it.', 58, '2016-06-01 18:05:12'),
(2315, 920, 'I really like the lyrics to this one!', 58, '2016-06-01 18:09:50'),
(2316, 908, 'I really like the lyrics to this song - especially the first verse talking about the hard times.  I like the movement that it seems to have despite being slower.', 58, '2016-06-01 18:12:07'),
(2317, 896, 'I must say I really like this song and thought about suggesting it, but I wasn''t sure how exactly it would work.  I didn''t think so much about it fro the perspective of MIT, like you say though.  It''s actually very relevant to today''s society which is cool.', 58, '2016-06-01 18:15:00'),
(2318, 831, 'Also - I think this would be a really cool mashup with Capital Kings - "You''ll Never Be Alone".  I''m thinking that we could intersperse the rap from the Capital Kings song with parts of this song, which I think would give a pretty cool conversation of us begging "Don''t leave me alone" and then God answering saying that he won''t."', 58, '2016-06-01 18:28:19'),
(2319, 880, 'Ooooh I love this!  It''s so groovy and has a great message.  I''d love it on it''s own also, but this is maybe something that could be mashed up with Hollyn - Alone.  I''m thinking that we could intersperse the rap parts of this between parts of that song, which I think would give a pretty cool conversation of us begging "Don''t leave me alone" and then God answering saying that he won''t.', 58, '2016-06-01 18:28:25'),
(2320, 731, 'I uploaded the Yale''s Living Water arrangement of this song, in case that sounds like a good arrangement to use. (:', 48, '2016-06-01 19:02:54'),
(2321, 898, 'Yessss I love this! :)', 58, '2016-06-01 19:34:21'),
(2322, 899, 'I really like it, and we could fix the repetitiveness just by cutting some of the chorus repeats.', 63, '2016-06-01 20:28:24'),
(2323, 731, 'Love this guy''s arrangement, can we use it?', 63, '2016-06-01 20:32:38'),
(2324, 880, 'YASSSSSS!!!', 63, '2016-06-01 20:45:28'),
(2325, 908, 'It''s a great song for me, this is something I have struggled with a lot, and I think other MIT kids do too, because we all like to appear self-sufficient, like we have it all figured out. But we don''t, and this song reminds us of that. It also has a missional aspect, even though it''s focused more on the confession side between Christians.', 63, '2016-06-01 20:53:54'),
(2326, 920, 'I also like the no solo idea, and making it a really choral piece, we could have fun with it.', 63, '2016-06-01 20:58:54'),
(2327, 905, 'I''ve always loved this song, it''s so upbeat and tells us that we are forgiven completely and forever. Because of what Christ did we know just how much He loves us and how big His grace is.', 63, '2016-06-01 21:07:52'),
(2328, 851, 'The song seems to be written from a place of romance, and I don''t know how the duet nature will be interpreted. It''s a beautiful way for Christians to deal with illness, but I don''t know if it''s good for us to do. ', 63, '2016-06-01 21:27:26'),
(2329, 831, 'Interesting idea. Although this one is in minor and the other in major (I think). In any case, both are really good songs--we could just have both!', 62, '2016-06-01 22:33:49'),
(2330, 10, 'Yes, bring the perc!!! That''s what I was thinking too.', 63, '2016-06-02 02:23:55'),
(2331, 841, 'This is great, and the more voices the better, we could do it and have a full sound I think, I''m just worried that so much is in latin that an average audience would miss a lot of it without a blurb.', 63, '2016-06-02 02:40:44'),
(2332, 718, 'This would be a duet featuring a Christian struggling in their walk and Christ. The lines could be divided something like this: (with minimal lyrical baptism - can be baptized differently too)\r\n\r\nhttps://docs.google.com/document/d/1sGHoYP5muZzh2esfLtmZM03e4DDCy_7o2VStDu0_dbs/pub\r\n\r\nA line which really resonates with me personally is: \r\n     "So I wonder where were you?\r\n     When all the roads I took came back to me*"\r\nAs it captures the frustration of our efforts to find our way back to God.', 53, '2016-12-01 05:01:56'),
(2333, 718, 'Duet Lyrical Bisection: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1sGHoYP5muZzh2esfLtmZM03e4DDCy_7o2VStDu0_dbs/pub', 53, '2016-12-01 05:06:47'),
(2334, 932, 'This song would be from the perspective of Jesus reaching out to carry us (like Brother by NeedtoBreathe) Also, this gets at how Christ is the "firstborn of many brothers" (Romans 8:28). The line which particularly speaks to me is "Even if we can''t find heaven, I''ll walk through Hell with you" because Christ did walk through Hell for us, and does not promise us heaven in this life but promises that He will be with us through even the greatest of trials (John 16:33 and Psalm 23:4). That said, this song would need to be carefully/prayerfully baptized, rewriting the bridge/pre-bridge and evaluating all the lyric''s implications such as with "if we can''t find heaven."\r\n', 53, '2016-12-01 05:21:31'),
(2335, 933, 'I love the beat and rhythm of this one, and I think it would be really easy to do. The message is super applicable to anyone who has ever struggled... so everyone.', 63, '2016-12-01 05:41:40'),
(2336, 935, 'From all my travelling, God has shown me that when all His people in all the languages He created lift up their voices to Him together in praise, we get a glimpse of what Heaven looks (and sounds!) like. I think this would be a great song to do again, depending on how many languages people in the group know/speak. We''d obviously tweak the languages used from this version to match the current group. If people could comment the languages they know just so we can gauge what spread of languages we''d have that''d be great :) I speak German and English.', 64, '2016-12-02 02:43:40'),
(2337, 936, 'BU opened BiDB with this last year with a very small group and rocked the house. This song was written in 2003, but I think given the current political climate it''s as relevant as ever. It doesn''t provide an answer to the question it asks, but I could see this working as an early song in the set, since we''ll certainly be singing about the answer (Jesus) later.', 62, '2016-12-02 03:16:08'),
(2338, 936, 'Also, this was implicit but I''m making it explicit, we could probably borrow their arrangement.', 62, '2016-12-02 03:17:33'),
(2339, 12, 'Trying to get some alto solos in here, and I think this would be a great one. The arrangement is really good. It''s a worship song that''s listenable and also has some cool spoken word in it. The message is also important to remember. Jesus is King over all the rulers of the earth. Moreso than that, our time here pales in comparison to the time we will spend worshiping Jesus in Heaven.', 62, '2016-12-02 03:30:50'),
(2340, 615, 'Added the Stanford Testimony version, which is what I recommend you listen to (that perc is fire). This isn''t really the kind of song I would normally like, but one day it just got really stuck in my head and I came to appreciate it.', 62, '2016-12-02 03:38:18'),
(2341, 414, 'Guys...it''s a bass solo! Part of a duet, but still! Chris Tomlin isn''t my favorite, but, y''know, pre-arranged, apparently the arrangement is good, "spring break friendly" worship song...I could see it fitting into a set.', 62, '2016-12-02 03:42:57'),
(2342, 877, 'Three things we always say we want more of: worship songs, pop songs, and mashups. This satisfies all three of those! This is pre-arranged but has never been sung before. I got the idea to combine these two songs and this mashup was born. I recommend you listen to the MIDI playback and follow along with the lyrics or on the arrangement PDF.', 62, '2016-12-02 03:49:28'),
(2343, 8, 'Maddie (I think) mentioned this song when somebody said a Spanish song could be good for Texas. I agree! This song isn''t really my style, but I think it''d be a good choice. I could see Riley owning the solo...I know basses have soloed it as well! Also, Easter.', 62, '2016-12-02 03:54:55'),
(2344, 878, 'Added Hollyn''s version of the song, and likewise changed solo to either. I could see us making an arrangement that uses aspects of both versions.', 62, '2016-12-02 03:57:23'),
(2345, 920, 'I really like Meiji''s idea for an arrangement of this', 62, '2016-12-02 03:59:11'),
(2346, 657, 'This song gives me a lot of happy feels and general happiness.  I love it musically and I think that has a really important message, especially in the times of college when I''ve personally found myself lost in my walk with God- it makes it really relatable.', 55, '2016-12-02 06:15:23'),
(2347, 657, 'Also, I''ve been wanting to sing the song "I won''t give up" by Jason Mraz for years and I think some parts of the chorus may mash up as a duet part with this song. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O1-4u9W-bns', 55, '2016-12-02 06:17:51'),
(2348, 657, 'A note for clarification to rid of possible confusion: there IS a subpar arrangement somewhere lying around, but it''s one that I would be hesitant to sing without a decent amount of rework.', 40, '2016-12-03 05:53:26'),
(2349, 935, 'Japanese (and obvs English)', 70, '2016-12-05 01:31:00'),
(2350, 30, 'I like this song and think it has a good message', 70, '2016-12-05 01:49:38'),
(2351, 132, 'I like this song too - it speaks of how God is all that we need and is waiting for us to see his love for us', 70, '2016-12-05 02:01:06'),
(2352, 937, 'this song reminds me (for obvious reasons) of the footprints story and it seems that for spring break you need some songs that aren''t super christian-y (what i have gathered from past comments. may not be true) don''t really understand the part right before the chorus but idk, could be fun to do a sia song', 70, '2016-12-05 02:08:07'),
(2353, 432, 'thought I would switch up the type of song I recommend. but also, I think this song would be a lot of fun and I think that we have a lot of peoples who would enjoy doing this song', 70, '2016-12-05 02:17:29'),
(2354, 937, 'I didn''t know what you meant by the footprints story, so I looked it up (and added a link for reference). Now I get it! I think "Lord knows you cant trust your head / When you''re standing on the edge" might be referring to how we can''t handle trials on our own and need God to carry us. The meaning might not be completely clear if you''ve never heard the poem, though.', 62, '2016-12-05 05:08:45'),
(2355, 938, 'Accidentally put in the wrong link at first and don''t know how to delete the video....so i just added the actual one afterwards - sorry.\r\n\r\nSo doing take me home would be awesome because PTX is awesome and because it is already a cappella it hopefully wouldn''t be too hard to arrange for us. Song meaning wise: I like the first verse and the chorus. I think those could be like how God is perfect and brings us hope, and then wanting to be with Him. On the otherhand, the parts that start with "don''t you forget" aren''t too applicable - maybe we could change it to something else? Also the second verse.... Hmm... it would be fun but maybe doesn''t send the message we want...', 70, '2016-12-05 05:19:22'),
(2356, 934, 'This song is a plea to God to take the reins of our lives -- to be greater, be higher, be louder, "be magnified." A line that resonates with me personally is "I don''t need to see everything/ Just more of you." This song tells us, "Trying to make sense of the sorrow[s] that [we] feel" and "staring at [our] problems" is not necessary. We don''t need to understand everything that goes on in this world, that happens to us. We just need God to "be greater than the worries in [our] live[s]", to "Be stronger than the weakness in [our] mind[s]." With Him, all the incompleteness will disappear.', 69, '2016-12-09 19:38:31'),
(2357, 415, '^ Agree with Barry -- Upbeat female solos sound really good! It will round out a setlist nicely.', 69, '2016-12-09 19:46:06'),
(2358, 432, 'Ooh, I like this! So laid-back and fun. We could come up with some fun choreo for this. It''s a bit repetitive though, so we''d probably cut it a bit (4 minutes is a bit long, I''d say). Also, perhaps we could borrow BU Mustard Seed''s arrangement, don''t know if we could contact them.', 69, '2016-12-09 19:51:13'),
(2359, 936, 'BU Mustard Seed did an awesome job with such a small group in the recording you posted above! I remember hearing this song in orchestra class in 6th grade for the first time, and it has really stuck with me since then. It''s relatable on all fronts, especially today, as Barry mentioned. I can totally see us doing this -- I think the audience will really enjoy it. ', 69, '2016-12-09 19:56:55'),
(2360, 63, 'I like this song. Very upbeat, I can see it as a really exciting arrangement, lots of syncopation. I feel like it will be a bit difficult to fully emulate the upbeatedness of the song, though we can definitely give it a shot.', 69, '2016-12-09 20:21:08'),
(2361, 63, 'Hey, I think we did Like a Match justice! Still, it''s important to be careful when choosing songs that need choreo to work, since we don''t always have a lot of room. Lyrically, the song is pretty non-explicit, which is good if we have a blurb or more explicit songs in a set, but it could be taken as a self-empowerment song on its own.', 62, '2016-12-11 17:25:32'),
(2362, 167, 'Such an upbeat song! Love it!', 69, '2016-12-11 18:29:49'),
(2363, 935, 'Chinese! This is a great idea.', 69, '2016-12-11 18:38:25'),
(2364, 219, 'MIT Cross Products wrote this song?', 69, '2016-12-11 18:42:14'),
(2365, 941, 'This song is a great illustration of Philippians 4:13, "I can do all things through Christ who gives me strength." One of my favorites lines in the song is "Doubt sees a mountain, no way around it/ Faith sees a victory, no doubt about it/ Fear sees a ceiling, hope sees the stars" -- it''s a beautiful drawn contrast between what we are without God and we can do with Him.', 69, '2016-12-11 19:00:11'),
(2366, 882, 'I love this song! ', 69, '2016-12-11 19:02:13'),
(2367, 219, 'Yep, it was written by Kathy Huang ''03 ', 62, '2016-12-11 19:25:30'),
(2368, 508, 'Just a note that we did sing this song just last spring (see concert video posted above).  I personally think it''s too soon to do again.', 55, '2016-12-11 19:44:05'),
(2369, 508, '^ Yes, I think a year is a bit too soon to do it again. Although it is a beautiful song!\r\n', 69, '2016-12-11 19:50:17'),
(2370, 703, 'I like this arrangement (2015 Spring). It would nice to do it again, if everyone else doesn''t think it''s too early to do it again. ', 69, '2016-12-11 20:04:15');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(2371, 5, 'I did this skit with my home church''s Taiwan Missions Team (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sSpAZ0lSqic) in the summer of 2015. I''m not particularly fond of the weird fun syllables in the arrangement, though; I''ve always thought of this song as more reflective, contemplative, and hopeful; rather than upbeat or energetic. Perhaps it''s the way I did it in the missions skit, with the serious themes of sin in the skit mingling with the song in the background. It definitely has a poignant message though. ^\r\n', 69, '2016-12-11 20:31:56'),
(2372, 5, 'To each their own I guess. I think the arrangement is excellent and does the original justice.', 62, '2016-12-11 20:58:09'),
(2373, 10, 'Added recording from Fall 2016, for which the arrangment was edited to be more energetic.', 62, '2016-12-13 05:30:20'),
(2374, 457, 'We ran this one in Fall 2016 as a two-female duet and included perc at the end. The arrangment has six parts not counting solo and perc, so part balance and choosing soloists can be difficult. Also, some of the parts feel like 6/8 and others feel like 3/4.', 62, '2016-12-13 05:34:30'),
(2375, 884, 'Sung in Fall 2016. I would probably recommend you tweak the arrangment if you want to do this one again, as the current one has a lot of difficult-to-sing rhythms.', 62, '2016-12-13 05:38:17'),
(2376, 922, 'Sung in Fall 2016. The arrangment was written for two male soloists going back and forth, reflecting the conversation that the song is, but we did it as one solo due to part balance. Honestly, I think it probably works better with one solo.', 62, '2016-12-13 05:40:06'),
(2377, 835, 'Did this in Fall 2016 and the crowd loved it. Choreo is a must on this one!', 62, '2016-12-13 05:41:53'),
(2378, 942, 'I can see this being a song from God to us, but I can just as easily see it as a song from me to a hypothetical girlfriend (and perhaps moreso due to the connotations of "darling"). I know it''s super popular in the CCM scene, but there might be better options for the same message.', 62, '2016-12-13 17:32:56'),
(2379, 948, 'Pre-Arranged?', 62, '2016-12-13 23:15:23'),
(2380, 843, 'Suggesting again for the same reasons I commented about above ^^^^', 64, '2016-12-14 03:27:24'),
(2381, 947, 'Living through all the sickness and pain and questions like I have this semester, this song has resonated a lot with me. Having the ability to declare these words to God in the same way that Jesus did when faced with the cross is something I have and will need to continue to constantly work at, but I think the message of encouragement in this song is really strong.', 64, '2016-12-14 04:07:05'),
(2382, 949, 'This is a happy upbeat song (I think it''s good for closing out a set).  Version posted is by Psalm 100 (another a cappella group).  It makes me happy to listen to and talks about how God has freed us from sin.', 55, '2016-12-14 15:58:39'),
(2383, 950, 'A few other Christian a cappella groups have sung this one- I think it''s a prayer to God.', 55, '2016-12-14 16:11:47'),
(2384, 218, 'Past comments indicated that people thought it was too hard or we don''t have the need for it.  But we did cool things this semester, this is a well-liked song I think, and it''s so pretty and happy and speaks to how amazing God is.', 55, '2016-12-14 16:18:58'),
(2385, 753, 'Over the summer, I went to Hillsong Church in LA and there was part of a sermon on this song.  I remember it specifically from all of the songs this summer.  It''s a little repetitive, but I think it could be arranged creatively.', 55, '2016-12-14 16:23:35'),
(2386, 951, 'So... Ingrid Michaelson has been one of my favorite artists for a while- and this was my favorite song by her when I first started listening way back in high school.  But I didn''t think of this as a Christian song until recently (Tufts Anchord did it!).  I think that this song would need a blurb and probably be paired in a set with a more explicit song, but this song is SB friendly, decently known, and talks about Love- how much we want to Love God, and how much we desire God''s love.', 55, '2016-12-14 16:29:52'),
(2387, 953, 'This is a good song to show the sacrifice that God made for us.  It''s a powerful slow male ballad and it''s really pretty.  Musically it I think it mashes up well with Awake My Soul (other song I suggested).  Message wise, I think it draws a cool parallel between death and awakeness and that Jesus died because he loves us and for our souls.\r\n\r\n', 55, '2016-12-14 16:40:22'),
(2388, 952, 'Although I like this song (it''s the reason I took French 1 sophomore spring.... *I make great life choices, I know), I feel like singing a song in French might not be the best idea for trying to get a message across', 70, '2016-12-14 16:40:27'),
(2389, 952, 'I do believe the song has a lot of power, and we are more than capable of introducing it with a blurb to explain the words of the song.  I am confident people will get the feeling of the longing and pain expressed in this song.  It is a beautiful song.', 48, '2016-12-14 16:49:28'),
(2390, 774, 'Love this song and the diamond analogy. It''s so uplifting!', 69, '2016-12-14 16:57:37'),
(2391, 727, 'I really like BYU''s version of this hymn. I think it could be a good option for doing something that focuses more on harmonies while still being interesting and beautiful.', 64, '2016-12-14 16:59:34'),
(2392, 957, 'I''ve always loved this song. I will admit that we''d have to have a pretty creative arrangement for the background parts to keep it interesting, but I think we could pull it off.', 64, '2016-12-14 17:06:53'),
(2393, 960, 'I interpret this song as our journey through this world toward the next. We''re constantly shaking off the excess and lies and blindness of the night, choosing instead to kneel and wait on God each moment. There''s a lot of theology buried in these lyrics, which is cool because it''s a song that''s well known in the secular sphere.', 50, '2016-12-14 17:21:15'),
(2394, 53, 'I really like the sense of longing in this song. We all deal with a lot of anxiety and searching and I like how this song brings us back to the source, to a God who has true peace and rest for us that the world can''t provide.', 57, '2016-12-14 17:22:51'),
(2395, 426, 'Bringing up an oldie! (kind of)\r\nI like the energy in this song and the imagery of Jesus bringing us back to life.', 57, '2016-12-14 17:25:12'),
(2396, 962, 'I love this song.  It is such a beautiful song, along a similar vein to "We Dance" by Steffany Gretzinger.  This song just sings of the beauty of our future marriage to Christ, with a feel of awe, wonder, and anticipation for the day when shall be wed with Christ, and made full in him, clothed in absolute joy, wonder, and beauty.', 48, '2016-12-14 17:33:41'),
(2397, 686, 'We all have idols. They may not be wood and stone like the idols in the Bible, but we idolize our individuality, academic performance, being approved of by others, and even being a "good Christian," to name a few. I like how in this song, we actually claim responsibility for choosing those idols instead of choosing God. Our sin isn''t just us trying to run after God and failing - sometimes it''s outright rebellion. But the fact that He still offers us His life is such a testament to His unbelievable love for us.', 50, '2016-12-14 17:34:08'),
(2398, 963, 'I think this song could be a way to portray the idea of giving up everything to follow God. It would be interesting to do and it''s a well-known song. The lyrics work kind of well, although there are a few spots that could be tweaked. Not sure if I myself am completely sold on it, but I''d like to hear other people''s inputs as well. ', 57, '2016-12-14 17:34:27'),
(2399, 964, 'A really pretty old Welsh hymn. It could be arranged more contemporary-style (Matt Redman, 1st video) or more traditional-style (Robin Mark, 2nd video).', 69, '2016-12-14 17:35:29'),
(2400, 965, 'I love the victory this song portrays! And the general pronouncement of truth throughout the entire thing. I feel like fear is rampant throughout MIT and easily ensnares us. The song provides a powerful message against that.', 57, '2016-12-14 17:40:42'),
(2401, 966, 'This song is so upbeat and uplifting. The lyrics state perhaps one of the most important truths the gospel brings us -- that no matter what we have done, we are never too far gone for His love to save us! "You will never outrun my love."', 69, '2016-12-14 17:44:58'),
(2402, 726, 'Might be fun to do this again. :)', 57, '2016-12-14 17:47:53'),
(2403, 967, 'This is a song all about testimonies, and it seems worth mentioning that some of our more powerful moments and songs at concert come when we share our own stories. Those can be our strongest testaments to the Gospel, and this song celebrates that.', 63, '2016-12-14 17:50:53'),
(2404, 969, 'This one was good for me personally, but it is a message that we all need to hear. It is just reminding us about how easy it is to forget that God is King, and brings us back to a place of humility before Him. ', 63, '2016-12-14 18:04:01'),
(2405, 973, 'Strong message for all of us. We all have chains of fear and sin that bind us, pain we want taken away, and times we feel lost. God is the answer to all of those. Plus it sounds like it could be very powerful musically and the words are very triumphant.', 63, '2016-12-14 18:08:48'),
(2406, 974, 'This song is so victorious, it''s hard to see the audience not getting swept up into it! It''s pretty Spring Break friendly as well.', 69, '2016-12-14 18:09:33'),
(2407, 971, 'I could imagine this being arranged for a cappella really easily. I also think it could work as a mashup with He Knows My Name. It''s a reallly similar message, just from a different perspective.', 62, '2016-12-14 18:11:20'),
(2408, 975, 'I can see this as a male or female solo. It''s got some pretty emotional vocals reflecting the awe and wonder our God inspires. One of my favorite lines is "How can the god of the galaxies/ Have a care for the little things."', 69, '2016-12-14 18:17:25'),
(2409, 977, 'This song is so victorious and has got a great message. Perfect love casts out fear! I think it will be relatively easy to arrange.', 69, '2016-12-14 18:19:54'),
(2410, 14, 'GLAD also did a version of this, which we could attempt to re-create for SATB.', 62, '2016-12-14 18:24:44'),
(2412, 374, 'yes! i was going to suggest it but forgot :)', 70, '2016-12-14 19:05:18'),
(2413, 374, 'Princeton sang this at BiDB 2016. We might be able to borrow their arrangment if we like it.', 62, '2016-12-14 19:12:31'),
