(2425, 988, 'i was thinking about suggesting this song but I don''t know if we could do it justice. But it is a freaking amazing song', 70, '2016-12-15 04:05:16'),
(2426, 994, 'This is a very hard song.  I don''t mean musically, but spiritually.  It most certainly addresses the subject of sexual sin and homosexuality, through individual people''s letters that express their pain, their fears, and their desperate need.  It would take a lot for us to sing a song like this, but I think God could break through the walls that would rise against us if we did this song, and open doors to revival that would not be opened up any other way.  There are a lot of people caught in the pain of their sin who are only told that they should accept it.  What would happen, if we spoke openly about the freedom promised in Christ, according to the pain that they feel?  This song is powerful, and very capable of being world-changing.', 48, '2016-12-15 04:28:26'),
(2427, 995, '* This song comes up on Google both as a Mormon hymn as well as a Christian hymn. This is worth praying about, though examination of the lyrics leave produces nothing immediately even remotely heretical.', 53, '2016-12-15 04:37:46'),
(2428, 995, 'This is another song inspired by listening to BYU Vocal Point. It is similar in style to Nearer My God to Thee; however in the place of the intensity, it captivates the listener with its poignant beauty. (It is actually fairly similar in style to Jesu Dulcis Memoria) Its beauty relies heavily on excellent group blend and dynamic control with a number of dissonant and unresolved phrases which build tension. It is a difficult song to perform well, but done so, it is an excellent addition to a concert. ', 53, '2016-12-15 04:42:17'),
(2429, 995, 'Regarding content, my soul cries out listening to this song. it is a prayer for ones soul, reminding oneself to take heart and be still in the presence of the Almighty. It is a prayer offered on bended knee, humbled by what rises against you from without and within. And BYU''s rendition so perfectly captures that tension and stillness.', 53, '2016-12-15 04:48:41'),
(2430, 619, 'I definitely we''re at the point that we could pull this off, both energy and arrangement-wise.', 62, '2016-12-15 16:21:00'),
(2431, 932, 'Yeah, I''d be concerned with the "if we can''t find heaven" line, and it''s fairly critical to the song. I know the meaning is that life isn''t always nice/easy, but I would not want to confuse people or de-legitimize the actual heaven we are promised.', 62, '2016-12-15 20:50:55'),
(2432, 415, 'I''m not sure how accurate the "true alto solo" comment was...it goes up to D5. They would need to have a strong head voice.', 62, '2016-12-15 20:56:34'),
