(2439, 952, 'Pentatonix did a cover of this, although we would obviously have to do it without the violin. I''m not really sure why we would sing it though. Longing for a father...our heavenly father in a "Trust In You" sort of way...or a hypothetical deadbeat earthly father? Either way, I''m not seeing a huge reason to sing it, meaning-wise.', 62, '2016-12-17 03:48:01'),
(2440, 979, 'I could see this working as a song from God''s perspective, with the bridge being our response. I''ve definitely heard this song being played around campus, and it''s EDM, so this would truly be a dive into popular music.', 62, '2016-12-17 03:55:45'),
(2441, 416, 'I checked the arrangement just now, and I think we could make it work with the current comp (tenor isn''t too low). People would need to be solid on their parts since there are splits galore, but I think it would be a good challenge for us. The focus of the piece is more on voices than syllables and rhythms, which we said we want more of. I think the earlier comments covered everything meaning-related, so see them. This could fit in pretty much any setlist.', 62, '2016-12-17 04:04:25'),
(2442, 984, 'Pre-arranged?', 62, '2016-12-17 04:06:23'),
(2443, 600, 'Added a video of Princeton KS performing our arrangement, since we never bothered to split Spring 2014, apparently. I think it was a great idea to cover the song, but the execution was just ok. I''m not really sure why it''s a duet, and the arrangment is very syllabic, with one part singing "nooh" on C5 almost the entire time. We could definitely do it again, although it would lack some of the "popular" feel it had at the time.', 62, '2016-12-17 04:27:00'),
(2444, 726, 'I''m not actually sure from whom we borrowed our arrangement...it might actually be the Selah version, or at least it''s really close. It''s super high-quality, and the song is so real. That said, this was just done Spring 2015...I''m not against doing it again, but I wouldn''t gun for it either.', 62, '2016-12-17 04:33:25'),
(2445, 949, 'I think Shane & Shane isn''t really my style, but it''s grown on me enough that I could see it working as a closer, given the right setlist.', 62, '2016-12-17 04:40:30'),
(2446, 996, 'Wait...NF sings?! I did not know that! This would work nicely in a set with Shoulders (4K&C) :)', 62, '2016-12-17 17:51:52'),
(2447, 988, 'UPenn Full Measure did this at BiDB 2016', 62, '2016-12-17 17:55:11'),
(2448, 998, 'Pre-Arranged?', 62, '2016-12-17 17:55:45'),
(2449, 979, 'Yeah, someone played this on a (catholic) retreat this year and I immediately thought it would be a really cool song for xprod to do.  I think an arrangement could be pretty interesting and I always think that it''s great to put a Christian twist on pop music.  Definitely would be cool for xprod to try an EDM song.', 58, '2016-12-18 04:18:55'),
(2450, 963, 'Oooh it would work really well if it weren''t for the use of "baby." You could tweak it, but I don''t think I would want to do that...I don''t want to validate the joke that you make a Christian song by just replacing "baby" with "Jesus."', 62, '2016-12-18 04:19:06'),
(2451, 979, 'And yes as you say Barry - Verses/Chorus work well from the perspective of God/Jesus, with the bridge as a response from us.', 58, '2016-12-18 04:19:44'),
