(2460, 736, 'I think this is a cool song, but I agree with the above comments that I''m not sure how it would translate to non-Christians', 58, '2016-12-18 04:35:53'),
(2461, 935, 'I also speak German (I''d be down to learn a Scottish Gaelic section if we could translate it into that).  For reference, we did this in Fall 2014 (it was my first solo in xprod!).  I think it''s sufficient time that we could possibly bring it back, since we have had shorter gaps in redoing songs before, but I do think it''s something to bear in mind and might prefer a new song if there was a choice between two.', 58, '2016-12-18 04:38:59'),
(2462, 984, 'I do think that this is a cool song and I love it when we sing it in prayer.  I''m not sure how well this (as with worship songs in general) would work into a setlist and how it would work in with the audience.  I feel the song has more of an impact if you''re actually singing it.  Saying that, it is powerful and could maybe work well in a mashup?', 58, '2016-12-18 04:42:40'),
(2463, 726, 'I agree with Barry.  Definitely not a reason to axe the song entirely, but if there was an option between two, I would probably go with a newer one.  It is a really great arrangement though and very powerful.', 58, '2016-12-18 04:46:26'),
(2464, 686, 'Something to consider: non-Christians might not understand what the songs means by "idols" without a blurb.', 62, '2016-12-18 04:48:57'),
