(2503, 978, '@Erica SB songs don''t all need to be SB Friendly, but at certain gigs (i.e. public schools, etc) we are asked specifically to not sing songs that specifically mention God/Jesus.', 64, '2016-12-22 04:54:37'),
(2504, 979, 'I agree with all the comments above. I think it would be cool to break out into a sound like this.', 64, '2016-12-22 04:59:37'),
(2505, 919, 'I completely agree with Becky. This wouldn''t be something we would sing without a blurb, but it would be incredibly powerful to sing at churches and youth groups and to serve as a reminder to us as a group.', 64, '2016-12-22 05:08:39'),
(2506, 933, 'I''ve heard this one through my Spotify discovery playlist and really liked it. It''s a solid reminder that God''s got it even when I don''t and the world seems like it''s going crazy.', 64, '2016-12-22 05:27:50'),
(2507, 749, 'Yeah, like for mashup or as an intro/outtro deal for another song.', 64, '2016-12-22 05:30:02'),
(2508, 963, 'Ahhh....not really feeling it. I agree with Barry on not wanting to validate that you can make a Christian song just by changing words from romantic things to Jesus. There are also other lines that I don''t really see fitting. "It may be hard for you to, Stop and believe" (this doesn''t really make sense for us to be saying this to God). "Give me one good reason Why I should never make a change And if you hold me Then all of this will go away" (I just don''t get how this works with us talking to God either).', 64, '2016-12-22 05:34:16'),
(2509, 726, 'Really love this song, but yeah it might be too soon.', 64, '2016-12-22 05:38:39'),
(2510, 686, 'I really like this one. I think this is another case of we wouldn''t sing this one in a situation that we couldn''t blurb. I think with a good blurb, it could be very powerful. When we recognize and admit that we have put other things above and before God, we can put them aside and ask God to speak life in our lives again as He helps take the idols away.', 64, '2016-12-22 05:43:44'),
(2511, 919, 'One idea I had after UCO praise night was us singing a song ("Heart of Worship" came to mind) without any arrangement at all, just like during xprod-style prayer. I would not want to do that with this one since it is less well known, but imagine if we arranged this one to end by flowing into Heart of Worship. It''d be a risk performance-wise, and I''d find it semi-ironic to practice it, but I think it could be really cool and powerful.', 62, '2016-12-22 06:14:14'),
(2512, 973, 'It reminds me of Brother musically. I know this one is up for a Grammy nomination.', 62, '2016-12-22 06:18:47'),
(2513, 984, 'Yeah, I agree this one tends to be more powerful when sung yourself rather than watching it be performed, but I think it could be good in a mashup. I don''t think we''ve arranged this before though...', 64, '2016-12-22 16:48:01'),
(2514, 167, 'Yeah, I think it''s too soon as well.', 64, '2016-12-22 16:50:32'),
(2515, 980, 'We''d definitely have to have a powerful soloist and really good arrangement to keep this techno feel, but it is catchy.', 64, '2016-12-22 16:59:13'),
(2516, 693, 'I''m tending to agree with Brian''s comment. We''d have to explain all the splits in a blurb and even then I don''t know if it will end up sounding coherent enough. Maybe would work as a mashup?', 64, '2016-12-22 17:02:20'),
(2517, 998, 'I think for the audience to connect with this we''d need a strong testimony through blurb.', 64, '2016-12-22 17:06:32'),
(2518, 988, 'I like UPenn''s verion (that bass doh)...Would need a wicked strong soloist too to do it justice.', 64, '2016-12-22 17:09:58'),
(2519, 996, 'I really like this! The echoing during the rap would be really cool translated to a cappella.', 64, '2016-12-22 17:12:36'),
(2520, 951, 'Nice and upbeat. Agree with the definite need for a blurb.', 64, '2016-12-22 17:15:25'),
(2521, 984, 'De-marked pre-arranged since I don''t think we''ve sung this. If somebody knows better, you can add the arrangement.', 62, '2016-12-22 17:22:45'),
(2522, 984, 'I actually think a song like this could work so well for us.  We spend so much time trying to express the love of God, His power, and salvation.  But what about at the end of it all, responding by expressing our love for Him?  Just presenting the sheer magnitude of Christ to our audience, by presenting the sheer magnitude of God to us and our lives.  I think ending our setlist with a worship song would be extremely powerful, and this song is certainly very expressive of our immense love of God, and awe and wonder at His name.', 48, '2016-12-22 18:53:38'),
(2523, 951, 'I love the sound and energy of this song, and think it is very capable of being a part of our setlists.  I know I especially love the line "Happy is the heart that still feels pain./Darkness drains and light will come again."  I can definitely speak to that line, and is something I believe the world needs to know.  That hurt is ok.', 48, '2016-12-22 18:58:50'),
(2524, 996, 'This song is so good.  It holds such power and clarity of the vision of God for His children, and the salvation He offers.  That it lasts more than one day, and is truly and utterly complete.  "Jesus, He gave it all to save you! / He carried the cross on His shoulders, / So you can start over."  I love it!', 48, '2016-12-22 19:05:09'),
(2525, 988, 'Oh. My. Goodness.  This is beautiful, and so exciting.  I couldn''t stop dancing to this!  I love it so much, it just reeks of joy, happiness, and excitement!  In a way, it is a worship song with the way it just expresses the beauty of God and how much we love him.  So good.', 48, '2016-12-22 19:12:30'),
(2526, 998, 'This is a perspective I don''t think we have ever touched.  It would be such a powerhouse if we were able to express the pain and loss carried in this song, because it is certainly something no one would expect us to address, and one few would expect God to be able to touch, let alone break the power of.', 48, '2016-12-22 19:21:09'),
(2527, 952, 'As I was requested to put my response here:  This song is not supposed to represent Christ, but instead what we''ve lost here on earth.  It is a powerful song for speaking to our expectation and longing for a good father, and questioning where all this brokenness came in.  It is a very relevant song to a lot of people, and I believe it would open them up to listen and believe that maybe fathers are meant to be different, and God could be a different father than the one they had - a good father.', 48, '2016-12-22 19:52:27'),
(2528, 973, 'I do find this song to be very generic, trying to say much, but not addressing anything.  We know what it means, but I am not certain people would value what the song is saying much if they did not already believe God could do such things.', 48, '2016-12-22 20:21:18'),
(2529, 933, 'I think this is a powerful song, and I prefer the version that is not edited for the radio.  It is a perspective we as Christians need to understand and believe, and one we need to represent as the truth of Christ in our pains to everyone who sees us.  That they may understand we really do believe, and know, that God is there in the eye of the storm, He remains in control, and He is love and peace, even while we are there.', 48, '2016-12-22 21:50:44'),
(2530, 973, 'I can almost hear this song mashing up with Safe (Phil Wickham).  I think it may even mash up a bit message wise with the general idea that God can do anything.', 55, '2016-12-23 01:12:05'),
(2531, 953, 'I really like this one. It''s beautiful and really honest.', 64, '2016-12-23 03:19:58'),
(2532, 949, 'Yeah, I could definitely see this as a closer as well. I really like the beginning.', 64, '2016-12-23 03:22:47'),
(2533, 416, 'Oooh I like this. I think we could definitely pull it off as a challenge song (kinda like Nearer!). Would definitely fit in almost any setlist.', 64, '2016-12-23 03:31:32'),
(2534, 995, 'This is another one of my favorite hymns. I love BYU''s rendition with a strong focus on the lyrics and the harmonies of the group rather than complex syllables.', 64, '2016-12-23 03:33:53'),
(2535, 172, '^^Agree with Becky. Do really like this song though,so pretty!', 64, '2016-12-23 03:35:52'),
(2536, 172, '"In our hearts a hope for a song, We barely understood " -> In the same way, the Spirit helps us in our weakness. We do not know what we ought to pray for, but the Spirit himself intercedes for us through wordless groans. Romans 8:26\r\n', 64, '2016-12-23 03:39:47'),
(2537, 374, 'Yeah, so much love. Also a really emotional song for me. But love, love, love.', 64, '2016-12-23 03:40:35'),
(2538, 960, 'Wow never thought about it in that way! Really like!', 64, '2016-12-23 03:44:53'),
(2539, 415, 'Aaah this is such an oldie favorite! Sounds like it would be a blast to sing!', 64, '2016-12-23 03:52:59'),
(2540, 932, 'Yeah, I''m concerned about our ability to rewrite lyrics for this well.', 64, '2016-12-23 03:54:52'),
(2541, 994, 'I agree that this is a very hard song. I agree that it could be very powerful. I''m unsure how convincing of a job we could do to do the song justice if we don''t have people who strongly connect to the content of each of the letters outlined in the song.', 64, '2016-12-23 04:06:47'),
(2542, 932, 'I don''t feel we need to rewrite this song, for we do not have to make it from the perspective of God/Jesus singing to us.  We can do it from the perspective of us to our brothers and sisters, to the audience.  We are a part of the church too, and we are made to be the hands and feet of God, to reach out to the lost, hold on to them, till they too learn of the God that lives within us, and become a part of his hands and feet.  Paul wrote in 1 Corinthians 11:1, "Follow my example, as I follow the example of Christ."  I think that is a statement the Church ignores too easily, that we too are a part of that chain of love and Salvation to the lost.  We are not Salvation, but we are meant to carry Him and share His love.  "And I know now, love, if your wings are broken / Borrow mine ''til yours can open, too."  "I''ll be your eyes ''til yours can shine / And I''ll be your arms, I''ll be your steady satellite / And when you can''t rise, well, I''ll crawl with you on hands and knees / ''Cause I... I''m gonna stand by you."', 48, '2016-12-23 16:46:27'),
(2543, 960, 'I love it.  We have so many songs and songs suggestions that sing about God waiting and longing for us, but that totally goes both ways.  That we must long for God, and there will be times where we have to wait.  We live in a world where so many have sought God, but never found Him.  And so they give up, they quit cause He never came when they looked for Him and prayed, despite how much we say over and over again that He is already here.  But what if we shared that there are times we too have to wait, and that God dwells in the wait, in the emptiness too.  That He is still here, still alive, and still moving for us, just as much as when we see and feel Him.  Our God is alive, and moves in the unseen as well as the seen.  "For we live by faith, and not by sight." 2 Corinthians 5:7', 48, '2016-12-23 17:04:12'),
(2544, 374, 'I love the opportunity to share the excitement and wonder we have of our God, and seeing Him in heaven.  People have such a narrow perspective of what Heaven is supposed to be, and how you are supposed to go.  I think this song, by painting the vision of the purpose and joy of Heaven, gives us a glimpse of what it means to live in Heaven, and how we should prepare our hearts if we long to live there.  It is such a beautiful, loving song.', 48, '2016-12-23 17:11:13'),
(2545, 172, 'We also can just stick with the Hebrew part of the song, and translate it.  It is far more explicit, and carries such an energy of joy and praise.\r\nA-shir-ra I''a-do-nai ki ga-oh ga-ah\r\n(I will sing to the Lord for He has triumphed gloriously)\r\nA-shir-ra I''a-do-nai ki ga-oh ga-ah\r\n(I will sing to the Lord for He has triumphed gloriously)\r\nMi-cha-mo-cha ba-e-lim adonai\r\n(Who is like You, oh Lord, among the celestials)\r\nMi-ka-mo-cha ne-dar-ba-ko-desh\r\n(Who is like You, majestic in holiness)\r\nNa-chi-tah v''-chas-d''-cha am zu ga-al-ta\r\n(In Your love, You lead the people You redeemed)\r\nNa-chi-tah v''-chas-d''-cha am zu ga-al-ta\r\n(In Your love, You lead the people You redeemed)\r\nA-shi-ra, a-shi-ra, A-shi-ra\r\nA-shir-ra I''a-do-nai ki ga-oh ga-ah\r\n(I will sing to the Lord for He has triumphed gloriously)\r\nA-shir-ra I''a-do-nai ki ga-oh ga-ah\r\n(I will sing to the Lord for He has triumphed gloriously)\r\nMi-cha-mo-cha ba-e-lim adonai\r\n(Who is like You, oh Lord, among the celestials)\r\nMi-ka-mo-cha ne-dar-ba-ko-desh\r\n(Who is like You, majestic in holiness)\r\nNa-chi-tah v''-chas-d''-cha am zu ga-al-ta\r\n(In Your love, You lead the people You redeemed)\r\nNa-chi-tah v''-chas-d''-cha am zu ga-al-ta\r\n(In Your love, You lead the people You redeemed)\r\nA-shi-ra, a-shi-ra, A-shi-ra', 48, '2016-12-23 17:19:51'),
(2546, 172, 'Wow, that failed.  Sorry, here is just a link to the translation, to keep it simple here:  http://www.allthelyrics.com/lyrics/prince_of_egypt_soundtrack/the_prine_of_egypt_when_you_believe-lyrics-203895.html', 48, '2016-12-23 17:21:05'),
(2547, 953, '"That when I drive the nails through Your hands / You do not recant / You never take it back... / And [You] loved my heart to death"  Wow.  If we do this song, I really want us to give it the depth of value and emotion the lyrics deserve.  I don''t even know how to express what I want to say right now, but this song could break down so many walls through prayer.', 48, '2016-12-23 18:11:43'),
(2548, 703, 'Since it''s only been a year, I think it''s too close unless there''s a specific reason to do it again - looking at comments on other songs, it seems like the general consensus is that songs within the last 2 years are a little close.', 58, '2016-12-24 11:22:34'),
(2549, 703, 'Yeah, I think anything within two years needs a good reason to re-do (e.g. fits SB location well, killer arrangment that would be good for group musically, etc.). Unless we just make a habit of re-doing a song every couple years--they did that with Joy a while back.', 62, '2016-12-24 17:11:07'),
(2550, 994, 'I don''t want to start a theological/political debate, but I''m a little concerned with the way the first letter addresses homosexuality. I think a lot of people (even some Christian) out there might disagree with the lyrics to the point that it prevents them from really hearing the message of the song. Since our primary goal is to share the Gospel with people, I wouldn''t want to let a small theological disagreement get in the way of them hearing it.', 62, '2016-12-24 17:17:06'),
(2551, 636, 'When I made the Spotify playlist of suggested songs, I ended up adding an Irish folk version, and I can''t help but smile when I listen to it! I do think the lyrics make sense, and they get across the joy of following Christ really well. That said, I do think it''s possible that some people could get confused by the metaphor. We also won''t sound like Irishmen at pub when we''re singing, so we won''t have that working for us XD', 62, '2016-12-24 17:20:27'),
(2552, 992, 'Huh. I''m coming to Mina the next time I want some Indie Christian music to listen to! Being still waiting for God to speak is something is something that doesn''t happen a lot at MIT, so it could be good to sing, although it might require a blurb for people to get it. I''d worry about the audience getting bored since it''s a fairly constant and chill song, but I like the sound.', 62, '2016-12-24 17:27:37'),
(2553, 994, 'I have a lot of hesitations when it comes to the song.  Both letters address tricky subjects.  While I understand the way that the Gospel and this song addresses both of these topics, I am concerned with us singing it in a set.  I agree a lot with what Barry has said.  I think that the topics covered in the song would make a lot of audiences uncomfortable to the point that they would almost disregard the rest of our set.  I see our purpose as a group to both minister to Christians and non-Christians.  I know both Christians and non-Christians who have struggled through both of these situations, but I almost feel that putting these struggles in a song lifts these problems to a level of "if you have done either of these things you have sinned", and I don''t think the song does a good enough job explaining that no matter the circumstances, God will forgive all.  ', 55, '2016-12-24 18:11:12'),
(2554, 950, 'I''m having some trouble seeing exactly what the verses are supposed to mean....Are we praying this to God? Is it a back and forth? What is "But lend me your heart and I''ll just let you fall. Lend me your eyes I can change what you see" supposed to mean?', 64, '2016-12-24 19:42:16'),
(2555, 904, 'This is one of my favorites! No matter what situation we are in whether we are running to God or away from Him, He does not fail and He works ALL things for the good of those who love Him!', 64, '2016-12-24 19:46:38'),
(2556, 985, 'I really like Moriah Peters, she reminds me of Francesca Battistelli''s newer style. I like how upbeat and encouraging this one is!', 64, '2016-12-24 19:58:45'),
(2557, 977, 'I completely agree, Erica!', 64, '2016-12-24 20:10:03'),
(2558, 880, 'I still really like this one. It would be a really cool style for us to try.', 64, '2016-12-24 20:17:08'),
(2559, 981, 'SB-friendly. I like the message of hope in the midst of troubles. Would probably need a good blurb, but I like it.', 57, '2016-12-24 22:17:38'),
(2560, 937, 'I like it! I see the part before the chorus meaning something like, you can''t trust logic or how you feel in difficult or scary situations that require faith, but that''s just me, haha.', 57, '2016-12-24 22:31:27'),
(2561, 907, 'Probably not what the original artist intended, but I could see this song talking about being brave enough to own up and confess our faults and sins, "to stand in the light and be seen as we are". It reminds me of 1 John 1: "This is the message we heard from Jesus and how declare to you: God is light and there is no darkness in him at all. So we are lying if we say we have fellowship with God but go on living in spiritual darkness; we are not practicing the truth. But if we are living in the light, as God is the light, then we have fellowship with each other, and the blood of Jesus, his Son, cleanses us from all sin." This song could be about living in the light. At least that''s what came to mind when I heard it.', 57, '2016-12-24 23:15:44'),
(2562, 974, 'Such an empowering and convicting song! God has set us free and has loved us so well, how can we continue to live in anxiety, stress, and fear?', 64, '2016-12-26 02:58:20'),
(2563, 967, 'I really like this one. It''s powerful and would be great to couple with a powerful blurb as well.', 64, '2016-12-26 03:15:23'),
(2564, 965, 'Ahhh this is another favorite and so powerful! As God''s redeemed children we are called to lay claim to the victory and freedom God has declared for us when he said "It is Finished" on the Cross. We are NO LONGER slaves to fear, God has conquered it all!', 64, '2016-12-26 03:29:14'),
(2565, 53, 'I totally agree!', 64, '2016-12-26 03:44:09'),
(2566, 473, 'I agree that this could be really good for CD pub. Even though it''s within the 2 year zone we''ve mentioned in other song comments, it might be worth picking up again for CD pub alone.', 64, '2016-12-26 03:47:05'),
(2567, 676, 'Echoing the comment above about the concern regarding reliability. How many of us have actually gotten everything we wanted and then realized it wasn''t what we wanted?', 64, '2016-12-26 03:58:16'),
(2568, 473, 'Just to comment on the "2 year zone", in past comments I think that''s been a reference to the last time we sang it, not since another group sings it.  We as a group haven''t sung this since before me (I think we sang it 2012-2013), so I definitely don''t think it''s too early to sing again.', 55, '2016-12-26 04:08:05');
INSERT INTO `comment` (`id`, `song_id`, `text`, `user_id`, `timestamp`) VALUES
(2569, 477, 'After seeing how well we pulled off Nearer last semester, I think we could definitely do a great job on this one too!', 64, '2016-12-26 04:10:03'),
(2570, 851, 'I''m still seeing this one as more focused on romance than anything else. Beautiful song, but not sure it translates very well for us.', 64, '2016-12-26 04:31:09'),
(2571, 936, 'I could definitely see this as an opener for a set. Definite second Barry''s point about needing to eventually answer the question it asks.', 64, '2016-12-26 04:57:19'),
(2572, 30, 'One of my favorite Casting Crowns songs. Echoing Maddie''s above comment.', 64, '2016-12-26 05:05:18'),
(2573, 8, 'Agreeing with Barry and Maddie that a Spanish song for Texas would be great. Also Easter. Even though this song style isn''t something I would typically be in to, I like it.', 64, '2016-12-26 05:13:44'),
(2574, 933, 'I almost hear the instrumental part mashing up with Oceans!', 55, '2016-12-26 05:18:19'),
(2575, 877, 'I remember this on from last cycle. I think it is a good option, but will be depend on how the setlist starts to shape up in terms of fit.', 64, '2016-12-26 05:18:25'),
(2576, 414, 'Bass solo! Pre-arranged! SB Friendly! All the things!', 64, '2016-12-26 05:23:54'),
(2577, 718, 'I like Brian''s baptized version. I''d only be down for doing this if we do altered lyrics. I don''t think I''d like it in a mashup. Need a killer tenor solo though.', 64, '2016-12-26 05:30:11'),
(2578, 965, 'This one is great! Love the defiance and power of the words. In no uncertain terms it declares our freedom from fear and all that enslaves us.', 63, '2016-12-26 20:18:41'),
(2579, 885, 'I like this song, maybe one other change would be to take out the baby and honey? Not difficult to change, and the vast majority of the song is great, especially with the changes you proposed!!', 63, '2016-12-26 20:30:21'),
(2580, 600, 'I agree a couple lyrical changes are in order, but most of the song is fine!', 63, '2016-12-26 21:39:07'),
(2581, 953, 'I wish it talked about the resurrection, but I do really like the message it brings though, and it brings new meaning to a phrase that has become pretty widely used. ', 63, '2016-12-26 23:04:26'),
(2582, 935, 'I could do Spanish, English, and probably a few others given enough time and something to listen to.', 63, '2016-12-27 00:33:00'),
(2583, 167, 'I was looking at the earlier comments about comfort zones and was thinking we shouldn''t skip a song just because we just did it, but we have so many songs and so few spots I understand the mentality. If it really works with some of the other songs, go for it, but other than that I wouldn''t do it.', 63, '2016-12-27 01:51:11'),
(2586, 172, 'With the lyrical change Hans suggested in 2015, I would be down to do this!', 63, '2016-12-27 02:02:04'),
(2587, 937, 'I like this one, I would maybe change the line in the first verse from "your pain" to "my pain"', 63, '2016-12-27 02:33:55'),
(2588, 508, 'Giving it a low rating solely because we just did it, but I love this one!', 63, '2016-12-27 03:22:43'),
(2589, 636, 'This is a song we sang at camp!! It''s great!! (should probably be arranged in a different way though to suit our group)', 68, '2016-12-27 03:34:07'),
(2590, 992, 'I am also worried about potential musical monotony, but it is a good message.', 63, '2016-12-27 03:54:55'),
(2591, 726, 'This song is fun, but if we did it I would want to twiddle with the arrangement a little, I think we could spice it up a bit.', 63, '2016-12-27 04:09:36'),
(2592, 851, 'I wonder if we would ever have the opportunity to actually talk about romantic love before Christ, and just the power and love He gives us to hold fast, and find the joy that so many no longer believe exists.  It would be quite a different take for Cross Products to do, and I don''t know if we could, but it is certainly an important question to ask and acknowledge among people our age.  What could God do in a concert where we have as an important part of our skit and theme, the relationship between two people and God, and not just one?', 48, '2016-12-27 04:19:34'),
(2593, 953, 'To reiterate and expand, I am kinda concerned about this only because it only talks about Christ dying, not his resurrection so much. It''s not a theological issue, and this is a beautiful song about sacrifice, but it needs to be followed by or accompanied a reminder that Christ did not stay dead, but He rose again. This can be a blurb or another song, but it is something to consider.', 63, '2016-12-27 04:27:14'),
(2594, 657, 'ditto what maddie said', 68, '2016-12-27 04:47:29'),
(2595, 657, 'It seems like the definition of fool changes throughout, might be kinda confusing for people.', 63, '2016-12-27 04:53:07'),
(2596, 988, 'This was my summer jam, it came up on K-Love so many times. It can be our Like a Match for next semester!', 69, '2016-12-27 05:00:29'),
(2597, 24, 'I think this one could be a powerful outreach song, and it has a good message for Christians as well. We cannot and are not expected to be perfect. We shouldn''t try to hide that imperfection behind a mask.', 63, '2016-12-27 07:01:45'),
(2598, 880, 'One comment, a little unclear in a later verse who the song is from the perspective of. It seems like the song is from God, but He isn''t wondering how we ended up where we are... Maybe shift that? Or explain it?', 63, '2016-12-27 07:12:23'),
(2599, 968, 'One lyrical change, The line " There''s a lot about me that''s never been told" to something like "There''s a lot about me you have never been told"', 63, '2016-12-27 07:31:08'),
(2600, 953, 'I don''t think we have to worry at all about this song talking about Christ''s death vs. His resurrection.  That is not the point of the song.  This song focuses on the magnitude of God''s love for us, that even as we ourselves sinned and hung Him on the cross with our bare hands, He stayed there and drank up all of our sin, dying so that we might be free.  That is the power of this song, that He did not recant His love, nor did He take it back, but instead He loved our heart to death.', 48, '2016-12-28 08:12:53'),
(2602, 1000, 'This song is straight fire. It talks about being 100% committed to the life that Christ has called us to, which is something that''s been on my mind a lot recently. Musically, I have some arrangment ideas that would be really cool (including a short perc solo in the middle). The solo''s pretty high, though, so it''d be a stretch pick for this semester.', 62, '2017-05-23 21:08:32'),
(2603, 952, 'I am re-suggesting this song, because I believe we always have our concerts try and tell the answer to the question from the beginning to the end.  It would be cool if we could start by asking the question.  And I think this song would help reveal to people how desperately they long to see and know a good father.  It fills me with longing every time, as well as shame for what we have done in this world, to fail as fathers.  It would be an excellent intro that would make people listen intently, and everyone would connect to it.  Christian and non-Christian - something we have real trouble doing.  We would also stand out anywhere with this song.  People know it.', 48, '2017-05-25 04:11:22'),
(2604, 726, 'Either as-is, or we could probably borrow the I Have Decided to Folllow Jesus mashup that Cornell did', 62, '2017-05-26 19:00:34'),
(2605, 5, 'We''ve got dudes now, let''s go', 62, '2017-05-27 20:27:53'),
(2606, 686, '^^reiterating what Meiji said above', 64, '2017-05-28 18:24:02'),
(2607, 953, 'I think depending on how the setlist shape ends up, this could be a really good fit. It''s honesty and focus on the action of God''s Love for us is really powerful.', 64, '2017-05-28 18:29:39'),
(2608, 919, 'I think this song would end up being more for the group than for every one of our audiences in the end, but no less powerful overall. Blurb needed.', 64, '2017-05-28 18:34:50'),
(2609, 1001, 'And whatever you do, whether in word or deed, do it all in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks to God the Father through him. - Colossians 3:17\r\n\r\nWe are to dedicate every aspect and part of our life and story to the glory of the Lord. He made both the hills and the valleys and He is Lord of both of them. I think this song is a great reminder and celebration of that. We could choose either acoustic or standard version depending on what upbeat level is needed in the set.', 64, '2017-05-28 19:07:15'),
(2610, 1002, 'Celebration music! I could see this as an awesome closer. All the clapping, all the dancing, all the awesome Gospel Choir background.', 64, '2017-05-28 19:13:35'),
(2611, 1003, 'This song is more one of ministry to other Christians than anything else, but it has a powerful message for everyone about what faith looks like. It is trusting in God regardless of whether He removes the pain from our lives, or answers our prayers the way we want. That is a pretty ridiculous faith! (The good kind of ridiculous)', 63, '2017-05-28 21:40:56'),
(2612, 1003, 'i like this song. i listened to it driving home from church retreat today!', 69, '2017-05-28 22:30:44'),
(2613, 5, 'oh gosh, this song would be so great to do with some dramatic choreo... brings back the feels, feels.', 69, '2017-05-28 22:32:12'),
(2614, 1000, 'fun fun fun fun fun fun fun song. woot!', 69, '2017-05-28 22:33:53'),
(2615, 910, 'good song and would do well with a mashup. It''s just personal bias but I heard this song so many times on k-love and the combination of that as well as that it''s so repetitive made me sick of it. sorry. ', 69, '2017-05-28 22:35:15'),
(2616, 1005, 'surrender....', 69, '2017-05-28 22:47:36'),
(2617, 952, 'Kinda reminds me of Where is the Love, except it is less general. With a good blurb, it could open us up, and talk specifically about the hurt the lack of a father can generate. Also, how we all as humans long for our parents to be there for us, and how even the best ones will let us down at times. It could work.', 63, '2017-05-28 22:49:12'),
(2618, 1006, 'Reflects beautifully on what kind of being God is. ', 69, '2017-05-28 23:02:19'),
(2619, 686, '', 63, '2017-05-28 23:53:10'),
(2620, 919, 'I actually don''t think this song requires a blurb; it pretty clearly says that what we are doing is about Jesus, not performance. Maybe the idols part of the bridge is more confusing, but you wouldn''t need to include it in an arrangement.', 62, '2017-05-29 01:26:54'),
(2621, 1007, 'Reminds me of the beauty of God''s creation, like a sunrise or something. I also think it might (or might not) sound really really really cool. No clue what the lyrics mean. We could probably ditch them if anyone thinks they are irrelevant.\r\n\r\nWorking on an arrangement right now just for the fun of it.', 71, '2017-05-29 16:44:22'),
(2622, 1008, 'Not particularly meaningful, but I probably fun for (1) the arranger (2) the choir (3) perc and (4) Craig. Perhaps an avant-garde intro?', 71, '2017-05-29 17:08:29'),
(2623, 1000, 'Yeah, really high solo. I could probably do it, but let''s bring on the prayer for even more new sops :) I really like the message like Barry said, and it is really upbeat and fun. Could be a great closer.', 64, '2017-05-30 15:42:02'),
(2624, 999, 'Will admit I am now I bit tired of this song after hearing it so much out and about, but still agree with my past self ^^', 64, '2017-05-30 15:48:27'),
(2625, 1008, 'Haha I listened to it before reading the comment, and I was thinking maybe for an avant-garde intro as well. I think this would actually be rather difficult to arrange since the arpeggio background would be difficult to mimic (unless we want Greater times ten) and we''d want to cut out much of the repitition.', 62, '2017-05-30 16:10:13'),
(2626, 1007, 'I''d never thought about doing something like this but it could actually be really cool to do a completely instrumental piece as a sort of time of reflection during the concert, or even "break it up" so to speak, by reading scripture during parts of it. I agree, Kevin. Beautiful and very reminicent of a sunrise. I would say ditch the lyrics.', 64, '2017-05-30 16:12:53'),
(2627, 1003, 'Mhm, yeah. It''s like Trust In You message-wise. Musically, I wish it was more interesting, but I love the lyrics. Perhaps we could come up with a more dynamic arrangement that approaches it from different angles, but even if we don''t it still could be worth having in the set.', 62, '2017-05-30 16:17:37'),
(2628, 1006, 'This song is more of a prayer, and I like the words and how they relate to living a life of ministry. But this style of song is difficult to arrange and perform in a way that is engaging. I could see it working in an otherwise mostly-upbeat set.', 62, '2017-05-30 17:01:19'),
(2629, 1009, 'I know it may seem crazy, considering this is not a specifically Christian song. But I think the lyrics could fit in well, depending on what other songs/theme we end up with and I think it would be awesome to do this A Capella. Also, I was talking with Meiji at the concert afterparty and she thought it seemed like a cool song to do!', 72, '2017-06-02 01:10:56'),
(2630, 716, 'This song was a very personal song for me and one of my teammates this past year. It speaks into what I think a lot of people struggle with when trying to encounter God and the ending is so powerful and haunting that I get chills every time I sing it.', 72, '2017-06-02 01:14:31'),
(2631, 1009, 'I knew my Psalm 100 radar was going off...they did a mashup of this song with Safe & Sound, another "secular" song, although I can see the relevance. I agree that it could work depending on the set. One could probably find a more explicit song with a similar meaning, but perhaps something like this would be better overall.', 62, '2017-06-02 04:13:43'),
(2632, 890, 'I can''t stop thinking how perfect a closing song this would be.  When we reach the end of our concerts, our hope and dream is that those who come to listen, Christian or not, would see God and recognize his immense presence and purpose in our lives.  And that we could never be done with him.  I think this song says that.  That walking with him, never stops getting better.  "Further and further my heart moves away from the shore.  Whatever it looks like, whatever may come I am Yours... Whether I sink, whether I swim, It makes no difference when I''m beautifully in over my head."  I wish I could say it better, but we need to know this.  Herein lies revival and the prize that is set before us.', 48, '2017-06-02 19:07:23'),
