(2760, 1016, 'That''s fair. I actually didn''t notice the usage of baby in Out of Hiding because that one is so obviously from God''s perspective. In general I don''t like the idea of changing lyrics, but I take back my unstated belief that baby in a God''s perspective song never works.', 62, '2017-06-13 12:35:36'),
(2761, 716, 'We actually opened with this one in S15 ^_^', 62, '2017-06-13 12:36:11'),
(2762, 926, 'I can only really imagine this as a set opener, but it''d be pretty fire. I''m imagining a perc + rap solo (duet) for the opener and then the group runs in with the na na na na na na. You wouldn''t even have to do the whole thing after that, and it''d be pretty light memorization-wise besides the rap.', 62, '2017-06-13 12:43:08'),
(2763, 1014, 'If we could find some good spoken word for it I can definitely see it.', 63, '2017-06-13 13:31:20'),
(2764, 926, 'I agree with Barry about this being a good opener!', 72, '2017-06-14 00:29:19'),
(2765, 1006, 'This song is beautiful, I think it would depend on what the other songs in the set were', 72, '2017-06-14 00:33:30'),
(2766, 537, 'OMG yeah, expanding the choreo and having this mashup again would be awesome and could be a really high powered part of the set!', 72, '2017-06-14 00:41:31'),
(2767, 1003, 'I like this song, but I''m not sure how well it would work, it would vastly depend on the other songs, beautiful song though!', 72, '2017-06-14 00:49:59'),
(2768, 1003, '^Above comment was supposed to be in a different song...sorry haha', 72, '2017-06-14 00:50:53'),
(2769, 890, 'I like this song, but I''m not sure how well it would work, it would vastly depend on the other songs, beautiful song though!', 72, '2017-06-14 00:51:28'),
(2770, 882, 'I really like the message in this song of God supporting us!', 72, '2017-06-14 01:00:51'),
(2771, 947, 'This song is beautiful and the message is great, I''d be down for this being one of our slow songs this semester!', 72, '2017-06-14 01:03:33'),
(2772, 1002, 'This definitely seems like it could be a good option for a closer!', 72, '2017-06-14 01:07:31'),
(2773, 5, 'I like it and could probably sing it tehe! :)', 72, '2017-06-14 01:12:51'),
(2774, 919, 'I think it depends on the setlist, but I really like the message in this song!', 72, '2017-06-14 01:25:57'),
(2775, 1000, 'This could be a really good closer depending on the setlist!! I also feel like we could have some fun choreo for this!', 72, '2017-06-14 01:27:40'),
(2776, 216, 'This could be a fun version of a hymn-like song to do!', 72, '2017-06-14 01:33:37'),
(2777, 619, 'This could definitely be a very similar song/choreo/energy to Like-A-Match', 72, '2017-06-14 01:39:59'),
(2778, 1024, 'I like how this acknowledges how we try to take control, when in reality we have to let God take control of our lives!', 72, '2017-06-14 01:56:22'),
(2779, 966, 'I like how this song really touches on how you can really never be too far gone!', 72, '2017-06-14 01:58:47'),
(2780, 545, 'I love this song and definitely like how it sounded...I would like doing this again!', 72, '2017-06-14 02:06:54'),
(2781, 708, 'So in the intro, he says it was originally Gregorian chant, which means it was definitely men initially who sang this. I am a huge fan of Latin and Gregorian chant (as some of you may know) and I love how this sounded with the women and can hear in my head how it could/would sound so powerful with both male and female voices, I would be strongly in favor of doing this!', 72, '2017-06-14 02:11:30'),
(2782, 974, 'Especially considering some things that have happened in my life recently with Christ, this song really rings true, I love the message and that it''s upbeat!', 72, '2017-06-14 02:21:42'),
(2783, 1020, 'I love this arrangement, I think it would be awesome to do this including using the Frozen background!', 72, '2017-06-14 02:25:32'),
(2784, 995, 'I really like the sound of this arrangement and I agree with Barry about potentially having two hymns as long as they''re different styles!', 72, '2017-06-14 02:28:53'),
(2785, 433, 'I really like the sound of the arrangement posted here!!', 72, '2017-06-14 02:38:19'),
(2786, 878, 'I actually really like the beat and lyrics of this song, it would be a good change of pace!', 72, '2017-06-14 02:42:18'),
(2787, 1020, 'My one thing is I would like the words sooner, they seem a bit late in the video. More hymn words!', 63, '2017-06-14 13:30:36'),
(2788, 708, 'I would be down if we lengthened it, and I think we could make it work for the whole group if we upped the complexity.', 63, '2017-06-14 13:34:01'),
(2789, 518, 'I want to be a bold witness, but this song seems kinda combative. Not sure if it''s the way I would want to be ministered to.\r\n', 63, '2017-06-15 00:49:11'),
(2790, 1008, '', 58, '2017-06-15 18:50:16'),
(2791, 936, 'Sung in Spring 2017. Arrangement is indeed solid. Did pretty intricate choreo and ended up having a different soloist for each verse and chorus.', 62, '2017-08-24 00:42:43'),
(2792, 132, 'Sung in Spring 2017 with an arrangement that was edited slightly to make the choruses softer and more energetic. It''s simple but repetitive and ended up being difficult to tune.', 62, '2017-08-24 00:47:12'),
(2793, 975, 'Sung in Spring 2017. Some of the parts are a bit on the trickier side but it has some interesting rhythms and syllables and people generally liked singing this one.', 62, '2017-08-24 00:48:41'),
(2794, 798, 'Sung in Spring 2017. Uses the classic worship song by the same name as an intro and outro. Otherwise a fairly standard piece.', 62, '2017-08-24 00:50:25'),
(2795, 8, 'Noting that we did this with one soloist in Spring 2017.', 62, '2017-08-24 00:52:43'),
(2796, 979, 'Sung in Spring 2017. We did this with choreo and the crowd really liked it. The arrangement is really simple and repetitive, especially for non-sops, so blending, tuning, and dynamics matter a lot.', 62, '2017-08-24 00:55:28'),
(2797, 918, 'Sung in Spring 2017. The intro in the video is a bit strange since we went straight from the last skit scene into the song. It''s written as a single solo, but we had separate soloists for the verses and choruses which ended up being a bit of a duet at the end. The arrangement is SMATBB but there''s a lot of rhythm overlap so it''s easy to learn. We had choreo, which is kind of necessary for this one. Makes a great closer; the crowd loved it.', 62, '2017-08-24 01:01:25');
